P_HTM[1]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa* **";
P_HTM[2]="*Majjhimanikāyo* **";
P_HTM[3]="*Mūlapaṇṇāsapāḷi* **";
P_HTM[4]="*5. Cūḷayamakavaggo* **";
P_HTM[5]="*1. Mūlapariyāyasutta**The Root of All Things*";
P_HTM[6]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ viharati subhagavane sālarājamūle.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Ukkaṭṭhā, in the Subhaga Forest at the root of a magnificent sal tree.*";
P_HTM[8]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[9]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[10]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[11]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[12]="*“sabbadhammamūlapariyāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the explanation of the root of all things.*";
P_HTM[13]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[14]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[15]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[16]="*“Idha, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto—**“Take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[17]="*pathaviṃ pathavito sañjānāti;**They perceive earth as earth.*";
P_HTM[18]="*pathaviṃ pathavito saññatvā pathaviṃ maññati, pathaviyā maññati, pathavito maññati, pathaviṃ meti maññati, pathaviṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with earth, they identify regarding earth, they identify as earth, they identify that ‘earth is mine’, they take pleasure in earth.*";
P_HTM[19]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[20]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (1)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[21]="*Āpaṃ āpato sañjānāti;**They perceive water as water.*";
P_HTM[22]="*āpaṃ āpato saññatvā āpaṃ maññati, āpasmiṃ maññati, āpato maññati, āpaṃ meti maññati, āpaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with water …*";
P_HTM[23]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[24]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (2)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[25]="*Tejaṃ tejato sañjānāti;**They perceive fire as fire.*";
P_HTM[26]="*tejaṃ tejato saññatvā tejaṃ maññati, tejasmiṃ maññati, tejato maññati, tejaṃ meti maññati, tejaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with fire …*";
P_HTM[27]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[28]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (3)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[29]="*Vāyaṃ vāyato sañjānāti;**They perceive air as air.*";
P_HTM[30]="*vāyaṃ vāyato saññatvā vāyaṃ maññati, vāyasmiṃ maññati, vāyato maññati, vāyaṃ meti maññati, vāyaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with air …*";
P_HTM[31]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[32]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (4)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[33]="*Bhūte bhūtato sañjānāti;**They perceive creatures as creatures.*";
P_HTM[34]="*bhūte bhūtato saññatvā bhūte maññati, bhūtesu maññati, bhūtato maññati, bhūte meti maññati, bhūte abhinandati.**But then they identify with creatures …*";
P_HTM[35]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[36]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (5)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[37]="*Deve devato sañjānāti;**They perceive gods as gods.*";
P_HTM[38]="*deve devato saññatvā deve maññati, devesu maññati, devato maññati, deve meti maññati, deve abhinandati.**But then they identify with gods …*";
P_HTM[39]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[40]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (6)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[41]="*Pajāpatiṃ pajāpatito sañjānāti;**They perceive the Creator as the Creator.*";
P_HTM[42]="*pajāpatiṃ pajāpatito saññatvā pajāpatiṃ maññati, pajāpatismiṃ maññati, pajāpatito maññati, pajāpatiṃ meti maññati, pajāpatiṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the Creator …*";
P_HTM[43]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[44]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (7)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[45]="*Brahmaṃ brahmato sañjānāti;**They perceive Brahmā as Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[46]="*brahmaṃ brahmato saññatvā brahmaṃ maññati, brahmasmiṃ maññati, brahmato maññati, brahmaṃ meti maññati, brahmaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with Brahmā …*";
P_HTM[47]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[48]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (8)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[49]="*Ābhassare ābhassarato sañjānāti;**They perceive the gods of streaming radiance as the gods of streaming radiance.*";
P_HTM[50]="*ābhassare ābhassarato saññatvā ābhassare maññati, ābhassaresu maññati, ābhassarato maññati, ābhassare meti maññati, ābhassare abhinandati.**But then they identify with the gods of streaming radiance …*";
P_HTM[51]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[52]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (9)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[53]="*Subhakiṇhe subhakiṇhato sañjānāti;**They perceive the gods replete with glory as the gods replete with glory.*";
P_HTM[54]="*subhakiṇhe subhakiṇhato saññatvā subhakiṇhe maññati, subhakiṇhesu maññati, subhakiṇhato maññati, subhakiṇhe meti maññati, subhakiṇhe abhinandati.**But then they identify with the gods replete with glory …*";
P_HTM[55]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[56]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (10)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[57]="*Vehapphale vehapphalato sañjānāti;**They perceive the gods of abundant fruit as the gods of abundant fruit.*";
P_HTM[58]="*vehapphale vehapphalato saññatvā vehapphale maññati, vehapphalesu maññati, vehapphalato maññati, vehapphale meti maññati, vehapphale abhinandati.**But then they identify with the gods of abundant fruit …*";
P_HTM[59]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[60]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (11)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[61]="*Abhibhuṃ abhibhuto sañjānāti;**They perceive the Overlord as the Overlord.*";
P_HTM[62]="*abhibhuṃ abhibhuto saññatvā abhibhuṃ maññati, abhibhusmiṃ maññati, abhibhuto maññati, abhibhuṃ meti maññati, abhibhuṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the Overlord …*";
P_HTM[63]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[64]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (12)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[65]="*Ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ ākāsānañcāyatanato sañjānāti;**They perceive the dimension of infinite space as the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[66]="*ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ ākāsānañcāyatanato saññatvā ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ maññati, ākāsānañcāyatanasmiṃ maññati, ākāsānañcāyatanato maññati, ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ meti maññati, ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the dimension of infinite space …*";
P_HTM[67]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[68]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (13)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[69]="*Viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ viññāṇañcāyatanato sañjānāti;**They perceive the dimension of infinite consciousness as the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[70]="*viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ viññāṇañcāyatanato saññatvā viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ maññati, viññāṇañcāyatanasmiṃ maññati, viññāṇañcāyatanato maññati, viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ meti maññati, viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the dimension of infinite consciousness …*";
P_HTM[71]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[72]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (14)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[73]="*Ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ ākiñcaññāyatanato sañjānāti;**They perceive the dimension of nothingness as the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[74]="*ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ ākiñcaññāyatanato saññatvā ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ maññati, ākiñcaññāyatanasmiṃ maññati, ākiñcaññāyatanato maññati, ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ meti maññati, ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the dimension of nothingness …*";
P_HTM[75]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[76]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (15)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[77]="*Nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ nevasaññānāsaññāyatanato sañjānāti;**They perceive the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception as the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[78]="*nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ nevasaññānāsaññāyatanato saññatvā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ maññati, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasmiṃ maññati, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanato maññati, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ meti maññati, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception …*";
P_HTM[79]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[80]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (16)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[81]="*Diṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhato sañjānāti;**They perceive the seen as the seen.*";
P_HTM[82]="*diṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhato saññatvā diṭṭhaṃ maññati, diṭṭhasmiṃ maññati, diṭṭhato maññati, diṭṭhaṃ meti maññati, diṭṭhaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the seen …*";
P_HTM[83]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[84]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (17)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[85]="*Sutaṃ sutato sañjānāti;**They perceive the heard as the heard.*";
P_HTM[86]="*sutaṃ sutato saññatvā sutaṃ maññati, sutasmiṃ maññati, sutato maññati, sutaṃ meti maññati, sutaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the heard …*";
P_HTM[87]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[88]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (18)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[89]="*Mutaṃ mutato sañjānāti;**They perceive the thought as the thought.*";
P_HTM[90]="*mutaṃ mutato saññatvā mutaṃ maññati, mutasmiṃ maññati, mutato maññati, mutaṃ meti maññati, mutaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the thought …*";
P_HTM[91]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[92]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (19)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[93]="*Viññātaṃ viññātato sañjānāti;**They perceive the known as the known.*";
P_HTM[94]="*viññātaṃ viññātato saññatvā viññātaṃ maññati, viññātasmiṃ maññati, viññātato maññati, viññātaṃ meti maññati, viññātaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with the known …*";
P_HTM[95]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[96]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (20)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[97]="*Ekattaṃ ekattato sañjānāti;**They perceive oneness as oneness.*";
P_HTM[98]="*ekattaṃ ekattato saññatvā ekattaṃ maññati, ekattasmiṃ maññati, ekattato maññati, ekattaṃ meti maññati, ekattaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with oneness …*";
P_HTM[99]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[100]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (21)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[101]="*Nānattaṃ nānattato sañjānāti;**They perceive diversity as diversity.*";
P_HTM[102]="*nānattaṃ nānattato saññatvā nānattaṃ maññati, nānattasmiṃ maññati, nānattato maññati, nānattaṃ meti maññati, nānattaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with diversity …*";
P_HTM[103]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[104]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (22)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[105]="*Sabbaṃ sabbato sañjānāti;**They perceive all as all.*";
P_HTM[106]="*sabbaṃ sabbato saññatvā sabbaṃ maññati, sabbasmiṃ maññati, sabbato maññati, sabbaṃ meti maññati, sabbaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with all …*";
P_HTM[107]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[108]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (23)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[109]="*Nibbānaṃ nibbānato sañjānāti;**They perceive extinguishment as extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[110]="*nibbānaṃ nibbānato saññatvā nibbānaṃ maññati, nibbānasmiṃ maññati, nibbānato maññati, nibbānaṃ meti maññati, nibbānaṃ abhinandati.**But then they identify with extinguishment, they identify regarding extinguishment, they identify as extinguishment, they identify that ‘extinguishment is mine’, they take pleasure in extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[111]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[112]="*‘Apariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi. (24)**Because they haven’t completely understood it, I say.*";
P_HTM[113]="*Puthujjanavasena paṭhamanayabhūmiparicchedo niṭṭhito.* **";
P_HTM[114]="*Yopi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sekkho appattamānaso anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamāno viharati, sopi pathaviṃ pathavito abhijānāti;**A mendicant who is a trainee, who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire, but lives aspiring to the supreme sanctuary, directly knows earth as earth.*";
P_HTM[115]="*pathaviṃ pathavito abhiññāya pathaviṃ mā maññi, pathaviyā mā maññi, pathavito mā maññi, pathaviṃ meti mā maññi, pathaviṃ mābhinandi.**But they shouldn’t identify with earth, they shouldn’t identify regarding earth, they shouldn’t identify as earth, they shouldn’t identify that ‘earth is mine’, they shouldn’t take pleasure in earth.*";
P_HTM[116]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[117]="*‘Pariññeyyaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi.**So that they may completely understand it, I say.*";
