P_HTM[144]="*Sekkhavasena dutiyanayabhūmiparicchedo niṭṭhito.* **";
P_HTM[145]="*Yopi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, sopi pathaviṃ pathavito abhijānāti;**A mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—directly knows earth as earth.*";
P_HTM[146]="*pathaviṃ pathavito abhiññāya pathaviṃ na maññati, pathaviyā na maññati, pathavito na maññati, pathaviṃ meti na maññati, pathaviṃ nābhinandati.**But they don’t identify with earth, they don’t identify regarding earth, they don’t identify as earth, they don’t identify that ‘earth is mine’, they don’t take pleasure in earth.*";
P_HTM[147]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[148]="*‘Pariññātaṃ tassā’ti vadāmi.**Because they have completely understood it, I say.*";
