P_HTM[1983]="*taṃ, sāriputta, vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Unless they give up that speech and that thought, and let go of that view, they will be cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[1984]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, evaṃ sampadamidaṃ, sāriputta, vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[1985]="*Taṃ vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.* **";
P_HTM[1986]="*Catasso kho imā, sāriputta, yoniyo.**Sāriputta, there are these four kinds of reproduction.*";
P_HTM[1987]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1988]="*Aṇḍajā yoni, jalābujā yoni, saṃsedajā yoni, opapātikā yoni.**Reproduction for creatures born from an egg, from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[1989]="*Katamā ca, sāriputta, aṇḍajā yoni?**And what is reproduction from an egg?*";
P_HTM[1990]="*Ye kho te, sāriputta, sattā aṇḍakosaṃ abhinibbhijja jāyanti—**There are beings who are born by breaking out of an eggshell.*";
P_HTM[1991]="*ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, aṇḍajā yoni.**This is called reproduction from an egg.*";
P_HTM[1992]="*Katamā ca, sāriputta, jalābujā yoni?**And what is reproduction from a womb?*";
P_HTM[1993]="*Ye kho te, sāriputta, sattā vatthikosaṃ abhinibbhijja jāyanti—**There are beings who are born by breaking out of the amniotic sac.*";
P_HTM[1994]="*ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, jalābujā yoni.**This is called reproduction from a womb.*";
P_HTM[1995]="*Katamā ca, sāriputta, saṃsedajā yoni?**And what is reproduction from moisture?*";
P_HTM[1996]="*Ye kho te, sāriputta, sattā pūtimacche vā jāyanti pūtikuṇape vā pūtikummāse vā candanikāye vā oḷigalle vā jāyanti—**There are beings who are born in a rotten fish, in a rotten corpse, in rotten dough, in a cesspool or a sump.*";
P_HTM[1997]="*ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, saṃsedajā yoni.**This is called reproduction from moisture.*";
P_HTM[1998]="*Katamā ca, sāriputta, opapātikā yoni?**And what is spontaneous reproduction?*";
P_HTM[1999]="*Devā, nerayikā, ekacce ca manussā, ekacce ca vinipātikā—**Gods, hell-beings, certain humans, and certain beings in the lower realms.*";
P_HTM[2000]="*ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, opapātikā yoni.**This is called spontaneous reproduction.*";
P_HTM[2001]="*Imā kho, sāriputta, catasso yoniyo.**These are the four kinds of reproduction.*";
