P_HTM[2007]="*Pañca kho imā, sāriputta, gatiyo.**There are these five destinations.*";
P_HTM[2008]="*Katamā pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2009]="*Nirayo, tiracchānayoni, pettivisayo, manussā, devā.**Hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, humanity, and the gods.*";
P_HTM[2010]="*Nirayañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, nirayagāmiñca maggaṃ, nirayagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;**I understand hell, and the path and practice that leads to hell.*";
P_HTM[2011]="*yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi.**And I understand how someone practicing that way, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2012]="*Tiracchānayoniñcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, tiracchānayonigāmiñca maggaṃ, tiracchānayonigāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;**I understand the animal realm …*";
P_HTM[2013]="*yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2014]="*Pettivisayañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, pettivisayagāmiñca maggaṃ, pettivisayagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2015]="*yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi.**the ghost realm …*";
P_HTM[2016]="*Manusse cāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, manussalokagāmiñca maggaṃ, manussalokagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;**humanity …*";
P_HTM[2017]="*yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjati tañca pajānāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2018]="*Deve cāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, devalokagāmiñca maggaṃ, devalokagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;**gods, and the path and practice that leads to the world of the gods.*";
P_HTM[2019]="*yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi.**And I understand how someone practicing that way, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[2020]="*Nibbānañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, nibbānagāmiñca maggaṃ, nibbānagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;**And I understand extinguishment, and the path and practice that leads to extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[2021]="*yathā paṭipanno ca āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati tañca pajānāmi.**And I understand how someone practicing that way realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2022]="*Idhāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2023]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatīti.**‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’*";
P_HTM[2024]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in hell, where they experience exclusively painful feelings, sharp and severe.*";
P_HTM[2025]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā pūrā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ vītadhūmānaṃ.**Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, full of glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked.*";
P_HTM[2026]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva aṅgārakāsuṃ paṇidhāya.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same pit of coals.*";
P_HTM[2027]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:*";
P_HTM[2028]="*‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā imaṃyeva aṅgārakāsuṃ āgamissatī’ti.**‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very pit of coals.’*";
P_HTM[2029]="*Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tassā aṅgārakāsuyā patitaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later they see that they have indeed fallen into that pit of coals, where they experience exclusively painful feelings, sharp and severe. …*";
P_HTM[2030]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—* **";
P_HTM[2031]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2032]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (1)* **";
P_HTM[2033]="*Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2034]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjissatīti.**‘This person … will be reborn in the animal realm.’*";
P_HTM[2035]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapannaṃ, dukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in the animal realm, where they experience painful feelings, sharp and severe.*";
P_HTM[2036]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, gūthakūpo sādhikaporiso, pūro gūthassa.**Suppose there was a sewer deeper than a man’s height, full to the brim with feces.*";
P_HTM[2037]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva gūthakūpaṃ paṇidhāya.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same sewer.*";
P_HTM[2038]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:*";
P_HTM[2039]="*‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā imaṃyeva gūthakūpaṃ āgamissatī’ti.**‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very sewer.’*";
P_HTM[2040]="*Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tasmiṃ gūthakūpe patitaṃ, dukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later they see that they have indeed fallen into that sewer, where they experience painful feelings, sharp and severe. …*";
P_HTM[2041]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—* **";
P_HTM[2042]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2043]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapannaṃ, dukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2044]="*Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2045]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjissatīti.**‘This person … will be reborn in the ghost realm.’*";
P_HTM[2046]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapannaṃ, dukkhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in the ghost realm, where they experience many painful feelings.*";
P_HTM[2047]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, rukkho visame bhūmibhāge jāto tanupattapalāso kabaracchāyo.**Suppose there was a tree growing on rugged ground, with thin foliage casting dappled shade.*";
P_HTM[2048]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva rukkhaṃ paṇidhāya.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same tree.*";
P_HTM[2049]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:*";
P_HTM[2050]="*‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā imaṃyeva rukkhaṃ āgamissatī’ti.**‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very tree.’*";
P_HTM[2051]="*Tamenaṃ passeyya, aparena samayena tassa rukkhassa chāyāya nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā dukkhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later they see them sitting or lying under that tree, where they experience many painful feelings. …*";
P_HTM[2052]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—* **";
P_HTM[2053]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2054]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapannaṃ, dukkhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2055]="*Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2056]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjissatīti.**‘This person … will be reborn among human beings.’*";
P_HTM[2057]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapannaṃ, sukhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn among human beings, where they experience many pleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[2058]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, rukkho same bhūmibhāge jāto bahalapattapalāso sandacchāyo.**Suppose there was a tree growing on smooth ground, with abundant foliage casting dense shade.*";
P_HTM[2059]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva rukkhaṃ paṇidhāya.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same tree.*";
P_HTM[2060]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:*";
P_HTM[2061]="*‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā imameva rukkhaṃ āgamissatī’ti.**‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very tree.’*";
P_HTM[2062]="*Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tassa rukkhassa chāyāya nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā sukhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later they see them sitting or lying under that tree, where they experience many pleasant feelings. …*";
P_HTM[2063]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—* **";
P_HTM[2064]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2065]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapannaṃ, sukhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2066]="*Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2067]="*‘tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissatī’ti.**‘This person … will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’*";
P_HTM[2068]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in a heavenly realm, where they experience exclusively pleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[2069]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, pāsādo, tatrāssa kūṭāgāraṃ ullittāvalittaṃ nivātaṃ phusitaggaḷaṃ pihitavātapānaṃ.**Suppose there was a stilt longhouse with a peaked roof, plastered inside and out, draft-free, with latches fastened and windows shuttered.*";
P_HTM[2070]="*Tatrāssa pallaṅko gonakatthato paṭikatthato paṭalikatthato kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo sauttaracchado ubhatolohitakūpadhāno.**And it had a couch spread with woolen covers—shag-piled, pure white, or embroidered with flowers—and spread with a fine deer hide, with a canopy above and red pillows at both ends.*";
P_HTM[2071]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva pāsādaṃ paṇidhāya.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same stilt longhouse.*";
P_HTM[2072]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:*";
P_HTM[2073]="*‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā imaṃyeva pāsādaṃ āgamissatī’ti.**‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very stilt longhouse.’*";
P_HTM[2074]="*Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tasmiṃ pāsāde tasmiṃ kūṭāgāre tasmiṃ pallaṅke nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later they see them sitting or lying in that stilt longhouse, where they experience exclusively pleasant feelings. …*";
P_HTM[2075]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—* **";
P_HTM[2076]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2077]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2078]="*Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2079]="*tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatīti.**‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that they will realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[2080]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements, experiencing exclusively pleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[2081]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā.**Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with smooth banks, delightful.*";
P_HTM[2082]="*Avidūre cassā tibbo vanasaṇḍo.**And nearby was a dark forest grove.*";
P_HTM[2083]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito ekāyanena maggena tameva pokkharaṇiṃ paṇidhāya.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that very same lotus pond.*";
P_HTM[2084]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:*";
P_HTM[2085]="*‘tathā bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā imaṃyeva pokkharaṇiṃ āgamissatī’ti.**‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that they will arrive at that very lotus pond.’*";
P_HTM[2086]="*Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā nhāyitvā ca pivitvā ca sabbadarathakilamathapariḷāhaṃ paṭippassambhetvā paccuttaritvā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later they would see that person after they had plunged into that lotus pond, bathed and drunk. When all their stress, weariness, and heat exhaustion had faded away, they emerged and sat or lay down in that woodland thicket, where they experienced exclusively pleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[2087]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[2088]="*‘tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatī’ti.**‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that they will realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[2089]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ.**Then some time later I see that they have indeed realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements, experiencing exclusively pleasant feelings.*";
P_HTM[2090]="*Imā kho, sāriputta, pañca gatiyo.**These are the five destinations.*";
P_HTM[2091]="*Yo kho maṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ jānantaṃ evaṃ passantaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:**When I know and see in this way, suppose someone were to say this:*";
P_HTM[2092]="*‘natthi samaṇassa gotamassa uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso;**‘The ascetic Gotama has no superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[2093]="*takkapariyāhataṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānan’ti**He teaches what he’s worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing his own perspective.’*";
P_HTM[2094]="*taṃ, sāriputta, vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Unless they give up that speech and that thought, and let go of that view, they will be cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2095]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya; evaṃ sampadamidaṃ, sāriputta, vadāmi**Just as a mendicant accomplished in ethics, immersion, and wisdom would reach enlightenment in this very life, such is the consequence, I say.*";
P_HTM[2096]="*taṃ vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Unless they give up that speech and thought, and let go of that view, they will be cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2097]="*Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, caturaṅgasamannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ caritā—**Sāriputta, I recall having practiced a spiritual path consisting of four factors.*";
P_HTM[2098]="*tapassī sudaṃ homi paramatapassī, lūkho sudaṃ homi paramalūkho, jegucchī sudaṃ homi paramajegucchī, pavivitto sudaṃ homi paramapavivitto.**I used to be a self-mortifier, the ultimate self-mortifier. I used to live rough, the ultimate rough-liver. I used to live in disgust at sin, the ultimate one living in disgust at sin. I used to be secluded, in ultimate seclusion.*";
P_HTM[2099]="*Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, tapassitāya hoti—acelako homi muttācāro hatthāpalekhano, naehibhaddantiko natiṭṭhabhaddantiko; nābhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyāmi.**And this is what my self-mortification was like. I went naked, ignoring conventions. I licked my hands, and didn’t come or stop when asked. I didn’t consent to food brought to me, or food prepared specially for me, or an invitation for a meal.*";
P_HTM[2100]="*So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāmi, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāmi, na eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, na saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī; na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivāmi;**I didn’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where food for distribution is advertised; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. I accepted no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drank no beer.*";
P_HTM[2101]="*so ekāgāriko vā homi ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā homi dvālopiko … pe … sattāgāriko vā homi sattālopiko;**I went to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls.*";
P_HTM[2102]="*ekissāpi dattiyā yāpemi, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpemi … pe … sattahipi dattīhi yāpemi;**I fed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day.*";
P_HTM[2103]="*ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāremi, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāremi … pe … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāremi; iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmi.**I ate once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. I lived committed to the practice of eating food at set intervals.*";
P_HTM[2104]="*So sākabhakkho vā homi, sāmākabhakkho vā homi, nīvārabhakkho vā homi, daddulabhakkho vā homi, haṭabhakkho vā homi, kaṇabhakkho vā homi, ācāmabhakkho vā homi, piññākabhakkho vā homi, tiṇabhakkho vā homi, gomayabhakkho vā homi, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpemi pavattaphalabhojī.**I ate herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. I survived on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit.*";
P_HTM[2105]="*So sāṇānipi dhāremi, masāṇānipi dhāremi, chavadussānipi dhāremi, paṃsukūlānipi dhāremi, tirīṭānipi dhāremi, ajinampi dhāremi, ajinakkhipampi dhāremi, kusacīrampi dhāremi, vākacīrampi dhāremi, phalakacīrampi dhāremi, kesakambalampi dhāremi, vāḷakambalampi dhāremi, ulūkapakkhampi dhāremi;**I wore robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings.*";
P_HTM[2106]="*kesamassulocakopi homi kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto;**I tore out hair and beard, committed to this practice.*";
P_HTM[2107]="*ubbhaṭṭhakopi homi āsanapaṭikkhitto;**I constantly stood, refusing seats.*";
P_HTM[2108]="*ukkuṭikopi homi ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto;**I squatted, committed to the endeavor of squatting.*";
P_HTM[2109]="*kaṇṭakāpassayikopi homi kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappemi;**I lay on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns my bed.*";
P_HTM[2110]="*sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmi—**I was committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening.*";
P_HTM[2111]="*iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmi.**And so I lived committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body.*";
P_HTM[2112]="*Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, tapassitāya hoti.**Such was my practice of self-mortification.*";
P_HTM[2113]="*Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, lūkhasmiṃ hoti—**And this is what my rough living was like.*";
P_HTM[2114]="*nekavassagaṇikaṃ rajojallaṃ kāye sannicitaṃ hoti papaṭikajātaṃ.**The dust and dirt built up on my body over many years until it started flaking off.*";
P_HTM[2115]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, tindukakhāṇu nekavassagaṇiko sannicito hoti papaṭikajāto, evamevāssu me, sāriputta, nekavassagaṇikaṃ rajojallaṃ kāye sannicitaṃ hoti papaṭikajātaṃ.**It’s like the trunk of a pale-moon ebony tree, which builds up bark over many years until it starts flaking off.*";
P_HTM[2116]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, na evaṃ hoti:**But it didn’t occur to me:*";
P_HTM[2117]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ imaṃ rajojallaṃ pāṇinā parimajjeyyaṃ, aññe vā pana me imaṃ rajojallaṃ pāṇinā parimajjeyyun’ti.**‘Oh, this dust and dirt must be rubbed off by my hand or another’s.’*";
P_HTM[2118]="*Evampi me, sāriputta, na hoti.**That didn’t occur to me.*";
P_HTM[2119]="*Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, lūkhasmiṃ hoti. (1)**Such was my rough living.*";
P_HTM[2120]="*Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, jegucchismiṃ hoti—**And this is what my living in disgust of sin was like.*";
P_HTM[2121]="*so kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, satova abhikkamāmi, satova paṭikkamāmi, yāva udakabindumhipi me dayā paccupaṭṭhitā hoti:**I’d step forward or back ever so mindfully. I was full of pity even regarding a drop of water, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2122]="*‘māhaṃ khuddake pāṇe visamagate saṅghātaṃ āpādesin’ti.**‘May I not accidentally injure any little creatures that happen to be in the wrong place.’*";
P_HTM[2123]="*Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, jegucchismiṃ hoti. (2)**Such was my living in disgust of sin.*";
P_HTM[2124]="*Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, pavivittasmiṃ hoti—**And this is what my seclusion was like.*";
P_HTM[2125]="*so kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, aññataraṃ araññāyatanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā viharāmi.**I would plunge deep into a wilderness region and stay there.*";
P_HTM[2126]="*Yadā passāmi gopālakaṃ vā pasupālakaṃ vā tiṇahārakaṃ vā kaṭṭhahārakaṃ vā vanakammikaṃ vā, vanena vanaṃ gahanena gahanaṃ ninnena ninnaṃ thalena thalaṃ sampatāmi.**When I saw a cowherd or a shepherd, or someone gathering grass or sticks, or a lumberjack, I’d flee from forest to forest, from thicket to thicket, from valley to valley, from uplands to uplands.*";
P_HTM[2127]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2128]="*Mā maṃ te addasaṃsu ahañca mā te addasanti.**So that I wouldn’t see them, nor they me.*";
P_HTM[2129]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, āraññako mago manusse disvā vanena vanaṃ gahanena gahanaṃ ninnena ninnaṃ thalena thalaṃ sampatati;**I fled like a wild deer seeing a human being.*";
P_HTM[2130]="*evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, yadā passāmi gopālakaṃ vā pasupālakaṃ vā tiṇahārakaṃ vā kaṭṭhahārakaṃ vā vanakammikaṃ vā vanena vanaṃ gahanena gahanaṃ ninnena ninnaṃ thalena thalaṃ sampatāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2131]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[2132]="*Mā maṃ te addasaṃsu ahañca mā te addasanti.* **";
P_HTM[2133]="*Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, pavivittasmiṃ hoti. (3)**Such was my practice of seclusion.*";
P_HTM[2134]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ye te goṭṭhā paṭṭhitagāvo apagatagopālakā, tattha catukkuṇḍiko upasaṅkamitvā yāni tāni vacchakānaṃ taruṇakānaṃ dhenupakānaṃ gomayāni tāni sudaṃ āhāremi.**I would go on all fours into the cow-pens after the cattle had left and eat the dung of the young suckling calves.*";
P_HTM[2135]="*Yāvakīvañca me, sāriputta, sakaṃ muttakarīsaṃ apariyādinnaṃ hoti, sakaṃyeva sudaṃ muttakarīsaṃ āhāremi.**As long as my own urine and excrement lasted, I would even eat that.*";
P_HTM[2136]="*Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, mahāvikaṭabhojanasmiṃ hoti. (4)**Such was my eating of most unnatural things.*";
P_HTM[2137]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, aññataraṃ bhiṃsanakaṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā viharāmi.**I would plunge deep into an awe-inspiring forest grove and stay there.*";
P_HTM[2138]="*Tatrāssudaṃ, sāriputta, bhiṃsanakassa vanasaṇḍassa bhiṃsanakatasmiṃ hoti—**It was so awe-inspiring that*";
P_HTM[2139]="*yo koci avītarāgo taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ pavisati, yebhuyyena lomāni haṃsanti.**normally it would make your hair stand on end if you weren’t free of greed.*";
P_HTM[2140]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, yā tā rattiyo sītā hemantikā antaraṭṭhakā himapātasamayā tathārūpāsu rattīsu rattiṃ abbhokāse viharāmi, divā vanasaṇḍe;**And on cold nights like the eight days of winter when the snow falls I stayed in the open by night and in the forest by day.*";
P_HTM[2141]="*gimhānaṃ pacchime māse divā abbhokāse viharāmi, rattiṃ vanasaṇḍe.**But in the last month of summer I’d stay in the open by day and in the forest by night.*";
P_HTM[2142]="*Apissu maṃ, sāriputta, ayaṃ anacchariyagāthā paṭibhāsi pubbe assutapubbā:**And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[2143]="*‘Sotatto sosinno ceva,**‘Scorched and frozen,*";
P_HTM[2144]="*eko bhiṃsanake vane;**alone in the awe-inspiring forest.*";
P_HTM[2145]="*Naggo na caggimāsīno,**Naked, no fire to sit beside,*";
P_HTM[2146]="*esanāpasuto munī’ti.**the sage still pursues his quest.’*";
P_HTM[2147]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, susāne seyyaṃ kappemi chavaṭṭhikāni upadhāya.**I would make my bed in a charnel ground, with the bones of the dead for a pillow.*";
P_HTM[2148]="*Apissu maṃ, sāriputta, gāmaṇḍalā upasaṅkamitvā oṭṭhubhantipi, omuttentipi, paṃsukenapi okiranti, kaṇṇasotesupi salākaṃ pavesenti.**Then the cowboys would come up to me. They’d spit and piss on me, throw mud on me, even poke sticks in my ears.*";
P_HTM[2149]="*Na kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, abhijānāmi tesu pāpakaṃ cittaṃ uppādetā.**But I don’t recall ever having a bad thought about them.*";
P_HTM[2150]="*Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, upekkhāvihārasmiṃ hoti.**Such was my abiding in equanimity.*";
P_HTM[2151]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2152]="*‘āhārena suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from food.’*";
P_HTM[2153]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[2154]="*‘kolehi yāpemā’ti.**‘Let’s live on jujubes.’*";
P_HTM[2155]="*Te kolampi khādanti, kolacuṇṇampi khādanti, kolodakampi pivanti—**So they eat jujubes and jujube powder, and drink jujube juice.*";
P_HTM[2156]="*anekavihitampi kolavikatiṃ paribhuñjanti.**And they enjoy many jujube concoctions.*";
P_HTM[2157]="*Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaṃyeva kolaṃ āhāraṃ āhāritā.**I recall eating just a single jujube.*";
P_HTM[2158]="*Siyā kho pana te, sāriputta, evamassa:**You might think that*";
P_HTM[2159]="*‘mahā nūna tena samayena kolo ahosī’ti.**at that time the jujubes must have been very big.*";
P_HTM[2160]="*Na kho panetaṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ.**But you should not see it like this.*";
P_HTM[2161]="*Tadāpi etaparamoyeva kolo ahosi seyyathāpi etarahi.**The jujubes then were at most the same size as today.*";
P_HTM[2162]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaṃyeva kolaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.**Eating so very little, my body became extremely emaciated.*";
P_HTM[2163]="*Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty-year-old or a corpse,*";
P_HTM[2164]="*Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,*";
P_HTM[2165]="*Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako unnatāvanato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,*";
P_HTM[2166]="*Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn.*";
P_HTM[2167]="*Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti; evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well.*";
P_HTM[2168]="*Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-gourd in the wind and sun.*";
P_HTM[2169]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, yāvassu me, sāriputta, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly.*";
P_HTM[2170]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face down right there.*";
P_HTM[2171]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, tameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anomajjāmi. Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, pāṇinā gattāni anomajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā patanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out.*";
P_HTM[2172]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2173]="*‘āhārena suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from food.’*";
P_HTM[2174]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[2175]="*‘muggehi yāpema … pe …**‘Let’s live on mung beans.’ …*";
P_HTM[2176]="*tilehi yāpema … pe …**‘Let’s live on sesame.’ …*";
P_HTM[2177]="*taṇḍulehi yāpemā’ti.**‘Let’s live on ordinary rice.’ …*";
P_HTM[2178]="*Te taṇḍulampi khādanti, taṇḍulacuṇṇampi khādanti, taṇḍulodakampi pivanti—* **";
P_HTM[2179]="*anekavihitampi taṇḍulavikatiṃ paribhuñjanti.* **";
P_HTM[2180]="*Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaṃyeva taṇḍulaṃ āhāraṃ āhāritā.* **";
P_HTM[2181]="*Siyā kho pana te, sāriputta, evamassa:* **";
P_HTM[2182]="*‘mahā nūna tena samayena taṇḍulo ahosī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2183]="*Na kho panetaṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2184]="*Tadāpi etaparamoyeva taṇḍulo ahosi, seyyathāpi etarahi.* **";
P_HTM[2185]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaṃyeva taṇḍulaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[2186]="*Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2187]="*Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2188]="*Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako unnatāvanato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2189]="*Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2190]="*Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti; evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2191]="*Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2192]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi. Yāvassu me, sāriputta, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2193]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya.* **";
P_HTM[2194]="*So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, tameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anomajjāmi. Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, pāṇinā gattāni anomajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā patanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out.*";
P_HTM[2195]="*Tāyapi kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamaṃ uttariṃ manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ.**But Sāriputta, I did not achieve any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones by that conduct, that practice, that grueling work.*";
P_HTM[2196]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2197]="*Imissāyeva ariyāya paññāya anadhigamā, yāyaṃ ariyā paññā adhigatā ariyā niyyānikā, niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**Because I didn’t achieve that noble wisdom that’s noble and emancipating, and which leads someone who practices it to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[2198]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2199]="*‘saṃsārena suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from transmigration.’*";
P_HTM[2200]="*Na kho pana so, sāriputta, saṃsāro sulabharūpo yo mayā asaṃsaritapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā, aññatra suddhāvāsehi devehi.**But it’s not easy to find a realm that I haven’t previously transmigrated to in all this long time, except for the gods of the pure abodes.*";
P_HTM[2201]="*Suddhāvāse cāhaṃ, sāriputta, deve saṃsareyyaṃ, nayimaṃ lokaṃ punarāgaccheyyaṃ.**For if I had transmigrated to the gods of the pure abodes I would not have returned to this realm again.*";
P_HTM[2202]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2203]="*‘upapattiyā suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from rebirth.’*";
P_HTM[2204]="*Na kho pana sā, sāriputta, upapatti sulabharūpā yā mayā anupapannapubbā iminā dīghena addhunā, aññatra suddhāvāsehi devehi.**But it’s not easy to find any rebirth that I haven’t previously been reborn in …*";
P_HTM[2205]="*Suddhāvāse cāhaṃ, sāriputta, deve upapajjeyyaṃ, nayimaṃ lokaṃ punarāgaccheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2206]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2207]="*‘āvāsena suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from abode of rebirth.’*";
P_HTM[2208]="*Na kho pana so, sāriputta, āvāso sulabharūpo yo mayā anāvuṭṭhapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā, aññatra suddhāvāsehi devehi.**But it’s not easy to find an abode where I haven’t previously abided …*";
P_HTM[2209]="*Suddhāvāse cāhaṃ, sāriputta, deve āvaseyyaṃ, nayimaṃ lokaṃ punarāgaccheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2210]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2211]="*‘yaññena suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from sacrifice.’*";
P_HTM[2212]="*Na kho pana so, sāriputta, yañño sulabharūpo yo mayā ayiṭṭhapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā, tañca kho raññā vā satā khattiyena muddhāvasittena brāhmaṇena vā mahāsālena.**But it’s not easy to find a sacrifice that I haven’t previously offered in all this long time, when I was an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin.*";
P_HTM[2213]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2214]="*‘aggiparicariyāya suddhī’ti.**‘Purity comes from serving the sacred flame.’*";
P_HTM[2215]="*Na kho pana so, sāriputta, aggi sulabharūpo yo mayā apariciṇṇapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā, tañca kho raññā vā satā khattiyena muddhāvasittena brāhmaṇena vā mahāsālena.**But it’s not easy to find a fire that I haven’t previously served in all this long time, when I was an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin.*";
P_HTM[2216]="*Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[2217]="*‘yāvadevāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso daharo hoti yuvā susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā tāvadeva paramena paññāveyyattiyena samannāgato hoti.**‘So long as this gentleman is youthful, young, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life he will be endowed with perfect lucidity of wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2218]="*Yato ca kho ayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso jiṇṇo hoti vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto, āsītiko vā nāvutiko vā vassasatiko vā jātiyā, atha tamhā paññāveyyattiyā, parihāyatī’ti.**But when he’s old, elderly, and senior, advanced in years, and has reached the final stage of life—eighty, ninety, or a hundred years old—he will lose his lucidity of wisdom.’*";
P_HTM[2219]="*Na kho panetaṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ.**But you should not see it like this.*";
P_HTM[2220]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, sāriputta, etarahi jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto, āsītiko me vayo vattati.**For now I am old, elderly, and senior, I’m advanced in years, and have reached the final stage of life. I am eighty years old.*";
P_HTM[2221]="*Idha me assu, sāriputta, cattāro sāvakā vassasatāyukā vassasatajīvino, paramāya satiyā ca gatiyā ca dhitiyā ca samannāgatā paramena ca paññāveyyattiyena.**Suppose I had four disciples with a lifespan of a hundred years. And they each were perfect in memory, range, retention, and perfect lucidity of wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2222]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, daḷhadhammā dhanuggaho sikkhito katahattho katūpāsano lahukena asanena appakasireneva tiriyaṃ tālacchāyaṃ atipāteyya,**Imagine how easily a well-trained expert archer with a strong bow would shoot a light arrow across the shadow of a palm tree.*";
P_HTM[2223]="*evaṃ adhimattasatimanto evaṃ adhimattagatimanto evaṃ adhimattadhitimanto evaṃ paramena paññāveyyattiyena samannāgatā.**That’s how extraordinary they were in memory, range, retention, and perfect lucidity of wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2224]="*Te maṃ catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ upādāyupādāya pañhaṃ puccheyyuṃ, puṭṭho puṭṭho cāhaṃ tesaṃ byākareyyaṃ, byākatañca me byākatato dhāreyyuṃ, na ca maṃ dutiyakaṃ uttari paṭipuccheyyuṃ.**They’d bring up questions about the four kinds of mindfulness meditation again and again, and I would answer each question. They’d remember the answers and not ask the same question twice.*";
P_HTM[2225]="*Aññatra asitapītakhāyitasāyitā aññatra uccārapassāvakammā, aññatra niddākilamathapaṭivinodanā apariyādinnāyevassa, sāriputta, tathāgatassa dhammadesanā, apariyādinnaṃyevassa tathāgatassa dhammapadabyañjanaṃ, apariyādinnaṃyevassa tathāgatassa pañhapaṭibhānaṃ.**And they’d pause only to eat and drink, go to the toilet, and sleep to dispel weariness. But the Realized One would not run out of Dhamma teachings, words and phrases of the teachings, or spontaneous answers.*";
P_HTM[2226]="*Atha me te cattāro sāvakā vassasatāyukā vassasatajīvino vassasatassa accayena kālaṃ kareyyuṃ.**And at the end of a hundred years my four disciples would pass away.*";
P_HTM[2227]="*Mañcakena cepi maṃ, sāriputta, pariharissatha, nevatthi tathāgatassa paññāveyyattiyassa aññathattaṃ.**Even if you have to carry me around on a stretcher, there will never be any deterioration in the Realized One’s lucidity of wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2228]="*Yaṃ kho taṃ, sāriputta, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**And if there’s anyone of whom it may be rightly said that*";
P_HTM[2229]="*‘asammohadhammo satto loke uppanno bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti, mameva taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya**a being not liable to delusion has arisen in the world for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans, it’s of me that this should be said.”*";
P_HTM[2230]="*‘asammohadhammo satto loke uppanno bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2231]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā nāgasamālo bhagavato piṭṭhito ṭhito hoti bhagavantaṃ bījayamāno.**Now at that time Venerable Nāgasamāla was standing behind the Buddha fanning him.*";
P_HTM[2232]="*Atha kho āyasmā nāgasamālo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then he said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[2233]="*“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[2234]="*Api hi me, bhante, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ sutvā lomāni haṭṭhāni.**While I was listening to this exposition of the teaching my hair stood up!*";
P_HTM[2235]="*Konāmo ayaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo”ti?**What is the name of this exposition of the teaching?”*";
P_HTM[2236]="*“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, nāgasamāla, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ lomahaṃsanapariyāyotveva naṃ dhārehī”ti.**“Well, Nāgasamāla, you may remember this exposition of the teaching as ‘The Hair-raising Discourse’.”*";
P_HTM[2237]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2238]="*Attamano āyasmā nāgasamālo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Nāgasamāla was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2239]="*Mahāsīhanādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2240]="*13. Mahādukkhakkhandhasutta**The Longer Discourse on the Mass of Suffering*";
P_HTM[2241]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2242]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2243]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃsu.**Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[2244]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:**Then it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[2245]="*“atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ,**“It’s too early to wander for alms in Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2246]="*yaṃ nūna mayaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyāmā”ti.**Why don’t we go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?”*";
P_HTM[2247]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu;**Then they went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and exchanged greetings with the wanderers there.*";
P_HTM[2248]="*sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. The wanderers said to them:*";
P_HTM[2249]="*“samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapeti, mayampi kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapema;**“Reverends, the ascetic Gotama advocates the complete understanding of sensual pleasures, and so do we.*";
P_HTM[2250]="*samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo rūpānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapeti, mayampi rūpānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapema;**The ascetic Gotama advocates the complete understanding of sights, and so do we.*";
P_HTM[2251]="*samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo vedanānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapeti, mayampi vedanānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapema;**The ascetic Gotama advocates the complete understanding of feelings, and so do we.*";
P_HTM[2252]="*idha no, āvuso, ko viseso, ko adhippayāso, kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ samaṇassa vā gotamassa amhākaṃ vā—**What, then, is the difference between the ascetic Gotama’s teaching and instruction and ours?”*";
P_HTM[2253]="*yadidaṃ dhammadesanāya vā dhammadesanaṃ, anusāsaniyā vā anusāsanin”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2254]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃsu, nappaṭikkosiṃsu;**Those mendicants neither approved nor dismissed that statement of the wanderers who follow other paths.*";
P_HTM[2255]="*anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu:**They got up from their seat, thinking,*";
P_HTM[2256]="*“bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmā”ti.**“We will learn the meaning of this statement from the Buddha himself.”*";
P_HTM[2257]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then, after the meal, when they returned from alms-round, they went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said:*";
P_HTM[2258]="*“idha mayaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisimha.* **";
P_HTM[2259]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2260]="*‘atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2261]="*yaṃ nūna mayaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2262]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodimha;* **";
P_HTM[2263]="*sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdimha. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho amhe, bhante, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2264]="*‘samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapeti, mayampi kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapema.* **";
P_HTM[2265]="*Samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo rūpānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapeti, mayampi rūpānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapema.* **";
P_HTM[2266]="*Samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo vedanānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapeti, mayampi vedanānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapema.* **";
P_HTM[2267]="*Idha no, āvuso, ko viseso, ko adhippayāso, kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ samaṇassa vā gotamassa amhākaṃ vā, yadidaṃ dhammadesanāya vā dhammadesanaṃ anusāsaniyā vā anusāsanin’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2268]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandimha, nappaṭikkosimha;* **";
P_HTM[2269]="*anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamimha:* **";
P_HTM[2270]="*‘bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2271]="*“Evaṃvādino, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:**“Mendicants, when wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say to them:*";
P_HTM[2272]="*‘ko panāvuso, kāmānaṃ assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**‘But reverends, what’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[2273]="*Ko rūpānaṃ assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to sights?*";
P_HTM[2274]="*Ko vedanānaṃ assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti?**What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to feelings?’*";
P_HTM[2275]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā na ceva sampāyissanti, uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjissanti.**Questioned like this, the wanderers who follow other paths would be stumped, and, in addition, would get frustrated.*";
P_HTM[2276]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2277]="*Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmiṃ.**Because they’re out of their element.*";
P_HTM[2278]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya yo imesaṃ pañhānaṃ veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyya, aññatra tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā, ito vā pana sutvā.**I don’t see anyone in this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—who could provide a satisfying answer to these questions except for the Realized One or his disciple or someone who has heard it from them.*";
P_HTM[2279]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ assādo?**And what is the gratification of sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[2280]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā.**There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2281]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2282]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2283]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[2284]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[2285]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[2286]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2287]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2288]="*Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—ayaṃ kāmānaṃ assādo.**The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation: this is the gratification of sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2289]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo?**And what is the drawback of sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[2290]="*Idha, bhikkhave, kulaputto yena sippaṭṭhānena jīvikaṃ kappeti—**It’s when a gentleman earns a living by means such as*";
P_HTM[2291]="*yadi muddāya yadi gaṇanāya yadi saṅkhānena yadi kasiyā yadi vaṇijjāya yadi gorakkhena yadi issatthena yadi rājaporisena yadi sippaññatarena—**computing, accounting, calculating, farming, trade, raising cattle, archery, government service, or one of the professions.*";
P_HTM[2292]="*sītassa purakkhato uṇhassa purakkhato ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassehi rissamāno khuppipāsāya mīyamāno;**But they must face cold and heat, being hurt by the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles, and risking death from hunger and thirst.*";
P_HTM[2293]="*ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2294]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, kulaputtassa evaṃ uṭṭhahato ghaṭato vāyamato te bhogā nābhinipphajjanti.**That gentleman might try hard, strive, and make an effort, but fail to earn any money.*";
P_HTM[2295]="*So socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati:**If this happens, they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion, saying:*";
P_HTM[2296]="*‘moghaṃ vata me uṭṭhānaṃ, aphalo vata me vāyāmo’ti.**‘Oh, my hard work is wasted. My efforts are fruitless!’*";
P_HTM[2297]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2298]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, kulaputtassa evaṃ uṭṭhahato ghaṭato vāyamato te bhogā abhinipphajjanti.**That gentleman might try hard, strive, and make an effort, and succeed in earning money.*";
P_HTM[2299]="*So tesaṃ bhogānaṃ ārakkhādhikaraṇaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti:**But they experience pain and sadness when they try to protect it, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2300]="*‘kinti me bhoge neva rājāno hareyyuṃ, na corā hareyyuṃ, na aggi daheyya, na udakaṃ vaheyya, na appiyā dāyādā hareyyun’ti.**‘How can I prevent my wealth from being taken by rulers or bandits, consumed by fire, swept away by flood, or taken by unloved heirs?’*";
P_HTM[2301]="*Tassa evaṃ ārakkhato gopayato te bhoge rājāno vā haranti, corā vā haranti, aggi vā dahati, udakaṃ vā vahati, appiyā vā dāyādā haranti.**And even though they protect it and ward it, rulers or bandits take it, or fire consumes it, or flood sweeps it away, or unloved heirs take it.*";
P_HTM[2302]="*So socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati:**They sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion:*";
P_HTM[2303]="*‘yampi me ahosi tampi no natthī’ti.**‘What used to be mine is gone.’*";
P_HTM[2304]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2305]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu rājānopi rājūhi vivadanti, khattiyāpi khattiyehi vivadanti, brāhmaṇāpi brāhmaṇehi vivadanti, gahapatīpi gahapatīhi vivadanti, mātāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi mātarā vivadati, pitāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi pitarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhātarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhaginiyā vivadati, bhaginīpi bhātarā vivadati, sahāyopi sahāyena vivadati.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures kings fight with kings, aristocrats fight with aristocrats, brahmins fight with brahmins, and householders fight with householders. A mother fights with her child, child with mother, father with child, and child with father. Brother fights with brother, brother with sister, sister with brother, and friend fights with friend.*";
P_HTM[2306]="*Te tattha kalahaviggahavivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ pāṇīhipi upakkamanti, leḍḍūhipi upakkamanti, daṇḍehipi upakkamanti, satthehipi upakkamanti.**Once they’ve started quarreling, arguing, and fighting, they attack each other with fists, stones, rods, and swords,*";
P_HTM[2307]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2308]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2309]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu asicammaṃ gahetvā, dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā, ubhatobyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ pakkhandanti usūsupi khippamānesu, sattīsupi khippamānāsu, asīsupi vijjotalantesu.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures they don their sword and shield, fasten their bow and arrows, and plunge into a battle massed on both sides, with arrows and spears flying and swords flashing.*";
P_HTM[2310]="*Te tattha usūhipi vijjhanti, sattiyāpi vijjhanti, asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti.**There they are struck with arrows and spears, and their heads are chopped off,*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2312]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2313]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu asicammaṃ gahetvā, dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā, addāvalepanā upakāriyo pakkhandanti usūsupi khippamānesu, sattīsupi khippamānāsu, asīsupi vijjotalantesu.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures they don their sword and shield, fasten their bow and arrows, and charge wetly plastered bastions, with arrows and spears flying and swords flashing.*";
P_HTM[2314]="*Te tattha usūhipi vijjhanti, sattiyāpi vijjhanti, chakaṇakāyapi osiñcanti, abhivaggenapi omaddanti, asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti.**There they are struck with arrows and spears, splashed with dung, crushed with spiked blocks, and their heads are chopped off,*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2316]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2317]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu sandhimpi chindanti, nillopampi haranti, ekāgārikampi karonti, paripanthepi tiṭṭhanti, paradārampi gacchanti.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures they break into houses, plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, and commit adultery.*";
P_HTM[2318]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā vividhā kammakāraṇā kārenti—**The rulers would arrest them and subject them to various punishments—*";
P_HTM[2319]="*kasāhipi tāḷenti, vettehipi tāḷenti, aḍḍhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷenti; hatthampi chindanti, pādampi chindanti, hatthapādampi chindanti, kaṇṇampi chindanti, nāsampi chindanti, kaṇṇanāsampi chindanti; bilaṅgathālikampi karonti, saṅkhamuṇḍikampi karonti, rāhumukhampi karonti, jotimālikampi karonti, hatthapajjotikampi karonti, erakavattikampi karonti, cīrakavāsikampi karonti, eṇeyyakampi karonti, baḷisamaṃsikampi karonti, kahāpaṇikampi karonti, khārāpatacchikampi karonti, palighaparivattikampi karonti, palālapīṭhakampi karonti, tattenapi telena osiñcanti, sunakhehipi khādāpenti, jīvantampi sūle uttāsenti, asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti.**whipping, caning, and clubbing; cutting off hands or feet, or both; cutting off ears or nose, or both; the ‘porridge pot’, the ‘shell-shave’, the ‘demon’s mouth’, the ‘garland of fire’, the ‘burning hand’, the ‘grass blades’, the ‘bark dress’, the ‘antelope’, the ‘meat hook’, the ‘coins’, the ‘acid pickle’, the ‘twisting bar’, the ‘straw mat’; being splashed with hot oil, being fed to the dogs, being impaled alive, and being beheaded.*";
P_HTM[2320]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**These result in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2321]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2322]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu kāyena duccaritaṃ caranti, vācāya duccaritaṃ caranti, manasā duccaritaṃ caranti.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures, they conduct themselves badly by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2323]="*Te kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2324]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo samparāyiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This is a drawback of sensual pleasures to do with lives to come, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2325]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**And what is the escape from sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[2326]="*Yo kho, bhikkhave, kāmesu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—idaṃ kāmānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for sensual pleasures: this is the escape from sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2327]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ kāmānaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti te vata sāmaṃ vā kāme parijānissanti, paraṃ vā tathattāya samādapessanti yathā paṭipanno kāme parijānissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand sensual pleasures’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are. It’s impossible for them to completely understand sensual pleasures themselves, or to instruct another so that, practicing accordingly, they will completely understand sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2328]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ kāmānaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti, te vata sāmaṃ vā kāme parijānissanti paraṃ vā tathattāya samādapessanti yathā paṭipanno kāme parijānissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand sensual pleasures’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are. It is possible for them to completely understand sensual pleasures themselves, or to instruct another so that, practicing accordingly, they will completely understand sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2329]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ assādo?**And what is the gratification of sights?*";
P_HTM[2330]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, khattiyakaññā vā brāhmaṇakaññā vā gahapatikaññā vā pannarasavassuddesikā vā soḷasavassuddesikā vā, nātidīghā nātirassā nātikisā nātithūlā nātikāḷī nāccodātā paramā sā, bhikkhave, tasmiṃ samaye subhā vaṇṇanibhāti?**Suppose there was a girl of the brahmins, aristocrats, or householders in her fifteenth or sixteenth year, neither too tall nor too short, neither too thin nor too fat, neither too dark nor too fair. Is she not at the height of her beauty and prettiness?”*";
P_HTM[2331]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2332]="*Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, subhaṃ vaṇṇanibhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—**“The pleasure and happiness that arise from this beauty and prettiness*";
P_HTM[2333]="*ayaṃ rūpānaṃ assādo.**is the gratification of sights.*";
P_HTM[2334]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo?**And what is the drawback of sights?*";
P_HTM[2335]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tameva bhaginiṃ passeyya aparena samayena āsītikaṃ vā nāvutikaṃ vā vassasatikaṃ vā jātiyā, jiṇṇaṃ gopānasivaṅkaṃ bhoggaṃ daṇḍaparāyanaṃ pavedhamānaṃ gacchantiṃ āturaṃ gatayobbanaṃ khaṇḍadantaṃ palitakesaṃ, vilūnaṃ khalitasiraṃ valinaṃ tilakāhatagattaṃ.**Suppose that some time later you were to see that same sister—eighty, ninety, or a hundred years old—bent double, crooked, leaning on a staff, trembling as they walk, ailing, past their prime, with teeth broken, hair grey and scanty or bald, skin wrinkled, and limbs blotchy.*";
P_HTM[2336]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[2337]="*yā purimā subhā vaṇṇanibhā sā antarahitā, ādīnavo pātubhūtoti?**Has not that former beauty vanished and the drawback become clear?”*";
P_HTM[2338]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2339]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.**“This is the drawback of sights.*";
P_HTM[2340]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tameva bhaginiṃ passeyya ābādhikaṃ dukkhitaṃ bāḷhagilānaṃ, sake muttakarīse palipannaṃ semānaṃ, aññehi vuṭṭhāpiyamānaṃ, aññehi saṃvesiyamānaṃ.**Furthermore, suppose that you were to see that same sister sick, suffering, gravely ill, collapsed in her own urine and feces, being picked up by some and put down by others.*";
P_HTM[2341]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[2342]="*yā purimā subhā vaṇṇanibhā sā antarahitā, ādīnavo pātubhūtoti?**Has not that former beauty vanished and the drawback become clear?”*";
P_HTM[2343]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2344]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.**“This too is the drawback of sights.*";
P_HTM[2345]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tameva bhaginiṃ passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya chaḍḍitaṃ—**Furthermore, suppose that you were to see that same sister as a corpse discarded in a charnel ground. And she had been dead for one, two, or three days, bloated, livid, and festering.*";
P_HTM[2346]="*ekāhamataṃ vā dvīhamataṃ vā tīhamataṃ vā, uddhumātakaṃ vinīlakaṃ vipubbakajātaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2347]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[2348]="*yā purimā subhā vaṇṇanibhā sā antarahitā, ādīnavo pātubhūtoti?**Has not that former beauty vanished and the drawback become clear?”*";
P_HTM[2349]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2350]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.**“This too is the drawback of sights.*";
P_HTM[2351]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tameva bhaginiṃ passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya chaḍḍitaṃ—**Furthermore, suppose that you were to see that same sister as a corpse discarded in a charnel ground. And she was being devoured by crows, hawks, vultures, herons, dogs, tigers, leopards, jackals, and many kinds of little creatures …*";
P_HTM[2352]="*kākehi vā khajjamānaṃ, kulalehi vā khajjamānaṃ, gijjhehi vā khajjamānaṃ, kaṅkehi vā khajjamānaṃ, sunakhehi vā khajjamānaṃ, byagghehi vā khajjamānaṃ, dīpīhi vā khajjamānaṃ, siṅgālehi vā khajjamānaṃ, vividhehi vā pāṇakajātehi khajjamānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2353]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, yā purimā subhā vaṇṇanibhā sā antarahitā, ādīnavo pātubhūtoti?* **";
P_HTM[2354]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.* **";
P_HTM[2355]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.* **";
P_HTM[2356]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tameva bhaginiṃ passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya chaḍḍitaṃ—**Furthermore, suppose that you were to see that same sister as a corpse discarded in a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[2357]="*aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ samaṃsalohitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ, aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ nimaṃsalohitamakkhitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ, aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ apagatamaṃsalohitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ, aṭṭhikāni apagatasambandhāni disāvidisāvikkhittāni—**And she had been reduced to a skeleton with flesh and blood, held together by sinews … a skeleton rid of flesh but smeared with blood, and held together by sinews … a skeleton rid of flesh and blood, held together by sinews …*";
P_HTM[2358]="*aññena hatthaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena pādaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena gopphakaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena jaṅghaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena ūruṭṭhikaṃ, aññena kaṭiṭṭhikaṃ, aññena phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena piṭṭhiṭṭhikaṃ, aññena khandhaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena gīvaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena hanukaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena dantaṭṭhikaṃ, aññena sīsakaṭāhaṃ.**bones without sinews scattered in every direction. Here a hand-bone, there a foot-bone, here a shin-bone, there a thigh-bone, here a hip-bone, there a rib-bone, here a back-bone, there an arm-bone, here a neck-bone, there a jaw-bone, here a tooth, there the skull. …*";
P_HTM[2359]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, yā purimā subhā vaṇṇanibhā sā antarahitā, ādīnavo pātubhūtoti?* **";
P_HTM[2360]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.* **";
P_HTM[2361]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.* **";
P_HTM[2362]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tameva bhaginiṃ passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya chaḍḍitaṃ—**Furthermore, suppose that you were to see that same sister as a corpse discarded in a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[2363]="*aṭṭhikāni setāni saṅkhavaṇṇapaṭibhāgāni, aṭṭhikāni puñjakitāni terovassikāni, aṭṭhikāni pūtīni cuṇṇakajātāni.**And she had been reduced to white bones, the color of shells … decrepit bones, heaped in a pile … bones rotted and crumbled to powder.*";
P_HTM[2364]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[2365]="*yā purimā subhā vaṇṇanibhā sā antarahitā, ādīnavo pātubhūtoti?**Has not that former beauty vanished and the drawback become clear?”*";
P_HTM[2366]="*‘Evaṃ, bhante’.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2367]="*Ayampi, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.**“This too is the drawback of sights.*";
P_HTM[2368]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**And what is the escape from sights?*";
P_HTM[2369]="*Yo, bhikkhave, rūpesu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—idaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for sights: this is the escape from sights.*";
P_HTM[2370]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ rūpānaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti te vata sāmaṃ vā rūpe parijānissanti, paraṃ vā tathattāya samādapessanti yathā paṭipanno rūpe parijānissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand sights’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are. It’s impossible for them to completely understand sights themselves, or to instruct another so that, practicing accordingly, they will completely understand sights.*";
P_HTM[2371]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ rūpānaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti te vata sāmaṃ vā rūpe parijānissanti paraṃ vā tathattāya samādapessanti yathā paṭipanno rūpe parijānissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand sights’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are. It is possible for them to completely understand sights themselves, or to instruct another so that, practicing accordingly, they will completely understand sights.*";
P_HTM[2372]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ assādo?**And what is the gratification of feelings?*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, neva tasmiṃ samaye attabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti;**At that time a mendicant doesn’t intend to hurt themselves, hurt others, or hurt both;*";
P_HTM[2375]="*abyābajjhaṃyeva tasmiṃ samaye vedanaṃ vedeti.**they feel only feelings that are not hurtful.*";
P_HTM[2376]="*Abyābajjhaparamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ assādaṃ vadāmi.**Freedom from being hurt is the ultimate gratification of feelings, I say.*";
P_HTM[2377]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[2378]="*yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā, upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[2379]="*yasmiṃ samaye, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, neva tasmiṃ samaye attabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti;**fourth absorption. At that time a mendicant doesn’t intend to hurt themselves, hurt others, or hurt both;*";
P_HTM[2380]="*abyābajjhaṃyeva tasmiṃ samaye vedanaṃ vedeti.**they feel only feelings that are not hurtful.*";
P_HTM[2381]="*Abyābajjhaparamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ assādaṃ vadāmi.**Freedom from being hurt is the ultimate gratification of feelings, I say.*";
P_HTM[2382]="*Ko ca, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ ādīnavo?**And what is the drawback of feelings?*";
P_HTM[2383]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, vedanā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā—ayaṃ vedanānaṃ ādīnavo.**That feelings are impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is their drawback.*";
P_HTM[2384]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**And what is the escape from feelings?*";
P_HTM[2385]="*Yo, bhikkhave, vedanāsu chandarāgavinayo, chandarāgappahānaṃ—idaṃ vedanānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for feelings: this is the escape from feelings.*";
P_HTM[2386]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ vedanānaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti, te vata sāmaṃ vā vedanaṃ parijānissanti, paraṃ vā tathattāya samādapessanti yathā paṭipanno vedanaṃ parijānissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand feelings’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are. It’s impossible for them to completely understand feelings themselves, or to instruct another so that, practicing accordingly, they will completely understand feelings.*";
P_HTM[2387]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ vedanānaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti te vata sāmaṃ vā vedanaṃ parijānissanti, paraṃ vā tathattāya samādapessanti yathā paṭipanno vedanaṃ parijānissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjatī”ti.**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand feelings’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are. It is possible for them to completely understand feelings themselves, or to instruct another so that, practicing accordingly, they will completely understand feelings.”*";
P_HTM[2388]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2389]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2390]="*14. Cūḷadukkhakkhandhasutta**The Shorter Discourse on the Mass of Suffering*";
P_HTM[2391]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2392]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2393]="*Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Mahānāma the Sakyan went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[2394]="*“dīgharattāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi:**“For a long time, sir, I have understood your teaching like this:*";
P_HTM[2395]="*‘lobho cittassa upakkileso, doso cittassa upakkileso, moho cittassa upakkileso’ti.**‘Greed, hate, and delusion are corruptions of the mind.’*";
P_HTM[2396]="*Evañcāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi:* **";
P_HTM[2397]="*‘lobho cittassa upakkileso, doso cittassa upakkileso, moho cittassa upakkileso’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2398]="*Atha ca pana me ekadā lobhadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti, dosadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti, mohadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti.**Despite understanding this, sometimes my mind is occupied by thoughts of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2399]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[2400]="*‘kosu nāma me dhammo ajjhattaṃ appahīno yena me ekadā lobhadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti, dosadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti, mohadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhantī’”ti.**I wonder what qualities remain in me that I have such thoughts?”*";
P_HTM[2401]="*“So eva kho te, mahānāma, dhammo ajjhattaṃ appahīno yena te ekadā lobhadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti, dosadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti, mohadhammāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti.**“Mahānāma, there is a quality that remains in you that makes you have such thoughts.*";
P_HTM[2402]="*So ca hi te, mahānāma, dhammo ajjhattaṃ pahīno abhavissa, na tvaṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvaseyyāsi, na kāme paribhuñjeyyāsi.**For if you had given up that quality you would not still be living at home and enjoying sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2403]="*Yasmā ca kho te, mahānāma, so eva dhammo ajjhattaṃ appahīno tasmā tvaṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasasi, kāme paribhuñjasi.**But because you haven’t given up that quality you are still living at home and enjoying sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2404]="*‘Appassādā kāmā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti—**Sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[2405]="*iti cepi, mahānāma, ariyasāvakassa yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ hoti, so ca aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ nādhigacchati, aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ;**Even though a noble disciple has clearly seen this with right wisdom, so long as they don’t achieve the rapture and bliss that are apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities, or something even more peaceful than that,*";
P_HTM[2406]="*atha kho so neva tāva anāvaṭṭī kāmesu hoti.**they might still return to sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2407]="*Yato ca kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvakassa ‘appassādā kāmā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ hoti, so ca aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ adhigacchati aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ;**But when they do achieve that rapture and bliss, or something more peaceful than that,*";
P_HTM[2408]="*atha kho so anāvaṭṭī kāmesu hoti.**they will not return to sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2409]="*Mayhampi kho, mahānāma, pubbeva sambodhā, anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato,**Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too clearly saw with right wisdom that:*";
P_HTM[2410]="*‘appassādā kāmā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ hoti,**‘Sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.’*";
P_HTM[2411]="*so ca aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ nājjhagamaṃ, aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ;**But so long as I didn’t achieve the rapture and bliss that are apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities, or something even more peaceful than that,*";
P_HTM[2412]="*atha khvāhaṃ neva tāva anāvaṭṭī kāmesu paccaññāsiṃ.**I didn’t announce that I would not return to sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2413]="*Yato ca kho me, mahānāma, ‘appassādā kāmā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ ahosi, so ca aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ ajjhagamaṃ, aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ;**But when I did achieve that rapture and bliss, or something more peaceful than that,*";
P_HTM[2414]="*athāhaṃ anāvaṭṭī kāmesu paccaññāsiṃ.**I announced that I would not return to sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*Ko ca, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ assādo?**And what is the gratification of sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[2416]="*Pañcime, mahānāma, kāmaguṇā.**There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2417]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2418]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā;**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[2420]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[2421]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[2422]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2423]="*ime kho, mahānāma, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2424]="*Yaṃ kho, mahānāma, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—**The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation: this is the gratification of sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2425]="*ayaṃ kāmānaṃ assādo.* **";
P_HTM[2426]="*Ko ca, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo?**And what is the drawback of sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Idha, mahānāma, kulaputto yena sippaṭṭhānena jīvikaṃ kappeti—**It’s when a gentleman earns a living by means such as*";
P_HTM[2428]="*yadi muddāya yadi gaṇanāya yadi saṅkhānena yadi kasiyā yadi vaṇijjāya yadi gorakkhena yadi issatthena yadi rājaporisena yadi sippaññatarena,**computing, accounting, calculating, farming, trade, raising cattle, archery, government service, or one of the professions.*";
P_HTM[2429]="*sītassa purakkhato uṇhassa purakkhato ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassehi rissamāno khuppipāsāya mīyamāno;**But they must face cold and heat, being hurt by the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles, and risking death from hunger and thirst.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Tassa ce, mahānāma, kulaputtassa evaṃ uṭṭhahato ghaṭato vāyamato te bhogā nābhinipphajjanti,**That gentleman might try hard, strive, and make an effort, but fail to earn any money.*";
P_HTM[2432]="*so socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati ‘moghaṃ vata me uṭṭhānaṃ, aphalo vata me vāyāmo’ti.**If this happens, they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion, saying: ‘Oh, my hard work is wasted. My efforts are fruitless!’*";
P_HTM[2433]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2434]="*Tassa ce, mahānāma, kulaputtassa evaṃ uṭṭhahato ghaṭato vāyamato te bhogā abhinipphajjanti.**That gentleman might try hard, strive, and make an effort, and succeed in earning money.*";
P_HTM[2435]="*So tesaṃ bhogānaṃ ārakkhādhikaraṇaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti:**But they experience pain and sadness when they try to protect it, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2436]="*‘kinti me bhoge neva rājāno hareyyuṃ, na corā hareyyuṃ, na aggi daheyya, na udakaṃ vaheyya, na appiyā vā dāyādā hareyyun’ti.**‘How can I prevent my wealth from being taken by rulers or bandits, consumed by fire, swept away by flood, or taken by unloved heirs?’*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Tassa evaṃ ārakkhato gopayato te bhoge rājāno vā haranti, corā vā haranti, aggi vā dahati, udakaṃ vā vahati, appiyā vā dāyādā haranti.**And even though they protect it and ward it, rulers or bandits take it, or fire consumes it, or flood sweeps it away, or unloved heirs take it.*";
P_HTM[2438]="*So socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati:**They sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion:*";
P_HTM[2439]="*‘yampi me ahosi tampi no natthī’ti.**‘What used to be mine is gone.’*";
P_HTM[2440]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2441]="*Puna caparaṃ, mahānāma, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu rājānopi rājūhi vivadanti, khattiyāpi khattiyehi vivadanti, brāhmaṇāpi brāhmaṇehi vivadanti, gahapatīpi gahapatīhi vivadanti, mātāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi mātarā vivadati, pitāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi pitarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhātarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhaginiyā vivadati, bhaginīpi bhātarā vivadati, sahāyopi sahāyena vivadati.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures kings fight with kings, aristocrats fight with aristocrats, brahmins fight with brahmins, and householders fight with householders. A mother fights with her child, child with mother, father with child, and child with father. Brother fights with brother, brother with sister, sister with brother, and friend fights with friend.*";
P_HTM[2442]="*Te tattha kalahaviggahavivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ pāṇīhipi upakkamanti, leḍḍūhipi upakkamanti, daṇḍehipi upakkamanti, satthehipi upakkamanti.**Once they’ve started quarreling, arguing, and fighting, they attack each other with fists, stones, rods, and swords,*";
P_HTM[2443]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2444]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Puna caparaṃ, mahānāma, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu asicammaṃ gahetvā, dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā, ubhatobyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ pakkhandanti usūsupi khippamānesu, sattīsupi khippamānāsu, asīsupi vijjotalantesu.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures they don their sword and shield, fasten their bow and arrows, and plunge into a battle massed on both sides, with arrows and spears flying and swords flashing.*";
P_HTM[2446]="*Te tattha usūhipi vijjhanti, sattiyāpi vijjhanti, asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti.**There they are struck with arrows and spears, and their heads are chopped off,*";
P_HTM[2447]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2448]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2449]="*Puna caparaṃ, mahānāma, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu asicammaṃ gahetvā, dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā, addāvalepanā upakāriyo pakkhandanti usūsupi khippamānesu, sattīsupi khippamānāsu, asīsupi vijjotalantesu.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures they don their sword and shield, fasten their bow and arrows, and charge wetly plastered bastions, with arrows and spears flying and swords flashing.*";
P_HTM[2450]="*Te tattha usūhipi vijjhanti, sattiyāpi vijjhanti, chakaṇakāyapi osiñcanti, abhivaggenapi omaddanti, asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti.**There they are struck with arrows and spears, splashed with dung, crushed with spiked blocks, and their heads are chopped off,*";
P_HTM[2451]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2452]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2453]="*Puna caparaṃ, mahānāma, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu sandhimpi chindanti, nillopampi haranti, ekāgārikampi karonti, paripanthepi tiṭṭhanti, paradārampi gacchanti.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures they break into houses, plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, and commit adultery.*";
P_HTM[2454]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā vividhā kammakāraṇā kārenti—**The rulers would arrest them and subject them to various punishments—*";
P_HTM[2455]="*kasāhipi tāḷenti, vettehipi tāḷenti, aḍḍhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷenti; hatthampi chindanti, pādampi chindanti, hatthapādampi chindanti, kaṇṇampi chindanti, nāsampi chindanti, kaṇṇanāsampi chindanti; bilaṅgathālikampi karonti, saṅkhamuṇḍikampi karonti, rāhumukhampi karonti, jotimālikampi karonti, hatthapajjotikampi karonti, erakavattikampi karonti, cīrakavāsikampi karonti, eṇeyyakampi karonti, baḷisamaṃsikampi karonti, kahāpaṇikampi karonti, khārāpatacchikampi karonti, palighaparivattikampi karonti, palālapīṭhakampi karonti, tattenapi telena osiñcanti, sunakhehipi khādāpenti, jīvantampi sūle uttāsenti, asināpi sīsaṃ chindanti.**whipping, caning, and clubbing; cutting off hands or feet, or both; cutting off ears or nose, or both; the ‘porridge pot’, the ‘shell-shave’, the ‘demon’s mouth’, the ‘garland of fire’, the ‘burning hand’, the ‘grass blades’, the ‘bark dress’, the ‘antelope’, the ‘meat hook’, the ‘coins’, the ‘acid pickle’, the ‘twisting bar’, the ‘straw mat’; being splashed with hot oil, being fed to the dogs, being impaled alive, and being beheaded.*";
P_HTM[2456]="*Te tattha maraṇampi nigacchanti, maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**These result in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[2457]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo sandiṭṭhiko dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This too is a drawback of sensual pleasures apparent in this very life, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2458]="*Puna caparaṃ, mahānāma, kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu kāyena duccaritaṃ caranti, vācāya duccaritaṃ caranti, manasā duccaritaṃ caranti.**Furthermore, for the sake of sensual pleasures, they conduct themselves badly by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Te kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā, apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2460]="*Ayampi, mahānāma, kāmānaṃ ādīnavo samparāyiko, dukkhakkhandho kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ kāmādhikaraṇaṃ kāmānameva hetu.**This is a drawback of sensual pleasures to do with lives to come, a mass of suffering caused by sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2461]="*Ekamidāhaṃ, mahānāma, samayaṃ rājagahe viharāmi gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**Mahānāma, this one time I was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[2462]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā nigaṇṭhā isigilipasse kāḷasilāyaṃ ubbhaṭṭhakā honti āsanapaṭikkhittā, opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti.**Now at that time several Jain ascetics on the slopes of Isigili at the Black Rock were constantly standing, refusing seats. And they felt painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion.*";
P_HTM[2463]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, mahānāma, sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena isigilipasse kāḷasilā yena te nigaṇṭhā tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā te nigaṇṭhe etadavocaṃ:**Then in the late afternoon, I came out of retreat and went to the Black Rock to visit those Jain ascetics. I said to them,*";
P_HTM[2464]="*‘kiṃ nu tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, ubbhaṭṭhakā āsanapaṭikkhittā, opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayathā’ti?**‘Reverends, why are you constantly standing, refusing seats, so that you feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion?’*";
P_HTM[2465]="*Evaṃ vutte, mahānāma, te nigaṇṭhā maṃ etadavocuṃ:**When I said this, those Jain ascetics said to me,*";
P_HTM[2466]="*‘nigaṇṭho, āvuso, nāṭaputto sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti:**‘Reverend, the Jain leader Nātaputta claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to know and see everything without exception, thus:*";
P_HTM[2467]="*“carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan”ti.**“Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.”*";
P_HTM[2468]="*So evamāha:**He says,*";
P_HTM[2469]="*“atthi kho vo, nigaṇṭhā, pubbe pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, taṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya nijjīretha;**“O Jain ascetics, you have done bad deeds in a past life. Wear them away with these severe and grueling austerities.*";
P_HTM[2470]="*yaṃ panettha etarahi kāyena saṃvutā vācāya saṃvutā manasā saṃvutā taṃ āyatiṃ pāpassa kammassa akaraṇaṃ;**And when you refrain from such deeds in the present by way of body, speech, and mind, you’re not doing any bad deeds for the future.*";
P_HTM[2471]="*iti purāṇānaṃ kammānaṃ tapasā byantibhāvā, navānaṃ kammānaṃ akaraṇā, āyatiṃ anavassavo;**So, due to eliminating past deeds by mortification, and not doing any new deeds, there’s nothing to come up in the future.*";
P_HTM[2472]="*āyatiṃ anavassavā kammakkhayo, kammakkhayā dukkhakkhayo, dukkhakkhayā vedanākkhayo, vedanākkhayā sabbaṃ dukkhaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ bhavissatī”ti.**With nothing to come up in the future, deeds end. With the ending of deeds, suffering ends. With the ending of suffering, feeling ends. And with the ending of feeling, all suffering will have been worn away.”*";
P_HTM[2473]="*Tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca, tena camha attamanā’ti.**We like and accept this, and we are satisfied with it.’*";
P_HTM[2474]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, mahānāma, te nigaṇṭhe etadavocaṃ:**When they said this, I said to them,*";
P_HTM[2475]="*‘kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, jānātha—**‘But reverends, do you know*";
P_HTM[2476]="*ahuvamheva mayaṃ pubbe na nāhuvamhā’ti?**for sure that you existed in the past, and it is not the case that you didn’t exist?’*";
P_HTM[2477]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No we don’t, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2478]="*‘Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, jānātha—**‘But reverends, do you know*";
P_HTM[2479]="*akaramheva mayaṃ pubbe pāpakammaṃ na nākaramhā’ti?**for sure that you did bad deeds in the past?’*";
P_HTM[2480]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No we don’t, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2481]="*‘Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, jānātha—**‘But reverends, do you know*";
P_HTM[2482]="*evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vā pāpakammaṃ akaramhā’ti?**that you did such and such bad deeds?’*";
P_HTM[2483]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No we don’t, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2484]="*‘Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, jānātha—**‘But reverends, do you know*";
P_HTM[2485]="*ettakaṃ vā dukkhaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ, ettakaṃ vā dukkhaṃ nijjīretabbaṃ, ettakamhi vā dukkhe nijjiṇṇe sabbaṃ dukkhaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ bhavissatī’ti?**that so much suffering has already been worn away? Or that so much suffering still remains to be worn away? Or that when so much suffering is worn away all suffering will have been worn away?’*";
P_HTM[2486]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No we don’t, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2487]="*‘Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, jānātha—**‘But reverends, do you know*";
P_HTM[2488]="*diṭṭheva dhamme akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadan’ti?**about giving up unskillful qualities in the present life and embracing skillful qualities?’*";
P_HTM[2489]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No we don’t, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2490]="*‘Iti kira tumhe, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, na jānātha—**‘So it seems that you don’t know any of these things.*";
P_HTM[2491]="*ahuvamheva mayaṃ pubbe na nāhuvamhāti, na jānātha—* **";
P_HTM[2492]="*akaramheva mayaṃ pubbe pāpakammaṃ na nākaramhāti, na jānātha—* **";
P_HTM[2493]="*evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vā pāpakammaṃ akaramhāti, na jānātha—* **";
P_HTM[2494]="*ettakaṃ vā dukkhaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ, ettakaṃ vā dukkhaṃ nijjīretabbaṃ, ettakamhi vā dukkhe nijjiṇṇe sabbaṃ dukkhaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ bhavissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2495]="*Na jānātha—* **";
P_HTM[2496]="*diṭṭheva dhamme akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2497]="*Evaṃ sante, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, ye loke luddā lohitapāṇino kurūrakammantā manussesu paccājātā te nigaṇṭhesu pabbajantī’ti?**That being so, when those in the world who are violent and bloody-handed and make their living by cruelty are reborn among humans they go forth as Jain ascetics.’*";
P_HTM[2498]="*‘Na kho, āvuso gotama, sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ;**‘Reverend Gotama, pleasure is not gained through pleasure; pleasure is gained through pain.*";
P_HTM[2499]="*sukhena cāvuso gotama, sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ abhavissa, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro sukhaṃ adhigaccheyya, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro sukhavihāritaro āyasmatā gotamenā’ti.**For if pleasure were to be gained through pleasure, King Seniya Bimbisāra of Māgadha would gain pleasure, since he lives in greater pleasure than Venerable Gotama.’*";
P_HTM[2500]="*‘Addhāyasmantehi nigaṇṭhehi sahasā appaṭisaṅkhā vācā bhāsitā:**‘Clearly the venerables have spoken rashly, without reflection.*";
P_HTM[2501]="*“na kho, āvuso gotama, sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2502]="*sukhena cāvuso gotama, sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ abhavissa, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro sukhaṃ adhigaccheyya, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro sukhavihāritaro āyasmatā gotamenā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2503]="*Api ca ahameva tattha paṭipucchitabbo:**Rather, I’m the one who should be asked about*";
P_HTM[2504]="*“ko nu kho āyasmantānaṃ sukhavihāritaro rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmā vā gotamo”ti?**who lives in greater pleasure, King Bimbisāra or Venerable Gotama?’*";
P_HTM[2505]="*Addhāvuso gotama, amhehi sahasā appaṭisaṅkhā vācā bhāsitā, na kho, āvuso gotama, sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ;**‘Clearly we spoke rashly and without reflection.*";
P_HTM[2506]="*sukhena cāvuso gotama, sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ abhavissa, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro sukhaṃ adhigaccheyya, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro sukhavihāritaro āyasmatā gotamenāti.* **";
P_HTM[2507]="*Api ca tiṭṭhatetaṃ, idānipi mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāma:**But forget about that. Now we ask Venerable Gotama:*";
P_HTM[2508]="*“ko nu kho āyasmantānaṃ sukhavihāritaro rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmā vā gotamo”ti?**“Who lives in greater pleasure, King Bimbisāra or Venerable Gotama?”'*";
P_HTM[2509]="*Tena hāvuso nigaṇṭhā, tumheva tattha paṭipucchissāmi, yathā vo khameyya tathā naṃ byākareyyātha.**‘Well then, reverends, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like.*";
P_HTM[2510]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññathāvuso nigaṇṭhā, pahoti rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro,**What do you think, reverends?*";
P_HTM[2511]="*aniñjamāno kāyena, abhāsamāno vācaṃ, satta rattindivāni ekantasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedī viharitun’ti?**Is King Bimbisāra capable of experiencing perfect happiness for seven days and nights without moving his body or speaking?’*";
P_HTM[2512]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No he is not, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2513]="*‘Taṃ kiṃ maññathāvuso nigaṇṭhā, pahoti rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro,**‘What do you think, reverends?*";
P_HTM[2514]="*aniñjamāno kāyena, abhāsamāno vācaṃ, cha rattindivāni … pe …**Is King Bimbisāra capable of experiencing perfect happiness for six days …*";
P_HTM[2515]="*pañca rattindivāni …**five days …*";
P_HTM[2516]="*cattāri rattindivāni …**four days …*";
P_HTM[2517]="*tīṇi rattindivāni …**three days …*";
P_HTM[2518]="*dve rattindivāni …**two days …*";
P_HTM[2519]="*ekaṃ rattindivaṃ ekantasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedī viharitun’ti?**one day?’*";
P_HTM[2520]="*‘No hidaṃ, āvuso’.**‘No he is not, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[2521]="*‘Ahaṃ kho, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, pahomi aniñjamāno kāyena, abhāsamāno vācaṃ, ekaṃ rattindivaṃ ekantasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedī viharituṃ.**‘But I am capable of experiencing perfect happiness for one day and night without moving my body or speaking.*";
P_HTM[2522]="*Ahaṃ kho, āvuso nigaṇṭhā, pahomi aniñjamāno kāyena, abhāsamāno vācaṃ, dve rattindivāni …**I am capable of experiencing perfect happiness for two days …*";
P_HTM[2523]="*tīṇi rattindivāni …**three days …*";
P_HTM[2524]="*cattāri rattindivāni …**four days …*";
P_HTM[2525]="*pañca rattindivāni …**five days …*";
P_HTM[2526]="*cha rattindivāni …**six days …*";
P_HTM[2527]="*satta rattindivāni ekantasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedī viharituṃ.**seven days.*";
P_HTM[2528]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññathāvuso nigaṇṭhā, evaṃ sante ko sukhavihāritaro rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro ahaṃ vā’ti?**What do you think, reverends? This being so, who lives in greater pleasure, King Bimbisāra or I?’*";
P_HTM[2529]="*‘Evaṃ sante āyasmāva gotamo sukhavihāritaro raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārenā’”ti.**‘This being so, Venerable Gotama lives in greater pleasure than King Bimbisāra.’”*";
P_HTM[2530]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2531]="*Attamano mahānāmo sakko bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Mahānāma the Sakyan was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Cūḷadukkhakkhandhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2533]="*15. Anumānasutta**Measuring Up*";
P_HTM[2534]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2535]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time Venerable Mahāmoggallāna was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Tatra kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2537]="*“āvuso bhikkhavo”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2538]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2539]="*Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this:*";
P_HTM[2540]="*“Pavāreti cepi, āvuso, bhikkhu:**“Suppose a mendicant invites*";
P_HTM[2541]="*‘vadantu maṃ āyasmanto, vacanīyomhi āyasmantehī’ti, so ca hoti dubbaco, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgato, akkhamo appadakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī na ceva vattabbaṃ maññanti, na ca anusāsitabbaṃ maññanti, na ca tasmiṃ puggale vissāsaṃ āpajjitabbaṃ maññanti.**other mendicants to admonish them. But they’re hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They're impatient, and don't take instruction respectfully. So their spiritual companions don’t think it’s worth advising and instructing them, and that person doesn’t gain their trust.*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Katame cāvuso, dovacassakaraṇā dhammā?**And what are the qualities that make them hard to admonish?*";
P_HTM[2543]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu pāpiccho hoti, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato.**Firstly, a mendicant has wicked desires, having fallen under the sway of wicked desires.*";
P_HTM[2544]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu pāpiccho hoti, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato—* **";
P_HTM[2545]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (1)**This is a quality that makes them difficult to admonish.*";
P_HTM[2546]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu attukkaṃsako hoti paravambhī.**Furthermore, a mendicant glorifies themselves and puts others down. …*";
P_HTM[2547]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu attukkaṃsako hoti paravambhī—* **";
P_HTM[2548]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2549]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhābhibhūto.**They’re irritable, overcome by anger …*";
P_HTM[2550]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhābhibhūto—* **";
P_HTM[2551]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2552]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu upanāhī.**They’re irritable, and hostile due to anger …*";
P_HTM[2553]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu upanāhī—* **";
P_HTM[2554]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2555]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu abhisaṅgī.**They’re irritable, and stubborn due to anger …*";
P_HTM[2556]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhahetu abhisaṅgī—* **";
P_HTM[2557]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2558]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā.**They’re irritable, and blurt out words bordering on anger …*";
P_HTM[2559]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā—* **";
P_HTM[2560]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (6)* **";
P_HTM[2561]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ paṭippharati.**When accused, they object to the accuser …*";
P_HTM[2562]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ paṭippharati—* **";
P_HTM[2563]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (7)* **";
P_HTM[2564]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ apasādeti.**When accused, they rebuke the accuser …*";
P_HTM[2565]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ apasādeti—* **";
P_HTM[2566]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (8)* **";
P_HTM[2567]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakassa paccāropeti.**When accused, they retort to the accuser …*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakassa paccāropeti—* **";
P_HTM[2569]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (9)* **";
P_HTM[2570]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When accused, they dodge the issue, distract the discussion with irrelevant points, and display annoyance, hate, and bitterness …*";
P_HTM[2571]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti—* **";
P_HTM[2572]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (10)* **";
P_HTM[2573]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena apadāne na sampāyati.**When accused, they don’t accept the consequences of their deeds …*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena apadāne na sampāyati—* **";
P_HTM[2575]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (11)* **";
P_HTM[2576]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī.**They are offensive and contemptuous …*";
P_HTM[2577]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī—* **";
P_HTM[2578]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (12)* **";
P_HTM[2579]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu issukī hoti maccharī.**They’re jealous and stingy …*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu issukī hoti maccharī—* **";
P_HTM[2581]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (13)* **";
P_HTM[2582]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu saṭho hoti māyāvī.**They’re devious and deceitful …*";
P_HTM[2583]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu saṭho hoti māyāvī—* **";
P_HTM[2584]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (14)* **";
P_HTM[2585]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu thaddho hoti atimānī.**They’re obstinate and vain …*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu thaddho hoti atimānī—* **";
P_HTM[2587]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (15)* **";
P_HTM[2588]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go.*";
P_HTM[2589]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī—* **";
P_HTM[2590]="*ayampi dhammo dovacassakaraṇo. (16)**This too is a quality that makes them difficult to admonish.*";
P_HTM[2591]="*Ime vuccantāvuso, dovacassakaraṇā dhammā.**These are the qualities that make them hard to admonish.*";
P_HTM[2592]="*No cepi, āvuso, bhikkhu pavāreti:**Suppose a mendicant doesn’t invite*";
P_HTM[2593]="*‘vadantu maṃ āyasmanto, vacanīyomhi āyasmantehī’ti, so ca hoti suvaco, sovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgato, khamo padakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī vattabbañceva maññanti, anusāsitabbañca maññanti, tasmiñca puggale vissāsaṃ āpajjitabbaṃ maññanti.**other mendicants to admonish them. But they’re easy to admonish, having qualities that make them easy to admonish. They're accepting, and take instruction respectfully. So their spiritual companions think it’s worth advising and instructing them, and that person gains their trust.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*Katame cāvuso, sovacassakaraṇā dhammā?**And what are the qualities that make them easy to admonish?*";
P_HTM[2595]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu na pāpiccho hoti, na pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato.**Firstly, a mendicant doesn’t have wicked desires …*";
P_HTM[2596]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu na pāpiccho hoti na pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato—* **";
P_HTM[2597]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (1)* **";
P_HTM[2598]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu anattukkaṃsako hoti aparavambhī.* **";
P_HTM[2599]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu anattukkaṃsako hoti aparavambhī—* **";
P_HTM[2600]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2601]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhābhibhūto.* **";
P_HTM[2602]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhābhibhūto—* **";
P_HTM[2603]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2604]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhahetu upanāhī.* **";
P_HTM[2605]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhahetu upanāhī—* **";
P_HTM[2606]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2607]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhahetu abhisaṅgī.* **";
P_HTM[2608]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhahetu abhisaṅgī—* **";
P_HTM[2609]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2610]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā.* **";
P_HTM[2611]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu na kodhano hoti na kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā—* **";
P_HTM[2612]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (6)* **";
P_HTM[2613]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ nappaṭippharati.* **";
P_HTM[2614]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ nappaṭippharati—* **";
P_HTM[2615]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (7)* **";
P_HTM[2616]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ na apasādeti.* **";
P_HTM[2617]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakaṃ na apasādeti—* **";
P_HTM[2618]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (8)* **";
P_HTM[2619]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakassa na paccāropeti.* **";
P_HTM[2620]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena codakassa na paccāropeti—* **";
P_HTM[2621]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (9)* **";
P_HTM[2622]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena na aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.* **";
P_HTM[2623]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena na aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti—* **";
P_HTM[2624]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (10)* **";
P_HTM[2625]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena apadāne sampāyati.* **";
P_HTM[2626]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu codito codakena apadāne sampāyati—* **";
P_HTM[2627]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (11)* **";
P_HTM[2628]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu amakkhī hoti apaḷāsī.* **";
P_HTM[2629]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu amakkhī hoti apaḷāsī—* **";
P_HTM[2630]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (12)* **";
P_HTM[2631]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu anissukī hoti amaccharī.* **";
P_HTM[2632]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu anissukī hoti amaccharī—* **";
P_HTM[2633]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (13)* **";
P_HTM[2634]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu asaṭho hoti amāyāvī.* **";
P_HTM[2635]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu asaṭho hoti amāyāvī—* **";
P_HTM[2636]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (14)* **";
P_HTM[2637]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu atthaddho hoti anatimānī.* **";
P_HTM[2638]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu atthaddho hoti anatimānī—* **";
P_HTM[2639]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (15)* **";
P_HTM[2640]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī.**Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t attached to their own views, not holding them tight, but letting them go easily.*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti, anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī—* **";
P_HTM[2642]="*ayampi dhammo sovacassakaraṇo. (16)* **";
P_HTM[2643]="*Ime vuccantāvuso, sovacassakaraṇā dhammā.**These are the qualities that make them easy to admonish.*";
P_HTM[2644]="*Tatrāvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ anuminitabbaṃ:**In such a case, a mendicant should measure themselves against another like this.*";
P_HTM[2645]="*‘yo khvāyaṃ puggalo pāpiccho, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;**‘This person has wicked desires, having fallen under the sway of wicked desires. And I don’t like or approve of this person.*";
P_HTM[2646]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ pāpiccho pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.**And if I were to fall under the sway of wicked desires, others wouldn’t like or approve of me.’*";
P_HTM[2647]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘na pāpiccho bhavissāmi, na pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (1)**A mendicant who knows this should give rise to the thought: ‘I will not fall under the sway of wicked desires.’ …*";
P_HTM[2648]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo attukkaṃsako paravambhī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2649]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ attukkaṃsako paravambhī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2650]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘anattukkaṃsako bhavissāmi aparavambhī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2651]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo kodhano kodhābhibhūto, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo.* **";
P_HTM[2652]="*Ahañceva kho panassaṃ kodhano kodhābhibhūto, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2653]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘na kodhano bhavissāmi na kodhābhibhūto’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2654]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo kodhano kodhahetu upanāhī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2655]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ kodhano kodhahetu upanāhī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2656]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘na kodhano bhavissāmi na kodhahetu upanāhī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2657]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo kodhano kodhahetu abhisaṅgī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2658]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ kodhano kodhahetu abhisaṅgī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2659]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘na kodhano bhavissāmi na kodhahetu abhisaṅgī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2660]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo kodhano kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2661]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ kodhano kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2662]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘na kodhano bhavissāmi na kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāressāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (6)* **";
P_HTM[2663]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo codito codakena codakaṃ paṭippharati, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2664]="*ahañceva kho pana codito codakena codakaṃ paṭipphareyyaṃ, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2665]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘codito codakena codakaṃ nappaṭippharissāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (7)* **";
P_HTM[2666]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo codito codakena codakaṃ apasādeti, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2667]="*ahañceva kho pana codito codakena codakaṃ apasādeyyaṃ, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2668]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘codito codakena codakaṃ na apasādessāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (8)* **";
P_HTM[2669]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo codito codakena codakassa paccāropeti, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2670]="*ahañceva kho pana codito codakena codakassa paccāropeyyaṃ, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2671]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘codito codakena codakassa na paccāropessāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (9)* **";
P_HTM[2672]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2673]="*ahañceva kho pana codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicareyyaṃ, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeyyaṃ, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukareyyaṃ, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2674]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘codito codakena na aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissāmi, na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmessāmi, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukarissāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (10)* **";
P_HTM[2675]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo codito codakena apadāne na sampāyati, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2676]="*ahañceva kho pana codito codakena apadāne na sampāyeyyaṃ, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2677]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘codito codakena apadāne sampāyissāmī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (11)* **";
P_HTM[2678]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo makkhī paḷāsī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2679]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ makkhī paḷāsī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2680]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘amakkhī bhavissāmi apaḷāsī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (12)* **";
P_HTM[2681]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo issukī maccharī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2682]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ issukī maccharī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2683]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘anissukī bhavissāmi amaccharī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (13)* **";
P_HTM[2684]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo saṭho māyāvī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2685]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ saṭho māyāvī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2686]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘asaṭho bhavissāmi amāyāvī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (14)* **";
P_HTM[2687]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo thaddho atimānī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;* **";
P_HTM[2688]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ thaddho atimānī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2689]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘atthaddho bhavissāmi anatimānī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (15)* **";
P_HTM[2690]="*‘Yo khvāyaṃ puggalo sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī, ayaṃ me puggalo appiyo amanāpo;**‘This person is attached to their own views, holding them tight and refusing to let go. And I don’t like or approve of this person.*";
P_HTM[2691]="*ahañceva kho panassaṃ sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī, ahampāssaṃ paresaṃ appiyo amanāpo’ti.**And if I were to be attached to my own views, holding them tight and refusing to let go, others wouldn’t like or approve of me.’*";
P_HTM[2692]="*Evaṃ jānantenāvuso, bhikkhunā ‘asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī bhavissāmi anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī’ti cittaṃ uppādetabbaṃ. (16)**A mendicant who knows this should give rise to the thought: ‘I will not be attached to my own views, holding them tight, but will let them go easily.’*";
P_HTM[2693]="*Tatrāvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:**In such a case, a mendicant should check themselves like this:*";
P_HTM[2694]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi pāpiccho, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato’ti?**‘Do I have wicked desires? Have I fallen under the sway of wicked desires?’*";
P_HTM[2695]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[2696]="*‘pāpiccho khomhi, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they have fallen under the sway of wicked desires. Then they should make an effort to give up those bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[2697]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[2698]="*‘na khomhi pāpiccho, na pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (1)**they haven’t fallen under the sway of wicked desires. Then they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities. …*";
P_HTM[2699]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2700]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi attukkaṃsako paravambhī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2701]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2702]="*‘attukkaṃsako khomhi paravambhī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2703]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2704]="*‘anattukkaṃsako khomhi aparavambhī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2705]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2706]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi kodhano kodhābhibhūto’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2707]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2708]="*‘kodhano khomhi kodhābhibhūto’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2709]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2710]="*‘na khomhi kodhano kodhābhibhūto’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2711]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2712]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi kodhano kodhahetu upanāhī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2713]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti ‘kodhano khomhi kodhahetu upanāhī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2714]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti ‘na khomhi kodhano kodhahetu upanāhī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2715]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2716]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi kodhano kodhahetu abhisaṅgī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2717]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2718]="*‘kodhano khomhi kodhahetu abhisaṅgī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2719]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2720]="*‘na khomhi kodhano kodhahetu abhisaṅgī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2721]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2722]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi kodhano kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2723]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2724]="*‘kodhano khomhi kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2725]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2726]="*‘na khomhi kodhano kodhasāmantā vācaṃ nicchāretā’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (6)* **";
P_HTM[2727]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2728]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi codito codakena codakaṃ paṭippharāmī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2729]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti ‘codito khomhi codakena codakaṃ paṭippharāmī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2730]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2731]="*‘codito khomhi codakena codakaṃ nappaṭippharāmī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (7)* **";
P_HTM[2732]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2733]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi codito codakena codakaṃ apasādemī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2734]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti ‘codito khomhi codakena codakaṃ apasādemī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2735]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2736]="*‘codito khomhi codakena codakaṃ na apasādemī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (8)* **";
P_HTM[2737]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2738]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi codito codakena codakassa paccāropemī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2739]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2740]="*‘codito khomhi codakena codakassa paccāropemī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2741]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2742]="*‘codito khomhi codakena codakassa na paccāropemī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (9)* **";
P_HTM[2743]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2744]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi codito codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarāmi, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmemi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaromī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2745]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2746]="*‘codito khomhi codakena aññenaññaṃ paṭicarāmi, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmemi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaromī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2747]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2748]="*‘codito khomhi codakena na aññenaññaṃ paṭicarāmi, na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmemi, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaromī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (10)* **";
P_HTM[2749]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2750]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi codito codakena apadāne na sampāyāmī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2751]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2752]="*‘codito khomhi codakena apadāne na sampāyāmī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2753]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2754]="*‘codito khomhi codakena apadāne sampāyāmī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (11)* **";
P_HTM[2755]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2756]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi makkhī paḷāsī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2757]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2758]="*‘makkhī khomhi paḷāsī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2759]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2760]="*‘amakkhī khomhi apaḷāsī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (12)* **";
P_HTM[2761]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2762]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi issukī maccharī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2763]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2764]="*‘issukī khomhi maccharī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2765]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2766]="*‘anissukī khomhi amaccharī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (13)* **";
P_HTM[2767]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2768]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi saṭho māyāvī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2769]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2770]="*‘saṭho khomhi māyāvī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2771]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2772]="*‘asaṭho khomhi amāyāvī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (14)* **";
P_HTM[2773]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2774]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi thaddho atimānī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2775]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2776]="*‘thaddho khomhi atimānī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2777]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[2778]="*‘atthaddho khomhi anatimānī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (15)* **";
P_HTM[2779]="*Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā attanāva attānaṃ evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2780]="*‘kiṃ nu khomhi sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2781]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[2782]="*‘sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī khomhi ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they are attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go. Then they should make an effort to give up those bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[2783]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[2784]="*‘asandiṭṭhiparāmāsī khomhi anādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī’ti, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (16)**they’re not attached to their own views, holding them tight, but let them go easily. Then they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[2785]="*Sace, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno sabbepime pāpake akusale dhamme appahīne attani samanupassati, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā sabbesaṃyeva imesaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant sees that they haven’t given up all these bad, unskillful qualities. Then they should make an effort to give them all up.*";
P_HTM[2786]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno sabbepime pāpake akusale dhamme pahīne attani samanupassati, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ, ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant sees that they have given up all these bad, unskillful qualities. Then they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[2787]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, itthī vā puriso vā, daharo yuvā maṇḍanajātiko, ādāse vā parisuddhe pariyodāte, acche vā udakapatte, sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno, sace tattha passati rajaṃ vā aṅgaṇaṃ vā, tasseva rajassa vā aṅgaṇassa vā pahānāya vāyamati;**Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of adornments, and they check their own reflection in a clean bright mirror or a clear bowl of water. If they see any dirt or blemish there, they’d try to remove it.*";
P_HTM[2788]="*no ce tattha passati rajaṃ vā aṅgaṇaṃ vā, teneva attamano hoti:**But if they don’t see any dirt or blemish there, they’re happy, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2789]="*‘lābhā vata me, parisuddhaṃ vata me’ti.**‘How fortunate that I’m clean!’*";
P_HTM[2790]="*Evameva kho, āvuso, sace bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno sabbepime pāpake akusale dhamme appahīne attani samanupassati, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā sabbesaṃyeva imesaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**In the same way, suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant sees that they haven’t given up all these bad, unskillful qualities. Then they should make an effort to give them all up.*";
P_HTM[2791]="*Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno sabbepime pāpake akusale dhamme pahīne attani samanupassati, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ, ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesū”ti.**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant sees that they have given up all these bad, unskillful qualities. Then they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.”*";
P_HTM[2792]="*Idamavocāyasmā mahāmoggallāno.**This is what Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said.*";
P_HTM[2793]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said.*";
P_HTM[2794]="*Anumānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2795]="*16. Cetokhilasutta**Emotional Barrenness*";
P_HTM[2796]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2797]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2798]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2799]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2800]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2801]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2802]="*“Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pañca cetokhilā appahīnā, pañca cetasovinibandhā asamucchinnā, so vatimasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**“Mendicants, when a mendicant has not given up five kinds of emotional barrenness and cut off five emotional shackles, it’s not possible for them to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2803]="*Katamāssa pañca cetokhilā appahīnā honti?**What are the five kinds of emotional barrenness they haven’t given up?*";
P_HTM[2804]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati.**Firstly, a mendicant has doubts about the Teacher. They’re uncertain, undecided, and lacking confidence.*";
P_HTM[2805]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2806]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ paṭhamo cetokhilo appahīno hoti.**This is the first kind of emotional barrenness they haven’t given up.*";
P_HTM[2807]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhamme kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant has doubts about the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2808]="*evamassāyaṃ dutiyo cetokhilo appahīno hoti.**This is the second kind of emotional barrenness.*";
P_HTM[2809]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṅghe kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati … pe …**They have doubts about the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[2810]="*evamassāyaṃ tatiyo cetokhilo appahīno hoti.**This is the third kind of emotional barrenness.*";
P_HTM[2811]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sikkhāya kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati.**They have doubts about the training …*";
P_HTM[2812]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sikkhāya kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.* **";
P_HTM[2813]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ catuttho cetokhilo appahīno hoti.**This is the fourth kind of emotional barrenness.*";
P_HTM[2814]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto.**Furthermore, a mendicant is angry and upset with their spiritual companions, resentful and closed off.*";
P_HTM[2815]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2816]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ pañcamo cetokhilo appahīno hoti.**This is the fifth kind of emotional barrenness they haven’t given up.*";
P_HTM[2817]="*Imāssa pañca cetokhilā appahīnā honti.**These are the five kinds of emotional barrenness they haven’t given up.*";
P_HTM[2818]="*Katamāssa pañca cetasovinibandhā asamucchinnā honti?**What are the five emotional shackles they haven’t cut off?*";
P_HTM[2819]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāme avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho.**Firstly, a mendicant isn’t free of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2820]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāme avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2821]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ paṭhamo cetasovinibandho asamucchinno hoti.**This is the first emotional shackle they haven’t cut off.*";
P_HTM[2822]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye avītarāgo hoti … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t free of greed for the body …*";
P_HTM[2823]="*evamassāyaṃ dutiyo cetasovinibandho asamucchinno hoti.**This is the second emotional shackle.*";
P_HTM[2824]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpe avītarāgo hoti … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t free of greed for form …*";
P_HTM[2825]="*evamassāyaṃ tatiyo cetasovinibandho asamucchinno hoti.**This is the third emotional shackle.*";
P_HTM[2826]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā seyyasukhaṃ passasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ anuyutto viharati.**They eat as much as they like until their belly is full, then indulge in the pleasures of sleeping, lying down, and drowsing …*";
P_HTM[2827]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā seyyasukhaṃ passasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ anuyutto viharati, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.* **";
P_HTM[2828]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ catuttho cetasovinibandho asamucchinno hoti.**This is the fourth emotional shackle.*";
P_HTM[2829]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti.**They live the spiritual life hoping to be reborn in one of the orders of gods, thinking: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’*";
P_HTM[2830]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2831]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ pañcamo cetasovinibandho asamucchinno hoti.**This is the fifth emotional shackle they haven’t cut off.*";
P_HTM[2832]="*Imāssa pañca cetasovinibandhā asamucchinnā honti.**These are the five emotional shackles they haven’t cut off.*";
P_HTM[2833]="*Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ime pañca cetokhilā appahīnā, ime pañca cetasovinibandhā asamucchinnā, so vatimasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When a mendicant has not given up these five kinds of emotional barrenness and cut off these five emotional shackles, it’s not possible for them to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2834]="*Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pañca cetokhilā pahīnā, pañca cetasovinibandhā susamucchinnā, so vatimasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When a mendicant has given up these five kinds of emotional barrenness and cut off these five emotional shackles, it is possible for them to achieve growth, improvement, and maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2835]="*Katamāssa pañca cetokhilā pahīnā honti?**What are the five kinds of emotional barrenness they’ve given up?*";
P_HTM[2836]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satthari na kaṅkhati na vicikicchati adhimuccati sampasīdati.**Firstly, a mendicant has no doubts about the Teacher. They’re not uncertain, undecided, or lacking confidence.*";
P_HTM[2837]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satthari na kaṅkhati na vicikicchati adhimuccati sampasīdati, tassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind inclines toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2838]="*Yassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ paṭhamo cetokhilo pahīno hoti.**This is the first kind of emotional barrenness they’ve given up.*";
P_HTM[2839]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhamme na kaṅkhati na vicikicchati adhimuccati sampasīdati … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant has no doubts about the teaching …*";
P_HTM[2840]="*evamassāyaṃ dutiyo cetokhilo pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[2841]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṅghe na kaṅkhati na vicikicchati adhimuccati sampasīdati … pe …**They have no doubts about the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[2842]="*evamassāyaṃ tatiyo cetokhilo pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[2843]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sikkhāya na kaṅkhati na vicikicchati adhimuccati sampasīdati … pe …**They have no doubts about the training …*";
P_HTM[2844]="*evamassāyaṃ catuttho cetokhilo pahīno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[2845]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu na kupito hoti na anattamano anāhatacitto akhilajāto.**They’re not angry and upset with their spiritual companions, not resentful or closed off.*";
P_HTM[2846]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu na kupito hoti na anattamano anāhatacitto akhilajāto, tassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind inclines toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2847]="*Yassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ pañcamo cetokhilo pahīno hoti.**This is the fifth kind of emotional barrenness they’ve given up.*";
P_HTM[2848]="*Imāssa pañca cetokhilā pahīnā honti.**These are the five kinds of emotional barrenness they’ve given up.*";
P_HTM[2849]="*Katamāssa pañca cetasovinibandhā susamucchinnā honti?**What are the five emotional shackles they’ve cut off?*";
P_HTM[2850]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāme vītarāgo hoti vigatacchando vigatapemo vigatapipāso vigatapariḷāho vigatataṇho.**Firstly, a mendicant is rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[2851]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāme vītarāgo hoti vigatacchando vigatapemo vigatapipāso vigatapariḷāho vigatataṇho, tassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind inclines toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2852]="*Yassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ paṭhamo cetasovinibandho susamucchinno hoti.**This is the first emotional shackle they’ve cut off.*";
P_HTM[2853]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye vītarāgo hoti … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant is rid of greed for the body …*";
P_HTM[2854]="*rūpe vītarāgo hoti … pe …**They’re rid of greed for form …*";
P_HTM[2855]="*na yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā seyyasukhaṃ passasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ anuyutto viharati.**They don’t eat as much as they like until their belly is full, then indulge in the pleasures of sleeping, lying down, and drowsing …*";
P_HTM[2856]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā seyyasukhaṃ passasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ anuyutto viharati, tassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.* **";
P_HTM[2857]="*Yassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ catuttho cetasovinibandho susamucchinno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[2858]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti.**They don’t live the spiritual life hoping to be reborn in one of the orders of gods, thinking: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’*";
P_HTM[2859]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti, tassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind inclines toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[2860]="*Yassa cittaṃ namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, evamassāyaṃ pañcamo cetasovinibandho susamucchinno hoti.**This is the fifth emotional shackle they’ve cut off.*";
P_HTM[2861]="*Imāssa pañca cetasovinibandhā susamucchinnā honti.**These are the five emotional shackles they’ve cut off.*";
P_HTM[2862]="*Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ime pañca cetokhilā pahīnā, ime pañca cetasovinibandhā susamucchinnā, so vatimasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When a mendicant has given up these five kinds of emotional barrenness and cut off these five emotional shackles, it is possible for them to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2863]="*So chandasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort …*";
P_HTM[2864]="*vīriyasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy, and active effort …*";
P_HTM[2865]="*cittasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to mental development, and active effort …*";
P_HTM[2866]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, ussoḷhīyeva pañcamī.**the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to inquiry, and active effort. And the fifth is sheer vigor.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*Sa kho so, bhikkhave, evaṃ ussoḷhipannarasaṅgasamannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo abhinibbidāya, bhabbo sambodhāya, bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**A mendicant who possesses these fifteen factors, including vigor, is capable of breaking out, becoming awakened, and reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2868]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kukkuṭiyā aṇḍāni aṭṭha vā dasa vā dvādasa vā.**Suppose there was a chicken with eight or ten or twelve eggs.*";
P_HTM[2869]="*Tānassu kukkuṭiyā sammā adhisayitāni sammā pariseditāni sammā paribhāvitāni.**And she properly sat on them to keep them warm and incubated.*";
P_HTM[2870]="*Kiñcāpi tassā kukkuṭiyā na evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**Even if that chicken doesn’t wish:*";
P_HTM[2871]="*‘aho vatime kukkuṭapotakā pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā aṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjeyyun’ti.**‘If only my chicks could break out of the eggshell with their claws and beak and hatch safely!’*";
P_HTM[2872]="*Atha kho bhabbāva te kukkuṭapotakā pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā aṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjituṃ.**Still they can break out and hatch safely.*";
P_HTM[2873]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ ussoḷhipannarasaṅgasamannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo abhinibbidāya, bhabbo sambodhāya, bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāyā”ti.**In the same way, a mendicant who possesses these fifteen factors, including vigor, is capable of breaking out, becoming awakened, and reaching the supreme sanctuary.”*";
P_HTM[2874]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2875]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2876]="*Cetokhilasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2877]="*17. Vanapatthasutta**Jungle Thickets*";
P_HTM[2878]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2879]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2880]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2881]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2882]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2883]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2884]="*“vanapatthapariyāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi,**“Mendicants, I will teach you an exposition about jungle thickets.*";
P_HTM[2885]="*taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[2886]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2887]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2888]="*“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharati.**“Mendicants, take the case of a mendicant who lives close by a jungle thicket.*";
P_HTM[2889]="*Tassa taṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāti.**As they do so, their mindfulness does not become established, their mind does not become immersed in samādhi, their defilements do not come to an end, and they do not arrive at the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2890]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchanti.**And the necessities of life that a renunciate requires—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—are hard to come by.*";
P_HTM[2891]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**That mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[2892]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharāmi, tassa me imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāmi.**‘While living close by this jungle thicket, my mindfulness does not become established, my mind does not become immersed in samādhi, my defilements do not come to an end, and I do not arrive at the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2893]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchantī’ti.**And the necessities of life that a renunciate requires—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—are hard to come by.’*";
P_HTM[2894]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā rattibhāgaṃ vā divasabhāgaṃ vā tamhā vanapatthā pakkamitabbaṃ, na vatthabbaṃ.**That mendicant should leave that jungle thicket that very time of night or day; they shouldn’t stay there.*";
P_HTM[2895]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharati.**Take another case of a mendicant who lives close by a jungle thicket.*";
P_HTM[2896]="*Tassa taṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāti.**Their mindfulness does not become established …*";
P_HTM[2897]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchanti.**But the necessities of life are easy to come by.*";
P_HTM[2898]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**That mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[2899]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharāmi. Tassa me imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāmi.**‘While living close by this jungle thicket, my mindfulness does not become established …*";
P_HTM[2900]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchanti.**But the necessities of life are easy to come by.*";
P_HTM[2901]="*Na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito na piṇḍapātahetu … pe … na senāsanahetu … pe … na gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**But I didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness for the sake of a robe, alms-food, lodgings, or medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2902]="*Atha ca pana me imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāmī’ti.**Moreover, while living close by this jungle thicket, my mindfulness does not become established …’*";
P_HTM[2903]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅkhāpi tamhā vanapatthā pakkamitabbaṃ, na vatthabbaṃ.**After reflection, that mendicant should leave that jungle thicket; they shouldn’t stay there.*";
P_HTM[2904]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharati.**Take another case of a mendicant who lives close by a jungle thicket.*";
P_HTM[2905]="*Tassa taṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti.**As they do so, their mindfulness becomes established, their mind becomes immersed in samādhi, their defilements come to an end, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2906]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, te kasirena samudāgacchanti. Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**But the necessities of life that a renunciate requires—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—are hard to come by. That mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[2907]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2908]="*Tassa me imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāmi.**‘While living close by this jungle thicket, my mindfulness becomes established …*";
P_HTM[2909]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchanti.**But the necessities of life are hard to come by.*";
P_HTM[2910]="*Na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, na piṇḍapātahetu … pe … na senāsanahetu … pe … na gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**But I didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness for the sake of a robe, alms-food, lodgings, or medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2911]="*Atha ca pana me imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāmī’ti.**Moreover, while living close by this jungle thicket, my mindfulness becomes established …’*";
P_HTM[2912]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅkhāpi tasmiṃ vanapatthe vatthabbaṃ, na pakkamitabbaṃ.**After reflection, that mendicant should stay in that jungle thicket; they shouldn’t leave.*";
P_HTM[2913]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharati.**Take another case of a mendicant who lives close by a jungle thicket.*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Tassa taṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti.**Their mindfulness becomes established …*";
P_HTM[2915]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchanti.**And the necessities of life are easy to come by.*";
P_HTM[2916]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**That mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[2917]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharāmi. Tassa me imaṃ vanapatthaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāmi.**‘While living close by this jungle thicket, my mindfulness becomes established …*";
P_HTM[2918]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchantī’ti.**And the necessities of life are easy to come by.’*";
P_HTM[2919]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā yāvajīvampi tasmiṃ vanapatthe vatthabbaṃ, na pakkamitabbaṃ.**That mendicant should stay in that jungle thicket for the rest of their life; they shouldn’t leave.*";
P_HTM[2920]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upanissāya viharati … pe …**Take the case of a mendicant who lives supported by a village …*";
P_HTM[2921]="*aññataraṃ nigamaṃ upanissāya viharati … pe …**town …*";
P_HTM[2922]="*aññataraṃ nagaraṃ upanissāya viharati … pe …**city …*";
P_HTM[2923]="*aññataraṃ janapadaṃ upanissāya viharati … pe …**country …*";
P_HTM[2924]="*aññataraṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharati.**an individual.*";
P_HTM[2925]="*Tassa taṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāti.**As they do so, their mindfulness does not become established, their mind does not become immersed in samādhi, their defilements do not come to an end, and they do not arrive at the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchanti.**And the necessities of life that a renunciate requires—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—are hard to come by....*";
P_HTM[2927]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2928]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharāmi. Tassa me imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2929]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2930]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā rattibhāgaṃ vā divasabhāgaṃ vā so puggalo anāpucchā pakkamitabbaṃ, nānubandhitabbo.**That mendicant should leave that person at any time of the day or night, without asking. They shouldn’t follow them. …*";
P_HTM[2931]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2932]="*Tassa taṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[2933]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, te appakasirena samudāgacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[2934]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2935]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharāmi. Tassa me imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2936]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[2937]="*Na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, na piṇḍapātahetu … pe … na senāsanahetu … pe … na gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.* **";
P_HTM[2938]="*Atha ca pana me imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati na upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ na samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā na parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nānupāpuṇāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2939]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅkhāpi so puggalo āpucchā pakkamitabbaṃ, nānubandhitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[2940]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2941]="*Tassa taṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[2942]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[2943]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2944]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharāmi. Tassa me imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2945]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te kasirena samudāgacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[2946]="*Na kho panāhaṃ cīvarahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, na piṇḍapātahetu … pe … na senāsanahetu … pe … na gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.* **";
P_HTM[2947]="*Atha ca pana me imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2948]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅkhāpi so puggalo anubandhitabbo, na pakkamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2949]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharati.**Take another case of a mendicant who lives supported by an individual.*";
P_HTM[2950]="*Tassa taṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti.**As they do so, their mindfulness becomes established, their mind becomes immersed in samādhi, their defilements come to an end, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2951]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchanti.**And the necessities of life that a renunciate requires—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—are easy to come by.*";
P_HTM[2952]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**That mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[2953]="*‘ahaṃ kho imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharāmi. Tassa me imaṃ puggalaṃ upanissāya viharato anupaṭṭhitā ceva sati upaṭṭhāti, asamāhitañca cittaṃ samādhiyati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāmi.**‘While living supported by this person, my mindfulness becomes established …*";
P_HTM[2954]="*Ye ca kho ime pabbajitena jīvitaparikkhārā samudānetabbā—cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā—te appakasirena samudāgacchantī’ti.**And the necessities of life are easy to come by.’*";
P_HTM[2955]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā yāvajīvampi so puggalo anubandhitabbo, na pakkamitabbaṃ, api panujjamānenapī”ti.**That mendicant should follow that person for the rest of their life. They shouldn’t leave them, even if sent away.”*";
P_HTM[2956]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2957]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2958]="*Vanapatthasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2959]="*18. Madhupiṇḍikasutta**The Honey-Cake*";
P_HTM[2960]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2961]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2962]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kapilavatthuṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Kapilavatthu for alms.*";
P_HTM[2963]="*Kapilavatthusmiṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena mahāvanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Kapilavatthu. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Great Wood,*";
P_HTM[2964]="*Mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā beluvalaṭṭhikāya mūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**plunged deep into it, and sat at the root of a young wood apple tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[2965]="*Daṇḍapāṇipi kho sakko jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena mahāvanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Daṇḍapāṇi the Sakyan, while going for a walk,*";
P_HTM[2966]="*Mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā yena beluvalaṭṭhikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**plunged deep into the Great Wood. He approached the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā daṇḍamolubbha ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho daṇḍapāṇi sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side leaning on his staff, and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[2968]="*“kiṃvādī samaṇo kimakkhāyī”ti?**“What does the ascetic teach? What does he explain?”*";
P_HTM[2969]="*“Yathāvādī kho, āvuso, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya na kenaci loke viggayha tiṭṭhati, yathā ca pana kāmehi visaṃyuttaṃ viharantaṃ taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ akathaṃkathiṃ chinnakukkuccaṃ bhavābhave vītataṇhaṃ saññā nānusenti—**“Sir, my teaching is such that one does not conflict with anyone in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. And it is such that perceptions do not underlie the brahmin who lives detached from sensual pleasures, without doubting, stripped of worry, and rid of craving for rebirth in this or that state.*";
P_HTM[2970]="*evaṃvādī kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evamakkhāyī”ti.**That’s what I teach, and that’s what I explain.”*";
P_HTM[2971]="*Evaṃ vutte, daṇḍapāṇi sakko sīsaṃ okampetvā, jivhaṃ nillāḷetvā, tivisākhaṃ nalāṭikaṃ nalāṭe vuṭṭhāpetvā daṇḍamolubbha pakkāmi.**When he had spoken, Daṇḍapāṇi shook his head, waggled his tongue, raised his eyebrows until his brow puckered in three furrows, and he departed leaning on his staff.*";
P_HTM[2972]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena nigrodhārāmo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the Banyan Tree Monastery, sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[2973]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**and told the mendicants what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2974]="*“idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kapilavatthuṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2975]="*Kapilavatthusmiṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena mahāvanaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃ divāvihārāya.* **";
P_HTM[2976]="*Mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā beluvalaṭṭhikāya mūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2977]="*Daṇḍapāṇipi kho, bhikkhave, sakko jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena mahāvanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.* **";
P_HTM[2978]="*Mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā yena beluvalaṭṭhikā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mayā saddhiṃ sammodi.* **";
P_HTM[2979]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā daṇḍamolubbha ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, daṇḍapāṇi sakko maṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[2980]="*‘kiṃvādī samaṇo kimakkhāyī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2981]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, daṇḍapāṇiṃ sakkaṃ etadavocaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2982]="*‘yathāvādī kho, āvuso, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya na kenaci loke viggayha tiṭṭhati, yathā ca pana kāmehi visaṃyuttaṃ viharantaṃ taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ akathaṅkathiṃ chinnakukkuccaṃ bhavābhave vītataṇhaṃ saññā nānusenti—* **";
P_HTM[2983]="*evaṃvādī kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evamakkhāyī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2984]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, daṇḍapāṇi sakko sīsaṃ okampetvā, jivhaṃ nillāḷetvā, tivisākhaṃ nalāṭikaṃ nalāṭe vuṭṭhāpetvā daṇḍamolubbha pakkāmī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2985]="*Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, one of the mendicants said to him,*";
P_HTM[2986]="*“kiṃvādī pana, bhante, bhagavā sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya na kenaci loke viggayha tiṭṭhati?**“But sir, what is the teaching such that the Buddha does not conflict with anyone in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans?*";
P_HTM[2987]="*Kathañca pana, bhante, bhagavantaṃ kāmehi visaṃyuttaṃ viharantaṃ taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ akathaṅkathiṃ chinnakukkuccaṃ bhavābhave vītataṇhaṃ saññā nānusentī”ti?**And how is it that perceptions do not underlie the Buddha, the brahmin who lives detached from sensual pleasures, without indecision, stripped of worry, and rid of craving for rebirth in this or that state?”*";
P_HTM[2988]="*“Yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.**“Mendicant, a person is beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions.*";
P_HTM[2989]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ.**If they don’t find anything worth approving, welcoming, or getting attached to in the source from which these arise,*";
P_HTM[2990]="*Esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ, esevanto paṭighānusayānaṃ, esevanto diṭṭhānusayānaṃ, esevanto vicikicchānusayānaṃ, esevanto mānānusayānaṃ, esevanto bhavarāgānusayānaṃ, esevanto avijjānusayānaṃ, esevanto daṇḍādānasatthādānakalahaviggahavivādatuvaṃtuvaṃpesuññamusāvādānaṃ.**just this is the end of the underlying tendencies to desire, repulsion, views, doubt, conceit, the desire to be reborn, and ignorance. This is the end of taking up the rod and the sword, the end of quarrels, arguments, and fights, of accusations, divisive speech, and lies.*";
P_HTM[2991]="*Etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī”ti.**This is where these bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.”*";
P_HTM[2992]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2993]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[2994]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:**Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered,*";
P_HTM[2995]="*“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā, uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail.*";
P_HTM[2996]="*‘yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.* **";
P_HTM[2997]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2998]="*Esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2999]="*etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3000]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?**Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[3001]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:**Then those mendicants thought,*";
P_HTM[3002]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“This Venerable Mahākaccāna is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[3003]="*Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3004]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā”ti.**Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.”*";
P_HTM[3005]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākaccānena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu.**Then those mendicants went to Mahākaccāna, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3006]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. They told him what had happened, and said:*";
P_HTM[3007]="*“idaṃ kho no, āvuso kaccāna, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[3008]="*‘yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.* **";
P_HTM[3009]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3010]="*Esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3011]="*etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3012]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso kaccāna, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[3013]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[3014]="*“yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.* **";
P_HTM[3015]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3016]="*Esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3017]="*etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī”’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3018]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyāti?* **";
P_HTM[3019]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso kaccāna, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[3020]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ, pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3021]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3022]="*Vibhajatāyasmā mahākaccāno”ti.**“May Venerable Mahākaccāna please explain this.”*";
P_HTM[3023]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva mūlaṃ, atikkamma khandhaṃ, sākhāpalāse sāraṃ pariyesitabbaṃ maññeyya;**“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But he’d pass over the roots and trunk, imagining that the heartwood should be sought in the branches and leaves.*";
P_HTM[3024]="*evaṃsampadamidaṃ āyasmantānaṃ satthari sammukhībhūte, taṃ bhagavantaṃ atisitvā, amhe etamatthaṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ maññatha.**Such is the consequence for the venerables. Though you were face to face with the Buddha, you passed him by, imagining that you should ask me about this matter.*";
P_HTM[3025]="*So hāvuso, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati, cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto, vattā pavattā, atthassa ninnetā, amatassa dātā, dhammassāmī tathāgato.**For he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is holiness. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3026]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi, yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[3027]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[3028]="*“Addhāvuso kaccāna, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati, cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto, vattā pavattā, atthassa ninnetā, amatassa dātā, dhammassāmī tathāgato.**“Certainly he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is holiness. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3029]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi, yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[3030]="*Yathā no bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāma.**We should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.*";
P_HTM[3031]="*Api cāyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ,**Still, Mahākaccāna is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[3032]="*pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**You are capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3033]="*Vibhajatāyasmā mahākaccāno agaruṃ katvā”ti.**Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”*";
P_HTM[3034]="*“Tena hāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, reverends, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[3035]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3036]="*Āyasmā mahākaccāno etadavoca:**Venerable Mahākaccāna said this:*";
P_HTM[3037]="*“Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[3038]="*‘yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.**‘A person is beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions.*";
P_HTM[3039]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ, esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ … pe …**If they don’t find anything worth approving, welcoming, or getting attached to in the source from which these arise …*";
P_HTM[3040]="*etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī’ti, imassa kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi—**This is where these bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.’ This is how I understand the detailed meaning of this passage for recitation.*";
P_HTM[3041]="*Cakkhuñcāvuso, paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā, yaṃ vedeti taṃ sañjānāti, yaṃ sañjānāti taṃ vitakketi, yaṃ vitakketi taṃ papañceti, yaṃ papañceti tatonidānaṃ purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti atītānāgatapaccuppannesu cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu.**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling. What you feel, you perceive. What you perceive, you think about. What you think about, you proliferate. What you proliferate about is the source from which a person is beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions. This occurs with respect to sights known by the eye in the past, future, and present.*";
P_HTM[3042]="*Sotañcāvuso, paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. …*";
P_HTM[3043]="*ghānañcāvuso, paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. …*";
P_HTM[3044]="*jivhañcāvuso, paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. …*";
P_HTM[3045]="*kāyañcāvuso, paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. …*";
P_HTM[3046]="*manañcāvuso, paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā, yaṃ vedeti taṃ sañjānāti, yaṃ sañjānāti taṃ vitakketi, yaṃ vitakketi taṃ papañceti, yaṃ papañceti tatonidānaṃ purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti atītānāgatapaccuppannesu manoviññeyyesu dhammesu.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling. What you feel, you perceive. What you perceive, you think about. What you think about, you proliferate. What you proliferate about is the source from which a person is beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions. This occurs with respect to thoughts known by the mind in the past, future, and present.*";
P_HTM[3047]="*So vatāvuso, cakkhusmiṃ sati rūpe sati cakkhuviññāṇe sati phassapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When there is the eye, sights, and eye consciousness, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘contact’.*";
P_HTM[3048]="*Phassapaññattiyā sati vedanāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When there is what’s known as contact, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘feeling’.*";
P_HTM[3049]="*Vedanāpaññattiyā sati saññāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When there is what’s known as feeling, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘perception’.*";
P_HTM[3050]="*Saññāpaññattiyā sati vitakkapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When there is what’s known as perception, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘thought’.*";
P_HTM[3051]="*Vitakkapaññattiyā sati papañcasaññāsaṅkhāsamudācaraṇapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When there is what’s known as thought, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘being beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions’.*";
P_HTM[3052]="*So vatāvuso, sotasmiṃ sati sadde sati … pe …**When there is the ear …*";
P_HTM[3053]="*ghānasmiṃ sati gandhe sati … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[3054]="*jivhāya sati rase sati … pe …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[3055]="*kāyasmiṃ sati phoṭṭhabbe sati … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[3056]="*manasmiṃ sati dhamme sati manoviññāṇe sati phassapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**mind, thoughts, and mind consciousness, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘contact’. …*";
P_HTM[3057]="*Phassapaññattiyā sati vedanāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.* **";
P_HTM[3058]="*Vedanāpaññattiyā sati saññāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.* **";
P_HTM[3059]="*Saññāpaññattiyā sati vitakkapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.* **";
P_HTM[3060]="*Vitakkapaññattiyā sati papañcasaññāsaṅkhāsamudācaraṇapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**When there is what’s known as thought, it’s possible to point out what’s known as ‘being beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions’.*";
P_HTM[3061]="*So vatāvuso, cakkhusmiṃ asati rūpe asati cakkhuviññāṇe asati phassapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When there is no eye, no sights, and no eye consciousness, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘contact’.*";
P_HTM[3062]="*Phassapaññattiyā asati vedanāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When there isn’t what’s known as contact, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘feeling’.*";
P_HTM[3063]="*Vedanāpaññattiyā asati saññāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When there isn’t what’s known as feeling, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘perception’.*";
P_HTM[3064]="*Saññāpaññattiyā asati vitakkapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When there isn’t what’s known as perception, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘thought’.*";
P_HTM[3065]="*Vitakkapaññattiyā asati papañcasaññāsaṅkhāsamudācaraṇapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When there isn’t what’s known as thought, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘being beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions’.*";
P_HTM[3066]="*So vatāvuso, sotasmiṃ asati sadde asati … pe …**When there is no ear …*";
P_HTM[3067]="*ghānasmiṃ asati gandhe asati … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[3068]="*jivhāya asati rase asati … pe …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[3069]="*kāyasmiṃ asati phoṭṭhabbe asati … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[3070]="*manasmiṃ asati dhamme asati manoviññāṇe asati phassapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**mind, no thoughts, and no mind consciousness, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘contact’. …*";
P_HTM[3071]="*Phassapaññattiyā asati vedanāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.* **";
P_HTM[3072]="*Vedanāpaññattiyā asati saññāpaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.* **";
P_HTM[3073]="*Saññāpaññattiyā asati vitakkapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.* **";
P_HTM[3074]="*Vitakkapaññattiyā asati papañcasaññāsaṅkhāsamudācaraṇapaññattiṃ paññāpessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**When there isn’t what’s known as thought, it’s not possible to point out what’s known as ‘being beset by concepts of identity that emerge from the proliferation of perceptions’.*";
P_HTM[3075]="*Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**This is how I understand the detailed meaning of that brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3076]="*‘yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3077]="*etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī’ti, imassa kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.* **";
P_HTM[3078]="*Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe āyasmanto bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this.*";
P_HTM[3079]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[3080]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**“Yes, reverend,” said those mendicants, approving and agreeing with what Mahākaccāna said. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then they said:*";
P_HTM[3081]="*“yaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[3082]="*‘yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.* **";
P_HTM[3083]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3084]="*Esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3085]="*etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3086]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[3087]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṃkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[3088]="*“yatonidānaṃ, bhikkhu, purisaṃ papañcasaññāsaṅkhā samudācaranti.* **";
P_HTM[3089]="*Ettha ce natthi abhinanditabbaṃ abhivaditabbaṃ ajjhositabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3090]="*Esevanto rāgānusayānaṃ, esevanto paṭighānusayānaṃ, esevanto diṭṭhānusayānaṃ, esevanto vicikicchānusayānaṃ, esevanto mānānusayānaṃ, esevanto bhavarāgānusayānaṃ, esevanto avijjānusayānaṃ, esevanto daṇḍādānasatthādānakalahaviggahavivādatuvaṃtuvaṃpesuññamusāvādānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3091]="*Etthete pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3092]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[3093]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[3094]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ, pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ, yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3095]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipucchimha.* **";
P_HTM[3096]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā mahākaccānena imehi ākārehi imehi padehi imehi byañjanehi attho vibhatto”ti.**“Mahākaccāna clearly explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these words and phrases.”*";
P_HTM[3097]="*“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, mahākaccāno; mahāpañño, bhikkhave, mahākaccāno.**“Mahākaccāna is astute, mendicants, he has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3098]="*Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi taṃ evamevaṃ byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ mahākaccānena byākataṃ.**If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the same way as Mahākaccāna.*";
P_HTM[3099]="*Eso cevetassa attho. Evañca naṃ dhārethā”ti.**That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”*";
P_HTM[3100]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3101]="*“seyyathāpi, bhante, puriso jighacchādubbalyapareto madhupiṇḍikaṃ adhigaccheyya, so yato yato sāyeyya, labhetheva sādurasaṃ asecanakaṃ.**“Sir, suppose a person who was weak with hunger was to obtain a honey-cake. Wherever they taste it, they would enjoy a sweet, delicious flavor.*";
P_HTM[3102]="*Evameva kho, bhante, cetaso bhikkhu dabbajātiko, yato yato imassa dhammapariyāyassa paññāya atthaṃ upaparikkheyya, labhetheva attamanataṃ, labhetheva cetaso pasādaṃ.**In the same way, wherever a sincere, capable mendicant might examine with wisdom the meaning of this exposition of the teaching they would only gain joy and clarity.*";
P_HTM[3103]="*Ko nāmo ayaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo”ti?**Sir, what is the name of this exposition of the teaching?”*";
P_HTM[3104]="*“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, ānanda, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ madhupiṇḍikapariyāyotveva naṃ dhārehī”ti.**“Well, Ānanda, you may remember this exposition of the teaching as ‘The Honey-Cake Discourse’.”*";
P_HTM[3105]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3106]="*Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3107]="*Madhupiṇḍikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3108]="*19. Dvedhāvitakkasutta**Two Kinds of Thought*";
P_HTM[3109]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3110]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3111]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3112]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3113]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3114]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3115]="*“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[3116]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ dvidhā katvā dvidhā katvā vitakke vihareyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I meditate by continually dividing my thoughts into two classes?’*";
P_HTM[3117]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yo cāyaṃ kāmavitakko yo ca byāpādavitakko yo ca vihiṃsāvitakko—**So I assigned sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts*";
P_HTM[3118]="*imaṃ ekaṃ bhāgamakāsiṃ;**to one class.*";
P_HTM[3119]="*yo cāyaṃ nekkhammavitakko yo ca abyāpādavitakko yo ca avihiṃsāvitakko—**And I assigned thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness*";
P_HTM[3120]="*imaṃ dutiyaṃ bhāgamakāsiṃ.**to the second class.*";
P_HTM[3121]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati kāmavitakko.**Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a sensual thought arose.*";
P_HTM[3122]="*So evaṃ pajānāmi:**I understood:*";
P_HTM[3123]="*‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ kāmavitakko.**‘This sensual thought has arisen in me.*";
P_HTM[3124]="*So ca kho attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko anibbānasaṃvattaniko’.**It leads to hurting myself, hurting others, and hurting both. It blocks wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it doesn’t lead to extinguishment.’*";
P_HTM[3125]="*‘Attabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati;**When I reflected that it leads to hurting myself, it went away.*";
P_HTM[3126]="*‘parabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati;**When I reflected that it leads to hurting others, it went away.*";
P_HTM[3127]="*‘ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati;**When I reflected that it leads to hurting both, it went away.*";
P_HTM[3128]="*‘paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko anibbānasaṃvattaniko’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati.**When I reflected that it blocks wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it doesn’t lead to extinguishment, it went away.*";
P_HTM[3129]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, uppannuppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ pajahameva vinodameva byantameva naṃ akāsiṃ.**So I gave up, got rid of, and eliminated any sensual thoughts that arose.*";
P_HTM[3130]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati byāpādavitakko … pe …**Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a malicious thought arose …*";
P_HTM[3131]="*uppajjati vihiṃsāvitakko.**a cruel thought arose.*";
P_HTM[3132]="*So evaṃ pajānāmi:**I understood:*";
P_HTM[3133]="*‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ vihiṃsāvitakko.**‘This cruel thought has arisen in me.*";
P_HTM[3134]="*So ca kho attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko anibbānasaṃvattaniko’.**It leads to hurting myself, hurting others, and hurting both. It blocks wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it doesn’t lead to extinguishment.’*";
P_HTM[3135]="*‘Attabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati;**When I reflected that it leads to hurting myself …*";
P_HTM[3136]="*‘parabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati;**hurting others …*";
P_HTM[3137]="*‘ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati;**hurting both, it went away.*";
P_HTM[3138]="*‘paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko anibbānasaṃvattaniko’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati.**When I reflected that it blocks wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it doesn’t lead to extinguishment, it went away.*";
P_HTM[3139]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, uppannuppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ pajahameva vinodameva byantameva naṃ akāsiṃ.**So I gave up, got rid of, and eliminated any cruel thoughts that arose.*";
P_HTM[3140]="*Yaññadeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, tathā tathā nati hoti cetaso.**Whatever a mendicant frequently thinks about and considers becomes their heart’s inclination.*";
P_HTM[3141]="*Kāmavitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, pahāsi nekkhammavitakkaṃ, kāmavitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassa taṃ kāmavitakkāya cittaṃ namati.**If they often think about and consider sensual thoughts, they’ve given up the thought of renunciation to cultivate sensual thought. Their mind inclines to sensual thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3142]="*Byāpādavitakkañce, bhikkhave … pe …**If they often think about and consider malicious thoughts … their mind inclines to malicious thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3143]="*vihiṃsāvitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, pahāsi avihiṃsāvitakkaṃ, vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassa taṃ vihiṃsāvitakkāya cittaṃ namati.**If they often think about and consider cruel thoughts … their mind inclines to cruel thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3144]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye kiṭṭhasambādhe gopālako gāvo rakkheyya.**Suppose it’s the last month of the rainy season, when the crops grow closely together, and a cowherd must take care of the cattle.*";
P_HTM[3145]="*So tā gāvo tato tato daṇḍena ākoṭeyya paṭikoṭeyya sannirundheyya sannivāreyya.**He’d tap and poke them with his staff on this side and that to keep them in check.*";
P_HTM[3146]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3147]="*Passati hi so, bhikkhave, gopālako tatonidānaṃ vadhaṃ vā bandhanaṃ vā jāniṃ vā garahaṃ vā.**For he sees that if they wander into the crops he could be executed, imprisoned, fined, or condemned.*";
P_HTM[3148]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, addasaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**In the same way, I saw that unskillful qualities have the drawbacks of sordidness and corruption, and that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3149]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati nekkhammavitakko.**Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a thought of renunciation arose.*";
P_HTM[3150]="*So evaṃ pajānāmi:**I understood:*";
P_HTM[3151]="*‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ nekkhammavitakko.**‘This thought of renunciation has arisen in me.*";
P_HTM[3152]="*So ca kho nevattabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattati, paññāvuddhiko avighātapakkhiko nibbānasaṃvattaniko’.**It doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both. It nourishes wisdom, it’s on the side of freedom from anguish, and it leads to extinguishment.’*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Rattiñcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi.**If I were to keep on thinking and considering this all night …*";
P_HTM[3154]="*Divasañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi.**all day …*";
P_HTM[3155]="*Rattindivañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi.**all night and day, I see no danger that would come from that.*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Api ca kho me aticiraṃ anuvitakkayato anuvicārayato kāyo kilameyya.**Still, thinking and considering for too long would tire my body.*";
P_HTM[3157]="*Kāye kilante cittaṃ ūhaññeyya.**And when the body is tired, the mind is stressed.*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Ūhate citte ārā cittaṃ samādhimhāti.**And when the mind is stressed, it’s far from immersion.*";
P_HTM[3159]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, ajjhattameva cittaṃ saṇṭhapemi sannisādemi ekodiṃ karomi samādahāmi.**So I stilled, settled, unified, and immersed my mind internally.*";
P_HTM[3160]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3161]="*‘Mā me cittaṃ ūhaññī’ti.**So that my mind would not be stressed.*";
P_HTM[3162]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati abyāpādavitakko … pe …**Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a thought of good will arose …*";
P_HTM[3163]="*uppajjati avihiṃsāvitakko.**a thought of harmlessness arose.*";
P_HTM[3164]="*So evaṃ pajānāmi:**I understood:*";
P_HTM[3165]="*‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ avihiṃsāvitakko.**‘This thought of harmlessness has arisen in me.*";
P_HTM[3166]="*So ca kho nevattabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattati, paññāvuddhiko avighātapakkhiko nibbānasaṃvattaniko’.**It doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both. It nourishes wisdom, it’s on the side of freedom from anguish, and it leads to extinguishment.’*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Rattiñcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi.**If I were to keep on thinking and considering this all night …*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Divasañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi.**all day …*";
P_HTM[3169]="*Rattindivañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi.**all night and day, I see no danger that would come from that.*";
P_HTM[3170]="*Api ca kho me aticiraṃ anuvitakkayato anuvicārayato kāyo kilameyya.**Still, thinking and considering for too long would tire my body.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Kāye kilante cittaṃ ūhaññeyya.**And when the body is tired, the mind is stressed.*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Ūhate citte ārā cittaṃ samādhimhāti.**And when the mind is stressed, it’s far from immersion.*";
P_HTM[3173]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, ajjhattameva cittaṃ saṇṭhapemi, sannisādemi, ekodiṃ karomi samādahāmi.**So I stilled, settled, unified, and immersed my mind internally.*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3175]="*‘Mā me cittaṃ ūhaññī’ti.**So that my mind would not be stressed.*";
P_HTM[3176]="*Yaññadeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, tathā tathā nati hoti cetaso.**Whatever a mendicant frequently thinks about and considers becomes their heart’s inclination.*";
P_HTM[3177]="*Nekkhammavitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, pahāsi kāmavitakkaṃ, nekkhammavitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassaṃ taṃ nekkhammavitakkāya cittaṃ namati.**If they often think about and consider thoughts of renunciation, they’ve given up sensual thought to cultivate the thought of renunciation. Their mind inclines to thoughts of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3178]="*Abyāpādavitakkañce, bhikkhave … pe …**If they often think about and consider thoughts of good will … their mind inclines to thoughts of good will.*";
P_HTM[3179]="*avihiṃsāvitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, pahāsi vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ, avihiṃsāvitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassa taṃ avihiṃsāvitakkāya cittaṃ namati.**If they often think about and consider thoughts of harmlessness … their mind inclines to thoughts of harmlessness.*";
P_HTM[3180]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse sabbasassesu gāmantasambhatesu gopālako gāvo rakkheyya, tassa rukkhamūlagatassa vā abbhokāsagatassa vā satikaraṇīyameva hoti:**Suppose it’s the last month of summer, when all the crops have been gathered into the neighborhood of a village, and a cowherd must take care of the cattle. While at the root of a tree or in the open he need only be mindful that*";
P_HTM[3181]="*‘etā gāvo’ti.**the cattle are there.*";
P_HTM[3182]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, satikaraṇīyameva ahosi:**In the same way I needed only to be mindful that*";
P_HTM[3183]="*‘ete dhammā’ti.**those things were there.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ ahosi asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, my mindfulness was established and lucid, my body was tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind was immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3185]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3186]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered and remained in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3187]="*Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihāsiṃ sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedesiṃ, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**And with the fading away of rapture, I entered and remained in the third absorption, where I meditated with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[3188]="*Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**With the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, I entered and remained in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[3189]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[3190]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. Seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi.**I recollected many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[3191]="*Ayaṃ kho me, bhikkhave, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā;**This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[3192]="*avijjā vihatā vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[3193]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had become immersed in samādhi like this, I extended it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[3194]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne … pe … ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā … pe … iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate, yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[3195]="*Ayaṃ kho me, bhikkhave, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā;**This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[3196]="*avijjā vihatā vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had become immersed in samādhi like this, I extended it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3198]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ.**I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.'*";
P_HTM[3199]="*‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ.**I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements.'*";
P_HTM[3200]="*Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi:**Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[3201]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsiṃ.**I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[3202]="*Ayaṃ kho me, bhikkhave, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā vijjā adhigatā;**This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[3203]="*avijjā vihatā vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[3204]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, araññe pavane mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalaṃ.**Suppose that in a forested wilderness there was an expanse of low-lying marshes,*";
P_HTM[3205]="*Tamenaṃ mahāmigasaṅgho upanissāya vihareyya.**and a large herd of deer lived nearby.*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Tassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya anatthakāmo ahitakāmo ayogakkhemakāmo.**Then along comes a person who wants to harm, injure, and threaten them.*";
P_HTM[3207]="*So yvāssa maggo khemo sovatthiko pītigamanīyo taṃ maggaṃ pidaheyya, vivareyya kummaggaṃ, odaheyya okacaraṃ, ṭhapeyya okacārikaṃ.**They close off the safe, secure path that leads to happiness, and open the wrong path. There they plant domesticated male and female deer as decoys*";
P_HTM[3208]="*Evañhi so, bhikkhave, mahāmigasaṅgho aparena samayena anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyya.**so that, in due course, that herd of deer would fall to ruin and disaster.*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Tasseva kho pana, bhikkhave, mahato migasaṅghassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmo.**Then along comes a person who wants to help keep the herd of deer safe.*";
P_HTM[3210]="*So yvāssa maggo khemo sovatthiko pītigamanīyo taṃ maggaṃ vivareyya, pidaheyya kummaggaṃ, ūhaneyya okacaraṃ, nāseyya okacārikaṃ.**They open up the safe, secure path that leads to happiness, and close off the wrong path. They get rid of the decoys*";
P_HTM[3211]="*Evañhi so, bhikkhave, mahāmigasaṅgho aparena samayena vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyya.**so that, in due course, that herd of deer would grow, increase, and mature.*";
P_HTM[3212]="*Upamā kho me ayaṃ, bhikkhave, katā atthassa viññāpanāya.**I’ve made up this simile to make a point.*";
P_HTM[3213]="*Ayaṃ cevettha attho—**And this is what it means.*";
P_HTM[3214]="*mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalanti kho, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘An expanse of low-lying marshes’ is a term for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[3215]="*Mahāmigasaṅghoti kho, bhikkhave, sattānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘A large herd of deer’ is a term for sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[3216]="*Puriso anatthakāmo ahitakāmo ayogakkhemakāmoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ.**‘A person who wants to harm, injure, and threaten them’ is a term for Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Kummaggoti kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhaṅgikassetaṃ micchāmaggassa adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**‘The wrong path’ is a term for the wrong eightfold path, that is,*";
P_HTM[3218]="*micchādiṭṭhiyā micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācāya micchākammantassa micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmassa micchāsatiyā micchāsamādhissa.**wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Okacaroti kho, bhikkhave, nandīrāgassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘A domesticated male deer’ is a term for desire with relishing.*";
P_HTM[3220]="*Okacārikāti kho, bhikkhave, avijjāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘A domesticated female deer’ is a term for ignorance.*";
P_HTM[3221]="*Puriso atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmoti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**‘A person who wants to help keep the herd of deer safe’ is a term for the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3222]="*Khemo maggo sovatthiko pītigamanīyoti kho, bhikkhave, ariyassetaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**‘The safe, secure path that leads to happiness’ is a term for the noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[3223]="*sammādiṭṭhiyā sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācāya sammākammantassa sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmassa sammāsatiyā sammāsamādhissa.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[3224]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, vivaṭo mayā khemo maggo sovatthiko pītigamanīyo, pihito kummaggo, ūhato okacaro, nāsitā okacārikā.**So, mendicants, I have opened up the safe, secure path to happiness and closed off the wrong path. And I have got rid of the male and female decoys.*";
P_HTM[3225]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā.**Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples.*";
P_HTM[3226]="*Etāni, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni; jhāyatha, bhikkhave, mā pamādattha; mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti.**Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.”*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3229]="*Dvedhāvitakkasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3230]="*20. Vitakkasaṇṭhānasutta**How to Stop Thinking*";
P_HTM[3231]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3232]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3234]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3235]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3236]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3237]="*“Adhicittamanuyuttena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā pañca nimittāni kālena kālaṃ manasi kātabbāni.**“Mendicants, a mendicant committed to the higher mind should focus on five foundations of meditation from time to time.*";
P_HTM[3238]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasi kātabbaṃ kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ.**Take a mendicant who is focusing on some foundation of meditation that gives rise to bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion. That mendicant should focus on some other foundation of meditation connected with the skillful.*";
P_HTM[3240]="*Tassa tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3241]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3242]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho palagaṇḍo vā palagaṇḍantevāsī vā sukhumāya āṇiyā oḷārikaṃ āṇiṃ abhinihaneyya abhinīhareyya abhinivatteyya;**It’s like a deft carpenter or their apprentice who’d knock out or extract a large peg with a finer peg.*";
P_HTM[3243]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasi kātabbaṃ kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ.**In the same way, a mendicant … should focus on some other foundation of meditation connected with the skillful …*";
P_HTM[3244]="*Tassa tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[3245]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati. (1)* **";
P_HTM[3246]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavo upaparikkhitabbo:**Now, suppose that mendicant is focusing on some other foundation of meditation connected with the skillful, but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion keep coming up. They should examine the drawbacks of those thoughts:*";
P_HTM[3247]="*‘itipime vitakkā akusalā, itipime vitakkā sāvajjā, itipime vitakkā dukkhavipākā’ti.**‘So these thoughts are unskillful, they’re blameworthy, and they result in suffering.’*";
P_HTM[3248]="*Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3250]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko ahikuṇapena vā kukkurakuṇapena vā manussakuṇapena vā kaṇṭhe āsattena aṭṭiyeyya harāyeyya jiguccheyya;**Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of adornments. If the corpse of a snake or a dog or a human were hung around their neck, they’d be horrified, repelled, and disgusted.*";
P_HTM[3251]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tamhāpi nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavo upaparikkhitabbo:**In the same way, a mendicant … should examine the drawbacks of those thoughts …*";
P_HTM[3252]="*‘itipime vitakkā akusalā, itipime vitakkā sāvajjā, itipime vitakkā dukkhavipākā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3253]="*Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[3254]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati. (2)* **";
P_HTM[3255]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāro āpajjitabbo.**Now, suppose that mendicant is examining the drawbacks of those thoughts, but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion keep coming up. They should try to ignore and forget about them.*";
P_HTM[3256]="*Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3257]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3258]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso āpāthagatānaṃ rūpānaṃ adassanakāmo assa;**Suppose there was a person with good eyesight, and some undesirable sights came into their range of vision.*";
P_HTM[3259]="*so nimīleyya vā aññena vā apalokeyya;**They’d just close their eyes or look away.*";
P_HTM[3260]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**In the same way, a mendicant … those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end …*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati. (3)* **";
P_HTM[3262]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikātabbaṃ.**Now, suppose that mendicant is ignoring and forgetting about those thoughts, but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion keep coming up. They should focus on stopping the formation of thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3263]="*Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3264]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3265]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sīghaṃ gaccheyya.**Suppose there was a person walking quickly.*";
P_HTM[3266]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[3267]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ sīghaṃ gacchāmi?**‘Why am I walking so quickly?*";
P_HTM[3268]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṇikaṃ gaccheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I slow down?’*";
P_HTM[3269]="*So saṇikaṃ gaccheyya.**So they’d slow down.*";
P_HTM[3270]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[3271]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ saṇikaṃ gacchāmi?**‘Why am I walking slowly?*";
P_HTM[3272]="*Yannūnāhaṃ tiṭṭheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I stand still?’*";
P_HTM[3273]="*So tiṭṭheyya.**So they’d stand still.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[3275]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ ṭhito?**‘Why am I standing still?*";
P_HTM[3276]="*Yannūnāhaṃ nisīdeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I sit down?’*";
P_HTM[3277]="*So nisīdeyya.**So they’d sit down.*";
P_HTM[3278]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[3279]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ nisinno?**‘Why am I sitting?*";
P_HTM[3280]="*Yannūnāhaṃ nipajjeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I lie down?’*";
P_HTM[3281]="*So nipajjeyya.**So they’d lie down.*";
P_HTM[3282]="*Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso oḷārikaṃ oḷārikaṃ iriyāpathaṃ abhinivajjetvā sukhumaṃ sukhumaṃ iriyāpathaṃ kappeyya.**And so that person would reject successively coarser postures and adopt more subtle ones.*";
P_HTM[3283]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**In the same way, a mendicant … those thoughts are given up and come to an end …*";
P_HTM[3284]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati. (4)* **";
P_HTM[3285]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi.**Now, suppose that mendicant is focusing on stopping the formation of thoughts, but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion keep coming up.*";
P_HTM[3286]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhitabbaṃ abhinippīḷetabbaṃ abhisantāpetabbaṃ.**With teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of the mouth, they should squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind.*";
P_HTM[3287]="*Tassa dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3289]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, balavā puriso dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ sīse vā gale vā khandhe vā gahetvā abhiniggaṇheyya abhinippīḷeyya abhisantāpeyya;**It’s like a strong man who grabs a weaker man by the head or throat or shoulder and squeezes, squashes, and tortures them.*";
P_HTM[3290]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi.**In the same way, a mendicant …*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhitabbaṃ abhinippīḷetabbaṃ abhisantāpetabbaṃ.**with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of the mouth, should squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind.*";
P_HTM[3292]="*Tassa dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati. (5)**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tassa tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**Now, take the mendicant who is focusing on some foundation of meditation that gives rise to bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion. They focus on some other foundation of meditation connected with the skillful …*";
P_HTM[3295]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.* **";
P_HTM[3296]="*Tesampi vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**They examine the drawbacks of those thoughts …*";
P_HTM[3297]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.* **";
P_HTM[3298]="*Tesampi vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**They try to ignore and forget about those thoughts …*";
P_HTM[3299]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.* **";
P_HTM[3300]="*Tesampi vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**They focus on stopping the formation of thoughts …*";
P_HTM[3301]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.* **";
P_HTM[3302]="*Dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**With teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of the mouth, they squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind. When they succeed in each of these things, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3303]="*Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti samādhiyati.**Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3304]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vasī vitakkapariyāyapathesu.**This is called a mendicant who is a master of the ways of thought.*";
P_HTM[3305]="*Yaṃ vitakkaṃ ākaṅkhissati taṃ vitakkaṃ vitakkessati, yaṃ vitakkaṃ nākaṅkhissati na taṃ vitakkaṃ vitakkessati.**They’ll think what they want to think, and they won’t think what they don’t want to think.*";
P_HTM[3306]="*Acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassā”ti.**They’ve cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit have made an end of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[3307]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3309]="*Vitakkasaṇṭhānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3310]="*Sīhanādavaggo niṭṭhito dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[3311]="*Cūḷasīhanādalomahaṃsavaro,* **";
P_HTM[3312]="*Mahācūḷadukkhakkhandhaanumānikasuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3313]="*Khilapatthamadhupiṇḍikadvidhāvitakka,* **";
P_HTM[3314]="*Pañcanimittakathā puna vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[3315]="*21. Kakacūpamasutta**The Simile of the Saw*";
P_HTM[3316]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3317]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ ativelaṃ saṃsaṭṭho viharati.**Now at that time, Venerable Phagguna of the Top-Knot was mixing too closely together with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[3319]="*Evaṃ saṃsaṭṭho āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ viharati—**So much so that*";
P_HTM[3320]="*sace koci bhikkhu āyasmato moḷiyaphaggunassa sammukhā tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, tenāyasmā moḷiyaphagguno kupito anattamano adhikaraṇampi karoti.**if any mendicant criticized those nuns in his presence, Phagguna of the Top-Knot got angry and upset, and even instigated disciplinary proceedings.*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Sace pana koci bhikkhu tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ sammukhā āyasmato moḷiyaphaggunassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, tena tā bhikkhuniyo kupitā anattamanā adhikaraṇampi karonti.**And if any mendicant criticized Phagguna of the Top-Knot in their presence, those nuns got angry and upset, and even instigated disciplinary proceedings.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*Evaṃ saṃsaṭṭho āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ viharati.**That’s how much Phagguna of the Top-Knot was mixing too closely together with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what was going on.*";
P_HTM[3324]="*“āyasmā, bhante, moḷiyaphagguno bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ ativelaṃ saṃsaṭṭho viharati.* **";
P_HTM[3325]="*Evaṃ saṃsaṭṭho, bhante, āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ viharati—* **";
P_HTM[3326]="*sace koci bhikkhu āyasmato moḷiyaphaggunassa sammukhā tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, tenāyasmā moḷiyaphagguno kupito anattamano adhikaraṇampi karoti.* **";
P_HTM[3327]="*Sace pana koci bhikkhu tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ sammukhā āyasmato moḷiyaphaggunassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, tena tā bhikkhuniyo kupitā anattamanā adhikaraṇampi karonti.* **";
P_HTM[3328]="*Evaṃ saṃsaṭṭho, bhante, āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ viharatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3329]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[3330]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena moḷiyaphaggunaṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell the mendicant Phagguna of the Top-Knot that*";
P_HTM[3331]="*‘satthā taṃ, āvuso phagguna, āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons him.”*";
P_HTM[3332]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā moḷiyaphagguno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ moḷiyaphaggunaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Phagguna of the Top-Knot and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3333]="*“satthā taṃ, āvuso phagguna, āmantetī”ti.**“Reverend Phagguna, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[3334]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā moḷiyaphagguno tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ moḷiyaphaggunaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” Phagguna replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[3335]="*“Saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, phagguna, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ ativelaṃ saṃsaṭṭho viharasi?**“Is it really true, Phagguna, that you’ve been mixing overly closely together with the nuns?*";
P_HTM[3336]="*Evaṃ saṃsaṭṭho kira tvaṃ, phagguna, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ viharasi—**So much so that*";
P_HTM[3337]="*sace koci bhikkhu tuyhaṃ sammukhā tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, tena tvaṃ kupito anattamano adhikaraṇampi karosi.**if any mendicant criticizes those nuns in your presence, you get angry and upset, and even instigate disciplinary proceedings?*";
P_HTM[3338]="*Sace pana koci bhikkhu tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ sammukhā tuyhaṃ avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, tena tā bhikkhuniyo kupitā anattamanā adhikaraṇampi karonti.**And if any mendicant criticizes you in those nuns’ presence, they get angry and upset, and even instigate disciplinary proceedings?*";
P_HTM[3339]="*Evaṃ saṃsaṭṭho kira tvaṃ, phagguna, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ viharasī”ti?**Is that how much you’re mixing overly closely together with the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[3340]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3341]="*“Nanu tvaṃ, phagguna, kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti?**“Phagguna, are you not a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness?”*";
P_HTM[3342]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3343]="*“Na kho te etaṃ, phagguna, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ ativelaṃ saṃsaṭṭho vihareyyāsi.**“As such, it’s not appropriate for you to mix so closely with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Tasmātiha, phagguna, tava cepi koci sammukhā tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyya, tatrāpi tvaṃ, phagguna, ye gehasitā chandā ye gehasitā vitakkā te pajaheyyāsi.**So if anyone criticizes those nuns in your presence, you should give up any desires or thoughts of the lay life.*";
P_HTM[3345]="*Tatrāpi te, phagguna, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**If that happens, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3346]="*‘na ceva me cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāmi, hitānukampī ca viharissāmi mettacitto, na dosantaro’ti.**‘My mind will be unaffected. I will blurt out no bad words. I will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.’*";
P_HTM[3347]="*Evañhi te, phagguna, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3348]="*Tasmātiha, phagguna, tava cepi koci sammukhā tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pāṇinā pahāraṃ dadeyya, leḍḍunā pahāraṃ dadeyya, daṇḍena pahāraṃ dadeyya, satthena pahāraṃ dadeyya. Tatrāpi tvaṃ, phagguna, ye gehasitā chandā ye gehasitā vitakkā te pajaheyyāsi.**So even if someone strikes those nuns with fists, stones, rods, and swords in your presence, you should give up any desires or thoughts of the lay life.*";
P_HTM[3349]="*Tatrāpi te, phagguna, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ**If that happens, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3350]="*‘na ceva me cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāmi, hitānukampī ca viharissāmi mettacitto, na dosantaro’ti.**‘My mind will be unaffected. I will blurt out no bad words. I will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.’*";
P_HTM[3351]="*Evañhi te, phagguna, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3352]="*Tasmātiha, phagguna, tava cepi koci sammukhā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyya, tatrāpi tvaṃ, phagguna, ye gehasitā chandā ye gehasitā vitakkā te pajaheyyāsi.**So if anyone criticizes you in your presence, you should give up any desires or thoughts of the lay life.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Tatrāpi te, phagguna, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ ‘na ceva me cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāmi, hitānukampī ca viharissāmi mettacitto, na dosantaro’ti.**If that happens, you should train like this: ‘My mind will be unaffected. I will blurt out no bad words. I will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.’*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Evañhi te, phagguna, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3355]="*Tasmātiha, phagguna, tava cepi koci pāṇinā pahāraṃ dadeyya, leḍḍunā pahāraṃ dadeyya, daṇḍena pahāraṃ dadeyya, satthena pahāraṃ dadeyya, tatrāpi tvaṃ, phagguna, ye gehasitā chandā ye gehasitā vitakkā te pajaheyyāsi.**So Phagguṇa, even if someone strikes you with fists, stones, rods, and swords, you should give up any desires or thoughts of the lay life.*";
P_HTM[3356]="*Tatrāpi te, phagguna, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ ‘na ceva me cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāmi, hitānukampī ca viharissāmi mettacitto, na dosantaro’ti.**If that happens, you should train like this: ‘My mind will be unaffected. I will blurt out no bad words. I will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.’*";
P_HTM[3357]="*Evañhi te, phagguna, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[3358]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3359]="*“ārādhayiṃsu vata me, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ekaṃ samayaṃ cittaṃ.**“Mendicants, I used to be satisfied with the mendicants.*";
P_HTM[3360]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū āmantesiṃ—**Once, I addressed them:*";
P_HTM[3361]="*ahaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ekāsanabhojanaṃ bhuñjāmi.**‘I eat my food in one sitting per day.*";
P_HTM[3362]="*Ekāsanabhojanaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhuñjamāno appābādhatañca sañjānāmi appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, I find that I’m healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[3363]="*Etha tumhepi, bhikkhave, ekāsanabhojanaṃ bhuñjatha.**You too should eat your food in one sitting per day.*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Ekāsanabhojanaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tumhepi bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānissatha appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañcāti.**Doing so, you’ll find that you’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.’*";
P_HTM[3365]="*Na me, bhikkhave, tesu bhikkhūsu anusāsanī karaṇīyā ahosi;**I didn’t have to keep on instructing those mendicants;*";
P_HTM[3366]="*satuppādakaraṇīyameva me, bhikkhave, tesu bhikkhūsu ahosi.**I just had to prompt their mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[3367]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, subhūmiyaṃ catumahāpathe ājaññaratho yutto assa ṭhito odhastapatodo.**Suppose a chariot stood harnessed to thoroughbreds at a level crossroads, with a goad ready.*";
P_HTM[3368]="*Tamenaṃ dakkho yoggācariyo assadammasārathi abhiruhitvā, vāmena hatthena rasmiyo gahetvā, dakkhiṇena hatthena patodaṃ gahetvā, yenicchakaṃ yadicchakaṃ sāreyyapi paccāsāreyyapi.**Then a deft horse trainer, a master charioteer, might mount the chariot, taking the reins in his right hand and goad in the left. He’d drive out and back wherever he wishes, whenever he wishes.*";
P_HTM[3369]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, na me tesu bhikkhūsu anusāsanī karaṇīyā ahosi,**In the same way, I didn’t have to keep on instructing those mendicants;*";
P_HTM[3370]="*satuppādakaraṇīyameva me, bhikkhave, tesu bhikkhūsu ahosi.**I just had to prompt their mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[3371]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, tumhepi akusalaṃ pajahatha, kusalesu dhammesu āyogaṃ karotha.**So, mendicants, give up what’s unskillful and devote yourselves to skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3372]="*Evañhi tumhepi imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatha.**In this way you’ll achieve growth, improvement, and maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre mahantaṃ sālavanaṃ.**Suppose that not far from a town or village there was a large grove of sal trees*";
P_HTM[3374]="*Tañcassa eḷaṇḍehi sañchannaṃ.**that was choked with castor-oil weeds.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Tassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmo.**Then along comes a person who wants to help protect and nurture that grove.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*So yā tā sālalaṭṭhiyo kuṭilā ojāpaharaṇiyo tā chetvā bahiddhā nīhareyya, antovanaṃ suvisodhitaṃ visodheyya.**They’d cut down the crooked sal saplings that were robbing the sap, and throw them out. They’d clean up the interior of the grove,*";
P_HTM[3377]="*Yā pana tā sālalaṭṭhiyo ujukā sujātā tā sammā parihareyya.**and properly care for the straight, well-formed sal saplings.*";
P_HTM[3378]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, sālavanaṃ aparena samayena vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyya.**In this way, in due course, that sal grove would grow, increase, and mature.*";
P_HTM[3379]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, tumhepi akusalaṃ pajahatha, kusalesu dhammesu āyogaṃ karotha.**In the same way, mendicants, give up what’s unskillful and devote yourselves to skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3380]="*Evañhi tumhepi imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatha.**In this way you’ll achieve growth, improvement, and maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[3381]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imissāyeva sāvatthiyā vedehikā nāma gahapatānī ahosi.**Once upon a time, mendicants, right here in Sāvatthī there was a housewife named Vedehikā.*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Vedehikāya, bhikkhave, gahapatāniyā evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**She had this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[3383]="*‘soratā vedehikā gahapatānī, nivātā vedehikā gahapatānī, upasantā vedehikā gahapatānī’ti.**‘The housewife Vedehikā is sweet, even-tempered, and calm.’*";
P_HTM[3384]="*Vedehikāya kho pana, bhikkhave, gahapatāniyā kāḷī nāma dāsī ahosi dakkhā analasā susaṃvihitakammantā.**Now, Vedehikā had a bonded maid named Kāḷī who was skilled, tireless, and well-organized in her work.*";
P_HTM[3385]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷiyā dāsiyā etadahosi:**Then Kāḷī thought,*";
P_HTM[3386]="*‘mayhaṃ kho ayyāya evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**‘My mistress has a good reputation as being*";
P_HTM[3387]="*“soratā vedehikā gahapatānī, nivātā vedehikā gahapatānī, upasantā vedehikā gahapatānī”ti.**sweet, even-tempered, and calm.*";
P_HTM[3388]="*Kiṃ nu kho me ayyā santaṃyeva nu kho ajjhattaṃ kopaṃ na pātukaroti udāhu asantaṃ**But does she actually have anger in her and just not show it? Or does she have no anger?*";
P_HTM[3389]="*udāhu mayhamevete kammantā susaṃvihitā yena me ayyā santaṃyeva ajjhattaṃ kopaṃ na pātukaroti, no asantaṃ?**Or is it just because my work is well-organized that she doesn’t show anger, even though she still has it inside?*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Yannūnāhaṃ ayyaṃ vīmaṃseyyan’ti.**Why don’t I test my mistress?’*";
P_HTM[3391]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷī dāsī divā uṭṭhāsi.**So Kāḷī got up during the day.*";
P_HTM[3392]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, vedehikā gahapatānī kāḷiṃ dāsiṃ etadavoca:**Vedehikā said to her,*";
P_HTM[3393]="*‘he je kāḷī’ti.**‘What the hell, Kāḷī!’*";
P_HTM[3394]="*‘Kiṃ, ayye’ti?**‘What is it, madam?’*";
P_HTM[3395]="*‘Kiṃ, je, divā uṭṭhāsī’ti?**‘You’re getting up in the day—what’s up with you, girl?’*";
P_HTM[3396]="*‘Na khvayye, kiñcī’ti.**‘Nothing, madam.’*";
P_HTM[3397]="*‘No vata re kiñci, pāpi dāsi, divā uṭṭhāsī’ti kupitā anattamanā bhākuṭiṃ akāsi.**‘Nothing’s up, you bad girl, but you get up in the day!’ Angry and upset, she scowled.*";
P_HTM[3398]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷiyā dāsiyā etadahosi:**Then Kāḷī thought,*";
P_HTM[3399]="*‘santaṃyeva kho me ayyā ajjhattaṃ kopaṃ na pātukaroti, no asantaṃ;**‘My mistress actually has anger in her and just doesn’t show it; it’s not that she has no anger.*";
P_HTM[3400]="*mayhamevete kammantā susaṃvihitā, yena me ayyā santaṃyeva ajjhattaṃ kopaṃ na pātukaroti, no asantaṃ.**It’s just because my work is well-organized that she doesn’t show anger, even though she still has it inside.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Yannūnāhaṃ bhiyyoso mattāya ayyaṃ vīmaṃseyyan’ti.**Why don’t I test my mistress further?’*";
P_HTM[3402]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷī dāsī divātaraṃyeva uṭṭhāsi.**So Kāḷī got up later in the day.*";
P_HTM[3403]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, vedehikā gahapatānī kāḷiṃ dāsiṃ etadavoca:**Vedehikā said to her,*";
P_HTM[3404]="*‘he je kāḷī’ti.**‘What the hell, Kāḷī!’*";
P_HTM[3405]="*‘Kiṃ, ayye’ti?**‘What is it, madam?’*";
P_HTM[3406]="*‘Kiṃ, je, divātaraṃ uṭṭhāsī’ti?**‘You’re getting up later in the day—what’s up with you, girl?’*";
P_HTM[3407]="*‘Na khvayye, kiñcī’ti.**‘Nothing, madam.’*";
P_HTM[3408]="*‘No vata re kiñci, pāpi dāsi, divātaraṃ uṭṭhāsī’ti kupitā anattamanā anattamanavācaṃ nicchāresi.**‘Nothing’s up, you bad girl, but you get up later in the day!’ Angry and upset, she blurted out angry words.*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷiyā dāsiyā etadahosi:**Then Kāḷī thought,*";
P_HTM[3410]="*‘santaṃyeva kho me ayyā ajjhattaṃ kopaṃ na pātukaroti, no asantaṃ.**‘My mistress actually has anger in her and just doesn’t show it; it’s not that she has no anger.*";
P_HTM[3411]="*Mayhamevete kammantā susaṃvihitā, yena me ayyā santaṃyeva ajjhattaṃ kopaṃ na pātukaroti, no asantaṃ.**It’s just because my work is well-organized that she doesn’t show anger, even though she still has it inside.*";
P_HTM[3412]="*Yannūnāhaṃ bhiyyoso mattāya ayyaṃ vīmaṃseyyan’ti.**Why don’t I test my mistress further?’*";
P_HTM[3413]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷī dāsī divātaraṃyeva uṭṭhāsi.**So Kāḷī got up even later in the day.*";
P_HTM[3414]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, vedehikā gahapatānī kāḷiṃ dāsiṃ etadavoca:**Vedehikā said to her,*";
P_HTM[3415]="*‘he je kāḷī’ti.**‘What the hell, Kāḷī!’*";
P_HTM[3416]="*‘Kiṃ, ayye’ti?**‘What is it, madam?’*";
P_HTM[3417]="*‘Kiṃ, je, divā uṭṭhāsī’ti?**‘You’re getting up even later in the day—what’s up with you, girl?’*";
P_HTM[3418]="*‘Na khvayye, kiñcī’ti.**‘Nothing, madam.’*";
P_HTM[3419]="*‘No vata re kiñci, pāpi dāsi, divā uṭṭhāsī’ti kupitā anattamanā aggaḷasūciṃ gahetvā sīse pahāraṃ adāsi, sīsaṃ vobhindi.**‘Nothing’s up, you bad girl, but you get up even later in the day!’ Angry and upset, she grabbed a rolling-pin and hit Kāḷī on the head, cracking it open.*";
P_HTM[3420]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, kāḷī dāsī bhinnena sīsena lohitena galantena paṭivissakānaṃ ujjhāpesi:**Then Kāḷī, with blood pouring from her cracked skull, denounced her mistress to the neighbors,*";
P_HTM[3421]="*‘passathayye, soratāya kammaṃ;**‘See, ladies, what the sweet one did!*";
P_HTM[3422]="*passathayye, nivātāya kammaṃ, passathayye, upasantāya kammaṃ.**See what the even-tempered one did! See what the calm one did!*";
P_HTM[3423]="*Kathañhi nāma ekadāsikāya divā uṭṭhāsīti kupitā anattamanā aggaḷasūciṃ gahetvā sīse pahāraṃ dassati, sīsaṃ vobhindissatī’ti.**How on earth can she grab a rolling-pin and hit her only maid on the head, cracking it open, just for getting up late?’*";
P_HTM[3424]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, vedehikāya gahapatāniyā aparena samayena evaṃ pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchi:**Then after some time the housewife Vedehikā got this bad reputation:*";
P_HTM[3425]="*‘caṇḍī vedehikā gahapatānī, anivātā vedehikā gahapatānī, anupasantā vedehikā gahapatānī’ti.**‘The housewife Vedehikā is fierce, ill-tempered, and not calm at all.’*";
P_HTM[3426]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu tāvadeva soratasorato hoti nivātanivāto hoti upasantūpasanto hoti yāva na amanāpā vacanapathā phusanti.**In the same way, a mendicant may be the sweetest of the sweet, the most even-tempered of the even-tempered, the calmest of the calm, so long as they don’t encounter any disagreeable criticism.*";
P_HTM[3427]="*Yato ca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ amanāpā vacanapathā phusanti, atha bhikkhu ‘sorato’ti veditabbo, ‘nivāto’ti veditabbo, ‘upasanto’ti veditabbo.**But it’s when they encounter disagreeable criticism that you’ll know whether they’re really sweet, even-tempered, and calm.*";
P_HTM[3428]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ ‘suvaco’ti vadāmi yo cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu suvaco hoti, sovacassataṃ āpajjati.**I don’t say that a mendicant is easy to admonish if they make themselves easy to admonish only for the sake of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[3429]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3430]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ alabhamāno na suvaco hoti, na sovacassataṃ āpajjati.**Because when they don’t get robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick, they’re no longer easy to admonish.*";
P_HTM[3431]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammaṃyeva sakkaronto, dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto, dhammaṃ mānento, dhammaṃ pūjento, dhammaṃ apacāyamāno suvaco hoti, sovacassataṃ āpajjati, tamahaṃ ‘suvaco’ti vadāmi.**But when a mendicant is easy to admonish purely because they honor, respect, revere, worship, and venerate the teaching, then I say that they’re easy to admonish.*";
P_HTM[3432]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘dhammaṃyeva sakkarontā, dhammaṃ garuṃ karontā, dhammaṃ mānentā, dhammaṃ pūjentā, dhammaṃ apacāyamānā suvacā bhavissāma, sovacassataṃ āpajjissāmā’ti.**So, mendicants, you should train yourselves: ‘We will be easy to admonish purely because we honor, respect, revere, worship, and venerate the teaching.’*";
P_HTM[3433]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3434]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, vacanapathā yehi vo pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ—**Mendicants, there are these five ways in which others might criticize you.*";
P_HTM[3435]="*kālena vā akālena vā;**Their speech may be timely or untimely,*";
P_HTM[3436]="*bhūtena vā abhūtena vā;**true or false,*";
P_HTM[3437]="*saṇhena vā pharusena vā;**gentle or harsh,*";
P_HTM[3438]="*atthasaṃhitena vā anatthasaṃhitena vā;**beneficial or harmful,*";
P_HTM[3439]="*mettacittā vā dosantarā vā.**from a heart of love or from secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Kālena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ akālena vā;**When others criticize you, they may do so in any of these ways.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*bhūtena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ abhūtena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3442]="*saṇhena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ pharusena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3443]="*atthasaṃhitena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ anatthasaṃhitena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3444]="*mettacittā vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ dosantarā vā.* **";
P_HTM[3445]="*Tatrāpi vo, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**If that happens, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3446]="*‘na ceva no cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāma, hitānukampī ca viharissāma mettacittā, na dosantarā.**‘Our minds will remain unaffected. We will blurt out no bad words. We will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3447]="*Tañca puggalaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā pharitvā viharissāma, tadārammaṇañca sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cittena vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharissāmā’ti.**We will meditate spreading a heart of love to that person. And with them as a basis, we will meditate spreading a heart full of love to everyone in the world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.’*";
P_HTM[3448]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3449]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso āgaccheyya kudālapiṭakaṃ ādāya.**Suppose a person was to come along carrying a spade and basket*";
P_HTM[3450]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**and say,*";
P_HTM[3451]="*‘ahaṃ imaṃ mahāpathaviṃ apathaviṃ karissāmī’ti.**‘I shall make this great earth be without earth!’*";
P_HTM[3452]="*So tatra tatra vikhaṇeyya, tatra tatra vikireyya, tatra tatra oṭṭhubheyya, tatra tatra omutteyya:**And they’d dig all over, scatter all over, spit all over, and urinate all over, saying,*";
P_HTM[3453]="*‘apathavī bhavasi, apathavī bhavasī’ti.**‘Be without earth! Be without earth!’*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3455]="*api nu so puriso imaṃ mahāpathaviṃ apathaviṃ kareyyā”ti?**Could that person make this great earth be without earth?”*";
P_HTM[3456]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3457]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3458]="*“Ayañhi, bhante, mahāpathavī gambhīrā appameyyā.**Because this great earth is deep and limitless.*";
P_HTM[3459]="*Sā na sukarā apathavī kātuṃ;**It’s not easy to make it be without earth.*";
P_HTM[3460]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[3461]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, pañcime vacanapathā yehi vo pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ—**“In the same way, there are these five ways in which others might criticize you.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*kālena vā akālena vā;**Their speech may be timely or untimely,*";
P_HTM[3463]="*bhūtena vā abhūtena vā;**true or false,*";
P_HTM[3464]="*saṇhena vā pharusena vā;**gentle or harsh,*";
P_HTM[3465]="*atthasaṃhitena vā anatthasaṃhitena vā;**beneficial or harmful,*";
P_HTM[3466]="*mettacittā vā dosantarā vā.**from a heart of love or from secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3467]="*Kālena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ akālena vā;**When others criticize you, they may do so in any of these ways.*";
P_HTM[3468]="*bhūtena vā bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ abhūtena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3469]="*saṇhena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ pharusena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3470]="*atthasaṃhitena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ anatthasaṃhitena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3471]="*mettacittā vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ dosantarā vā.* **";
P_HTM[3472]="*Tatrāpi vo, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**If that happens, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3473]="*‘na ceva no cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāma, hitānukampī ca viharissāma mettacittā na dosantarā.**‘Our minds will remain unaffected. We will blurt out no bad words. We will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3474]="*Tañca puggalaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā pharitvā viharissāma, tadārammaṇañca sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ pathavisamena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharissāmā’ti.**We will meditate spreading a heart of love to that person. And with them as a basis, we will meditate spreading a heart like the earth to everyone in the world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.’*";
P_HTM[3475]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3476]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso āgaccheyya lākhaṃ vā haliddiṃ vā nīlaṃ vā mañjiṭṭhaṃ vā ādāya.**Suppose a person was to come along with dye such as red lac, turmeric, indigo, or rose madder,*";
P_HTM[3477]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**and say,*";
P_HTM[3478]="*‘ahaṃ imasmiṃ ākāse rūpaṃ likhissāmi, rūpapātubhāvaṃ karissāmī’ti.**‘I shall draw pictures on the sky, making pictures appear there.’*";
P_HTM[3479]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3480]="*api nu so puriso imasmiṃ ākāse rūpaṃ likheyya, rūpapātubhāvaṃ kareyyā”ti?**Could that person draw pictures on the sky?”*";
P_HTM[3481]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3482]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3483]="*“Ayañhi, bhante, ākāso arūpī anidassano.**Because the sky is formless and invisible.*";
P_HTM[3484]="*Tattha na sukaraṃ rūpaṃ likhituṃ, rūpapātubhāvaṃ kātuṃ;**It’s not easy to draw pictures there.*";
P_HTM[3485]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[3486]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, pañcime vacanapathā yehi vo pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ kālena vā akālena vā … pe …**“In the same way, there are these five ways in which others might criticize you …*";
P_HTM[3487]="*tadārammaṇañca sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ ākāsasamena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharissāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3488]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3489]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso āgaccheyya ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ ādāya.**Suppose a person was to come along carrying a blazing grass torch,*";
P_HTM[3490]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**and say,*";
P_HTM[3491]="*‘ahaṃ imāya ādittāya tiṇukkāya gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ santāpessāmi samparitāpessāmī’ti.**‘I shall burn and scorch the river Ganges with this blazing grass torch.’*";
P_HTM[3492]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3493]="*api nu so puriso ādittāya tiṇukkāya gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ santāpeyya samparitāpeyyā”ti?**Could that person burn and scorch the river Ganges with a blazing grass torch?”*";
P_HTM[3494]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3495]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3496]="*“Gaṅgā hi, bhante, nadī gambhīrā appameyyā.**Because the river Ganges is deep and limitless.*";
P_HTM[3497]="*Sā na sukarā ādittāya tiṇukkāya santāpetuṃ samparitāpetuṃ;**It’s not easy to burn and scorch it with a blazing grass torch.*";
P_HTM[3498]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[3499]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, pañcime vacanapathā yehi vo pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ kālena vā akālena vā … pe …**“In the same way, there are these five ways in which others might criticize you …*";
P_HTM[3500]="*tadārammaṇañca sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ gaṅgāsamena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharissāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3501]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3502]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, biḷārabhastā madditā sumadditā suparimadditā, mudukā tūlinī chinnasassarā chinnabhabbharā.**Suppose there was a catskin bag that was rubbed, well-rubbed, very well-rubbed, soft, silky, rid of rustling and crackling.*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya kaṭṭhaṃ vā kathalaṃ vā ādāya.**Then a person comes along carrying a stick or a stone,*";
P_HTM[3504]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**and says,*";
P_HTM[3505]="*‘ahaṃ imaṃ biḷārabhastaṃ madditaṃ sumadditaṃ suparimadditaṃ, mudukaṃ tūliniṃ, chinnasassaraṃ chinnabhabbharaṃ kaṭṭhena vā kathalena vā sarasaraṃ karissāmi bharabharaṃ karissāmī’ti.**‘I shall make this soft catskin bag rustle and crackle with this stick or stone.’*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3507]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ biḷārabhastaṃ madditaṃ sumadditaṃ suparimadditaṃ, mudukaṃ tūliniṃ, chinnasassaraṃ chinnabhabbharaṃ kaṭṭhena vā kathalena vā sarasaraṃ kareyya, bharabharaṃ kareyyā”ti?**Could that person make that soft catskin bag rustle and crackle with that stick or stone?”*";
P_HTM[3508]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3509]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3510]="*“Amu hi, bhante, biḷārabhastā madditā sumadditā suparimadditā, mudukā tūlinī, chinnasassarā chinnabhabbharā.**Because that catskin bag is rubbed, well-rubbed, very well-rubbed, soft, silky, rid of rustling and crackling.*";
P_HTM[3511]="*Sā na sukarā kaṭṭhena vā kathalena vā sarasaraṃ kātuṃ bharabharaṃ kātuṃ;**It’s not easy to make it rustle or crackle with a stick or stone.*";
P_HTM[3512]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[3513]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, pañcime vacanapathā yehi vo pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ**“In the same way, there are these five ways in which others might criticize you.*";
P_HTM[3514]="*kālena vā akālena vā;**Their speech may be timely or untimely,*";
P_HTM[3515]="*bhūtena vā abhūtena vā;**true or false,*";
P_HTM[3516]="*saṇhena vā pharusena vā;**gentle or harsh,*";
P_HTM[3517]="*atthasaṃhitena vā anatthasaṃhitena vā;**beneficial or harmful,*";
P_HTM[3518]="*mettacittā vā dosantarā vā.**from a heart of love or from secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3519]="*Kālena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ akālena vā;**When others criticize you, they may do so in any of these ways.*";
P_HTM[3520]="*bhūtena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ abhūtena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3521]="*saṇhena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ pharusena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3522]="*atthasaṃhitena vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ anatthasaṃhitena vā;* **";
P_HTM[3523]="*mettacittā vā, bhikkhave, pare vadamānā vadeyyuṃ dosantarā vā.* **";
P_HTM[3524]="*Tatrāpi vo, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**If that happens, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3525]="*‘na ceva no cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāma hitānukampī ca viharissāma mettacittā na dosantarā.**‘Our minds will remain unaffected. We will blurt out no bad words. We will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3526]="*Tañca puggalaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā pharitvā viharissāma, tadārammaṇañca sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ biḷārabhastāsamena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharissāmā’ti.**We will meditate spreading a heart of love to that person. And with them as a basis, we will meditate spreading a heart like a catskin bag to everyone in the world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.’*";
P_HTM[3527]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3528]="*Ubhatodaṇḍakena cepi, bhikkhave, kakacena corā ocarakā aṅgamaṅgāni okanteyyuṃ, tatrāpi yo mano padūseyya, na me so tena sāsanakaro.**Even if low-down bandits were to sever you limb from limb, anyone who had a malevolent thought on that account would not be following my instructions.*";
P_HTM[3529]="*Tatrāpi vo, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**If that happens, you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[3530]="*‘na ceva no cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ bhavissati, na ca pāpikaṃ vācaṃ nicchāressāma, hitānukampī ca viharissāma mettacittā na dosantarā.**‘Our minds will remain unaffected. We will blurt out no bad words. We will remain full of compassion, with a heart of love and no secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3531]="*Tañca puggalaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā pharitvā viharissāma tadārammaṇañca sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharissāmā’ti.**We will meditate spreading a heart of love to that person. And with them as a basis, we will meditate spreading a heart full of love to everyone in the world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.’*";
P_HTM[3532]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[3533]="*Imañca tumhe, bhikkhave, kakacūpamaṃ ovādaṃ abhikkhaṇaṃ manasi kareyyātha.**If you frequently reflect on this advice—the simile of the saw—*";
P_HTM[3534]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, taṃ vacanapathaṃ, aṇuṃ vā thūlaṃ vā, yaṃ tumhe nādhivāseyyāthā”ti?**do you see any criticism, large or small, that you could not endure?”*";
P_HTM[3535]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3536]="*“Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, imaṃ kakacūpamaṃ ovādaṃ abhikkhaṇaṃ manasikarotha.**“So, mendicants, you should frequently reflect on this advice, the simile of the saw.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*Taṃ vo bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**This will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[3538]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3539]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3540]="*Kakacūpamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3541]="*22. Alagaddūpamasutta**The Simile of the Snake*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3543]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Tena kho pana samayena ariṭṭhassa nāma bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti:**Now at that time a mendicant called Ariṭtha, who had previously been a vulture trapper, had the following harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[3545]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, the acts that he says are obstructions are not really obstructions for the one who performs them.”*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Assosuṃ kho sambahulā bhikkhū:**Several mendicants heard about this.*";
P_HTM[3547]="*“ariṭṭhassa kira nāma bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[3548]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3549]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etadavocuṃ:**They went up to Ariṭṭha and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3550]="*“saccaṃ kira te, āvuso ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:**“Is it really true, Reverend Ariṭṭha, that you have such a harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[3551]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.**‘As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, the acts that he says are obstructions are not really obstructions for the one who performs them’?”*";
P_HTM[3552]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“Absolutely, reverends. As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, the acts that he says are obstructions are not really obstructions for the one who performs them.”*";
P_HTM[3553]="*Atha kho tepi bhikkhū ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetukāmā samanuyuñjanti samanugāhanti samanubhāsanti:**Then, wishing to dissuade Ariṭṭha from his view, the mendicants pursued, pressed, and grilled him,*";
P_HTM[3554]="*“mā hevaṃ, āvuso ariṭṭha, avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi; na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**“Don’t say that, Ariṭṭha! Don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for misrepresentation of the Buddha is not good. And the Buddha would not say that.*";
P_HTM[3555]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso ariṭṭha, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā, alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**In many ways the Buddha has said that obstructive acts are obstructive, and that they really do obstruct the one who performs them.*";
P_HTM[3556]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**The Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[3557]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**With the similes of a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[3558]="*maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**a lump of meat …*";
P_HTM[3559]="*tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**a grass torch …*";
P_HTM[3560]="*aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**a pit of glowing coals …*";
P_HTM[3561]="*supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**a dream …*";
P_HTM[3562]="*yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**borrowed goods …*";
P_HTM[3563]="*rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**fruit on a tree …*";
P_HTM[3564]="*asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**a butcher’s knife and chopping block …*";
P_HTM[3565]="*sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**a staking sword …*";
P_HTM[3566]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo”ti.**a snake’s head, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.”*";
P_HTM[3567]="*Evampi kho ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tehi bhikkhūhi samanuyuñjiyamāno samanugāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno tadeva pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati:**But even though the mendicants pursued, pressed, and grilled him in this way, Ariṭṭha obstinately stuck to his misconception and insisted on stating it.*";
P_HTM[3568]="*“evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3569]="*Yato kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When they weren’t able to dissuade Ariṭṭha from his view, the mendicants went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[3570]="*“ariṭṭhassa nāma, bhante, bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[3571]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3572]="*Assumha kho mayaṃ, bhante:* **";
P_HTM[3573]="*‘ariṭṭhassa kira nāma bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[3574]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3575]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yena ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etadavocumha:* **";
P_HTM[3576]="*‘saccaṃ kira te, āvuso ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[3577]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[3578]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo amhe etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[3579]="*‘evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3580]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetukāmā samanuyuñjimha samanugāhimha samanubhāsimha:* **";
P_HTM[3581]="*‘mā hevaṃ, āvuso ariṭṭha, avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi; na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[3582]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso ariṭṭha, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā, alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.* **";
P_HTM[3583]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[3584]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3585]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3586]="*Evampi kho, bhante, ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo amhehi samanuyuñjiyamāno samanugāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno tadeva pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati:* **";
P_HTM[3587]="*‘evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3588]="*Yato kho mayaṃ, bhante, nāsakkhimha ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha mayaṃ etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocemā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3589]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[3590]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell the mendicant Ariṭṭha, formerly a vulture trapper, that*";
P_HTM[3591]="*‘satthā taṃ, āvuso ariṭṭha, āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons him.”*";
P_HTM[3592]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā, yena ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Ariṭṭha and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3593]="*“satthā taṃ, āvuso ariṭṭha, āmantetī”ti.**“Reverend Ariṭṭha, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[3594]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” Ariṭṭha replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[3595]="*“saccaṃ kira te, ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:**“Is it really true, Ariṭṭha, that you have such a harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[3596]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti?**‘As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, the acts that he says are obstructions are not really obstructions for the one who performs them’?”*";
P_HTM[3597]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi: ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.**“Absolutely, sir. As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, the acts that he says are obstructions are not really obstructions for the one who performs them.”*";
P_HTM[3598]="*“Kassa kho nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mayā evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi?**“Silly man, who on earth have you ever known me to teach in that way?*";
P_HTM[3599]="*Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, anekapariyāyena antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā? Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**Haven’t I said in many ways that obstructive acts are obstructive, and that they really do obstruct the one who performs them?*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**I’ve said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[3601]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**With the similes of a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[3602]="*maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**a lump of meat …*";
P_HTM[3603]="*tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**a grass torch …*";
P_HTM[3604]="*aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**a pit of glowing coals …*";
P_HTM[3605]="*supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**a dream …*";
P_HTM[3606]="*yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**borrowed goods …*";
P_HTM[3607]="*rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**fruit on a tree …*";
P_HTM[3608]="*asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**a butcher’s knife and chopping block …*";
P_HTM[3609]="*sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**a staking sword …*";
P_HTM[3610]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**a snake’s head, I’ve said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[3611]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, moghapurisa, attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhasi, attānañca khanasi, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavasi.**But still you misrepresent me by your wrong grasp, harm yourself, and make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[3612]="*Tañhi te, moghapurisa, bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**This will be for your lasting harm and suffering.”*";
P_HTM[3613]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3614]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3615]="*api nāyaṃ ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo usmīkatopi imasmiṃ dhammavinaye”ti?**Has this mendicant Ariṭṭha kindled even a spark of wisdom in this teaching and training?”*";
P_HTM[3616]="*“Kiñhi siyā, bhante;**“How could that be, sir?*";
P_HTM[3617]="*no hetaṃ, bhante”ti.**No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3618]="*Evaṃ vutte, ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi.**When this was said, Ariṭṭha sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[3619]="*Atha kho bhagavā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etadavoca:**Knowing this, the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[3620]="*“paññāyissasi kho tvaṃ, moghapurisa, etena sakena pāpakena diṭṭhigatena.**“Silly man, you will be known by your own harmful misconception.*";
P_HTM[3621]="*Idhāhaṃ bhikkhū paṭipucchissāmī”ti.**I’ll question the mendicants about this.”*";
P_HTM[3622]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3623]="*“tumhepi me, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha yathāyaṃ ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhati, attānañca khanati, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatī”ti?**“Mendicants, do you understand my teachings as Ariṭṭha does, when he misrepresents me by his wrong grasp, harms himself, and makes much bad karma?”*";
P_HTM[3624]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Anekapariyāyena hi no, bhante, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā;**For in many ways the Buddha has said that obstructive acts are obstructive, and that they really do obstruct the one who performs them.*";
P_HTM[3626]="*alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.* **";
P_HTM[3627]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**The Buddha has said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[3628]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … pe …**With the similes of a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[3629]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo”ti.**a snake’s head, the Buddha has said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.”*";
P_HTM[3630]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, sādhu, kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha.**“Good, good, mendicants! It’s good that you understand my teaching like this.*";
P_HTM[3631]="*Anekapariyāyena hi kho, bhikkhave, antarāyikā dhammā vuttā mayā, alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**For in many ways I have said that obstructive acts are obstructive …*";
P_HTM[3632]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[3633]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3634]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**I’ve said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[3635]="*Atha ca panāyaṃ ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhati, attānañca khanati, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**But still this Ariṭṭha misrepresents me by his wrong grasp, harms himself, and makes much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[3636]="*Tañhi tassa moghapurisassa bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for his lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[3637]="*So vata, bhikkhave, aññatreva kāmehi aññatra kāmasaññāya aññatra kāmavitakkehi kāme paṭisevissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**Truly, mendicants, it’s not possible to perform sensual acts without sensual pleasures, sensual perceptions, and sensual thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3638]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacce moghapurisā dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti—**Take a foolish person who memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[3639]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[3640]="*Te taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā tesaṃ dhammānaṃ paññāya atthaṃ na upaparikkhanti.**But they don’t examine the meaning of those teachings with wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3641]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā paññāya atthaṃ anupaparikkhataṃ na nijjhānaṃ khamanti.**and so don’t come to a reflective acceptance of them.*";
P_HTM[3642]="*Te upārambhānisaṃsā ceva dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti itivādappamokkhānisaṃsā ca.**They just memorize the teaching for the sake of finding fault and winning debates.*";
P_HTM[3643]="*Yassa catthāya dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhonti.**They don’t realize the goal for which they memorized them.*";
P_HTM[3644]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā duggahitā dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti.**Because they’re wrongly grasped, those teachings lead to their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[3645]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3646]="*Duggahitattā, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ.**Because of their wrong grasp of the teachings.*";
P_HTM[3647]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso alagaddatthiko alagaddagavesī alagaddapariyesanaṃ caramāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of a snake. And while wandering in search of a snake*";
P_HTM[3648]="*So passeyya mahantaṃ alagaddaṃ.**they’d see a big snake,*";
P_HTM[3649]="*Tamenaṃ bhoge vā naṅguṭṭhe vā gaṇheyya.**and grasp it by the coil or the tail.*";
P_HTM[3650]="*Tassa so alagaddo paṭiparivattitvā hatthe vā bāhāya vā aññatarasmiṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅge ḍaṃseyya.**But that snake would twist back and bite them on the hand or the arm or limb,*";
P_HTM[3651]="*So tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[3652]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3653]="*Duggahitattā, bhikkhave, alagaddassa.**Because of their wrong grasp of the snake.*";
P_HTM[3654]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacce moghapurisā dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti—**In the same way, a foolish person memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[3655]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3656]="*Te taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā tesaṃ dhammānaṃ paññāya atthaṃ na upaparikkhanti.* **";
P_HTM[3657]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā paññāya atthaṃ anupaparikkhataṃ na nijjhānaṃ khamanti.* **";
P_HTM[3658]="*Te upārambhānisaṃsā ceva dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti itivādappamokkhānisaṃsā ca.* **";
P_HTM[3659]="*Yassa catthāya dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhonti.* **";
P_HTM[3660]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā duggahitā dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti.**and those teachings lead to their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[3661]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3662]="*Duggahitattā, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ.**Because of their wrong grasp of the teachings.*";
P_HTM[3663]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacce kulaputtā dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti—**Now, take a gentleman who memorizes the teaching—*";
P_HTM[3664]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[3665]="*Te taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā tesaṃ dhammānaṃ paññāya atthaṃ upaparikkhanti.**And once they’ve memorized them, they examine their meaning with wisdom,*";
P_HTM[3666]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā paññāya atthaṃ upaparikkhataṃ nijjhānaṃ khamanti.**and come to a reflective acceptance of them.*";
P_HTM[3667]="*Te na ceva upārambhānisaṃsā dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti na itivādappamokkhānisaṃsā ca.**They don’t memorize the teaching for the sake of finding fault and winning debates.*";
P_HTM[3668]="*Yassa catthāya dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti tañcassa atthaṃ anubhonti.**They realize the goal for which they memorized them.*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā suggahitā dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti.**Because they’re correctly grasped, those teachings lead to their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3670]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3671]="*Suggahitattā bhikkhave dhammānaṃ.**Because of their correct grasp of the teachings.*";
P_HTM[3672]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso alagaddatthiko alagaddagavesī alagaddapariyesanaṃ caramāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of a snake. And while wandering in search of a snake*";
P_HTM[3673]="*So passeyya mahantaṃ alagaddaṃ.**they’d see a big snake,*";
P_HTM[3674]="*Tamenaṃ ajapadena daṇḍena suniggahitaṃ niggaṇheyya.**and hold it down carefully with a cleft stick.*";
P_HTM[3675]="*Ajapadena daṇḍena suniggahitaṃ niggahitvā, gīvāya suggahitaṃ gaṇheyya.**Only then would they correctly grasp it by the neck.*";
P_HTM[3676]="*Kiñcāpi so, bhikkhave, alagaddo tassa purisassa hatthaṃ vā bāhaṃ vā aññataraṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ bhogehi paliveṭheyya, atha kho so neva tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**And even though that snake might wrap its coils around that person’s hand or arm or some other limb, that wouldn’t result in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[3677]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3678]="*Suggahitattā, bhikkhave, alagaddassa.**Because of their correct grasp of the snake.*";
P_HTM[3679]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacce kulaputtā dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti—**In the same way, a gentleman memorizes the teaching …*";
P_HTM[3680]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3681]="*Te taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā tesaṃ dhammānaṃ paññāya atthaṃ upaparikkhanti.* **";
P_HTM[3682]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā paññāya atthaṃ upaparikkhataṃ nijjhānaṃ khamanti.* **";
P_HTM[3683]="*Te na ceva upārambhānisaṃsā dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti, na itivādappamokkhānisaṃsā ca.* **";
P_HTM[3684]="*Yassa catthāya dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti, tañcassa atthaṃ anubhonti.* **";
P_HTM[3685]="*Tesaṃ te dhammā suggahitā dīgharattaṃ atthāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti.**and those teachings lead to their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3687]="*Suggahitattā, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ.**Because of their correct grasp of the teachings.*";
P_HTM[3688]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yassa me bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājāneyyātha, tathā naṃ dhāreyyātha.**So, mendicants, when you understand what I’ve said, you should remember it accordingly.*";
P_HTM[3689]="*Yassa ca pana me bhāsitassa atthaṃ na ājāneyyātha, ahaṃ vo tattha paṭipucchitabbo, ye vā panāssu viyattā bhikkhū.**But if I’ve said anything that you don’t understand, you should ask me about it, or some competent mendicants.*";
P_HTM[3690]="*Kullūpamaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi nittharaṇatthāya, no gahaṇatthāya.**Mendicants, I will teach you how the Dhamma is similar to a raft: it’s for crossing over, not for holding on.*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[3692]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3693]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3694]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso addhānamaggappaṭipanno.**“Suppose there was a person traveling along the road.*";
P_HTM[3695]="*So passeyya mahantaṃ udakaṇṇavaṃ, orimaṃ tīraṃ sāsaṅkaṃ sappaṭibhayaṃ, pārimaṃ tīraṃ khemaṃ appaṭibhayaṃ;**They’d see a large deluge, whose near shore was dubious and perilous, while the far shore was a sanctuary free of peril.*";
P_HTM[3696]="*na cassa nāvā santāraṇī uttarasetu vā apārā pāraṃ gamanāya.**But there was no ferryboat or bridge for crossing over.*";
P_HTM[3697]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think,*";
P_HTM[3698]="*‘ayaṃ kho mahāudakaṇṇavo, orimaṃ tīraṃ sāsaṅkaṃ sappaṭibhayaṃ, pārimaṃ tīraṃ khemaṃ appaṭibhayaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3699]="*natthi ca nāvā santāraṇī uttarasetu vā apārā pāraṃ gamanāya.* **";
P_HTM[3700]="*Yannūnāhaṃ tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ saṅkaḍḍhitvā, kullaṃ bandhitvā, taṃ kullaṃ nissāya hatthehi ca pādehi ca vāyamamāno sotthinā pāraṃ uttareyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I gather grass, sticks, branches, and leaves and make a raft? Riding on the raft, and paddling with my hands and feet, I can safely reach the far shore.’*";
P_HTM[3701]="*Atha kho so, bhikkhave, puriso tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ saṅkaḍḍhitvā, kullaṃ bandhitvā taṃ kullaṃ nissāya hatthehi ca pādehi ca vāyamamāno sotthinā pāraṃ uttareyya.**And so they’d do exactly that.*";
P_HTM[3702]="*Tassa purisassa uttiṇṇassa pāraṅgatassa evamassa:**And when they’d crossed over to the far shore, they’d think,*";
P_HTM[3703]="*‘bahukāro kho me ayaṃ kullo;**‘This raft has been very helpful to me.*";
P_HTM[3704]="*imāhaṃ kullaṃ nissāya hatthehi ca pādehi ca vāyamamāno sotthinā pāraṃ uttiṇṇo.**Riding on the raft, and paddling with my hands and feet, I have safely crossed over to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[3705]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ kullaṃ sīse vā āropetvā khandhe vā uccāretvā yena kāmaṃ pakkameyyan’ti.**Why don’t I hoist it on my head or pick it up on my shoulder and go wherever I want?’*";
P_HTM[3706]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3707]="*api nu so puriso evaṃkārī tasmiṃ kulle kiccakārī assā”ti?**Would that person be doing what should be done with that raft?”*";
P_HTM[3708]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3709]="*“Kathaṃkārī ca so, bhikkhave, puriso tasmiṃ kulle kiccakārī assa?**“And what, mendicants, should that person do with the raft?*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa uttiṇṇassa pāraṅgatassa evamassa:**When they’d crossed over they should think,*";
P_HTM[3711]="*‘bahukāro kho me ayaṃ kullo;**‘This raft has been very helpful to me. …*";
P_HTM[3712]="*imāhaṃ kullaṃ nissāya hatthehi ca pādehi ca vāyamamāno sotthinā pāraṃ uttiṇṇo.* **";
P_HTM[3713]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ kullaṃ thale vā ussādetvā udake vā opilāpetvā yena kāmaṃ pakkameyyan’ti.**Why don’t I beach it on dry land or set it adrift on the water and go wherever I want?’*";
P_HTM[3714]="*Evaṃkārī kho so, bhikkhave, puriso tasmiṃ kulle kiccakārī assa.**That’s what that person should do with the raft.*";
P_HTM[3715]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, kullūpamo mayā dhammo desito nittharaṇatthāya, no gahaṇatthāya.**In the same way, I have taught how the teaching is similar to a raft: it’s for crossing over, not for holding on.*";
P_HTM[3716]="*Kullūpamaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desitaṃ, ājānantehi dhammāpi vo pahātabbā pageva adhammā.**By understanding the simile of the raft, you will even give up the teachings, let alone what is against the teachings.*";
P_HTM[3717]="*Chayimāni, bhikkhave, diṭṭhiṭṭhānāni.**Mendicants, there are these six grounds for views.*";
P_HTM[3718]="*Katamāni cha?**What six?*";
P_HTM[3719]="*Idha, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto,**Take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[3720]="*rūpaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**They regard form like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[3721]="*vedanaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**They also regard feeling …*";
P_HTM[3722]="*saññaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**perception …*";
P_HTM[3723]="*saṅkhāre ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**choices …*";
P_HTM[3724]="*yampi taṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ, anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**whatever is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[3725]="*yampi taṃ diṭṭhiṭṭhānaṃ—**And the same for this ground for views:*";
P_HTM[3726]="*so loko so attā, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassāmīti—**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After death I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, and will last forever and ever.’*";
P_HTM[3727]="*tampi ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati.**They also regard this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[3728]="*Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido sappurisadhamme suvinīto,**But an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[3729]="*rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati;**They regard form like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[3730]="*vedanaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati;**They also regard feeling …*";
P_HTM[3731]="*saññaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati;**perception …*";
P_HTM[3732]="*saṅkhāre ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati;**choices …*";
P_HTM[3733]="*yampi taṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ, anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tampi ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati;**whatever is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[3734]="*yampi taṃ diṭṭhiṭṭhānaṃ—**And the same for this ground for views:*";
P_HTM[3735]="*so loko so attā, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassāmīti—**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After death I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, and will last forever and ever.’*";
P_HTM[3736]="*tampi ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**They also regard this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[3737]="*So evaṃ samanupassanto asati na paritassatī”ti.**Seeing in this way they’re not anxious about what doesn’t exist.”*";
P_HTM[3738]="*Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3739]="*“siyā nu kho, bhante, bahiddhā asati paritassanā”ti?**“Sir, can there be anxiety about what doesn’t exist externally?”*";
P_HTM[3740]="*“Siyā, bhikkhū”ti—bhagavā avoca.**“There can, mendicant,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3741]="*“Idha bhikkhu ekaccassa evaṃ hoti:**“It’s when someone thinks,*";
P_HTM[3742]="*‘ahu vata me, taṃ vata me natthi;**‘Oh, but it used to be mine, and it is mine no more.*";
P_HTM[3743]="*siyā vata me, taṃ vatāhaṃ na labhāmī’ti.**Oh, but it could be mine, and I will get it no more.’*";
P_HTM[3744]="*So socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[3745]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, bahiddhā asati paritassanā hotī”ti.**That’s how there is anxiety about what doesn’t exist externally.”*";
P_HTM[3746]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, bahiddhā asati aparitassanā”ti?**“But can there be no anxiety about what doesn’t exist externally?”*";
P_HTM[3747]="*“Siyā, bhikkhū”ti—bhagavā avoca.**“There can, mendicant,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3748]="*“Idha bhikkhu ekaccassa na evaṃ hoti:**“It’s when someone doesn’t think,*";
P_HTM[3749]="*‘ahu vata me, taṃ vata me natthi;**‘Oh, but it used to be mine, and it is mine no more.*";
P_HTM[3750]="*siyā vata me, taṃ vatāhaṃ na labhāmī’ti.**Oh, but it could be mine, and I will get it no more.’*";
P_HTM[3751]="*So na socati na kilamati na paridevati na urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[3752]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, bahiddhā asati aparitassanā hotī”ti.**That’s how there is no anxiety about what doesn’t exist externally.”*";
P_HTM[3753]="*“Siyā nu kho, bhante, ajjhattaṃ asati paritassanā”ti?**“But can there be anxiety about what doesn’t exist internally?”*";
P_HTM[3754]="*“Siyā, bhikkhū”ti—bhagavā avoca.**“There can, mendicant,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3755]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekaccassa evaṃ diṭṭhi hoti:**“It’s when someone has such a view:*";
P_HTM[3756]="*‘so loko so attā, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassāmī’ti.**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After death I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, and will last forever and ever.’*";
P_HTM[3757]="*So suṇāti tathāgatassa vā tathāgatasāvakassa vā sabbesaṃ diṭṭhiṭṭhānādhiṭṭhānapariyuṭṭhānābhinivesānusayānaṃ samugghātāya sabbasaṅkhārasamathāya sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggāya taṇhākkhayāya virāgāya nirodhāya nibbānāya dhammaṃ desentassa.**They hear the Realized One or their disciple teaching Dhamma for the uprooting of all grounds, fixations, obsessions, insistences, and underlying tendencies regarding views; for the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3758]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think,*";
P_HTM[3759]="*‘ucchijjissāmi nāmassu, vinassissāmi nāmassu, nassu nāma bhavissāmī’ti.**‘Whoa, I’m going to be annihilated and destroyed! I won’t exist any more!’*";
P_HTM[3760]="*So socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[3761]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, ajjhattaṃ asati paritassanā hotī”ti.**That’s how there is anxiety about what doesn’t exist internally.”*";
P_HTM[3762]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, ajjhattaṃ asati aparitassanā”ti?**“But can there be no anxiety about what doesn’t exist internally?”*";
P_HTM[3763]="*“Siyā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca.**“There can,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3764]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekaccassa na evaṃ diṭṭhi hoti:**“It’s when someone doesn’t have such a view:*";
P_HTM[3765]="*‘so loko so attā, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassāmī’ti.**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After death I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, and will last forever and ever.’*";
P_HTM[3766]="*So suṇāti tathāgatassa vā tathāgatasāvakassa vā sabbesaṃ diṭṭhiṭṭhānādhiṭṭhānapariyuṭṭhānābhinivesānusayānaṃ samugghātāya sabbasaṅkhārasamathāya sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggāya taṇhākkhayāya virāgāya nirodhāya nibbānāya dhammaṃ desentassa.**They hear the Realized One or their disciple teaching Dhamma for the uprooting of all grounds, fixations, obsessions, insistences, and underlying tendencies regarding views; for the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3767]="*Tassa na evaṃ hoti:**It never occurs to them,*";
P_HTM[3768]="*‘ucchijjissāmi nāmassu, vinassissāmi nāmassu, nassu nāma bhavissāmī’ti.**‘Whoa, I’m going to be annihilated and destroyed! I won’t exist any more!’*";
P_HTM[3769]="*So na socati na kilamati na paridevati na urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**They don’t sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[3770]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, ajjhattaṃ asati aparitassanā hoti.**That’s how there is no anxiety about what doesn’t exist internally.*";
P_HTM[3771]="*Taṃ, bhikkhave, pariggahaṃ pariggaṇheyyātha, yvāssa pariggaho nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva tiṭṭheyya.**Mendicants, it would make sense to be possessive about something that’s permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, and will last forever and ever.*";
P_HTM[3772]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, taṃ pariggahaṃ yvāssa pariggaho nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva tiṭṭheyyā”ti?**But do you see any such possession?”*";
P_HTM[3773]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3774]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[3775]="*Ahampi kho taṃ, bhikkhave, pariggahaṃ na samanupassāmi yvāssa pariggaho nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo sassatisamaṃ tatheva tiṭṭheyya.**I also can’t see any such possession.*";
P_HTM[3776]="*Taṃ, bhikkhave, attavādupādānaṃ upādiyetha, yaṃsa attavādupādānaṃ upādiyato na uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā.**It would make sense to grasp at a doctrine of self that didn’t give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, taṃ attavādupādānaṃ yaṃsa attavādupādānaṃ upādiyato na uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**But do you see any such doctrine of self?”*";
P_HTM[3778]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3779]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[3780]="*Ahampi kho taṃ, bhikkhave, attavādupādānaṃ na samanupassāmi yaṃsa attavādupādānaṃ upādiyato na uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā.**I also can’t see any such doctrine of self.*";
P_HTM[3781]="*Taṃ, bhikkhave, diṭṭhinissayaṃ nissayetha yaṃsa diṭṭhinissayaṃ nissayato na uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā.**It would make sense to rely on a view that didn’t give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[3782]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, taṃ diṭṭhinissayaṃ yaṃsa diṭṭhinissayaṃ nissayato na uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**But do you see any such view to rely on?”*";
P_HTM[3783]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3784]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[3785]="*Ahampi kho taṃ, bhikkhave, diṭṭhinissayaṃ na samanupassāmi yaṃsa diṭṭhinissayaṃ nissayato na uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”.**I also can’t see any such view to rely on.*";
P_HTM[3786]="*“Attani vā, bhikkhave, sati ‘attaniyaṃ me’ti assā”ti?**Mendicants, were a self to exist, would there be the thought, ‘Belonging to my self’?”*";
P_HTM[3787]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3788]="*“Attaniye vā, bhikkhave, sati ‘attā me’ti assā”ti?**“Were what belongs to a self to exist, would there be the thought, ‘My self’?”*";
P_HTM[3789]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3790]="*“Attani ca, bhikkhave, attaniye ca saccato thetato anupalabbhamāne, yampi taṃ diṭṭhiṭṭhānaṃ:**“But self and what belongs to a self are not acknowledged as a genuine fact. This being so, is not the following a totally foolish teaching:*";
P_HTM[3791]="*‘so loko so attā, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo, sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassāmī’ti—**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After death I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, and will last forever and ever’?”*";
P_HTM[3792]="*nanāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kevalo paripūro bāladhammo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3793]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante, kevalo hi, bhante, paripūro bāladhammo”ti.**“What else could it be, sir? It’s a totally foolish teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3794]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3795]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[3796]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3797]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[3798]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3799]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ—**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[3800]="*etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[3801]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3802]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3803]="*vedanā … pe …**Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[3804]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[3805]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[3806]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[3807]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3808]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[3809]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3810]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ—**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[3811]="*etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[3812]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3813]="*“Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ, ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā, hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā, yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**“So, mendicants, you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[3814]="*Yā kāci vedanā … pe …**You should truly see any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[3815]="*yā kāci saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[3816]="*ye keci saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[3817]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ, ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā, hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā, yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[3818]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmiṃ nibbindati, vedanāya nibbindati, saññāya nibbindati, saṅkhāresu nibbindati, viññāṇasmiṃ nibbindati,**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3819]="*nibbidā virajjati, virāgā vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[3820]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[3821]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ukkhittapaligho itipi, saṃkiṇṇaparikkho itipi, abbūḷhesiko itipi, niraggaḷo itipi, ariyo pannaddhajo pannabhāro visaṃyutto itipi.**This is called a mendicant who has lifted up the cross-bar, filled in the trench, and pulled up the pillar; who is unbarred, a noble one with banner and burden put down, detached.*";
P_HTM[3822]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ukkhittapaligho hoti?**And how has a mendicant lifted the cross-bar?*";
P_HTM[3823]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno avijjā pahīnā hoti, ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā, āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**It’s when a mendicant has given up ignorance, cut it off at the root, made it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3824]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ukkhittapaligho hoti.**That’s how a mendicant has lifted the cross-bar.*";
P_HTM[3825]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṅkiṇṇaparikkho hoti?**And how has a mendicant filled in the trench?*";
P_HTM[3826]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ponobbhaviko jātisaṃsāro pahīno hoti, ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato, āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**It’s when a mendicant has given up transmigrating through births in future lives, cut it off at the root, made it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3827]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṅkiṇṇaparikkho hoti.**That’s how a mendicant has filled in the trench.*";
P_HTM[3828]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abbūḷhesiko hoti?**And how has a mendicant pulled up the pillar?*";
P_HTM[3829]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno taṇhā pahīnā hoti, ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā, āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**It’s when a mendicant has given up craving, cut it off at the root, made it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3830]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abbūḷhesiko hoti.**That’s how a mendicant has pulled up the pillar.*";
P_HTM[3831]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu niraggaḷo hoti?**And how is a mendicant unbarred?*";
P_HTM[3832]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pañca orambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti, ucchinnamūlāni tālāvatthukatāni anabhāvaṅkatāni, āyatiṃ anuppādadhammāni.**It’s when a mendicant has given up the five lower fetters, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them, so they’re unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3833]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu niraggaḷo hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is unbarred.*";
P_HTM[3834]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyo pannaddhajo pannabhāro visaṃyutto hoti?**And how is a mendicant a noble one with banner and burden put down, detached?*";
P_HTM[3835]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asmimāno pahīno hoti, ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato, āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**It’s when a mendicant has given up the conceit ‘I am’, cut it off at the root, made it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3836]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyo pannaddhajo pannabhāro visaṃyutto hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a noble one with banner and burden put down, detached.*";
P_HTM[3837]="*Evaṃ vimuttacittaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ saindā devā sabrahmakā sapajāpatikā anvesaṃ nādhigacchanti:**When a mendicant’s mind is freed like this, the gods together with Indra, Brahmā, and Pajāpati, search as they may, will not find*";
P_HTM[3838]="*‘idaṃ nissitaṃ tathāgatassa viññāṇan’ti.**anything that such a Realized One’s consciousness depends on.*";
P_HTM[3839]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3840]="*Diṭṭhevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, dhamme tathāgataṃ ananuvijjoti vadāmi.**Because even in the present life the Realized One is undiscoverable, I say.*";
P_HTM[3841]="*Evaṃvādiṃ kho maṃ, bhikkhave, evamakkhāyiṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā asatā tucchā musā abhūtena abbhācikkhanti:**Though I speak and explain like this, certain ascetics and brahmins misrepresent me with the false, hollow, lying, untruthful claim:*";
P_HTM[3842]="*‘venayiko samaṇo gotamo, sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññāpetī’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is an exterminator. He advocates the annihilation, eradication, and obliteration of an existing being.’*";
P_HTM[3843]="*Yathā cāhaṃ na, bhikkhave, yathā cāhaṃ na vadāmi, tathā maṃ te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asatā tucchā musā abhūtena abbhācikkhanti:**I have been falsely misrepresented as being what I am not, and saying what I do not say.*";
P_HTM[3844]="*‘venayiko samaṇo gotamo, sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññāpetī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3845]="*Pubbe cāhaṃ, bhikkhave, etarahi ca dukkhañceva paññāpemi, dukkhassa ca nirodhaṃ.**In the past, as today, what I describe is suffering and the cessation of suffering.*";
P_HTM[3846]="*Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ akkosanti paribhāsanti rosenti vihesenti, tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa na hoti āghāto na appaccayo na cetaso anabhiraddhi.**This being so, if others abuse, attack, harass, and trouble the Realized One, he doesn’t get resentful, bitter, and emotionally exasperated.*";
P_HTM[3847]="*Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa na hoti ānando na somanassaṃ na cetaso uppilāvitattaṃ.**Or if others honor, respect, revere, or venerate him, he doesn’t get thrilled, elated, and emotionally excited.*";
P_HTM[3848]="*Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare vā tathāgataṃ sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa evaṃ hoti:**He just thinks,*";
P_HTM[3849]="*‘yaṃ kho idaṃ pubbe pariññātaṃ tattha me evarūpā kārā karīyantī’ti.**‘They do such things for what has already been completely understood.’*";
P_HTM[3850]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, tumhe cepi pare akkoseyyuṃ paribhāseyyuṃ roseyyuṃ viheseyyuṃ, tatra tumhe hi na āghāto na appaccayo na cetaso anabhiraddhi karaṇīyā.**So, mendicants, if others abuse, attack, harass, and trouble you, don’t make yourselves resentful, bitter, and emotionally exasperated.*";
P_HTM[3851]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, tumhe cepi pare sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi na ānando na somanassaṃ na cetaso uppilāvitattaṃ karaṇīyaṃ.**Or if others honor, respect, revere, or venerate you, don’t make yourselves thrilled, elated, and emotionally excited.*";
P_HTM[3852]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, tumhe cepi pare sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, tatra tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Just think,*";
P_HTM[3853]="*‘yaṃ kho idaṃ pubbe pariññātaṃ, tatthame evarūpā kārā karīyantī’ti.**‘They do such things for what has already been completely understood.’*";
P_HTM[3854]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yaṃ na tumhākaṃ taṃ pajahatha;**So, mendicants, give up what isn't yours.*";
P_HTM[3855]="*taṃ vo pahīnaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3856]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ?**And what isn’t yours?*";
P_HTM[3857]="*Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha;**Form isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3858]="*taṃ vo pahīnaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3859]="*Vedanā, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha;**Feeling …*";
P_HTM[3860]="*sā vo pahīnā dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[3861]="*Saññā, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha;**perception …*";
P_HTM[3862]="*sā vo pahīnā dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[3863]="*Saṅkhārā, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, te pajahatha;**choices …*";
P_HTM[3864]="*te vo pahīnā dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissanti.* **";
P_HTM[3865]="*Viññāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha;**consciousness isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3866]="*taṃ vo pahīnaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3867]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3868]="*yaṃ imasmiṃ jetavane tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ, taṃ jano hareyya vā daheyya vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kareyya.**Suppose a person was to carry off the grass, sticks, branches, and leaves in this Jeta’s Grove, or burn them, or do what they want with them.*";
P_HTM[3869]="*Api nu tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Would you think,*";
P_HTM[3870]="*‘amhe jano harati vā dahati vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karotī’”ti?**‘This person is carrying us off, burning us, or doing what they want with us?’”*";
P_HTM[3871]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3872]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3873]="*“Na hi no etaṃ, bhante, attā vā attaniyaṃ vā”ti.**Because that’s neither self nor belonging to self.”*";
P_HTM[3874]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yaṃ na tumhākaṃ taṃ pajahatha;**“In the same way, mendicants, give up what isn't yours.*";
P_HTM[3875]="*taṃ vo pahīnaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3876]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ?**And what isn’t yours?*";
P_HTM[3877]="*Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha;**Form …*";
P_HTM[3878]="*taṃ vo pahīnaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[3879]="*Vedanā, bhikkhave … pe …**feeling …*";
P_HTM[3880]="*saññā, bhikkhave …**perception …*";
P_HTM[3881]="*saṅkhārā, bhikkhave … pe …**choices …*";
P_HTM[3882]="*viññāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha;**consciousness isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3883]="*taṃ vo pahīnaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3884]="*Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko.**Thus the teaching has been well explained by me, made clear, opened, illuminated, and stripped of patchwork.*";
P_HTM[3885]="*Evaṃ svākkhāte, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite chinnapilotike ye te bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya.**In this teaching there are mendicants who are perfected, who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment. For them, there is no cycle of rebirths to be found. …*";
P_HTM[3886]="*Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko.* **";
P_HTM[3887]="*Evaṃ svākkhāte, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite chinnapilotike yesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, sabbe te opapātikā, tattha parinibbāyino, anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā.**In this teaching there are mendicants who have given up the five lower fetters. All of them are reborn spontaneously. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world. …*";
P_HTM[3888]="*Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko.* **";
P_HTM[3889]="*Evaṃ svākkhāte, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite chinnapilotike yesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tīṇi saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, rāgadosamohā tanubhūtā, sabbe te sakadāgāmino, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti.**In this teaching there are mendicants who, having given up three fetters, and weakened greed, hate, and delusion, are once-returners. All of them come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. …*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko.* **";
P_HTM[3891]="*Evaṃ svākkhāte, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite chinnapilotike yesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tīṇi saṃyojanāni pahīnāni, sabbe te sotāpannā, avinipātadhammā, niyatā sambodhiparāyanā.**In this teaching there are mendicants who have ended three fetters. All of them are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. …*";
P_HTM[3892]="*Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko.* **";
P_HTM[3893]="*Evaṃ svākkhāte, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite chinnapilotike ye te bhikkhū dhammānusārino saddhānusārino sabbe te sambodhiparāyanā.**In this teaching there are mendicants who are followers of principles, or followers by faith. All of them are bound for awakening.*";
P_HTM[3894]="*Evaṃ svākkhāto, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo uttāno vivaṭo pakāsito chinnapilotiko.**Thus the teaching has been well explained by me, made clear, opened, illuminated, and stripped of patchwork.*";
P_HTM[3895]="*Evaṃ svākkhāte, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme uttāne vivaṭe pakāsite chinnapilotike yesaṃ mayi saddhāmattaṃ pemamattaṃ sabbe te saggaparāyanā”ti.**In this teaching there are those who have a degree of faith and love for me. All of them are bound for heaven.”*";
P_HTM[3896]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3897]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3898]="*Alagaddūpamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3899]="*23. Vammikasutta**The Ant-Hill*";
P_HTM[3900]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3901]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3902]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā kumārakassapo andhavane viharati.**Now at that time Venerable Kassapa the Prince was staying in the Dark Forest.*";
P_HTM[3903]="*Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ andhavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāyasmā kumārakassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā āyasmantaṃ kumārakassapaṃ etadavoca:**Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Dark Forest, went up to Kassapa the Prince, stood to one side, and said:*";
P_HTM[3904]="*“Bhikkhu bhikkhu, ayaṃ vammiko rattiṃ dhūmāyati, divā pajjalati.**“Monk, monk! This ant-hill fumes by night and flames by day.*";
P_HTM[3905]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3906]="*‘abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**‘Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3907]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa laṅgiṃ**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a bar:*";
P_HTM[3908]="*‘laṅgī, bhadante’ti.**‘A bar, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3909]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3910]="*‘ukkhipa laṅgiṃ;**‘Throw out the bar!*";
P_HTM[3911]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3912]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa uddhumāyikaṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a bullfrog:*";
P_HTM[3913]="*‘Uddhumāyikā, bhadante’ti.**‘A bullfrog, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3914]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3915]="*‘ukkhipa uddhumāyikaṃ;**‘Throw out the bullfrog!*";
P_HTM[3916]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3917]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa dvidhāpathaṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a forked path:*";
P_HTM[3918]="*‘Dvidhāpatho, bhadante’ti.**‘A forked path, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3919]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3920]="*‘ukkhipa dvidhāpathaṃ;**‘Throw out the forked path!*";
P_HTM[3921]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3922]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa caṅgavāraṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a box:*";
P_HTM[3923]="*‘Caṅgavāro, bhadante’ti.**‘A box, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3924]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3925]="*‘ukkhipa caṅgavāraṃ;**‘Throw out the box!*";
P_HTM[3926]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3927]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa kummaṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a tortoise:*";
P_HTM[3928]="*‘Kummo, bhadante’ti.**‘A tortoise, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3929]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3930]="*‘ukkhipa kummaṃ;**‘Throw out the tortoise!*";
P_HTM[3931]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3932]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa asisūnaṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw an axe and block:*";
P_HTM[3933]="*‘Asisūnā, bhadante’ti.**‘An axe and block, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3934]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3935]="*‘ukkhipa asisūnaṃ;**‘Throw out the axe and block!*";
P_HTM[3936]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3937]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa maṃsapesiṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a lump of meat:*";
P_HTM[3938]="*‘Maṃsapesi, bhadante’ti.**‘A lump of meat, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3939]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3940]="*‘ukkhipa maṃsapesiṃ;**‘Throw out the lump of meat!*";
P_HTM[3941]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā’ti.**Take up the sword and dig, O sage!’*";
P_HTM[3942]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya addasa nāgaṃ.**Taking up the sword and digging, the sage saw a dragon:*";
P_HTM[3943]="*‘Nāgo, bhadante’ti.**‘A dragon, sir!’*";
P_HTM[3944]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:**The brahmin said,*";
P_HTM[3945]="*‘tiṭṭhatu nāgo, mā nāgaṃ ghaṭṭesi; namo karohi nāgassā’ti.**‘Leave the dragon! Do not disturb the dragon! Worship the dragon!’*";
P_HTM[3946]="*Ime kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pañhe bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā puccheyyāsi, yathā ca te bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsi.**Mendicant, go to the Buddha and ask him about this riddle. You should remember it in line with his answer.*";
P_HTM[3947]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ, bhikkhu, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo imesaṃ pañhānaṃ veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyya aññatra tathāgatena vā, tathāgatasāvakena vā, ito vā pana sutvā”ti—**I don’t see anyone in this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—who could provide a satisfying answer to this riddle except for the Realized One or his disciple or someone who has heard it from them.”*";
P_HTM[3948]="*Idamavoca sā devatā.**That is what that deity said*";
P_HTM[3949]="*Idaṃ vatvā tatthevantaradhāyi.**before vanishing right there.*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Atha kho āyasmā kumārakassapo tassā rattiyā accayena yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā kumārakassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then, when the night had passed, Kassapa the Prince went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then he asked:*";
P_HTM[3951]="*“imaṃ, bhante, rattiṃ aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ andhavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhante, sā devatā maṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[3952]="*‘bhikkhu bhikkhu, ayaṃ vammiko rattiṃ dhūmāyati, divā pajjalati.* **";
P_HTM[3953]="*Brāhmaṇo evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[3954]="*“abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3955]="*Abhikkhaṇanto sumedho satthaṃ ādāya … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3956]="*ito vā pana sutvā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3957]="*Idamavoca, bhante, sā devatā.* **";
P_HTM[3958]="*Idaṃ vatvā tatthevantaradhāyi.* **";
P_HTM[3959]="*Ko nu kho, bhante, vammiko, kā rattiṃ dhūmāyanā, kā divā pajjalanā, ko brāhmaṇo, ko sumedho, kiṃ satthaṃ, kiṃ abhikkhaṇaṃ, kā laṅgī, kā uddhumāyikā, ko dvidhāpatho, kiṃ caṅgavāraṃ, ko kummo, kā asisūnā, kā maṃsapesi, ko nāgo”ti?**“Sir, what is the ant-hill? What is the fuming by night and flaming by day? Who is the brahmin, and who the sage? What are the sword, the digging, the bar, the bullfrog, the forked path, the box, the tortoise, the axe and block, and the lump of meat? And what is the dragon?”*";
P_HTM[3960]="*“‘Vammiko’ti kho, bhikkhu, imassetaṃ cātumahābhūtikassa kāyassa adhivacanaṃ, mātāpettikasambhavassa odanakummāsūpacayassa aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammassa. (1)**“Mendicant, ‘ant-hill’ is a term for this body made up of the four primary elements, produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction.*";
P_HTM[3961]="*Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, divā kammante ārabbha rattiṃ anuvitakketi anuvicāreti—**Thinking and considering all night about what you did during the day—*";
P_HTM[3962]="*ayaṃ rattiṃ dhūmāyanā.**this is the fuming at night.*";
P_HTM[3963]="*Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, rattiṃ anuvitakketvā anuvicāretvā divā kammante payojeti kāyena vācāya ‘manasā’—**The work you apply yourself to during the day by body, speech, and mind after thinking about it all night—*";
P_HTM[3964]="*ayaṃ divā pajjalanā. (2–3.)**this is the flaming by day.*";
P_HTM[3965]="*‘Brāhmaṇo’ti kho, bhikkhu, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**‘Brahmin’ is a term for the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3966]="*‘Sumedho’ti kho, bhikkhu, sekkhassetaṃ bhikkhuno adhivacanaṃ. (4–5.)**‘Sage’ is a term for the trainee mendicant.*";
P_HTM[3967]="*‘Satthan’ti kho, bhikkhu, ariyāyetaṃ paññāya adhivacanaṃ.**‘Sword’ is a term for noble wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3968]="*‘Abhikkhaṇan’ti kho, bhikkhu, vīriyārambhassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. (6–7.)**‘Digging’ is a term for being energetic.*";
P_HTM[3969]="*‘Laṅgī’ti kho, bhikkhu, avijjāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Bar’ is a term for ignorance.*";
P_HTM[3970]="*Ukkhipa laṅgiṃ, pajaha avijjaṃ;**‘Throw out the bar’ means ‘give up ignorance,*";
P_HTM[3971]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (8)**take up the sword, sage, and dig.’*";
P_HTM[3972]="*‘Uddhumāyikā’ti kho, bhikkhu, kodhūpāyāsassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Bullfrog’ is a term for anger and distress.*";
P_HTM[3973]="*Ukkhipa uddhumāyikaṃ, pajaha kodhūpāyāsaṃ;**‘Throw out the bullfrog’ means ‘give up anger and distress’ …*";
P_HTM[3974]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (9)* **";
P_HTM[3975]="*‘Dvidhāpatho’ti kho, bhikkhu, vicikicchāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘A forked path’ is a term for doubt.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*Ukkhipa dvidhāpathaṃ, pajaha vicikicchaṃ;**‘Throw out the forked path’ means ‘give up doubt’ …*";
P_HTM[3977]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (10)* **";
P_HTM[3978]="*‘Caṅgavāran’ti kho, bhikkhu, pañcannetaṃ nīvaraṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**‘Box’ is a term for the five hindrances, that is:*";
P_HTM[3979]="*kāmacchandanīvaraṇassa, byāpādanīvaraṇassa, thinamiddhanīvaraṇassa, uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇassa, vicikicchānīvaraṇassa.**the hindrances of sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt.*";
P_HTM[3980]="*Ukkhipa caṅgavāraṃ, pajaha pañca nīvaraṇe;**‘Throw out the box’ means ‘give up the five hindrances’ …*";
P_HTM[3981]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (11)* **";
P_HTM[3982]="*‘Kummo’ti kho, bhikkhu, pañcannetaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**‘Tortoise’ is a term for the five grasping aggregates, that is:*";
P_HTM[3983]="*rūpupādānakkhandhassa, vedanupādānakkhandhassa, saññupādānakkhandhassa, saṅkhārupādānakkhandhassa, viññāṇupādānakkhandhassa.**form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3984]="*Ukkhipa kummaṃ, pajaha pañcupādānakkhandhe;**‘Throw out the tortoise’ means ‘give up the five grasping aggregates’ …*";
P_HTM[3985]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (12)* **";
P_HTM[3986]="*‘Asisūnā’ti kho, bhikkhu, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ—**‘Axe and block’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3987]="*cakkhuviññeyyānaṃ rūpānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3988]="*sotaviññeyyānaṃ saddānaṃ … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[3989]="*ghānaviññeyyānaṃ gandhānaṃ … pe …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[3990]="*jivhāviññeyyānaṃ rasānaṃ … pe …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[3991]="*kāyaviññeyyānaṃ phoṭṭhabbānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ piyarūpānaṃ kāmūpasaṃhitānaṃ rajanīyānaṃ.**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3992]="*Ukkhipa asisūnaṃ, pajaha pañca kāmaguṇe;**‘Throw out the axe and block’ means ‘give up the five kinds of sensual stimulation’ …*";
P_HTM[3993]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (13)* **";
P_HTM[3994]="*‘Maṃsapesī’ti kho, bhikkhu, nandīrāgassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Lump of meat’ is a term for desire with relishing.*";
P_HTM[3995]="*Ukkhipa maṃsapesiṃ, pajaha nandīrāgaṃ;**‘Throw out the lump of meat’ means ‘give up desire with relishing’ …*";
P_HTM[3996]="*abhikkhaṇa, sumedha, satthaṃ ādāyāti ayametassa attho. (14)* **";
P_HTM[3997]="*‘Nāgo’ti kho, bhikkhu, khīṇāsavassetaṃ bhikkhuno adhivacanaṃ.**‘Dragon’ is a term for a mendicant who has ended the defilements.*";
P_HTM[3998]="*Tiṭṭhatu nāgo, mā nāgaṃ ghaṭṭesi; namo karohi nāgassāti ayametassa attho”ti. (15)**This is the meaning of: ‘Leave the dragon! Do not disturb the dragon! Worship the dragon.’”*";
P_HTM[3999]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4000]="*Attamano āyasmā kumārakassapo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Kassapa the Prince was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4001]="*Vammikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4002]="*24. Rathavinītasutta**Prepared Chariots*";
P_HTM[4003]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4004]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4005]="*Atha kho sambahulā jātibhūmakā bhikkhū jātibhūmiyaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭhā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:**Then several mendicants who had completed the rainy season residence in their native land went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[4006]="*“Ko nu kho, bhikkhave, jātibhūmiyaṃ jātibhūmakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ evaṃ sambhāvito:**“In your native land, mendicants, which of the native mendicants is esteemed in this way:*";
P_HTM[4007]="*‘attanā ca appiccho appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca santuṭṭho santuṭṭhikathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca pavivitto pavivekakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho asaṃsaggakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca āraddhavīriyo vīriyārambhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca sīlasampanno sīlasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca samādhisampanno samādhisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca paññāsampanno paññāsampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca vimuttisampanno vimuttisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, ovādako viññāpako sandassako samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnan’”ti?**‘Personally having few wishes, they speak to the mendicants on having few wishes. Personally having contentment, seclusion, aloofness, energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom, they speak to the mendicants on all these things. They’re an adviser and instructor, one who educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires their spiritual companions.’”*";
P_HTM[4008]="*“Puṇṇo nāma, bhante, āyasmā mantāṇiputto jātibhūmiyaṃ jātibhūmakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ evaṃ sambhāvito:**“Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta, sir, is esteemed in this way in our native land.”*";
P_HTM[4009]="*‘attanā ca appiccho appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā, attanā ca santuṭṭho … pe … ovādako viññāpako sandassako samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4010]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti.**Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was meditating not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4011]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:**Then he thought:*";
P_HTM[4012]="*“lābhā āyasmato puṇṇassa mantāṇiputtassa, suladdhalābhā āyasmato puṇṇassa mantāṇiputtassa,**“Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta is fortunate, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[4013]="*yassa viññū sabrahmacārī satthu sammukhā anumassa anumassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, tañca satthā abbhanumodati.**in that his sensible spiritual companions praise him point by point in the presence of the Teacher, and that the Teacher seconds that appreciation.*";
P_HTM[4014]="*Appeva nāma mayampi kadāci karahaci āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena saddhiṃ samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti.**Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet Venerable Puṇṇa, and we can have a discussion.”*";
P_HTM[4015]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed in Rājagaha as long as he wished, he set out for Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4016]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari.**Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[4017]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**where he stayed in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4018]="*Assosi kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto: “bhagavā kira sāvatthiṃ anuppatto; sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme”ti.**Puṇṇa heard that the Buddha had arrived at Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4019]="*Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**Then he set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out for Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4020]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Eventually he came to Sāvatthī and Jeta’s Grove. He went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[4021]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[4022]="*Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**Then, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, Puṇṇa got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he went to the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4024]="*“yassa kho tvaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, puṇṇassa nāma bhikkhuno mantāṇiputtassa abhiṇhaṃ kittayamāno ahosi, so bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena andhavanaṃ tena pakkanto divāvihārāyā”ti.**“Reverend Sāriputta, the mendicant named Puṇṇa, of whom you have often spoken so highly, after being inspired by a talk of the Buddha’s, left for the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation.”*";
P_HTM[4025]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto taramānarūpo nisīdanaṃ ādāya āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi sīsānulokī.**Sāriputta quickly grabbed his sitting cloth and followed behind Puṇṇa, keeping sight of his head.*";
P_HTM[4026]="*Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**Puṇṇa plunged deep into the Dark Forest and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[4027]="*Āyasmāpi kho sāriputto andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**And Sāriputta did likewise.*";
P_HTM[4028]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Puṇṇa, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4029]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Puṇṇa:*";
P_HTM[4030]="*“Bhagavati no, āvuso, brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Reverend, is our spiritual life lived under the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[4031]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[4032]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of ethics?”*";
P_HTM[4033]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4034]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of mind?”*";
P_HTM[4035]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4036]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of view?”*";
P_HTM[4037]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4038]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification through overcoming doubt?”*";
P_HTM[4039]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4040]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths?”*";
P_HTM[4041]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4042]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Then is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the practice?”*";
P_HTM[4043]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4044]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**“Is the spiritual life lived under the Buddha for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision?”*";
P_HTM[4045]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4046]="*“‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**“When asked each of these questions, you answered, ‘Certainly not.’*";
P_HTM[4047]="*‘Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4048]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhatthaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4049]="*kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4050]="*maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4051]="*paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4052]="*kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4053]="*Kimatthaṃ carahāvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti?**Then what exactly is the purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[4054]="*“Anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti.**“The purpose of living the spiritual life under the Buddha is extinguishment by not grasping.”*";
P_HTM[4055]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?**“Reverend, is purification of ethics extinguishment by not grasping?”*";
P_HTM[4056]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4057]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4058]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.* **";
P_HTM[4059]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4060]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.* **";
P_HTM[4061]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4062]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.* **";
P_HTM[4063]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4064]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.* **";
P_HTM[4065]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4066]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.* **";
P_HTM[4067]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?**“Is purification of knowledge and vision extinguishment by not grasping?”*";
P_HTM[4068]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4069]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānan”ti?**“Then is extinguishment by not grasping something apart from these things?”*";
P_HTM[4070]="*“No hidaṃ, āvuso”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4071]="*“‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.**“When asked each of these questions, you answered, ‘Certainly not.’*";
P_HTM[4072]="*‘Kiṃ panāvuso, cittavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4073]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, diṭṭhivisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4074]="*kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi …* **";
P_HTM[4075]="*maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi …* **";
P_HTM[4076]="*paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi …* **";
P_HTM[4077]="*‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4078]="*‘Kiṃ panāvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānan’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘no hidaṃ, āvuso’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[4079]="*Yathākathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[4080]="*“Sīlavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.**“If the Buddha had declared purification of ethics to be extinguishment by not grasping, he would have declared that which has grasping to be extinguishment by not grasping. …*";
P_HTM[4081]="*Cittavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.* **";
P_HTM[4082]="*Diṭṭhivisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.* **";
P_HTM[4083]="*Kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.* **";
P_HTM[4084]="*Maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.* **";
P_HTM[4085]="*Paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.* **";
P_HTM[4086]="*Ñāṇadassanavisuddhiñce, āvuso, bhagavā anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya, saupādānaṃyeva samānaṃ anupādāparinibbānaṃ paññapeyya.**If the Buddha had declared purification of knowledge and vision to be extinguishment by not grasping, he would have declared that which has grasping to be extinguishment by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4087]="*Aññatra ce, āvuso, imehi dhammehi anupādāparinibbānaṃ abhavissa, puthujjano parinibbāyeyya.**But if extinguishment by not grasping was something apart from these things, an ordinary person would become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*Puthujjano hi, āvuso, aññatra imehi dhammehi.**For an ordinary person lacks these things.*";
P_HTM[4089]="*Tena hāvuso, upamaṃ te karissāmi;**Well then, reverend, I shall give you a simile.*";
P_HTM[4090]="*upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti.**For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said.*";
P_HTM[4091]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasantassa sākete kiñcideva accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ uppajjeyya.**Suppose that, while staying in Sāvatthī, King Pasenadi of Kosala had some urgent business come up in Sāketa.*";
P_HTM[4092]="*Tassa antarā ca sāvatthiṃ antarā ca sāketaṃ satta rathavinītāni upaṭṭhapeyyuṃ.**Now, between Sāvatthī and Sāketa seven prepared chariots were stationed ready for him.*";
P_HTM[4093]="*Atha kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sāvatthiyā nikkhamitvā antepuradvārā paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya, paṭhamena rathavinītena dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya.**Then Pasenadi, having departed Sāvatthī, mounted the first prepared chariot by the gate of the royal compound. The first prepared chariot would bring him to the second, where he’d dismount and mount the second chariot.*";
P_HTM[4094]="*Dutiyena rathavinītena tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya.**The second prepared chariot would bring him to the third …*";
P_HTM[4095]="*Tatiyena rathavinītena catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya.**The third prepared chariot would bring him to the fourth …*";
P_HTM[4096]="*Catutthena rathavinītena pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya.**The fourth prepared chariot would bring him to the fifth …*";
P_HTM[4097]="*Pañcamena rathavinītena chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya.**The fifth prepared chariot would bring him to the sixth …*";
P_HTM[4098]="*Chaṭṭhena rathavinītena sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇeyya, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjeyya, sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruheyya.**The sixth prepared chariot would bring him to the seventh, where he’d dismount and mount the seventh chariot.*";
P_HTM[4099]="*Sattamena rathavinītena sāketaṃ anupāpuṇeyya antepuradvāraṃ.**The seventh prepared chariot would bring him to the gate of the royal compound of Sāketa.*";
P_HTM[4100]="*Tamenaṃ antepuradvāragataṃ samānaṃ mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**And when he was at the gate, friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would ask him:*";
P_HTM[4101]="*‘iminā tvaṃ, mahārāja, rathavinītena sāvatthiyā sāketaṃ anuppatto antepuradvāran’ti?**‘Great king, did you come to Sāketa from Sāvatthī by this prepared chariot?’*";
P_HTM[4102]="*Kathaṃ byākaramāno nu kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno byākareyyā”ti?**If asked this, how should King Pasenadi rightly reply?”*";
P_HTM[4103]="*“Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno byākareyya:**“The king should reply:*";
P_HTM[4104]="*‘idha me sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasantassa sākete kiñcideva accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ uppajji.**‘Well, while staying in Sāvatthī, I had some urgent business come up in Sāketa.*";
P_HTM[4105]="*Tassa me antarā ca sāvatthiṃ antarā ca sāketaṃ satta rathavinītāni upaṭṭhapesuṃ.**Now, between Sāvatthī and Sāketa seven prepared chariots were stationed ready for me.*";
P_HTM[4106]="*Atha khvāhaṃ sāvatthiyā nikkhamitvā antepuradvārā paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.**Then, having departed Sāvatthī, I mounted the first prepared chariot by the gate of the royal compound.*";
P_HTM[4107]="*Paṭhamena rathavinītena dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, paṭhamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.**The first prepared chariot brought me to the second, where I dismounted and mounted the second chariot. …*";
P_HTM[4108]="*Dutiyena rathavinītena tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, dutiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4109]="*Tatiyena rathavinītena catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, tatiyaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4110]="*Catutthena rathavinītena pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, catutthaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4111]="*Pañcamena rathavinītena chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, pañcamaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4112]="*Chaṭṭhena rathavinītena sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ pāpuṇiṃ, chaṭṭhaṃ rathavinītaṃ vissajjiṃ, sattamaṃ rathavinītaṃ abhiruhiṃ.**The sixth prepared chariot brought me to the seventh, where I dismounted and mounted the seventh chariot.*";
P_HTM[4113]="*Sattamena rathavinītena sāketaṃ anuppatto antepuradvāran’ti.**The seventh prepared chariot brought me to the gate of the royal compound of Sāketa.’*";
P_HTM[4114]="*Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, āvuso, rājā pasenadi kosalo sammā byākaramāno byākareyyā”ti.**That’s how King Pasenadi should rightly reply.”*";
P_HTM[4115]="*“Evameva kho, āvuso, sīlavisuddhi yāvadeva cittavisuddhatthā, cittavisuddhi yāvadeva diṭṭhivisuddhatthā, diṭṭhivisuddhi yāvadeva kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhatthā, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi yāvadeva maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva ñāṇadassanavisuddhatthā, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi yāvadeva anupādāparinibbānatthā.**“In the same way, reverend, purification of ethics is only for the sake of purification of mind. Purification of mind is only for the sake of purification of view. Purification of view is only for the sake of purification through overcoming doubt. Purification through overcoming doubt is only for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths. Purification of knowledge and vision of the variety of paths is only for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision of the practice. Purification of knowledge and vision of the practice is only for the sake of purification of knowledge and vision. Purification of knowledge and vision is only for the sake of extinguishment by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4116]="*Anupādāparinibbānatthaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti.**The spiritual life is lived under the Buddha for the sake of extinguishment by not grasping.”*";
P_HTM[4117]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Sāriputta said to Puṇṇa,*";
P_HTM[4118]="*“konāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti?**“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual companions?”*";
P_HTM[4119]="*“Puṇṇoti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ;**“Reverend, my name is Puṇṇa.*";
P_HTM[4120]="*mantāṇiputtoti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti.**And I am known as Mantāṇiputta among my spiritual companions.”*";
P_HTM[4121]="*“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso.**“It’s incredible, reverend, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[4122]="*Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena, evameva āyasmatā puṇṇena mantāṇiputtena gambhīrā gambhīrapañhā anumassa anumassa byākatā.**Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta has answered each deep question point by point, as a learned disciple who rightly understands the teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[4123]="*Lābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ, suladdhalābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ,**It is fortunate for his spiritual companions, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[4124]="*ye āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ labhanti dassanāya, labhanti payirūpāsanāya.**that they get to see Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāṇiputta and pay homage to him.*";
P_HTM[4125]="*Celaṇḍukena cepi sabrahmacārī āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ muddhanā pariharantā labheyyuṃ dassanāya, labheyyuṃ payirūpāsanāya, tesampi lābhā tesampi suladdhaṃ, amhākampi lābhā amhākampi suladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ puṇṇaṃ mantāṇiputtaṃ labhāma dassanāya, labhāma payirūpāsanāyā”ti.**Even if they only got to see him and pay respects to him by carrying him around on their heads on a roll of cloth, it would still be very fortunate for them! And it’s fortunate for me, so very fortunate, that I get to see the venerable and pay homage to him.”*";
P_HTM[4126]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā puṇṇo mantāṇiputto āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Puṇṇa said to Sāriputta,*";
P_HTM[4127]="*“ko nāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti?**“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual companions?”*";
P_HTM[4128]="*“Upatissoti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ;**“Reverend, my name is Upatissa.*";
P_HTM[4129]="*sāriputtoti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti.**And I am known as Sāriputta among my spiritual companions.”*";
P_HTM[4130]="*“Satthukappena vata kira, bho, sāvakena saddhiṃ mantayamānā na jānimha:**“Goodness! I had no idea I was consulting with the Venerable Sāriputta, the disciple who is fit to be compared with the Teacher himself!*";
P_HTM[4131]="*‘āyasmā sāriputto’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4132]="*Sace hi mayaṃ jāneyyāma ‘āyasmā sāriputto’ti, ettakampi no nappaṭibhāseyya.**If I’d known, I wouldn’t have said so much.*";
P_HTM[4133]="*Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso.**It’s incredible, reverend, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[4134]="*Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena, evameva āyasmatā sāriputtena gambhīrā gambhīrapañhā anumassa anumassa pucchitā.**Venerable Sāriputta has asked each deep question point by point, as a learned disciple who rightly understands the teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[4135]="*Lābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ suladdhalābhā sabrahmacārīnaṃ,**It is fortunate for his spiritual companions, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[4136]="*ye āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ labhanti dassanāya, labhanti payirūpāsanāya.**that they get to see Venerable Sāriputta and pay homage to him.*";
P_HTM[4137]="*Celaṇḍukena cepi sabrahmacārī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ muddhanā pariharantā labheyyuṃ dassanāya, labheyyuṃ payirūpāsanāya, tesampi lābhā tesampi suladdhaṃ, amhākampi lābhā amhākampi suladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ labhāma dassanāya, labhāma payirūpāsanāyā”ti.**Even if they only got to see him and pay respects to him by carrying him around on their heads on a roll of cloth, it would still be very fortunate for them! And it’s fortunate for me, so very fortunate, that I get to see the venerable and pay homage to him.”*";
P_HTM[4138]="*Itiha te ubhopi mahānāgā aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ samanumodiṃsūti.**And so these two spiritual giants agreed with each others’ fine words.*";
P_HTM[4139]="*Rathavinītasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4140]="*25. Nivāpasutta**Fodder*";
P_HTM[4141]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4142]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4143]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4144]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4145]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4147]="*“Na, bhikkhave, nevāpiko nivāpaṃ nivapati migajātānaṃ:**“Mendicants, a trapper doesn’t cast bait for deer thinking,*";
P_HTM[4148]="*‘imaṃ me nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ migajātā paribhuñjantā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ yāpentū’ti.**‘May the deer, enjoying this bait, be healthy and in good condition. May they live long and prosper!’*";
P_HTM[4149]="*Evañca kho, bhikkhave, nevāpiko nivāpaṃ nivapati migajātānaṃ:**A trapper casts bait for deer thinking,*";
P_HTM[4150]="*‘imaṃ me nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ migajātā anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissanti, anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjissanti, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjissanti, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissanti imasmiṃ nivāpe’ti.**‘When these deer intrude on where I cast the bait, they’ll recklessly enjoy eating it. They’ll become indulgent, then they’ll become negligent, and then they’ll be vulnerable on account of this bait.’*";
P_HTM[4151]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, paṭhamā migajātā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu, te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.**And indeed, the first herd of deer intruded on where the trapper cast the bait and recklessly enjoyed eating it. They became indulgent, then they became negligent, and then they were vulnerable to the trapper on account of that bait.*";
P_HTM[4152]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the first herd of deer failed to get free from the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4153]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, dutiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**So then a second herd of deer thought up a plan,*";
P_HTM[4154]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.**‘The first herd of deer became indulgent …*";
P_HTM[4155]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.* **";
P_HTM[4156]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**and failed to get free of the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4157]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti.**Why don’t we avoid eating the bait altogether? Avoiding dangerous food, we can venture deep into a wilderness region and live there.’*";
P_HTM[4158]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihariṃsu.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4159]="*Tesaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse, tiṇodakasaṅkhaye, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.**But when it came to the last month of summer, the grass and water ran out. Their bodies became much too thin,*";
P_HTM[4160]="*Tesaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyānaṃ balavīriyaṃ parihāyi.**and they lost their strength and energy.*";
P_HTM[4161]="*Balavīriye parihīne tameva nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa paccāgamiṃsu.**So they went back to that same place where the trapper had cast bait.*";
P_HTM[4162]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.**Intruding on that place, they recklessly enjoyed eating it …*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.* **";
P_HTM[4164]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, dutiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the second herd failed to get free from the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4165]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, tatiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**So then a third herd of deer thought up a plan,*";
P_HTM[4166]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa … pe …**‘The first …*";
P_HTM[4167]="*evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4168]="*Yepi te dutiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**and second herds of deer …*";
P_HTM[4169]="*“ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4170]="*evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4171]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4172]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihariṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4173]="*Tesaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse tiṇodakasaṅkhaye adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[4174]="*Tesaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyānaṃ balavīriyaṃ parihāyi.* **";
P_HTM[4175]="*Balavīriye parihīne tameva nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa paccāgamiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4176]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4177]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.* **";
P_HTM[4178]="*Evañhi te dutiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**failed to get free of the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4179]="*Yannūna mayaṃ amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa upanissāya āsayaṃ kappeyyāma.**Why don’t we set up our lair close by the place where the trapper has cast the bait?*";
P_HTM[4180]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissāma, ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjissāma, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjissāma, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissāma nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe’ti.**Then we can intrude on it and enjoy eating without being reckless. We won’t become indulgent, then we won’t become negligent, and then we won’t be vulnerable to the trapper on account of that bait.’*";
P_HTM[4181]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa upanissāya āsayaṃ kappayiṃsu.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4182]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu, te tattha ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.* **";
P_HTM[4183]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, nevāpikassa ca nevāpikaparisāya ca etadahosi:**So the trapper and his companions thought,*";
P_HTM[4184]="*‘saṭhāssunāmime tatiyā migajātā ketabino, iddhimantāssunāmime tatiyā migajātā parajanā;**‘Wow, this third herd of deer is so sneaky and devious, they must be some kind of unnatural spirits with psychic power!*";
P_HTM[4185]="*imañca nāma nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ paribhuñjanti, na ca nesaṃ jānāma āgatiṃ vā gatiṃ vā.**For they eat the bait we’ve cast without us knowing how they come and go.*";
P_HTM[4186]="*Yannūna mayaṃ imaṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mahatīhi daṇḍavākarāhi samantā sappadesaṃ anuparivāreyyāma, appeva nāma tatiyānaṃ migajātānaṃ āsayaṃ passeyyāma, yattha te gāhaṃ gaccheyyun’ti.**Why don’t we surround the bait on all sides by staking out high nets? Hopefully we might get to see their lair, where they go to hide out.’*";
P_HTM[4187]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mahatīhi daṇḍavākarāhi samantā sappadesaṃ anuparivāresuṃ.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4188]="*Addasaṃsu kho, bhikkhave, nevāpiko ca nevāpikaparisā ca tatiyānaṃ migajātānaṃ āsayaṃ, yattha te gāhaṃ agamaṃsu.**And they saw where the third herd of deer had their lair, where they went to hide out.*";
P_HTM[4189]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, tatiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the third herd failed to get free from the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4190]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, catutthā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**So then a fourth herd of deer thought up a plan,*";
P_HTM[4191]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā … pe …**‘The first …*";
P_HTM[4192]="*evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4193]="*Yepi te dutiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**second …*";
P_HTM[4194]="*“ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4195]="*evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4196]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4197]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭiviramiṃsu … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4198]="*evañhi te dutiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4199]="*Yepi te tatiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**and third herds of deer …*";
P_HTM[4200]="*“ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4201]="*evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4202]="*Yepi te dutiyā migajātā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[4203]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā migajātā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4204]="*evañhi te paṭhamā migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4205]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4206]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā paṭiviramiṃsu … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4207]="*evañhi te dutiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4208]="*Yannūna mayaṃ amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa upanissāya āsayaṃ kappeyyāma, tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissāma, ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjissāma, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjissāma, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissāma nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4209]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa upanissāya āsayaṃ kappayiṃsu, tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu, te tattha ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.* **";
P_HTM[4210]="*Tatra nevāpikassa ca nevāpikaparisāya ca etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[4211]="*“saṭhāssunāmime tatiyā migajātā ketabino, iddhimantāssunāmime tatiyā migajātā parajanā, imañca nāma nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ paribhuñjanti.* **";
P_HTM[4212]="*Na ca nesaṃ jānāma āgatiṃ vā gatiṃ vā.* **";
P_HTM[4213]="*Yannūna mayaṃ imaṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mahatīhi daṇḍavākarāhi samantā sappadesaṃ anuparivāreyyāma, appeva nāma tatiyānaṃ migajātānaṃ āsayaṃ passeyyāma, yattha te gāhaṃ gaccheyyun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4214]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mahatīhi daṇḍavākarāhi samantā sappadesaṃ anuparivāresuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4215]="*Addasaṃsu kho nevāpiko ca nevāpikaparisā ca tatiyānaṃ migajātānaṃ āsayaṃ, yattha te gāhaṃ agamaṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4216]="*Evañhi te tatiyāpi migajātā na parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**failed to get free of the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4217]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yattha agati nevāpikassa ca nevāpikaparisāya ca tatrāsayaṃ kappeyyāma, tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissāma, ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjissāma, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjissāma, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissāma nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe’ti.**Why don’t we set up our lair somewhere the trapper and his companions can’t go? Then we can intrude on where the trapper has cast the bait and enjoy eating it without being reckless. We won’t become indulgent, then we won’t become negligent, and then we won’t be vulnerable to the trapper on account of that bait.’*";
P_HTM[4218]="*Te yattha agati nevāpikassa ca nevāpikaparisāya ca tatrāsayaṃ kappayiṃsu.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4219]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ nevāpikassa ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu, te tattha ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ nevāpikassa amusmiṃ nivāpe.* **";
P_HTM[4220]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, nevāpikassa ca nevāpikaparisāya ca etadahosi:**So the trapper and his companions thought,*";
P_HTM[4221]="*‘saṭhāssunāmime catutthā migajātā ketabino, iddhimantāssunāmime catutthā migajātā parajanā.**‘Wow, this fourth herd of deer is so sneaky and devious, they must be some kind of unnatural spirits with psychic power!*";
P_HTM[4222]="*Imañca nāma nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ paribhuñjanti, na ca nesaṃ jānāma āgatiṃ vā gatiṃ vā.**For they eat the bait we’ve cast without us knowing how they come and go.*";
P_HTM[4223]="*Yannūna mayaṃ imaṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mahatīhi daṇḍavākarāhi samantā sappadesaṃ anuparivāreyyāma, appeva nāma catutthānaṃ migajātānaṃ āsayaṃ passeyyāma yattha te gāhaṃ gaccheyyun’ti.**Why don’t we surround the bait on all sides by staking out high nets? Hopefully we might get to see their lair, where they go to hide out.’*";
P_HTM[4224]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mahatīhi daṇḍavākarāhi samantā sappadesaṃ anuparivāresuṃ.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4225]="*Neva kho, bhikkhave, addasaṃsu nevāpiko ca nevāpikaparisā ca catutthānaṃ migajātānaṃ āsayaṃ, yattha te gāhaṃ gaccheyyuṃ.**But they couldn’t see where the fourth herd of deer had their lair, where they went to hide out.*";
P_HTM[4226]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, nevāpikassa ca nevāpikaparisāya ca etadahosi:**So the trapper and his companions thought,*";
P_HTM[4227]="*‘sace kho mayaṃ catutthe migajāte ghaṭṭessāma, te ghaṭṭitā aññe ghaṭṭissanti te ghaṭṭitā aññe ghaṭṭissanti.**‘If we disturb this fourth herd of deer, they’ll disturb others, who in turn will disturb even more.*";
P_HTM[4228]="*Evaṃ imaṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ sabbaso migajātā parimuñcissanti.**Then all of the deer will be free from this bait we’ve cast.*";
P_HTM[4229]="*Yannūna mayaṃ catutthe migajāte ajjhupekkheyyāmā’ti.**Why don’t we just keep an eye on that fourth herd?’*";
P_HTM[4230]="*Ajjhupekkhiṃsu kho, bhikkhave, nevāpiko ca nevāpikaparisā ca catutthe migajāte.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4231]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, catutthā migajātā parimucciṃsu nevāpikassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the fourth herd of deer got free from the trapper’s power.*";
P_HTM[4232]="*Upamā kho me ayaṃ, bhikkhave, katā atthassa viññāpanāya.**I’ve made up this simile to make a point.*";
P_HTM[4233]="*Ayaṃ cevettha attho—**And this is what it means.*";
P_HTM[4234]="*nivāpoti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Bait’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[4235]="*Nevāpikoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ.**‘Trapper’ is a term for Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[4236]="*Nevāpikaparisāti kho, bhikkhave, māraparisāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Trapper’s companions’ is a term for Māra’s assembly.*";
P_HTM[4237]="*Migajātāti kho, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Deer’ is a term for ascetics and brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4238]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.**Now, the first group of ascetics and brahmins intruded on where the bait and the material delights of the world were cast by Māra and recklessly enjoyed eating it.*";
P_HTM[4239]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.**They became indulgent, then they became negligent, and then they were vulnerable to Māra on account of that bait and the material delights of the world.*";
P_HTM[4240]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the first group of ascetics and brahmins failed to get free from Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4241]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, paṭhamā migajātā tathūpame ahaṃ ime paṭhame samaṇabrāhmaṇe vadāmi.**This first group of ascetics and brahmins is just like the first herd of deer, I say.*";
P_HTM[4242]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, dutiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**So then a second group of ascetics and brahmins thought up a plan,*";
P_HTM[4243]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.**‘The first group of ascetics and brahmins became indulgent …*";
P_HTM[4244]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.* **";
P_HTM[4245]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**and failed to get free of Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4246]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti.**Why don’t we avoid eating the bait and the world’s material delights altogether? Avoiding dangerous food, we can venture deep into a wilderness region and live there.’*";
P_HTM[4247]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmāti.* **";
P_HTM[4248]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihariṃsu.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4249]="*Te tattha sākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, sāmākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, nīvārabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, daddulabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, haṭabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, kaṇabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, ācāmabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, piññākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, tiṇabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, gomayabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ, vanamūlaphalāhārā yāpesuṃ pavattaphalabhojī.**They ate herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survived on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit.*";
P_HTM[4250]="*Tesaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse, tiṇodakasaṅkhaye, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.**But when it came to the last month of summer, the grass and water ran out. Their bodies became much too thin,*";
P_HTM[4251]="*Tesaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyānaṃ balavīriyaṃ parihāyi.**and they lost their strength and energy.*";
P_HTM[4252]="*Balavīriye parihīne cetovimutti parihāyi.**Because of this, they lost their heart’s release,*";
P_HTM[4253]="*Cetovimuttiyā parihīnāya tameva nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa paccāgamiṃsu tāni ca lokāmisāni.**so they went back to that same place where Māra had cast the bait and the material delights of the world.*";
P_HTM[4254]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.**Intruding on that place, they recklessly enjoyed eating them …*";
P_HTM[4255]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.* **";
P_HTM[4256]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, dutiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the second group of ascetics and brahmins failed to get free from Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4257]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, dutiyā migajātā tathūpame ahaṃ ime dutiye samaṇabrāhmaṇe vadāmi.**This second group of ascetics and brahmins is just like the second herd of deer, I say.*";
P_HTM[4258]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, tatiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**So then a third group of ascetics and brahmins thought up a plan,*";
P_HTM[4259]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni … pe ….**‘The first …*";
P_HTM[4260]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4261]="*Yepi te dutiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**and second groups of ascetics and brahmins …*";
P_HTM[4262]="*“ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[4263]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4264]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4265]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4266]="*Bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihariṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4267]="*Te tattha sākabhakkhāpi ahesuṃ … pe … pavattaphalabhojī.* **";
P_HTM[4268]="*Tesaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse tiṇodakasaṅkhaye adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[4269]="*Tesaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyānaṃ balavīriyaṃ parihāyi, balavīriye parihīne cetovimutti parihāyi, cetovimuttiyā parihīnāya tameva nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa paccāgamiṃsu tāni ca lokāmisāni.* **";
P_HTM[4270]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4271]="*Te tattha anupakhajja mucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, mattā samānā pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, pamattā samānā yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.* **";
P_HTM[4272]="*Evañhi te dutiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**failed to get free of Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4273]="*Yannūna mayaṃ amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni upanissāya āsayaṃ kappeyyāma, tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissāma, ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjissāma, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjissāma, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissāma mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise’ti.**Why don’t we set up our lair close by the place where Māra has cast the bait and those material delights of the world? Then we can intrude on it and enjoy eating without being reckless. We won’t become indulgent, then we won’t become negligent, and then we won’t be vulnerable to Māra on account of that bait and those material delights of the world.’*";
P_HTM[4274]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni upanissāya āsayaṃ kappayiṃsu.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4275]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4276]="*Te tattha ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.* **";
P_HTM[4277]="*Api ca kho evaṃdiṭṭhikā ahesuṃ—**Still, they had such views as these:*";
P_HTM[4278]="*sassato loko itipi, asassato loko itipi;**‘The world is eternal’ or ‘The world is not eternal’;*";
P_HTM[4279]="*antavā loko itipi, anantavā loko itipi;**‘The world is finite’ or ‘The world is infinite’;*";
P_HTM[4280]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ itipi, aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ itipi;**‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are different things’;*";
P_HTM[4281]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā itipi, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā itipi, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā itipi, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā itipi.**or that after death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.*";
P_HTM[4282]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, tatiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the third group of ascetics and brahmins failed to get free from Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4283]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, tatiyā migajātā tathūpame ahaṃ ime tatiye samaṇabrāhmaṇe vadāmi.**This third group of ascetics and brahmins is just like the third herd of deer, I say.*";
P_HTM[4284]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, catutthā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**So then a fourth group of ascetics and brahmins thought up a plan,*";
P_HTM[4285]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa … pe ….**‘The first …*";
P_HTM[4286]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4287]="*Yepi te dutiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ:**second …*";
P_HTM[4288]="*‘ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[4289]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4290]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭivirameyyāma bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4291]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[4292]="*Evañhi te dutiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4293]="*Yepi te tatiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā … pe ….**and third groups of ascetics and brahmins …*";
P_HTM[4294]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4295]="*Yepi te dutiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃ samacintesuṃ ye kho te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[4296]="*Evañhi te paṭhamā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4297]="*Yannūna mayaṃ sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭivirameyyāma, bhayabhogā paṭiviratā araññāyatanāni ajjhogāhetvā vihareyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4298]="*Te sabbaso nivāpabhojanā lokāmisā paṭiviramiṃsu … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[4299]="*Evañhi te dutiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.* **";
P_HTM[4300]="*Yannūna mayaṃ amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni upanissāya āsayaṃ kappeyyāma.* **";
P_HTM[4301]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissāma, ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjissāma, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjissāma, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissāma mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmiseti.* **";
P_HTM[4302]="*Te amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni upanissāya āsayaṃ kappayiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4303]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4304]="*Te tattha ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4305]="*Amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4306]="*Appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.* **";
P_HTM[4307]="*Api ca kho evaṃdiṭṭhikā ahesuṃ sassato loko itipi … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4308]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā itipi.* **";
P_HTM[4309]="*Evañhi te tatiyāpi samaṇabrāhmaṇā na parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**failed to get free of Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4310]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yattha agati mārassa ca māraparisāya ca tatrāsayaṃ kappeyyāma.**Why don’t we set up our lair somewhere Māra and his assembly can’t go?*";
P_HTM[4311]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjissāma, ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjissāma, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjissāma, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā bhavissāma mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmiseti.**Then we can intrude on where Māra has cast the bait and those material delights of the world, and enjoy eating without being reckless. We won’t become indulgent, then we won’t become negligent, and then we won’t be vulnerable to Māra on account of that bait and those material delights of the world.’*";
P_HTM[4312]="*Te yattha agati mārassa ca māraparisāya ca tatrāsayaṃ kappayiṃsu.**And that’s just what they did.*";
P_HTM[4313]="*Tatrāsayaṃ kappetvā amuṃ nivāpaṃ nivuttaṃ mārassa amūni ca lokāmisāni ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjiṃsu, te tattha ananupakhajja amucchitā bhojanāni bhuñjamānā na madaṃ āpajjiṃsu, amattā samānā na pamādaṃ āpajjiṃsu, appamattā samānā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā ahesuṃ mārassa amusmiṃ nivāpe amusmiñca lokāmise.* **";
P_HTM[4314]="*Evañhi te, bhikkhave, catutthā samaṇabrāhmaṇā parimucciṃsu mārassa iddhānubhāvā.**And that’s how the fourth group of ascetics and brahmins got free from Māra’s power.*";
P_HTM[4315]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, catutthā migajātā tathūpame ahaṃ ime catutthe samaṇabrāhmaṇe vadāmi.**This fourth group of ascetics and brahmins is just like the fourth herd of deer, I say.*";
P_HTM[4316]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, agati mārassa ca māraparisāya ca?**And where is it that Māra and his assembly can’t go?*";
P_HTM[4317]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4318]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu andhamakāsi māraṃ, apadaṃ vadhitvā māracakkhuṃ adassanaṃ gato pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra, put out his eyes without a trace, and gone where the Wicked One cannot see.*";
P_HTM[4319]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4320]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4321]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[4322]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4323]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4324]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4325]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[4326]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4327]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4328]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4329]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[4330]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4331]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4332]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati. Paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end.*";
P_HTM[4334]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu andhamakāsi māraṃ, apadaṃ vadhitvā māracakkhuṃ adassanaṃ gato pāpimato tiṇṇo loke visattikan”ti.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra, put out his eyes without a trace, and gone where the Wicked One cannot see. And they’ve crossed over clinging to the world.”*";
P_HTM[4335]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4336]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4337]="*Nivāpasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4338]="*26. Pāsarāsisutta**The Noble Search*";
P_HTM[4339]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4340]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4341]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[4342]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Ānanda and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4343]="*“cirassutā no, āvuso ānanda, bhagavato sammukhā dhammī kathā.**“Reverend, it’s been a long time since we’ve heard a Dhamma talk from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4344]="*Sādhu mayaṃ, āvuso ānanda, labheyyāma bhagavato sammukhā dhammiṃ kathaṃ savanāyā”ti.**It would be good if we got to hear a Dhamma talk from the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4345]="*“Tena hāyasmanto yena rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamo tenupasaṅkamatha;**“Well then, reverends, go to the brahmin Rammaka’s hermitage.*";
P_HTM[4346]="*appeva nāma labheyyātha bhagavato sammukhā dhammiṃ kathaṃ savanāyā”ti.**Hopefully you’ll get to hear a Dhamma talk from the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4347]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4348]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, the Buddha addressed Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4349]="*“āyāmānanda, yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkamissāma divāvihārāyā”ti.**“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother for the day’s meditation.”*";
P_HTM[4350]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.*";
P_HTM[4351]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the Eastern Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4352]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**In the late afternoon the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4353]="*“āyāmānanda, yena pubbakoṭṭhako tenupasaṅkamissāma gattāni parisiñcitun”ti.**“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the eastern gate to bathe.”*";
P_HTM[4354]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.*";
P_HTM[4355]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena pubbakoṭṭhako tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ.**So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the eastern gate to bathe.*";
P_HTM[4356]="*Pubbakoṭṭhake gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni pubbāpayamāno.**When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying himself.*";
P_HTM[4357]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Ānanda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4358]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamo avidūre.**“Sir, the hermitage of the brahmin Rammaka is nearby.*";
P_HTM[4359]="*Ramaṇīyo, bhante, rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamo;**It’s so delightful,*";
P_HTM[4360]="*pāsādiko, bhante, rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamo.**so lovely.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā yena rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamo tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**Please visit it out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[4362]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[4363]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamo tenupasaṅkami.**He went to the brahmin Rammaka’s hermitage.*";
P_HTM[4364]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assame dhammiyā kathāya sannisinnā honti.**Now at that time several mendicants were sitting together in the hermitage talking about the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4365]="*Atha kho bhagavā bahidvārakoṭṭhake aṭṭhāsi kathāpariyosānaṃ āgamayamāno.**The Buddha stood outside the door waiting for the talk to end.*";
P_HTM[4366]="*Atha kho bhagavā kathāpariyosānaṃ viditvā ukkāsitvā aggaḷaṃ ākoṭesi.**When he knew the talk had ended he cleared his throat and knocked with the latch.*";
P_HTM[4367]="*Vivariṃsu kho te bhikkhū bhagavato dvāraṃ.**The mendicants opened the door for the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4368]="*Atha kho bhagavā rammakassa brāhmaṇassa assamaṃ pavisitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**and he entered the hermitage, where he sat on the seat spread out*";
P_HTM[4369]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4370]="*“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā?**“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now?*";
P_HTM[4371]="*Kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[4372]="*“Bhagavantameva kho no, bhante, ārabbha dhammī kathā vippakatā, atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti.**“Sir, our unfinished discussion on the teaching was about the Buddha himself when the Buddha arrived.”*";
P_HTM[4373]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4374]="*Etaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ patirūpaṃ kulaputtānaṃ saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitānaṃ yaṃ tumhe dhammiyā kathāya sannisīdeyyātha.**It’s appropriate for gentlemen like you, who have gone forth in faith from the lay life to homelessness, to sit together and talk about the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4375]="*Sannipatitānaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dvayaṃ karaṇīyaṃ—**When you’re sitting together you should do one of two things:*";
P_HTM[4376]="*dhammī vā kathā, ariyo vā tuṇhībhāvo.**discuss the teachings or keep noble silence.*";
P_HTM[4377]="*Dvemā, bhikkhave, pariyesanā—**Mendicants, there are these two searches:*";
P_HTM[4378]="*ariyā ca pariyesanā, anariyā ca pariyesanā.**the noble search and the ignoble search.*";
P_HTM[4379]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, anariyā pariyesanā?**And what is the ignoble search?*";
P_HTM[4380]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhammaṃyeva pariyesati, attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhammaṃyeva pariyesati, attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhammaṃyeva pariyesati, attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhammaṃyeva pariyesati, attanā sokadhammo samāno sokadhammaṃyeva pariyesati, attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**It’s when someone who is themselves liable to be reborn seeks what is also liable to be reborn. Themselves liable to grow old, fall sick, die, sorrow, and become corrupted, they seek what is also liable to these things.*";
P_HTM[4381]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, jātidhammaṃ vadetha?**And what should be described as liable to be reborn?*";
P_HTM[4382]="*Puttabhariyaṃ, bhikkhave, jātidhammaṃ, dāsidāsaṃ jātidhammaṃ, ajeḷakaṃ jātidhammaṃ, kukkuṭasūkaraṃ jātidhammaṃ, hatthigavāssavaḷavaṃ jātidhammaṃ, jātarūparajataṃ jātidhammaṃ.**Partners and children, male and female bondservants, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and elephants and cattle are liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[4383]="*Jātidhammā hete, bhikkhave, upadhayo.**These attachments are liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[4384]="*Etthāyaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhāpanno attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone who is tied, infatuated, and attached to such things, themselves liable to being reborn, seeks what is also liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[4385]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, jarādhammaṃ vadetha?**And what should be described as liable to grow old?*";
P_HTM[4386]="*Puttabhariyaṃ, bhikkhave, jarādhammaṃ, dāsidāsaṃ jarādhammaṃ, ajeḷakaṃ jarādhammaṃ, kukkuṭasūkaraṃ jarādhammaṃ, hatthigavāssavaḷavaṃ jarādhammaṃ, jātarūparajataṃ jarādhammaṃ.**Partners and children, male and female bondservants, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and elephants and cattle are liable to grow old.*";
P_HTM[4387]="*Jarādhammā hete, bhikkhave, upadhayo.**These attachments are liable to grow old.*";
P_HTM[4388]="*Etthāyaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhāpanno attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone who is tied, infatuated, and attached to such things, themselves liable to grow old, seeks what is also liable to grow old.*";
P_HTM[4389]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, byādhidhammaṃ vadetha?**And what should be described as liable to fall sick?*";
P_HTM[4390]="*Puttabhariyaṃ, bhikkhave, byādhidhammaṃ, dāsidāsaṃ byādhidhammaṃ, ajeḷakaṃ byādhidhammaṃ, kukkuṭasūkaraṃ byādhidhammaṃ, hatthigavāssavaḷavaṃ byādhidhammaṃ.**Partners and children, male and female bondservants, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and elephants and cattle are liable to fall sick.*";
P_HTM[4391]="*Byādhidhammā hete, bhikkhave, upadhayo.**These attachments are liable to fall sick.*";
P_HTM[4392]="*Etthāyaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhāpanno attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone who is tied, infatuated, and attached to such things, themselves liable to falling sick, seeks what is also liable to fall sick.*";
P_HTM[4393]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, maraṇadhammaṃ vadetha?**And what should be described as liable to die?*";
P_HTM[4394]="*Puttabhariyaṃ, bhikkhave, maraṇadhammaṃ, dāsidāsaṃ maraṇadhammaṃ, ajeḷakaṃ maraṇadhammaṃ, kukkuṭasūkaraṃ maraṇadhammaṃ, hatthigavāssavaḷavaṃ maraṇadhammaṃ.**Partners and children, male and female bondservants, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and elephants and cattle are liable to die.*";
P_HTM[4395]="*Maraṇadhammā hete, bhikkhave, upadhayo.**These attachments are liable to die.*";
P_HTM[4396]="*Etthāyaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhāpanno attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone who is tied, infatuated, and attached to such things, themselves liable to die, seeks what is also liable to die.*";
P_HTM[4397]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sokadhammaṃ vadetha?**And what should be described as liable to sorrow?*";
P_HTM[4398]="*Puttabhariyaṃ, bhikkhave, sokadhammaṃ, dāsidāsaṃ sokadhammaṃ, ajeḷakaṃ sokadhammaṃ, kukkuṭasūkaraṃ sokadhammaṃ, hatthigavāssavaḷavaṃ sokadhammaṃ.**Partners and children, male and female bondservants, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and elephants and cattle are liable to sorrow.*";
P_HTM[4399]="*Sokadhammā hete, bhikkhave, upadhayo.**These attachments are liable to sorrow.*";
P_HTM[4400]="*Etthāyaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhāpanno attanā sokadhammo samāno sokadhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone who is tied, infatuated, and attached to such things, themselves liable to sorrow, seeks what is also liable to sorrow.*";
P_HTM[4401]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, saṅkilesadhammaṃ vadetha?**And what should be described as liable to corruption?*";
P_HTM[4402]="*Puttabhariyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅkilesadhammaṃ, dāsidāsaṃ saṅkilesadhammaṃ, ajeḷakaṃ saṅkilesadhammaṃ, kukkuṭasūkaraṃ saṅkilesadhammaṃ, hatthigavāssavaḷavaṃ saṅkilesadhammaṃ, jātarūparajataṃ saṅkilesadhammaṃ.**Partners and children, male and female bondservants, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, elephants and cattle, and gold and money are liable to corruption.*";
P_HTM[4403]="*Saṅkilesadhammā hete, bhikkhave, upadhayo.**These attachments are liable to corruption.*";
P_HTM[4404]="*Etthāyaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhāpanno attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhammaṃyeva pariyesati.**Someone who is tied, infatuated, and attached to such things, themselves liable to corruption, seeks what is also liable to corruption.*";
P_HTM[4405]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, anariyā pariyesanā.**This is the ignoble search.*";
P_HTM[4406]="*Katamā ca, bhikkhave, ariyā pariyesanā?**And what is the noble search?*";
P_HTM[4407]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajātaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati, attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati, attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā abyādhiṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati, attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā amataṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati, attanā sokadhammo samāno sokadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asokaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati, attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asaṅkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesati.**It’s when someone who is themselves liable to be reborn, understanding the drawbacks in being liable to be reborn, seeks the unborn supreme sanctuary, extinguishment. Themselves liable to grow old, fall sick, die, sorrow, and become corrupted, understanding the drawbacks in these things, they seek the unaging, unailing, undying, sorrowless, uncorrupted supreme sanctuary, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[4408]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyā pariyesanā.**This is the noble search.*";
P_HTM[4409]="*Ahampi sudaṃ, bhikkhave, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddho bodhisattova samāno attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi, attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi, attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi, attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi, attanā sokadhammo samāno sokadhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi, attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi.**Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too, being liable to be reborn, sought what is also liable to be reborn. Myself liable to grow old, fall sick, die, sorrow, and become corrupted, I sought what is also liable to these things.*";
P_HTM[4410]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[4411]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi, attanā jarādhammo samāno … pe … byādhidhammo samāno … maraṇadhammo samāno … sokadhammo samāno … attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhammaṃyeva pariyesāmi?**‘Why do I, being liable to be reborn, grow old, fall sick, sorrow, die, and become corrupted, seek things that have the same nature?*";
P_HTM[4412]="*Yannūnāhaṃ attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajātaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyeseyyaṃ, attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyeseyyaṃ, attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā abyādhiṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyeseyyaṃ, attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā amataṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyeseyyaṃ, attanā sokadhammo samāno sokadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asokaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyeseyyaṃ, attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asaṅkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyeseyyan’ti.**Why don’t I seek the unborn, unaging, unailing, undying, sorrowless, uncorrupted supreme sanctuary, extinguishment?’*";
P_HTM[4413]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, aparena samayena daharova samāno susukāḷakeso, bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ.**Some time later, while still black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life—though my mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces—I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4414]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ. upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**Once I had gone forth I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4415]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso kālāma, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend Kālāma, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[4416]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, āḷāro kālāmo maṃ etadavoca:**Āḷāra Kālāma replied,*";
P_HTM[4417]="*‘viharatāyasmā;**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[4418]="*tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own tradition with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[4419]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[4420]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi theravādañca, ‘jānāmi passāmī’ti ca paṭijānāmi ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[4421]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4422]="*‘na kho āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti;**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Āḷāra Kālāma declares: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[4423]="*addhā āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharatī’ti.**Surely he meditates knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[4424]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4425]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, to what extent do you say you’ve realized this teaching with your own insight?’*";
P_HTM[4426]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, āḷāro kālāmo ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, he declared the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[4427]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4428]="*‘na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Āḷāra Kālāma who has faith,*";
P_HTM[4429]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi vīriyaṃ, mayhampatthi vīriyaṃ;**energy,*";
P_HTM[4430]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi sati, mayhampatthi sati;**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[4431]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi samādhi, mayhampatthi samādhi;**immersion,*";
P_HTM[4432]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi paññā, mayhampatthi paññā.**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[4433]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ āḷāro kālāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti, tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Āḷāra Kālāma says he has realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[4434]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[4435]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4436]="*‘Ettāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, have you realized this teaching with your own insight up to this point, and declare having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[4437]="*‘Ettāvatā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemī’ti.**‘I have, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[4438]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too, reverend, have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[4439]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[4440]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[4441]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi.**So the teaching that I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[4442]="*Yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[4443]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi, yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi.**So the teaching that I know, you know, and the teaching that you know, I know.*";
P_HTM[4444]="*Iti yādiso ahaṃ tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso ahaṃ.**I am like you and you are like me.*";
P_HTM[4445]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, ubhova santā imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharāmā’ti.**Come now, reverend! We should both lead this community together.’*";
P_HTM[4446]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, āḷāro kālāmo ācariyo me samāno attano antevāsiṃ maṃ samānaṃ attanā samasamaṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my teacher Āḷāra Kālāma placed me, his student, on the same position as him, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[4447]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4448]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva ākiñcaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of nothingness.’*";
P_HTM[4449]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4450]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃ kusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4451]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[4452]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, udako rāmaputto maṃ etadavoca:**Uddaka replied,*";
P_HTM[4453]="*‘viharatāyasmā;**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[4454]="*tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own tradition with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[4455]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[4456]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi theravādañca, ‘jānāmi passāmī’ti ca paṭijānāmi ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[4457]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4458]="*‘na kho rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi;**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Rāma declared: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[4459]="*addhā rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ vihāsī’ti.**Surely he meditated knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[4460]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4461]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, to what extent did Rāma say he’d realized this teaching with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[4462]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, udako rāmaputto nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, Uddaka, son of Rāma, declared the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4463]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4464]="*‘na kho rāmasseva ahosi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Rāma who had faith,*";
P_HTM[4465]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi vīriyaṃ, mayhampatthi vīriyaṃ;**energy,*";
P_HTM[4466]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi sati, mayhampatthi sati;**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[4467]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi samādhi, mayhampatthi samādhi,**immersion,*";
P_HTM[4468]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi paññā, mayhampatthi paññā.**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[4469]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi, tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Rāma said he had realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[4470]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[4471]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4472]="*‘Ettāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, had Rāma realized this teaching with his own insight up to this point, and declared having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[4473]="*‘Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti.**‘He had, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[4474]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[4475]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[4476]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[4477]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi, taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi.**So the teaching that Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[4478]="*Yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi, taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[4479]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi, yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi, taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi.**So the teaching that Rāma directly knew, you know, and the teaching you know, Rāma directly knew.*";
P_HTM[4480]="*Iti yādiso rāmo ahosi tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso rāmo ahosi.**Rāma was like you and you are like Rāma.*";
P_HTM[4481]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, tuvaṃ imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharā’ti.**Come now, reverend! You should lead this community.’*";
P_HTM[4482]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, udako rāmaputto sabrahmacārī me samāno ācariyaṭṭhāne maṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my spiritual companion Uddaka, son of Rāma, placed me in the position of a teacher, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[4483]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4484]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’*";
P_HTM[4485]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4486]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃ kusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno magadhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena uruvelā senānigamo tadavasariṃ.**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. Traveling stage by stage in the Magadhan lands, I arrived at Senanigama near Uruvelā.*";
P_HTM[4487]="*Tatthaddasaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ, pāsādikañca vanasaṇḍaṃ, nadiñca sandantiṃ setakaṃ supatitthaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ, samantā ca gocaragāmaṃ.**There I saw a delightful park, a lovely grove with a flowing river that was clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby was a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[4488]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4489]="*‘ramaṇīyo vata bho bhūmibhāgo, pāsādiko ca vanasaṇḍo, nadī ca sandati setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā, samantā ca gocaragāmo.**‘This park is truly delightful, a lovely grove with a flowing river that’s clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby there’s a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[4490]="*Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāyā’ti.**This is good enough for a gentleman who wishes to put forth effort in meditation.’*";
P_HTM[4491]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, tattheva nisīdiṃ—**So I sat down right there, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4492]="*alamidaṃ padhānāyāti.**‘This is good enough for meditation.’*";
P_HTM[4493]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, attanā jātidhammo samāno jātidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajātaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamāno ajātaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃ, attanā jarādhammo samāno jarādhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamāno ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃ, attanā byādhidhammo samāno byādhidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā abyādhiṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamāno abyādhiṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃ, attanā maraṇadhammo samāno maraṇadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā amataṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃ, attanā sokadhammo samāno sokadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asokaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃ, attanā saṅkilesadhammo samāno saṅkilesadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asaṅkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamāno asaṅkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃ.**And so, being myself liable to be reborn, understanding the drawbacks in being liable to be reborn, I sought the unborn supreme sanctuary, extinguishment—and I found it. Being myself liable to grow old, fall sick, die, sorrow, and become corrupted, understanding the drawbacks in these things, I sought the unaging, unailing, undying, sorrowless, uncorrupted supreme sanctuary, extinguishment—and I found it.*";
P_HTM[4494]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**Knowledge and vision arose in me:*";
P_HTM[4495]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’ti.**‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’*";
P_HTM[4496]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4497]="*‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo.**‘This principle I have discovered is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[4498]="*Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā.**But people like attachment, they love it and enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[4499]="*Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ—idappaccayatā paṭiccasamuppādo.**It’s hard for them to see this thing; that is, specific conditionality, dependent origination.*";
P_HTM[4500]="*Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ yadidaṃ—sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ.**It’s also hard for them to see this thing; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[4501]="*Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ, so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā’ti.**And if I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which would be wearying and troublesome for me.’*";
P_HTM[4502]="*Apissu maṃ, bhikkhave, imā anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā:**And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[4503]="*‘Kicchena me adhigataṃ,**‘I’ve struggled hard to realize this,*";
P_HTM[4504]="*halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ;**enough with trying to explain it!*";
P_HTM[4505]="*Rāgadosaparetehi,**This teaching is not easily understood*";
P_HTM[4506]="*nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho.**by those mired in greed and hate.*";
P_HTM[4507]="*Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ,**Those caught up in greed can’t see*";
P_HTM[4508]="*gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ;**what’s subtle, going against the stream,*";
P_HTM[4509]="*Rāgarattā na dakkhanti,**deep, hard to see, and very fine,*";
P_HTM[4510]="*tamokhandhena āvuṭā’ti.**for they’re shrouded in a mass of darkness.’*";
P_HTM[4511]="*Itiha me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati, no dhammadesanāya.**So, as I reflected like this, my mind inclined to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[4512]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmuno sahampatissa mama cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya etadahosi:**Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing what I was thinking, thought,*";
P_HTM[4513]="*‘nassati vata bho loko, vinassati vata bho loko, yatra hi nāma tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati, no dhammadesanāyā’ti.**‘Oh my goodness! The world will be lost, the world will perish! For the mind of the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, inclines to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.’*";
P_HTM[4514]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito mama purato pāturahosi.**Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4515]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yenāhaṃ tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā maṃ etadavoca:**He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said,*";
P_HTM[4516]="*‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ.**‘Sir, let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! Let the Holy One teach the Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[4517]="*Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā, assavanatā dhammassa parihāyanti.**There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because they haven’t heard the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4518]="*Bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro’ti.**There will be those who understand the teaching!’*";
P_HTM[4519]="*Idamavoca, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati.**That’s what Brahmā Sahampati said.*";
P_HTM[4520]="*Idaṃ vatvā athāparaṃ etadavoca:**Then he went on to say:*";
P_HTM[4521]="*‘Pāturahosi magadhesu pubbe,**‘Among the Magadhans there appeared in the past*";
P_HTM[4522]="*Dhammo asuddho samalehi cintito;**an impure teaching thought up by those still stained.*";
P_HTM[4523]="*Apāpuretaṃ amatassa dvāraṃ,**Fling open the door to the deathless!*";
P_HTM[4524]="*Suṇantu dhammaṃ vimalenānubuddhaṃ.**Let them hear the teaching the immaculate one discovered.*";
P_HTM[4525]="*Sele yathā pabbatamuddhaniṭṭhito,**Standing high on a rocky mountain,*";
P_HTM[4526]="*Yathāpi passe janataṃ samantato;**you can see the people all around.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*Tathūpamaṃ dhammamayaṃ sumedha,**In just the same way, all-seer, wise one,*";
P_HTM[4528]="*Pāsādamāruyha samantacakkhu;**ascend the palace built of Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[4529]="*Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ janatamapetasoko,**You’re free of sorrow; but look at these people*";
P_HTM[4530]="*Avekkhassu jātijarābhibhūtaṃ.**overwhelmed with sorrow, oppressed by rebirth and old age.*";
P_HTM[4531]="*Uṭṭhehi vīra vijitasaṅgāma,**Rise, hero! Victor in battle, leader of the caravan,*";
P_HTM[4532]="*Satthavāha aṇaṇa vicara loke;**wander the world without obligation.*";
P_HTM[4533]="*Desassu bhagavā dhammaṃ,**Let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[4534]="*Aññātāro bhavissantī’ti.**There will be those who understand!’*";
P_HTM[4535]="*Atha kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmuno ca ajjhesanaṃ viditvā sattesu ca kāruññataṃ paṭicca buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokesiṃ.**Then, understanding Brahmā’s invitation, I surveyed the world with the eye of a Buddha, because of my compassion for sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[4536]="*Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe, tikkhindriye mudindriye, svākāre dvākāre, suviññāpaye duviññāpaye, appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante.**And I saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes; with keen faculties and with weak faculties, with good qualities and with bad qualities, easy to teach and hard to teach. And some of them lived seeing the danger in the fault to do with the next world, while others did not.*";
P_HTM[4537]="*Seyyathāpi nāma uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni antonimuggaposīni, appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni samodakaṃ ṭhitāni, appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakaṃ accuggamma ṭhitāni anupalittāni udakena;**It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. Some of them sprout and grow in the water reaching the water’s surface. And some of them sprout and grow in the water but rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to them.*";
P_HTM[4538]="*evameva kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento addasaṃ satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe, tikkhindriye mudindriye, svākāre dvākāre, suviññāpaye duviññāpaye, appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante.**In the same way, I saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes.*";
P_HTM[4539]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmānaṃ sahampatiṃ gāthāya paccabhāsiṃ:**Then I replied in verse to Brahmā Sahampati:*";
P_HTM[4540]="*‘Apārutā tesaṃ amatassa dvārā,**‘Flung open are the doors to the deathless!*";
P_HTM[4541]="*Ye sotavanto pamuñcantu saddhaṃ;**Let those with ears to hear decide their faith.*";
P_HTM[4542]="*Vihiṃsasaññī paguṇaṃ na bhāsiṃ,**Thinking it would be troublesome, Brahmā, I did not teach*";
P_HTM[4543]="*Dhammaṃ paṇītaṃ manujesu brahme’ti.**the sophisticated, sublime Dhamma among humans.’*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati ‘katāvakāso khomhi bhagavatā dhammadesanāyā’ti maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi.**Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing that his request for me to teach the Dhamma had been granted, bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right, before vanishing right there.*";
P_HTM[4545]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[4546]="*‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;**‘Who should I teach first of all?*";
P_HTM[4547]="*ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti?**Who will quickly understand this teaching?’*";
P_HTM[4548]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4549]="*‘ayaṃ kho āḷāro kālāmo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātiko.**‘That Āḷāra Kālāma is astute, competent, clever, and has long had little dust in his eyes.*";
P_HTM[4550]="*Yannūnāhaṃ āḷārassa kālāmassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ.**Why don’t I teach him first of all?*";
P_HTM[4551]="*So imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti.**He’ll quickly understand the teaching.’*";
P_HTM[4552]="*Atha kho maṃ, bhikkhave, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca:**But a deity came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[4553]="*‘sattāhakālaṅkato, bhante, āḷāro kālāmo’ti.**‘Sir, Āḷāra Kālāma passed away seven days ago.’*";
P_HTM[4554]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**And knowledge and vision arose in me,*";
P_HTM[4555]="*‘sattāhakālaṅkato āḷāro kālāmo’ti.**‘Āḷāra Kālāma passed away seven days ago.’*";
P_HTM[4556]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**I thought,*";
P_HTM[4557]="*‘mahājāniyo kho āḷāro kālāmo.**‘This is a great loss for Āḷāra Kālāma.*";
P_HTM[4558]="*Sace hi so imaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, khippameva ājāneyyā’ti.**If he had heard the teaching, he would have understood it quickly.’*";
P_HTM[4559]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[4560]="*‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;**‘Who should I teach first of all?*";
P_HTM[4561]="*ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti?**Who will quickly understand this teaching?’*";
P_HTM[4562]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4563]="*‘ayaṃ kho udako rāmaputto paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātiko.**‘That Uddaka, son of Rāma, is astute, competent, clever, and has long had little dust in his eyes.*";
P_HTM[4564]="*Yannūnāhaṃ udakassa rāmaputtassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ.**Why don’t I teach him first of all?*";
P_HTM[4565]="*So imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti.**He’ll quickly understand the teaching.’*";
P_HTM[4566]="*Atha kho maṃ, bhikkhave, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca:**But a deity came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[4567]="*‘abhidosakālaṅkato, bhante, udako rāmaputto’ti.**‘Sir, Uddaka, son of Rāma, passed away just last night.’*";
P_HTM[4568]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**And knowledge and vision arose in me,*";
P_HTM[4569]="*‘abhidosakālaṅkato udako rāmaputto’ti.**‘Uddaka, son of Rāma, passed away just last night.’*";
P_HTM[4570]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**I thought,*";
P_HTM[4571]="*‘mahājāniyo kho udako rāmaputto.**‘This is a great loss for Uddaka.*";
P_HTM[4572]="*Sace hi so imaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, khippameva ājāneyyā’ti.**If he had heard the teaching, he would have understood it quickly.’*";
P_HTM[4573]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[4574]="*‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;**‘Who should I teach first of all?*";
P_HTM[4575]="*ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti?**Who will quickly understand this teaching?’*";
P_HTM[4576]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[4577]="*‘bahukārā kho me pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū, ye maṃ padhānapahitattaṃ upaṭṭhahiṃsu.**‘The group of five mendicants were very helpful to me. They looked after me during my time of resolute striving.*";
P_HTM[4578]="*Yannūnāhaṃ pañcavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan’ti.**Why don’t I teach them first of all?’*";
P_HTM[4579]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[4580]="*‘kahaṃ nu kho etarahi pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū viharantī’ti?**‘Where are the group of five mendicants staying these days?’*";
P_HTM[4581]="*Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena pañcavaggiye bhikkhū bārāṇasiyaṃ viharante isipatane migadāye.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman I saw that the group of five mendicants were staying near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[4582]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, uruvelāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena bārāṇasī tena cārikaṃ pakkamiṃ.**So, when I had stayed in Uruvelā as long as I wished, I set out for Benares.*";
P_HTM[4583]="*Addasā kho maṃ, bhikkhave, upako ājīvako antarā ca gayaṃ antarā ca bodhiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannaṃ.**While I was traveling along the road between Gaya and Bodhgaya, the Ājīvaka ascetic Upaka saw me*";
P_HTM[4584]="*Disvāna maṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[4585]="*‘vippasannāni kho te, āvuso, indriyāni, parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto.**‘Reverend, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[4586]="*Kaṃsi tvaṃ, āvuso, uddissa pabbajito, ko vā te satthā, kassa vā tvaṃ dhammaṃ rocesī’ti?**In whose name have you gone forth, reverend? Who is your Teacher? Whose teaching do you believe in?’*";
P_HTM[4587]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, upakaṃ ājīvakaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsiṃ:**I replied to Upaka in verse:*";
P_HTM[4588]="*‘Sabbābhibhū sabbavidūhamasmi,**‘I am the champion, the knower of all,*";
P_HTM[4589]="*Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalitto;**unsullied in the midst of all things.*";
P_HTM[4590]="*Sabbañjaho taṇhākkhaye vimutto,**I’ve given up all, freed through the ending of craving.*";
P_HTM[4591]="*Sayaṃ abhiññāya kamuddiseyyaṃ.**When I know for myself, who should I follow?*";
P_HTM[4592]="*Na me ācariyo atthi,**I have no teacher.*";
P_HTM[4593]="*sadiso me na vijjati;**There is no-one like me.*";
P_HTM[4594]="*Sadevakasmiṃ lokasmiṃ,**In the world with its gods,*";
P_HTM[4595]="*natthi me paṭipuggalo.**I have no counterpart.*";
P_HTM[4596]="*Ahañhi arahā loke,**For in this world, I am the perfected one;*";
P_HTM[4597]="*ahaṃ satthā anuttaro;**I am the supreme Teacher.*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Ekomhi sammāsambuddho,**I alone am fully awakened,*";
P_HTM[4599]="*sītibhūtosmi nibbuto.**cooled, extinguished.*";
P_HTM[4600]="*Dhammacakkaṃ pavattetuṃ,**I am going to the city of Kāsi*";
P_HTM[4601]="*Gacchāmi kāsinaṃ puraṃ;**to roll forth the Wheel of Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[4602]="*Andhībhūtasmiṃ lokasmiṃ,**In this world that is so blind,*";
P_HTM[4603]="*Āhañchaṃ amatadundubhin’ti.**I’ll beat the deathless drum!’*";
P_HTM[4604]="*‘Yathā kho tvaṃ, āvuso, paṭijānāsi, arahasi anantajino’ti.**‘According to what you claim, reverend, you ought to be the Infinite Victor.’*";
P_HTM[4605]="*‘Mādisā ve jinā honti,**‘The victors are those who, like me,*";
P_HTM[4606]="*ye pattā āsavakkhayaṃ;**have reached the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4607]="*Jitā me pāpakā dhammā,**I have conquered bad qualities, Upaka—*";
P_HTM[4608]="*tasmāhamupaka jino’ti.**that’s why I’m a victor.’*";
P_HTM[4609]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, upako ājīvako ‘hupeyyapāvuso’ti vatvā sīsaṃ okampetvā ummaggaṃ gahetvā pakkāmi.**When I had spoken, Upaka said: ‘If you say so, reverend.’ Shaking his head, he took a wrong turn and left.*";
P_HTM[4610]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bārāṇasī isipatanaṃ migadāyo yena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃ.**Traveling stage by stage, I arrived at Benares, and went to see the group of five mendicants in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[4611]="*Addasaṃsu kho maṃ, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū dūrato āgacchantaṃ.**The group of five mendicants saw me coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[4612]="*Disvāna aññamaññaṃ saṇṭhapesuṃ:**and stopped each other, saying,*";
P_HTM[4613]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, samaṇo gotamo āgacchati bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya.**‘Here comes the ascetic Gotama. He’s so indulgent; he strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.*";
P_HTM[4614]="*So neva abhivādetabbo, na paccuṭṭhātabbo; nāssa pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**We shouldn’t bow to him or rise for him or receive his bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[4615]="*Api ca kho āsanaṃ ṭhapetabbaṃ, sace ākaṅkhissati nisīdissatī’ti.**But we can set out a seat; he can sit if he likes.’*";
P_HTM[4616]="*Yathā yathā kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, upasaṅkamiṃ tathā tathā pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu sakāya katikāya saṇṭhātuṃ.**Yet as I drew closer, the group of five mendicants were unable to stop themselves as they had agreed.*";
P_HTM[4617]="*Appekacce maṃ paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesuṃ, appekacce āsanaṃ paññapesuṃ, appekacce pādodakaṃ upaṭṭhapesuṃ.**Some came out to greet me and receive my bowl and robe, some spread out a seat, while others set out water for washing my feet.*";
P_HTM[4618]="*Api ca kho maṃ nāmena ca āvusovādena ca samudācaranti.**But they still addressed me by name and as ‘reverend’.*";
P_HTM[4619]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So I said to them,*";
P_HTM[4620]="*‘mā, bhikkhave, tathāgataṃ nāmena ca āvusovādena ca samudācaratha.**‘Mendicants, don’t address me by name and as ‘reverend’.*";
P_HTM[4621]="*Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.**The Realized One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4622]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ, amatamadhigataṃ, ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[4623]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.**By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[4624]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**But they said to me,*";
P_HTM[4625]="*‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ, kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti?**‘Reverend Gotama, even by that conduct, that practice, that grueling work you did not achieve any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones. How could you have achieved such a state now that you’ve become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence?’*";
P_HTM[4626]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So I said to them,*";
P_HTM[4627]="*‘na, bhikkhave, tathāgato bāhulliko, na padhānavibbhanto, na āvatto bāhullāya.**‘The Realized One has not become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.*";
P_HTM[4628]="*Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.**The Realized One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4629]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ, amatamadhigataṃ, ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[4630]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.**By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life.’*";
P_HTM[4631]="*Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**But for a second time they said to me,*";
P_HTM[4632]="*‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ, kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti?**‘Reverend Gotama … you’ve returned to indulgence.’*";
P_HTM[4633]="*Dutiyampi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So for a second time I said to them,*";
P_HTM[4634]="*‘na, bhikkhave, tathāgato bāhulliko … pe …**‘The Realized One has not become indulgent …’*";
P_HTM[4635]="*upasampajja viharissathā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4636]="*Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**But for a third time they said to me,*";
P_HTM[4637]="*‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ, kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti?**‘Reverend Gotama, even by that conduct, that practice, that grueling work you did not achieve any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones. How could you have achieved such a state now that you’ve become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence?’*";
P_HTM[4638]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So I said to them,*";
P_HTM[4639]="*‘abhijānātha me no tumhe, bhikkhave, ito pubbe evarūpaṃ pabhāvitametan’ti?**‘Mendicants, have you ever known me to speak like this before?’*";
P_HTM[4640]="*‘No hetaṃ, bhante’.**‘No sir, we have not.’*";
P_HTM[4641]="*‘Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.**‘The Realized One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4642]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ, amatamadhigataṃ, ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[4643]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.**By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[4644]="*Asakkhiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū saññāpetuṃ.**I was able to persuade the group of five mendicants.*";
P_HTM[4645]="*Dvepi sudaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ovadāmi, tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caranti.**Then sometimes I advised two mendicants, while the other three went for alms.*";
P_HTM[4646]="*Yaṃ tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā āharanti tena chabbaggiyā yāpema.**Then those three would feed all six of us with what they brought back.*";
P_HTM[4647]="*Tayopi sudaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ovadāmi, dve bhikkhū piṇḍāya caranti.**Sometimes I advised three mendicants, while the other two went for alms.*";
P_HTM[4648]="*Yaṃ dve bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā āharanti tena chabbaggiyā yāpema.**Then those two would feed all six of us with what they brought back.*";
P_HTM[4649]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū mayā evaṃ ovadiyamānā evaṃ anusāsiyamānā attanā jātidhammā samānā jātidhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajātaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamānā ajātaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃsu, attanā jarādhammā samānā jarādhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamānā ajaraṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃsu, attanā byādhidhammā samānā … pe … attanā maraṇadhammā samānā … attanā sokadhammā samānā … attanā saṃkilesadhammā samānā saṃkilesadhamme ādīnavaṃ viditvā asaṃkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ pariyesamānā asaṃkiliṭṭhaṃ anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ nibbānaṃ ajjhagamaṃsu.**As the group of five mendicants were being advised and instructed by me like this, being themselves liable to be reborn, understanding the drawbacks in being liable to be reborn, they sought the unborn supreme sanctuary, extinguishment—and they found it. Being themselves liable to grow old, fall sick, die, sorrow, and become corrupted, understanding the drawbacks in these things, they sought the unaging, unailing, undying, sorrowless, uncorrupted supreme sanctuary, extinguishment—and they found it.*";
P_HTM[4650]="*Ñāṇañca pana nesaṃ dassanaṃ udapādi:**Knowledge and vision arose in them:*";
P_HTM[4651]="*‘akuppā no vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’ti.**‘Our freedom is unshakable; this is our last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’*";
P_HTM[4652]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā.**Mendicants, there are these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[4653]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4654]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[4655]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[4656]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[4657]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[4658]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[4659]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[4660]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ime pañca kāmaguṇe gathitā mucchitā ajjhopannā anādīnavadassāvino anissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjanti, te evamassu veditabbā:**There are ascetics and brahmins who enjoy these five kinds of sensual stimulation tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape. You should understand that they*";
P_HTM[4661]="*‘anayamāpannā byasanamāpannā yathākāmakaraṇīyā pāpimato’.**have met with calamity and disaster, and are vulnerable to the Wicked One.*";
P_HTM[4662]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, āraññako mago baddho pāsarāsiṃ adhisayeyya.**Suppose a deer in the wilderness was lying caught on a pile of snares.*";
P_HTM[4663]="*So evamassa veditabbo:**You’d know that it*";
P_HTM[4664]="*‘anayamāpanno byasanamāpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo luddassa.**has met with calamity and disaster, and is vulnerable to the hunter.*";
P_HTM[4665]="*Āgacchante ca pana ludde yena kāmaṃ na pakkamissatī’ti.**And when the hunter comes, it cannot flee where it wants.*";
P_HTM[4666]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ime pañca kāmaguṇe gathitā mucchitā ajjhopannā anādīnavadassāvino anissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjanti, te evamassu veditabbā:**In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who enjoy these five kinds of sensual stimulation tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape. You should understand that they*";
P_HTM[4667]="*‘anayamāpannā byasanamāpannā yathākāmakaraṇīyā pāpimato’.**have met with calamity and disaster, and are vulnerable to the Wicked One.*";
P_HTM[4668]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ime pañca kāmaguṇe agathitā amucchitā anajjhopannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjanti, te evamassu veditabbā:**There are ascetics and brahmins who enjoy these five kinds of sensual stimulation without being tied, infatuated, or attached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape. You should understand that they*";
P_HTM[4669]="*‘na anayamāpannā na byasanamāpannā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā pāpimato’.**haven’t met with calamity and disaster, and are not vulnerable to the Wicked One.*";
P_HTM[4670]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, āraññako mago abaddho pāsarāsiṃ adhisayeyya.**Suppose a deer in the wilderness was lying on a pile of snares without being caught.*";
P_HTM[4671]="*So evamassa veditabbo:**You’d know that it*";
P_HTM[4672]="*‘na anayamāpanno na byasanamāpanno na yathākāmakaraṇīyo luddassa.**hasn’t met with calamity and disaster, and isn’t vulnerable to the hunter.*";
P_HTM[4673]="*Āgacchante ca pana ludde yena kāmaṃ pakkamissatī’ti.**And when the hunter comes, it can flee where it wants.*";
P_HTM[4674]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ime pañca kāmaguṇe agathitā amucchitā anajjhopannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjanti, te evamassu veditabbā:**In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who enjoy these five kinds of sensual stimulation without being tied, infatuated, or attached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape. You should understand that they*";
P_HTM[4675]="*‘na anayamāpannā na byasanamāpannā na yathākāmakaraṇīyā pāpimato’.**haven’t met with calamity and disaster, and are not vulnerable to the Wicked One.*";
P_HTM[4676]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, āraññako mago araññe pavane caramāno vissattho gacchati, vissattho tiṭṭhati, vissattho nisīdati, vissattho seyyaṃ kappeti.**Suppose there was a wild deer wandering in the forest that walked, stood, sat, and laid down in confidence.*";
P_HTM[4677]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4678]="*Anāpāthagato, bhikkhave, luddassa.**Because it’s out of the hunter’s range.*";
P_HTM[4679]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**In the same way, a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4680]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu andhamakāsi māraṃ apadaṃ, vadhitvā māracakkhuṃ adassanaṃ gato pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra, put out his eyes without a trace, and gone where the Wicked One cannot see.*";
P_HTM[4681]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4682]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4683]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[4684]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4685]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4686]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4687]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[4688]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4689]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4690]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4691]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[4692]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4693]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4694]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave … pe … pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra …*";
P_HTM[4695]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end.*";
P_HTM[4696]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu andhamakāsi māraṃ apadaṃ, vadhitvā māracakkhuṃ adassanaṃ gato pāpimato.**This is called a mendicant who has blinded Māra, put out his eyes without a trace, and gone where the Wicked One cannot see.*";
P_HTM[4697]="*Tiṇṇo loke visattikaṃ vissattho gacchati, vissattho tiṭṭhati, vissattho nisīdati, vissattho seyyaṃ kappeti.**They’ve crossed over clinging to the world. And they walk, stand, sit, and lie down in confidence.*";
P_HTM[4698]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4699]="*Anāpāthagato, bhikkhave, pāpimato”ti.**Because they’re out of the Wicked One’s range.”*";
P_HTM[4700]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4701]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4702]="*Pāsarāsisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4703]="*27. Cūḷahatthipadopamasutta**The Shorter Elephant’s Footprint Simile*";
P_HTM[4704]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4705]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4706]="*Tena kho pana samayena jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena sāvatthiyā niyyāti divādivassa.**Now at that time the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi drove out from Sāvatthī in the middle of the day in an all-white chariot drawn by mares.*";
P_HTM[4707]="*Addasā kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo pilotikaṃ paribbājakaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**He saw the wanderer Pilotika coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[4708]="*Disvāna pilotikaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4709]="*“Handa kuto nu bhavaṃ vacchāyano āgacchati divādivassā”ti?**“So, Master Vacchāyana, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?”*";
P_HTM[4710]="*“Ito hi kho ahaṃ, bho, āgacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa santikā”ti.**“Just now, good sir, I’ve come from the presence of the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[4711]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññati bhavaṃ vacchāyano samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ paṇḍito maññe”ti.**“What do you think of the ascetic Gotama’s lucidity of wisdom? Do you think he’s astute?”*";
P_HTM[4712]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jānissāmi.**“My good man, who am I to judge the ascetic Gotama’s lucidity of wisdom?*";
P_HTM[4713]="*Sopi nūnassa tādisova yo samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jāneyyā”ti.**You’d really have to be on the same level to judge his lucidity of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[4714]="*“Uḷārāya khalu bhavaṃ vacchāyano samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsāya pasaṃsatī”ti.**“Master Vacchāyana praises the ascetic Gotama with lofty praise indeed.”*";
P_HTM[4715]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsissāmi,**“Who am I to praise the ascetic Gotama?*";
P_HTM[4716]="*pasatthapasatthova so bhavaṃ gotamo seṭṭho devamanussānan”ti.**He is praised by the praised as the best of gods and humans.”*";
P_HTM[4717]="*“Kaṃ pana bhavaṃ vacchāyano atthavasaṃ sampassamāno samaṇe gotame evaṃ abhippasanno”ti?**“But for what reason are you so devoted to the ascetic Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[4718]="*“Seyyathāpi, bho, kusalo nāgavaniko nāgavanaṃ paviseyya.**“Suppose that a skilled elephant tracker were to enter an elephant wood.*";
P_HTM[4719]="*So passeyya nāgavane mahantaṃ hatthipadaṃ, dīghato ca āyataṃ, tiriyañca vitthataṃ.**There he’d see a large elephant’s footprint, long and broad.*";
P_HTM[4720]="*So niṭṭhaṃ gaccheyya:**He’d draw the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4721]="*‘mahā vata bho nāgo’ti.**‘This must be a big bull elephant.’*";
P_HTM[4722]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, bho, yato addasaṃ samaṇe gotame cattāri padāni athāhaṃ niṭṭhamagamaṃ:**In the same way, because I saw four footprints of the ascetic Gotama I drew the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4723]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[4724]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4725]="*Idhāhaṃ, bho, passāmi ekacce khattiyapaṇḍite nipuṇe kataparappavāde vālavedhirūpe, te bhindantā maññe caranti paññāgatena diṭṭhigatāni.**Firstly, I see some clever aristocrats who are subtle, accomplished in the doctrines of others, hair-splitters. You’d think they live to demolish convictions with their intellect.*";
P_HTM[4726]="*Te suṇanti:**They hear,*";
P_HTM[4727]="*‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osarissatī’ti.**‘So, gentlemen, that ascetic Gotama will come down to such and such village or town.’*";
P_HTM[4728]="*Te pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharonti:**They formulate a question, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4729]="*‘imaṃ mayaṃ pañhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchissāma.**‘We’ll approach the ascetic Gotama and ask him this question.*";
P_HTM[4730]="*Evañce no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evamassa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāma.**If he answers like this, we’ll refute him like that;*";
P_HTM[4731]="*Evañcepi no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evampissa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāmā’ti.**and if he answers like that, we’ll refute him like this.’*";
P_HTM[4732]="*Te suṇanti:**When they hear that*";
P_HTM[4733]="*‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osaṭo’ti.**he has come down*";
P_HTM[4734]="*Te yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkamanti.**they approach him.*";
P_HTM[4735]="*Te samaṇo gotamo dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti.**The ascetic Gotama educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires them with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[4736]="*Te samaṇena gotamena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā na ceva samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, kutossa vādaṃ āropessanti?**They don’t even get around to asking their question to the ascetic Gotama, so how could they refute his answer?*";
P_HTM[4737]="*Aññadatthu samaṇasseva gotamassa sāvakā sampajjanti.**Invariably, they become his disciples.*";
P_HTM[4738]="*Yadāhaṃ, bho, samaṇe gotame imaṃ paṭhamaṃ padaṃ addasaṃ athāhaṃ niṭṭhamagamaṃ:**When I saw this first footprint of the ascetic Gotama, I drew the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4739]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti. (1)**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[4740]="*Puna caparāhaṃ, bho, passāmi idhekacce brāhmaṇapaṇḍite … pe … (2)**Furthermore, I see some clever brahmins …*";
P_HTM[4741]="*gahapatipaṇḍite …**some clever householders …*";
P_HTM[4742]="*pe … (3)**they become his disciples.*";
P_HTM[4743]="*samaṇapaṇḍite nipuṇe kataparappavāde vālavedhirūpe te bhindantā maññe caranti paññāgatena diṭṭhigatāni.**Furthermore, I see some clever ascetics who are subtle, accomplished in the doctrines of others, hair-splitters. …*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Te suṇanti:* **";
P_HTM[4745]="*‘samaṇo khalu bho gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osarissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4746]="*Te pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharonti ‘imaṃ mayaṃ pañhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchissāma.* **";
P_HTM[4747]="*Evañce no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evamassa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāma.* **";
P_HTM[4748]="*Evañcepi no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evampissa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4749]="*Te suṇanti ‘samaṇo khalu bho gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osaṭo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4750]="*Te yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkamanti.* **";
P_HTM[4751]="*Te samaṇo gotamo dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti.* **";
P_HTM[4752]="*Te samaṇena gotamena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā na ceva samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, kutossa vādaṃ āropessanti?**They don’t even get around to asking their question to the ascetic Gotama, so how could they refute his answer?*";
P_HTM[4753]="*Aññadatthu samaṇaṃyeva gotamaṃ okāsaṃ yācanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**Invariably, they ask the ascetic Gotama for the chance to go forth.*";
P_HTM[4754]="*Te samaṇo gotamo pabbājeti.**And he gives them the going-forth.*";
P_HTM[4755]="*Te tattha pabbajitā samānā vūpakaṭṭhā appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharantā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**Soon after going forth, living withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, they realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4756]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say,*";
P_HTM[4757]="*‘manaṃ vata, bho, anassāma, manaṃ vata, bho, panassāma;**‘We were almost lost! We almost perished!*";
P_HTM[4758]="*mayañhi pubbe assamaṇāva samānā samaṇamhāti paṭijānimha, abrāhmaṇāva samānā brāhmaṇamhāti paṭijānimha, anarahantova samānā arahantamhāti paṭijānimha.**For we used to claim that we were ascetics, brahmins, and perfected ones, but we were none of these things.*";
P_HTM[4759]="*Idāni khomha samaṇā, idāni khomha brāhmaṇā, idāni khomha arahanto’ti.**But now we really are ascetics, brahmins, and perfected ones!’*";
P_HTM[4760]="*Yadāhaṃ, bho, samaṇe gotame imaṃ catutthaṃ padaṃ addasaṃ athāhaṃ niṭṭhamagamaṃ:**When I saw this fourth footprint of the ascetic Gotama, I drew the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4761]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti. (4)**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[4762]="*Yato kho ahaṃ, bho, samaṇe gotame imāni cattāri padāni addasaṃ athāhaṃ niṭṭhamagamaṃ:**It’s because I saw these four footprints of the ascetic Gotama that I drew the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4763]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’”ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’”*";
P_HTM[4764]="*Evaṃ vutte, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo sabbasetā vaḷavābhirathā orohitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udānesi:**When he had spoken, Jāṇussoṇi got down from his chariot, arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and was inspired to exclaim three times:*";
P_HTM[4765]="*“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4766]="*namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa;**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4767]="*namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassāti.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4768]="*Appeva nāma mayampi kadāci karahaci tena bhotā gotamena saddhiṃ samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti.**Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet Master Gotama, and we can have a discussion.”*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Atha kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4770]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[4771]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yāvatako ahosi pilotikena paribbājakena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[4773]="*“na kho, brāhmaṇa, ettāvatā hatthipadopamo vitthārena paripūro hoti.**“Brahmin, the simile of the elephant’s footprint is not yet completed in detail.*";
P_HTM[4774]="*Api ca, brāhmaṇa, yathā hatthipadopamo vitthārena paripūro hoti**As to how it is completed in detail,*";
P_HTM[4775]="*taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4776]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes sir,” Jāṇussoṇi replied.*";
P_HTM[4777]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4778]="*“Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, nāgavaniko nāgavanaṃ paviseyya.**“Suppose that an elephant tracker were to enter an elephant wood.*";
P_HTM[4779]="*So passeyya nāgavane mahantaṃ hatthipadaṃ, dīghato ca āyataṃ, tiriyañca vitthataṃ.**There they’d see a large elephant’s footprint, long and broad.*";
P_HTM[4780]="*Yo hoti kusalo nāgavaniko neva tāva niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**A skilled elephant tracker wouldn’t yet come to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4781]="*‘mahā vata bho nāgo’ti.**‘This must be a big bull elephant.’*";
P_HTM[4782]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[4783]="*Santi hi, brāhmaṇa, nāgavane vāmanikā nāma hatthiniyo mahāpadā, tāsaṃ petaṃ padaṃ assāti.**Because in an elephant wood there are dwarf she-elephants with big footprints, and this footprint might be one of theirs.*";
P_HTM[4784]="*So tamanugacchati.* **";
P_HTM[4785]="*Tamanugacchanto passati nāgavane mahantaṃ hatthipadaṃ, dīghato ca āyataṃ, tiriyañca vitthataṃ, uccā ca nisevitaṃ.**They keep following the track until they see a big footprint, long and broad, and, high up, signs of usage.*";
P_HTM[4786]="*Yo hoti kusalo nāgavaniko neva tāva niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**A skilled elephant tracker wouldn’t yet come to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4787]="*‘mahā vata bho nāgo’ti.**‘This must be a big bull elephant.’*";
P_HTM[4788]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[4789]="*Santi hi, brāhmaṇa, nāgavane uccā kāḷārikā nāma hatthiniyo mahāpadā, tāsaṃ petaṃ padaṃ assāti.**Because in an elephant wood there are tall she-elephants with long trunks and big footprints, and this footprint might be one of theirs.*";
P_HTM[4790]="*So tamanugacchati.* **";
P_HTM[4791]="*Tamanugacchanto passati nāgavane mahantaṃ hatthipadaṃ, dīghato ca āyataṃ, tiriyañca vitthataṃ, uccā ca nisevitaṃ, uccā ca dantehi ārañjitāni.**They keep following the track until they see a big footprint, long and broad, and, high up, signs of usage and tusk-marks.*";
P_HTM[4792]="*Yo hoti kusalo nāgavaniko neva tāva niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**A skilled elephant tracker wouldn’t yet come to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4793]="*‘mahā vata bho nāgo’ti.**‘This must be a big bull elephant.’*";
P_HTM[4794]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[4795]="*Santi hi, brāhmaṇa, nāgavane uccā kaṇerukā nāma hatthiniyo mahāpadā, tāsaṃ petaṃ padaṃ assāti.**Because in an elephant wood there are tall and fully-grown she-elephants with big footprints, and this footprint might be one of theirs.*";
P_HTM[4796]="*So tamanugacchati.* **";
P_HTM[4797]="*Tamanugacchanto passati nāgavane mahantaṃ hatthipadaṃ, dīghato ca āyataṃ, tiriyañca vitthataṃ, uccā ca nisevitaṃ, uccā ca dantehi ārañjitāni, uccā ca sākhābhaṅgaṃ.**They keep following the track until they see a big footprint, long and broad, and, high up, signs of usage, tusk-marks, and broken branches.*";
P_HTM[4798]="*Tañca nāgaṃ passati rukkhamūlagataṃ vā abbhokāsagataṃ vā gacchantaṃ vā tiṭṭhantaṃ vā nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā.**And they see that bull elephant walking, standing, sitting, or lying down at the root of a tree or in the open.*";
P_HTM[4799]="*So niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**Then they’d come to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4800]="*‘ayameva so mahānāgo’ti.**‘This is that big bull elephant.’*";
P_HTM[4801]="*Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, idha tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**In the same way, brahmin, a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[4802]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He realizes with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[4803]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ; kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely complete and pure.*";
P_HTM[4804]="*Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto.**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some good family.*";
P_HTM[4805]="*So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati.**They gain faith in the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[4806]="*So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:**and reflect,*";
P_HTM[4807]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajopatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[4808]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[4809]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[4810]="*So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4811]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[4812]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī. Athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati.**They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving.*";
P_HTM[4813]="*Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.**They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[4814]="*Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa.**They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words.*";
P_HTM[4815]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[4816]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable, and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[4817]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[4818]="*So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid injuring plants and seeds.*";
P_HTM[4819]="*ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato, virato vikālabhojanā,**They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[4820]="*naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.*";
P_HTM[4821]="*mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, perfumes, and makeup.*";
P_HTM[4822]="*uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid high and luxurious beds.*";
P_HTM[4823]="*jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid receiving gold and money,*";
P_HTM[4824]="*āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**raw grains,*";
P_HTM[4825]="*āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**raw meat,*";
P_HTM[4826]="*itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**women and girls,*";
P_HTM[4827]="*dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**male and female bondservants,*";
P_HTM[4828]="*ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**goats and sheep,*";
P_HTM[4829]="*kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**chickens and pigs,*";
P_HTM[4830]="*hatthigavāssavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**elephants, cows, horses, and mares,*";
P_HTM[4831]="*khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**and fields and land.*";
P_HTM[4832]="*dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid running errands and messages;*";
P_HTM[4833]="*kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti,**buying and selling;*";
P_HTM[4834]="*tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti,**falsifying weights, metals, or measures;*";
P_HTM[4835]="*ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti,**bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;*";
P_HTM[4836]="*chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti.**mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.*";
P_HTM[4837]="*So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[4838]="*Seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti sapattabhārova ḍeti;**They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden.*";
P_HTM[4839]="*evameva bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[4840]="*So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[4841]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they see a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[4842]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[4843]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[4844]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[4845]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[4846]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[4847]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[4848]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[4849]="*So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[4850]="*So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti.**They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.*";
P_HTM[4851]="*So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato**When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble contentment, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness,*";
P_HTM[4852]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[4853]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya, parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[4854]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*Byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will.*";
P_HTM[4856]="*Thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[4857]="*Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati, ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[4858]="*Vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[4859]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe,**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4860]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4861]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa, tathāgatapadaṃ itipi, tathāgatanisevitaṃ itipi, tathāgatārañjitaṃ itipi.**This, brahmin, is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ and also ‘used by the Realized One’ and also ‘marked by the Realized One’.*";
P_HTM[4862]="*Na tveva tāva ariyasāvako niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**But a noble disciple wouldn’t yet come to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4863]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[4864]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa … pe …**This too is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ …*";
P_HTM[4866]="*suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4867]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa … pe …**This too is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ …*";
P_HTM[4869]="*suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4870]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa, tathāgatapadaṃ itipi, tathāgatanisevitaṃ itipi, tathāgatārañjitaṃ itipi.**This too is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ …*";
P_HTM[4872]="*Na tveva tāva ariyasāvako niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:* **";
P_HTM[4873]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4874]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[4875]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ, dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives, that is, one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. … They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[4876]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa, tathāgatapadaṃ itipi, tathāgatanisevitaṃ itipi, tathāgatārañjitaṃ itipi.**This too is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ …*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Na tveva tāva ariyasāvako niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:* **";
P_HTM[4878]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4879]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[4880]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human, they understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[4881]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa, tathāgatapadaṃ itipi, tathāgatanisevitaṃ itipi, tathāgatārañjitaṃ itipi.**This too is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ …*";
P_HTM[4882]="*Na tveva tāva ariyasāvako niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:* **";
P_HTM[4883]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4884]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4885]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[4886]="*‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[4887]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa, tathāgatapadaṃ itipi, tathāgatanisevitaṃ itipi, tathāgatārañjitaṃ itipi.**This, brahmin, is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ and also ‘used by the Realized One’ and also ‘marked by the Realized One’.*";
P_HTM[4888]="*Na tveva tāva ariyasāvako niṭṭhaṃ gato hoti, api ca kho niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**At this point a noble disciple has not yet come to a conclusion, but they are coming to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4889]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[4890]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4891]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[4892]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[4893]="*Idampi vuccati, brāhmaṇa, tathāgatapadaṃ itipi, tathāgatanisevitaṃ itipi, tathāgatārañjitaṃ itipi.**This, brahmin, is called ‘a footprint of the Realized One’ and also ‘used by the Realized One’ and also ‘marked by the Realized One’.*";
P_HTM[4894]="*Ettāvatā kho, brāhmaṇa, ariyasāvako niṭṭhaṃ gato hoti:**At this point a noble disciple has come to the conclusion,*";
P_HTM[4895]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[4896]="*Ettāvatā kho, brāhmaṇa, hatthipadopamo vitthārena paripūro hotī”ti.**And it is at this point that the simile of the elephant’s footprint has been completed in detail.”*";
P_HTM[4897]="*Evaṃ vutte, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4898]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[4899]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[4900]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[4901]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4902]="*Cūḷahatthipadopamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4903]="*28. Mahāhatthipadopamasutta**The Longer Simile of the Elephant’s Footprint*";
P_HTM[4904]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4905]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4906]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4908]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4909]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[4910]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, yāni kānici jaṅgalānaṃ pāṇānaṃ padajātāni sabbāni tāni hatthipade samodhānaṃ gacchanti, hatthipadaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati yadidaṃ mahantattena;**“The footprints of all creatures that walk can fit inside an elephant’s footprint, so an elephant’s footprint is said to be the biggest of them all.*";
P_HTM[4911]="*evameva kho, āvuso, ye keci kusalā dhammā sabbete catūsu ariyasaccesu saṅgahaṃ gacchanti.**In the same way, all skillful qualities can be included in the four noble truths.*";
P_HTM[4912]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4913]="*Dukkhe ariyasacce, dukkhasamudaye ariyasacce, dukkhanirodhe ariyasacce, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasacce.**The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.*";
P_HTM[4914]="*Katamañcāvuso, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ?**And what is the noble truth of suffering?*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Jātipi dukkhā, jarāpi dukkhā, maraṇampi dukkhaṃ, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsāpi dukkhā, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ; saṅkhittena, pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā.**Rebirth is suffering; old age is suffering; death is suffering; sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are suffering; not getting what you wish for is suffering. In brief, the five grasping aggregates are suffering.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*Katame cāvuso, pañcupādānakkhandhā?**And what are the five grasping aggregates?*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho.**They are as follows: the grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4918]="*Katamo cāvuso, rūpupādānakkhandho?**And what is the grasping aggregate of form?*";
P_HTM[4919]="*Cattāri ca mahābhūtāni, catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāya rūpaṃ.**The four primary elements, and form derived from the four primary elements.*";
P_HTM[4920]="*Katamā cāvuso, cattāro mahābhūtā?**And what are the four primary elements?*";
P_HTM[4921]="*Pathavīdhātu, āpodhātu, tejodhātu, vāyodhātu.**The elements of earth, water, fire, and air.*";
P_HTM[4922]="*Katamā cāvuso, pathavīdhātu?**And what is the earth element?*";
P_HTM[4923]="*Pathavīdhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The earth element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[4924]="*Katamā cāvuso, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu?**And what is the interior earth element?*";
P_HTM[4925]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ kakkhaḷaṃ kharigataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything hard, solid, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[4926]="*kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ kakkhaḷaṃ kharigataṃ upādinnaṃ.**head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, intestines, mesentery, undigested food, feces, or anything else hard, solid, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[4927]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu.**This is called the interior earth element.*";
P_HTM[4928]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu, yā ca bāhirā pathavīdhātu, pathavīdhāturevesā.**The interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just the earth element.*";
P_HTM[4929]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4930]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindati, pathavīdhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you grow disillusioned with the earth element, detaching the mind from the earth element.*";
P_HTM[4931]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ bāhirā āpodhātu pakuppati.**There comes a time when the exterior water element flares up.*";
P_HTM[4932]="*Antarahitā tasmiṃ samaye bāhirā pathavīdhātu hoti.**At that time the exterior earth element vanishes.*";
P_HTM[4933]="*Tassā hi nāma, āvuso, bāhirāya pathavīdhātuyā tāva mahallikāya aniccatā paññāyissati, khayadhammatā paññāyissati, vayadhammatā paññāyissati, vipariṇāmadhammatā paññāyissati.**So for all its great age, the earth element will be revealed as impermanent, liable to end, vanish, and perish.*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Kiṃ panimassa mattaṭṭhakassa kāyassa taṇhupādinnassa ‘ahanti vā mamanti vā asmī’ti vā? Atha khvāssa notevettha hoti.**What then of this short-lived body derived from craving? Rather than take it to be ‘I’ or ‘mine’ or ‘I am’, they still just consider it to be none of these things.*";
P_HTM[4935]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ pare akkosanti paribhāsanti rosenti vihesenti, so evaṃ pajānāti:**If others abuse, attack, harass, and trouble that mendicant, they understand:*";
P_HTM[4936]="*‘uppannā kho me ayaṃ sotasamphassajā dukkhavedanā.**‘This painful feeling born of ear contact has arisen in me.*";
P_HTM[4937]="*Sā ca kho paṭicca, no apaṭicca.**That’s dependent, not independent.*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Kiṃ paṭicca?**Dependent on what?*";
P_HTM[4939]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca’.**Dependent on contact.’*";
P_HTM[4940]="*So phasso aniccoti passati, vedanā aniccāti passati, saññā aniccāti passati, saṅkhārā aniccāti passati, viññāṇaṃ aniccanti passati.**They see that contact, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[4941]="*Tassa dhātārammaṇameva cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati.**Based on that element alone, their mind becomes eager, confident, settled, and decided.*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ pare aniṭṭhehi akantehi amanāpehi samudācaranti—**Others might treat that mendicant with disliking, loathing, and detestation,*";
P_HTM[4943]="*pāṇisamphassenapi leḍḍusamphassenapi daṇḍasamphassenapi satthasamphassenapi.**striking them with fists, stones, sticks, and swords.*";
P_HTM[4944]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[4945]="*‘tathābhūto kho ayaṃ kāyo yathābhūtasmiṃ kāye pāṇisamphassāpi kamanti, leḍḍusamphassāpi kamanti, daṇḍasamphassāpi kamanti, satthasamphassāpi kamanti.**‘This body is such that fists, stones, sticks, and swords strike it.*";
P_HTM[4946]="*Vuttaṃ kho panetaṃ bhagavatā kakacūpamovāde:**But the Buddha has said in the Simile of the Saw:*";
P_HTM[4947]="*“ubhatodaṇḍakena cepi, bhikkhave, kakacena corā ocarakā aṅgamaṅgāni okanteyyuṃ, tatrāpi yo mano padūseyya na me so tena sāsanakaro”ti.**“Even if low-down bandits were to sever you limb from limb, anyone who had a malevolent thought on that account would not be following my instructions.”*";
P_HTM[4948]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ bhavissati asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ.**My energy shall be roused up and unflagging, my mindfulness established and lucid, my body tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[4949]="*Kāmaṃ dāni imasmiṃ kāye pāṇisamphassāpi kamantu, leḍḍusamphassāpi kamantu, daṇḍasamphassāpi kamantu, satthasamphassāpi kamantu, karīyati hidaṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanan’ti.**Gladly now, let fists, stones, sticks, and swords strike this body! For this is how the instructions of the Buddhas are followed.’*";
P_HTM[4950]="*Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhāti.**While recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful may not become stabilized in them.*";
P_HTM[4951]="*So tena saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:**In that case they stir up a sense of urgency:*";
P_HTM[4952]="*‘alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ,**‘It’s my loss, my misfortune,*";
P_HTM[4953]="*yassa me evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato, upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhātī’ti.**that while recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful does not become stabilized in me.’*";
P_HTM[4954]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, suṇisā sasuraṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati;**They’re like a daughter-in-law who stirs up a sense of urgency when they see their father-in-law.*";
P_HTM[4955]="*evameva kho, āvuso, tassa ce bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato, upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhāti, so tena saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:* **";
P_HTM[4956]="*‘alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ, yassa me evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato, upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhātī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4957]="*Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato upekkhā kusalanissitā saṇṭhāti, so tena attamano hoti.**But if, while recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful does become stabilized in them, they’re happy with that.*";
P_HTM[4958]="*Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bahukataṃ hoti.**At this point, much has been done by that mendicant.*";
P_HTM[4959]="*Katamā cāvuso, āpodhātu?**And what is the water element?*";
P_HTM[4960]="*Āpodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The water element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[4961]="*Katamā cāvuso, ajjhattikā āpodhātu?**And what is the interior water element?*";
P_HTM[4962]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ āpo āpogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s water, watery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[4963]="*pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttaṃ, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ āpo āpogataṃ upādinnaṃ—**bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine, or anything else that’s water, watery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[4964]="*ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, ajjhattikā āpodhātu.**This is called the interior water element.*";
P_HTM[4965]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā āpodhātu yā ca bāhirā āpodhātu, āpodhāturevesā.**The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water element.*";
P_HTM[4966]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4967]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā āpodhātuyā nibbindati, āpodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you grow disillusioned with the water element, detaching the mind from the water element.*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ bāhirā āpodhātu pakuppati.**There comes a time when the exterior water element flares up.*";
P_HTM[4969]="*Sā gāmampi vahati, nigamampi vahati, nagarampi vahati, janapadampi vahati, janapadapadesampi vahati.**It sweeps away villages, towns, cities, countries, and regions.*";
P_HTM[4970]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ mahāsamudde yojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti, dviyojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti, tiyojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti, catuyojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti, pañcayojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti, chayojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti, sattayojanasatikānipi udakāni ogacchanti.**There comes a time when the water in the ocean sinks down a hundred leagues, or two, three, four, five, six, up to seven hundred leagues.*";
P_HTM[4971]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ mahāsamudde sattatālampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, chattālampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, pañcatālampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, catuttālampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, titālampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, dvitālampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, tālamattampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti.**There comes a time when the water in the ocean stands just seven palm trees deep, or six, five, four, three, two, or even just one palm tree deep.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ mahāsamudde sattaporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, chapporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, pañcaporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, catupporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, tiporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, dviporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, porisamattampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti.**There comes a time when the water in the ocean stands just seven fathoms deep, or six, five, four, three, two, or even just one fathom deep.*";
P_HTM[4973]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ mahāsamudde aḍḍhaporisampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, kaṭimattampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, jāṇukamattampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti, gopphakamattampi udakaṃ saṇṭhāti.**There comes a time when the water in the ocean stands just half a fathom deep, or waist deep, or knee deep, or even just ankle deep.*";
P_HTM[4974]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo, yaṃ mahāsamudde aṅgulipabbatemanamattampi udakaṃ na hoti.**There comes a time when there isn’t enough water in the ocean even to wet the tip of your finger.*";
P_HTM[4975]="*Tassā hi nāma, āvuso, bāhirāya āpodhātuyā tāva mahallikāya aniccatā paññāyissati, khayadhammatā paññāyissati, vayadhammatā paññāyissati, vipariṇāmadhammatā paññāyissati.**So for all its great age, the water element will be revealed as impermanent, liable to end, vanish, and perish.*";
P_HTM[4976]="*Kiṃ panimassa mattaṭṭhakassa kāyassa taṇhupādinnassa ‘ahanti vā mamanti vā asmī’ti vā? Atha khvāssa notevettha hoti … pe …**What then of this short-lived body produced by craving? Rather than take it to be ‘I’ or ‘mine’ or ‘I am’, they still just consider it to be none of these things. …*";
P_HTM[4977]="*tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṃghaṃ anussarato upekkhā kusalanissitā saṇṭhāti. So tena attamano hoti.**If, while recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful does become stabilized in them, they’re happy with that.*";
P_HTM[4978]="*Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bahukataṃ hoti.**At this point, much has been done by that mendicant.*";
P_HTM[4979]="*Katamā cāvuso, tejodhātu?**And what is the fire element?*";
P_HTM[4980]="*Tejodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The fire element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[4981]="*Katamā cāvuso, ajjhattikā tejodhātu?**And what is the interior fire element?*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ tejo tejogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s fire, fiery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[4983]="*yena ca santappati, yena ca jīrīyati, yena ca pariḍayhati, yena ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ sammā pariṇāmaṃ gacchati, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ tejo tejogataṃ upādinnaṃ—**that which warms, that which ages, that which heats you up when feverish, that which properly digests food and drink, or anything else that’s fire, fiery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[4984]="*ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, ajjhattikā tejodhātu.**This is called the interior fire element.*";
P_HTM[4985]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā tejodhātu yā ca bāhirā tejodhātu, tejodhāturevesā.**The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire element.*";
P_HTM[4986]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[4987]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā tejodhātuyā nibbindati, tejodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you grow disillusioned with the fire element, detaching the mind from the fire element.*";
P_HTM[4988]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ bāhirā tejodhātu pakuppati.**There comes a time when the exterior fire element flares up.*";
P_HTM[4989]="*Sā gāmampi dahati, nigamampi dahati, nagarampi dahati, janapadampi dahati, janapadapadesampi dahati.**It burns up villages, towns, cities, countries, and regions until*";
P_HTM[4990]="*Sā haritantaṃ vā panthantaṃ vā selantaṃ vā udakantaṃ vā ramaṇīyaṃ vā bhūmibhāgaṃ āgamma anāhārā nibbāyati.**it reaches a green field, a roadside, a cliff’s edge, a body of water, or cleared parkland, where it’s extinguished for lack of fuel.*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ kukkuṭapattenapi nhārudaddulenapi aggiṃ gavesanti.**There comes a time when they go looking for a fire, taking just chicken feathers and strips of sinew as kindling.*";
P_HTM[4992]="*Tassā hi nāma, āvuso, bāhirāya tejodhātuyā tāva mahallikāya aniccatā paññāyissati, khayadhammatā paññāyissati, vayadhammatā paññāyissati, vipariṇāmadhammatā paññāyissati.**So for all its great age, the fire element will be revealed as impermanent, liable to end, vanish, and perish.*";
P_HTM[4993]="*Kiṃ panimassa mattaṭṭhakassa kāyassa taṇhupādinnassa ‘ahanti vā mamanti vā asmī’ti vā?**What then of this short-lived body derived from craving? Rather than take it to be ‘I’ or ‘mine’ or ‘I am’, they still just consider it to be none of these things. …*";
P_HTM[4994]="*Atha khvāssa notevettha hoti … pe … tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato upekkhā kusalanissitā saṇṭhāti, so tena attamano hoti.**If, while recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful does become stabilized in them, they’re happy with that.*";
P_HTM[4995]="*Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bahukataṃ hoti.**At this point, much has been done by that mendicant.*";
P_HTM[4996]="*Katamā cāvuso, vāyodhātu?**And what is the air element?*";
P_HTM[4997]="*Vāyodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The air element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[4998]="*Katamā cāvuso, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu?**And what is the interior air element?*";
P_HTM[4999]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ vāyo vāyogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s wind, windy, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[5000]="*uddhaṅgamā vātā, adhogamā vātā, kucchisayā vātā, koṭṭhāsayā vātā, aṅgamaṅgānusārino vātā, assāso passāso iti, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ vāyo vāyogataṃ upādinnaṃ—**winds that go up or down, winds in the belly or the bowels, winds that flow through the limbs, in-breaths and out-breaths, or anything else that’s wind, windy, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[5001]="*ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu.**This is called the interior air element.*";
P_HTM[5002]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā vāyodhātu, yā ca bāhirā vāyodhātu, vāyodhāturevesā.**The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air element.*";
P_HTM[5003]="*‘Taṃ netaṃ mama nesohamasmi na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[5004]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā vāyodhātuyā nibbindati vāyodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the air element, detaching the mind from the air element.*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ bāhirā vāyodhātu pakuppati.**There comes a time when the exterior air element flares up.*";
P_HTM[5006]="*Sā gāmampi vahati, nigamampi vahati, nagarampi vahati, janapadampi vahati, janapadapadesampi vahati.**It sweeps away villages, towns, cities, countries, and regions.*";
P_HTM[5007]="*Hoti kho so, āvuso, samayo yaṃ gimhānaṃ pacchime māse tālavaṇṭenapi vidhūpanenapi vātaṃ pariyesanti, ossavanepi tiṇāni na icchanti.**There comes a time, in the last month of summer, when they look for wind by using a palm-leaf or fan, and even the grasses in the drip-fringe of a thatch roof don’t stir.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Tassā hi nāma, āvuso, bāhirāya vāyodhātuyā tāva mahallikāya aniccatā paññāyissati, khayadhammatā paññāyissati, vayadhammatā paññāyissati, vipariṇāmadhammatā paññāyissati.**So for all its great age, the air element will be revealed as impermanent, liable to end, vanish, and perish.*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Kiṃ panimassa mattaṭṭhakassa kāyassa taṇhupādinnassa ‘ahanti vā mamanti vā asmī’ti vā? Atha khvāssa notevettha hoti.**What then of this short-lived body derived from craving? Rather than take it to be ‘I’ or ‘mine’ or ‘I am’, they still just consider it to be none of these things. …*";
P_HTM[5010]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ pare akkosanti paribhāsanti rosenti vihesenti.**If others abuse, attack, harass, and trouble that mendicant, they understand:*";
P_HTM[5011]="*So evaṃ pajānāti, uppannā kho me ayaṃ sotasamphassajā dukkhā vedanā.**‘This painful feeling born of ear contact has arisen in me.*";
P_HTM[5012]="*Sā ca kho paṭicca, no apaṭicca.**That’s dependent, not independent.*";
P_HTM[5013]="*Kiṃ paṭicca?**Dependent on what?*";
P_HTM[5014]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca.**Dependent on contact.*";
P_HTM[5015]="*Sopi phasso aniccoti passati, vedanā aniccāti passati, saññā aniccāti passati, saṅkhārā aniccāti passati, viññāṇaṃ aniccanti passati.**They see that contact, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[5016]="*Tassa dhātārammaṇameva cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati.**Based on that element alone, their mind becomes eager, confident, settled, and decided.*";
P_HTM[5017]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ pare aniṭṭhehi akantehi amanāpehi samudācaranti, pāṇisamphassenapi leḍḍusamphassenapi daṇḍasamphassenapi satthasamphassenapi.**Others might treat that mendicant with disliking, loathing, and detestation, striking them with fists, stones, sticks, and swords.*";
P_HTM[5018]="*So evaṃ pajānāti ‘tathābhūto kho ayaṃ kāyo yathābhūtasmiṃ kāye pāṇisamphassāpi kamanti, leḍḍusamphassāpi kamanti, daṇḍasamphassāpi kamanti, satthasamphassāpi kamanti.**They understand: ‘This body is such that fists, stones, sticks, and swords strike it.*";
P_HTM[5019]="*Vuttaṃ kho panetaṃ bhagavatā kakacūpamovāde “ubhatodaṇḍakena cepi, bhikkhave, kakacena corā ocarakā aṅgamaṅgāni okanteyyuṃ. Tatrāpi yo mano padūseyya, na me so tena sāsanakaro”ti.**But the Buddha has said in the Simile of the Saw: “Even if low-down bandits were to sever you limb from limb, anyone who had a thought of hate on that account would not be following my instructions.”*";
P_HTM[5020]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ bhavissati asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ.**My energy shall be roused up and unflagging, my mindfulness established and lucid, my body tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[5021]="*Kāmaṃ dāni imasmiṃ kāye pāṇisamphassāpi kamantu, leḍḍusamphassāpi kamantu, daṇḍasamphassāpi kamantu, satthasamphassāpi kamantu. Karīyati hidaṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanan’ti.**Gladly now, let fists, stones, sticks, and swords strike this body! For this is how the instructions of the Buddhas are followed.’*";
P_HTM[5022]="*Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhāti.**While recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful may not become stabilized in them.*";
P_HTM[5023]="*So tena saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:**In that case they stir up a sense of urgency:*";
P_HTM[5024]="*‘alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ.**‘It’s my loss, my misfortune,*";
P_HTM[5025]="*Yassa me evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhātī’ti.**that while recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful does not become stabilized in me.’*";
P_HTM[5026]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, suṇisā sasuraṃ disvā saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati;**They’re like a daughter-in-law who stirs up a sense of urgency when they see their father-in-law.*";
P_HTM[5027]="*evameva kho, āvuso, tassa ce bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato, upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhāti.* **";
P_HTM[5028]="*So tena saṃvijjati saṃvegaṃ āpajjati:* **";
P_HTM[5029]="*‘alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5030]="*Yassa me evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato, upekkhā kusalanissitā na saṇṭhātī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5031]="*Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno evaṃ buddhaṃ anussarato, evaṃ dhammaṃ anussarato, evaṃ saṅghaṃ anussarato, upekkhā kusalanissitā saṇṭhāti, so tena attamano hoti.**But if, while recollecting the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in this way, equanimity based on the skillful does become stabilized in them, they’re happy with that.*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bahukataṃ hoti.**At this point, much has been done by that mendicant.*";
P_HTM[5033]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṭṭhañca paṭicca valliñca paṭicca tiṇañca paṭicca mattikañca paṭicca ākāso parivārito agārantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati;**When a space is enclosed by sticks, creepers, grass, and mud it becomes known as a ‘building’.*";
P_HTM[5034]="*evameva kho, āvuso, aṭṭhiñca paṭicca nhāruñca paṭicca maṃsañca paṭicca cammañca paṭicca ākāso parivārito rūpantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**In the same way, when a space is enclosed by bones, sinews, flesh, and skin it becomes known as a ‘form’.*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Ajjhattikañceva, āvuso, cakkhuṃ aparibhinnaṃ hoti, bāhirā ca rūpā na āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, no ca tajjo samannāhāro hoti, neva tāva tajjassa viññāṇabhāgassa pātubhāvo hoti.**Reverends, though the eye is intact internally, so long as exterior sights don’t come into range and there’s no corresponding engagement, there’s no manifestation of the corresponding type of consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5036]="*Ajjhattikañceva, āvuso, cakkhuṃ aparibhinnaṃ hoti bāhirā ca rūpā āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, no ca tajjo samannāhāro hoti, neva tāva tajjassa viññāṇabhāgassa pātubhāvo hoti.**Though the eye is intact internally and exterior sights come into range, so long as there’s no corresponding engagement, there’s no manifestation of the corresponding type of consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5037]="*Yato ca kho, āvuso, ajjhattikañceva cakkhuṃ aparibhinnaṃ hoti, bāhirā ca rūpā āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, tajjo ca samannāhāro hoti. Evaṃ tajjassa viññāṇabhāgassa pātubhāvo hoti.**But when the eye is intact internally and exterior sights come into range and there is corresponding engagement, there is the manifestation of the corresponding type of consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Yaṃ tathābhūtassa rūpaṃ taṃ rūpupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati, yā tathābhūtassa vedanā sā vedanupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati, yā tathābhūtassa saññā sā saññupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati, ye tathābhūtassa saṅkhārā te saṅkhārupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchanti, yaṃ tathābhūtassa viññāṇaṃ taṃ viññāṇupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati.**The form produced in this way is included in the grasping aggregate of form. The feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness produced in this way are each included in the corresponding grasping aggregate.*";
P_HTM[5039]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[5040]="*‘evañhi kira imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ saṅgaho sannipāto samavāyo hoti.**‘So this is how there comes to be inclusion, gathering together, and joining together into these five grasping aggregates.*";
P_HTM[5041]="*Vuttaṃ kho panetaṃ bhagavatā:**But the Buddha has said:*";
P_HTM[5042]="*“yo paṭiccasamuppādaṃ passati so dhammaṃ passati;**“One who sees dependent origination sees the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5043]="*yo dhammaṃ passati so paṭiccasamuppādaṃ passatī”ti.**One who sees the teaching sees dependent origination.”*";
P_HTM[5044]="*Paṭiccasamuppannā kho panime yadidaṃ pañcupādānakkhandhā.**And these five grasping aggregates are indeed dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[5045]="*Yo imesu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chando ālayo anunayo ajjhosānaṃ so dukkhasamudayo.**The desire, adherence, attraction, and attachment for these five grasping aggregates is the origin of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5046]="*Yo imesu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, so dukkhanirodho’ti.**Giving up and getting rid of desire and greed for these five grasping aggregates is the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bahukataṃ hoti.**At this point, much has been done by that mendicant.*";
P_HTM[5048]="*Ajjhattikañceva, āvuso, sotaṃ aparibhinnaṃ hoti … pe …**Though the ear …*";
P_HTM[5049]="*ghānaṃ aparibhinnaṃ hoti …**nose …*";
P_HTM[5050]="*jivhā aparibhinnā hoti …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[5051]="*kāyo aparibhinno hoti …**body …*";
P_HTM[5052]="*mano aparibhinno hoti, bāhirā ca dhammā na āpāthaṃ āgacchanti no ca tajjo samannāhāro hoti, neva tāva tajjassa viññāṇabhāgassa pātubhāvo hoti.**mind is intact internally, so long as exterior thoughts don’t come into range and there’s no corresponding engagement, there’s no manifestation of the corresponding type of consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5053]="*Ajjhattiko ceva, āvuso, mano aparibhinno hoti, bāhirā ca dhammā āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, no ca tajjo samannāhāro hoti, neva tāva tajjassa viññāṇabhāgassa pātubhāvo hoti.**Though the mind is intact internally and exterior thoughts come into range, so long as there’s no corresponding engagement, there’s no manifestation of the corresponding type of consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5054]="*Yato ca kho, āvuso, ajjhattiko ceva mano aparibhinno hoti, bāhirā ca dhammā āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, tajjo ca samannāhāro hoti, evaṃ tajjassa viññāṇabhāgassa pātubhāvo hoti.**But when the mind is intact internally and exterior thoughts come into range and there is corresponding engagement, there is the manifestation of the corresponding type of consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Yaṃ tathābhūtassa rūpaṃ taṃ rūpupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati, yā tathābhūtassa vedanā sā vedanupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati, yā tathābhūtassa saññā sā saññupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati, ye tathābhūtassa saṅkhārā te saṅkhārupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchanti, yaṃ tathābhūtassa viññāṇaṃ taṃ viññāṇupādānakkhandhe saṅgahaṃ gacchati.**The form produced in this way is included in the grasping aggregate of form. The feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness produced in this way are each included in the corresponding grasping aggregate.*";
P_HTM[5056]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[5057]="*‘evañhi kira imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ saṅgaho sannipāto samavāyo hoti.**‘So this is how there comes to be inclusion, gathering together, and joining together into these five grasping aggregates.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Vuttaṃ kho panetaṃ bhagavatā:**But the Buddha has also said:*";
P_HTM[5059]="*“yo paṭiccasamuppādaṃ passati so dhammaṃ passati;**“One who sees dependent origination sees the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5060]="*yo dhammaṃ passati so paṭiccasamuppādaṃ passatī”ti.**One who sees the teaching sees dependent origination.”*";
P_HTM[5061]="*Paṭiccasamuppannā kho panime yadidaṃ pañcupādānakkhandhā.**And these five grasping aggregates are indeed dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[5062]="*Yo imesu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chando ālayo anunayo ajjhosānaṃ so dukkhasamudayo.**The desire, adherence, attraction, and attachment for these five grasping aggregates is the origin of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5063]="*Yo imesu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ so dukkhanirodho’ti.**Giving up and getting rid of desire and greed for these five grasping aggregates is the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5064]="*Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bahukataṃ hotī”ti.**At this point, much has been done by that mendicant.”*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Idamavoca āyasmā sāriputto.**That’s what Venerable Sāriputta said.*";
P_HTM[5066]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what Sāriputta said.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Mahāhatthipadopamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5068]="*29. Mahāsāropamasutta**The Longer Simile of the Heartwood*";
P_HTM[5069]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5070]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left.*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[5072]="*“Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**“Mendicants, take the case of a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking,*";
P_HTM[5073]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5074]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5075]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5076]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5077]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attānukkaṃseti paraṃ vambheti:**And they glorify themselves and put others down because of that:*";
P_HTM[5078]="*‘ahamasmi lābhasakkārasilokavā, ime panaññe bhikkhū appaññātā appesakkhā’ti.**‘I’m the one with possessions, honor, and popularity. These other mendicants are obscure and insignificant.’*";
P_HTM[5079]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.**And so they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding those possessions, honor, and popularity. And being negligent they live in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5080]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But, passing over the heartwood, softwood, bark, and shoots, he’d cut off the branches and leaves and depart imagining they were heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5081]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say,*";
P_HTM[5082]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5083]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.**That’s why he passed them over, cut off the branches and leaves, and departed imagining they were heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5084]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’ …*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5086]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5087]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5088]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5089]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5090]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti ‘ahamasmi lābhasakkārasilokavā, ime panaññe bhikkhū appaññātā appesakkhā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5091]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[5092]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sākhāpalāsaṃ aggahesi brahmacariyassa;**This is called a mendicant who has grabbed the branches and leaves of the spiritual life*";
P_HTM[5093]="*tena ca vosānaṃ āpādi.**and stopped short with that.*";
P_HTM[5094]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[5095]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5096]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5097]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5098]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re not happy with that, and haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5099]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5100]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati.**Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding those possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.**Being diligent, they become accomplished in ethics.*";
P_HTM[5102]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5103]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:**And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that:*";
P_HTM[5104]="*‘ahamasmi sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo, ime panaññe bhikkhū dussīlā pāpadhammā’ti.**‘I’m the one who is ethical, of good character. These other mendicants are unethical, of bad character.’*";
P_HTM[5105]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.**And so they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding their accomplishment in ethics. And being negligent they live in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5106]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ, papaṭikaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But, passing over the heartwood, softwood, and bark, he’d cut off the shoots and depart imagining they were heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5107]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say,*";
P_HTM[5108]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5109]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ, papaṭikaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno;**That’s why he passed them over, cut off the shoots, and departed imagining they were heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5110]="*yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’ …*";
P_HTM[5111]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5112]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5113]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5114]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5115]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5116]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5117]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5118]="*Appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5119]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5120]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:* **";
P_HTM[5121]="*‘ahamasmi sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo, ime panaññe bhikkhū dussīlā pāpadhammā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5122]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[5123]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu papaṭikaṃ aggahesi brahmacariyassa;**This is called a mendicant who has grabbed the shoots of the spiritual life*";
P_HTM[5124]="*tena ca vosānaṃ āpādi.**and stopped short with that.*";
P_HTM[5125]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[5126]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5127]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5128]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity. …*";
P_HTM[5129]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5130]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5131]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5132]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5133]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5134]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5135]="*Appamatto samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.**Being diligent, they achieve immersion.*";
P_HTM[5136]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5137]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:**And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that:*";
P_HTM[5138]="*‘ahamasmi samāhito ekaggacitto, ime panaññe bhikkhū asamāhitā vibbhantacittā’ti.**‘I’m the one with immersion and unified mind. These other mendicants lack immersion, they have straying minds.’*";
P_HTM[5139]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.**And so they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that accomplishment in immersion. And being negligent they live in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5140]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ tacaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But, passing over the heartwood and softwood, he’d cut off the bark and depart imagining it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5141]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya ‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say: ‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5142]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ tacaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.**That’s why he passed them over, cut off the bark, and departed imagining it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5143]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’ …*";
P_HTM[5144]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5145]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5146]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5147]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5148]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5149]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5150]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5151]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5152]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5153]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5154]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5155]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:* **";
P_HTM[5156]="*‘ahamasmi samāhito ekaggacitto, ime panaññe bhikkhū asamāhitā vibbhantacittā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5157]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[5158]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tacaṃ aggahesi brahmacariyassa;**This is called a mendicant who has grabbed the bark of the spiritual life*";
P_HTM[5159]="*tena ca vosānaṃ āpādi.**and stopped short with that.*";
P_HTM[5160]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[5161]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5162]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5163]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity. …*";
P_HTM[5164]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5165]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5166]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5167]="*Appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5168]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5169]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5170]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5171]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5172]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5173]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati appamatto samāno ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti.**Being diligent, they achieve knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5174]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5175]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:**And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that,*";
P_HTM[5176]="*‘ahamasmi jānaṃ passaṃ viharāmi.**‘I’m the one who meditates knowing and seeing.*";
P_HTM[5177]="*Ime panaññe bhikkhū ajānaṃ apassaṃ viharantī’ti.**These other mendicants meditate without knowing and seeing.’*";
P_HTM[5178]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.**And so they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that knowledge and vision. And being negligent they live in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5179]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ phegguṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But, passing over the heartwood, he’d cut out the softwood and depart imagining it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5180]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say,*";
P_HTM[5181]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ na aññāsi phegguṃ na aññāsi tacaṃ na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5182]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ phegguṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.**That’s why he passed them over, cut out the softwood, and departed imagining it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’ …*";
P_HTM[5184]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5185]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5186]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5187]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5188]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5189]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5190]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5191]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5192]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5193]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5194]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5195]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5196]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5197]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5198]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:* **";
P_HTM[5199]="*‘ahamasmi jānaṃ passaṃ viharāmi, ime panaññe bhikkhū ajānaṃ apassaṃ viharantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5200]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena majjati pamajjati pamādaṃ āpajjati, pamatto samāno dukkhaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[5201]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu phegguṃ aggahesi brahmacariyassa;**This is called a mendicant who has grabbed the softwood of the spiritual life*";
P_HTM[5202]="*tena ca vosānaṃ āpādi.**and stopped short with that.*";
P_HTM[5203]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking,*";
P_HTM[5204]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5205]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5206]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5207]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti, na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re not happy with that, and haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5208]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5209]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.**Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding those possessions, honor, and popularity. Being diligent, they become accomplished in ethics.*";
P_HTM[5210]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5211]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5212]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.**Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that accomplishment in ethics. Being diligent, they achieve immersion.*";
P_HTM[5213]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5214]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5215]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti.**Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that accomplishment in immersion. Being diligent, they achieve knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5216]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5217]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5218]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno asamayavimokkhaṃ ārādheti.**Nor do they become indulgent and fall into negligence regarding that knowledge and vision. Being diligent, they achieve permanent liberation.*";
P_HTM[5219]="*Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu tāya asamayavimuttiyā parihāyetha.**And it’s impossible for that mendicant to fall away from that irreversible liberation.*";
P_HTM[5220]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato sāraññeva chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti jānamāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. He’d cut out just the heartwood and depart knowing it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say,*";
P_HTM[5222]="*‘aññāsi vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāraṃ, aññāsi phegguṃ, aññāsi tacaṃ, aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**‘This gentleman knows what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, and branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5223]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato sāraññeva chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti jānamāno.**That’s why he cut out just the heartwood and departed knowing it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5224]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ anubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he will succeed.’ …*";
P_HTM[5225]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5226]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5227]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5228]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5229]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti, na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5230]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5231]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5232]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5233]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5234]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5235]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5236]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5237]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5238]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5239]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5240]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena na majjati nappamajjati na pamādaṃ āpajjati, appamatto samāno asamayavimokkhaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5241]="*Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu tāya asamayavimuttiyā parihāyetha.**It’s impossible for that mendicant to fall away from that irreversible liberation.*";
P_HTM[5242]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, nayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ lābhasakkārasilokānisaṃsaṃ, na sīlasampadānisaṃsaṃ, na samādhisampadānisaṃsaṃ, na ñāṇadassanānisaṃsaṃ.**And so, mendicants, this spiritual life is not lived for the sake of possessions, honor, and popularity, or for accomplishment in ethics, or for accomplishment in immersion, or for knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5243]="*Yā ca kho ayaṃ, bhikkhave, akuppā cetovimutti—**Rather, the goal, heartwood, and final end of the spiritual life is the unshakable freedom of heart.”*";
P_HTM[5244]="*etadatthamidaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyaṃ, etaṃ sāraṃ etaṃ pariyosānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5245]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5246]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5247]="*Mahāsāropamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5248]="*30. Cūḷasāropamasutta**The Shorter Simile of the Heartwood*";
P_HTM[5249]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5250]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5251]="*Atha kho piṅgalakoccho brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin Piṅgalakoccha went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5252]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho piṅgalakoccho brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[5253]="*“yeme, bho gotama, samaṇabrāhmaṇā saṃghino gaṇino gaṇācariyā ñātā yasassino titthakarā sādhusammatā, bahujanassa,**“Master Gotama, there are those ascetics and brahmins who lead an order and a community, and teach a community. They’re well-known and famous religious founders, regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*seyyathidaṃ—pūraṇo kassapo, makkhali gosālo, ajito kesakambalo, pakudho kaccāyano, sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto,**Namely: Pūraṇa Kassapa, Makkhali Gosāla, Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta, Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta, Pakudha Kaccāyana, and Ajita Kesakambala.*";
P_HTM[5255]="*sabbete sakāya paṭiññāya abbhaññaṃsu sabbeva nābbhaññaṃsu, udāhu ekacce abbhaññaṃsu ekacce nābbhaññaṃsū”ti?**According to their own claims, did all of them have direct knowledge, or none of them, or only some?”*";
P_HTM[5256]="*“Alaṃ, brāhmaṇa, tiṭṭhatetaṃ—**“Enough, brahmin, let this be:*";
P_HTM[5257]="*sabbete sakāya paṭiññāya abbhaññaṃsu sabbeva nābbhaññaṃsu, udāhu ekacce abbhaññaṃsu ekacce nābbhaññaṃsūti.**‘According to their own claims, did all of them have direct knowledge, or none of them, or only some?’*";
P_HTM[5258]="*Dhammaṃ te, brāhmaṇa, desessāmi,**I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[5259]="*taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5260]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho piṅgalakoccho brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes sir,” Piṅgalakoccha replied.*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5262]="*“Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**“Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But, passing over the heartwood, softwood, bark, and shoots, he’d cut off the branches and leaves and depart imagining they were heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say:*";
P_HTM[5264]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**‘This gentleman doesn’t know what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5265]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.**That’s why he passed them over, cut off the branches and leaves, and departed imagining they were heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5266]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he won’t succeed.’*";
P_HTM[5267]="*Seyyathāpi vā pana, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ, papaṭikaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was another person in need of heartwood … he’d cut off the shoots and depart imagining they were heartwood …*";
P_HTM[5268]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5269]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5270]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ papaṭikaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5271]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5272]="*Seyyathāpi vā pana, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ, tacaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was another person in need of heartwood … he’d cut off the bark and depart imagining it was heartwood …*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5274]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5275]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ, tacaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5276]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5277]="*Seyyathāpi vā pana, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ, phegguṃ chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.**Suppose there was another person in need of heartwood … he’d cut out the softwood and depart imagining it was heartwood …*";
P_HTM[5278]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5279]="*‘na vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso aññāsi sāraṃ, na aññāsi phegguṃ, na aññāsi tacaṃ, na aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, na aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5280]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ, phegguṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5281]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5282]="*Seyyathāpi vā pana, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato sāraññeva chetvā ādāya pakkameyya ‘sāran’ti jānamāno.**Suppose there was another person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. He’d cut out just the heartwood and depart knowing it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**If a person with good eyesight saw him they’d say:*";
P_HTM[5284]="*‘aññāsi vatāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāraṃ, aññāsi phegguṃ, aññāsi tacaṃ, aññāsi papaṭikaṃ, aññāsi sākhāpalāsaṃ.**‘This gentleman knows what heartwood, softwood, bark, shoots, or branches and leaves are.*";
P_HTM[5285]="*Tathā hayaṃ bhavaṃ puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato sāraññeva chetvā ādāya pakkanto “sāran”ti jānamāno.**That’s why he cut out just the heartwood and departed knowing it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5286]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ anubhavissatī’ti.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he will succeed.’*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco puggalo saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**In the same way, take a certain person who goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[5288]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5289]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5290]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5291]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, and they’ve got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5292]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:**And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that:*";
P_HTM[5293]="*‘ahamasmi lābhasakkārasilokavā, ime panaññe bhikkhū appaññātā appesakkhā’ti.**‘I’m the one with possessions, honor, and popularity. These other mendicants are obscure and insignificant.’*";
P_HTM[5294]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya na chandaṃ janeti, na vāyamati, olīnavuttiko ca hoti sāthaliko.**They become lazy and slack regarding their possessions, honor, and popularity, not generating enthusiasm or trying to realize those things that are better and finer. …*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Seyyathāpi so, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ atikkamma papaṭikaṃ, sākhāpalāsaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5296]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[5297]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**They’re like the person who mistakes branches and leaves for heartwood, I say.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[5299]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5300]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5301]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5302]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5303]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5304]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.* **";
P_HTM[5305]="*So sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5306]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5307]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:* **";
P_HTM[5308]="*‘ahamasmi sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo, ime panaññe bhikkhū dussīlā pāpadhammā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5309]="*Sīlasampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya na chandaṃ janeti, na vāyamati, olīnavuttiko ca hoti sāthaliko.**They become lazy and slack regarding their accomplishment in ethics, not generating enthusiasm or trying to realize those things that are better and finer. …*";
P_HTM[5310]="*Seyyathāpi so, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ atikkamma tacaṃ, papaṭikaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5311]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ, tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[5312]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**They’re like the person who mistakes shoots for heartwood, I say.*";
P_HTM[5313]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[5314]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,* **";
P_HTM[5315]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5316]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5317]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti, na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5318]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5319]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.* **";
P_HTM[5320]="*So sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5321]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5322]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5323]="*Sīlasampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.* **";
P_HTM[5324]="*So samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5325]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5326]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:* **";
P_HTM[5327]="*‘ahamasmi samāhito ekaggacitto, ime panaññe bhikkhū asamāhitā vibbhantacittā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5328]="*Samādhisampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca, tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya na chandaṃ janeti, na vāyamati, olīnavuttiko ca hoti sāthaliko.**They become lazy and slack regarding their accomplishment in immersion, not generating enthusiasm or trying to realize those things that are better and finer. …*";
P_HTM[5329]="*Seyyathāpi so, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ atikkamma phegguṃ, tacaṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5330]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[5331]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**They’re like the person who mistakes bark for heartwood, I say.*";
P_HTM[5332]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness …*";
P_HTM[5333]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5334]="*antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5335]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.* **";
P_HTM[5336]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5337]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5338]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.* **";
P_HTM[5339]="*So sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5340]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5341]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5342]="*Sīlasampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.* **";
P_HTM[5343]="*So samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5344]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5345]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.* **";
P_HTM[5346]="*Samādhisampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.* **";
P_HTM[5347]="*So ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[5348]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti, paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.* **";
P_HTM[5349]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti:* **";
P_HTM[5350]="*‘ahamasmi jānaṃ passaṃ viharāmi, ime panaññe bhikkhū ajānaṃ apassaṃ viharantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5351]="*Ñāṇadassanena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya na chandaṃ janeti, na vāyamati, olīnavuttiko ca hoti sāthaliko.**They become lazy and slack regarding their knowledge and vision, not generating enthusiasm or trying to realize those things that are better and finer. …*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Seyyathāpi so, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva sāraṃ, phegguṃ chetvā ādāya pakkanto ‘sāran’ti maññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[5353]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ nānubhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[5354]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**They’re like the person who mistakes softwood for heartwood, I say.*";
P_HTM[5355]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**Next, take a gentleman who has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[5356]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto,**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5357]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5358]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti.**When they’ve gone forth they generate possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5359]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano hoti, na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re not happy with that, and haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5360]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5361]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.**They don’t become lazy and slack regarding their possessions, honor, and popularity, but generate enthusiasm and try to realize those things that are better and finer.*";
P_HTM[5362]="*So sīlasampadaṃ ārādheti.**They become accomplished in ethics.*";
P_HTM[5363]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5364]="*So tāya sīlasampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5365]="*Sīlasampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.**They don’t become lazy and slack regarding their accomplishment in ethics, but generate enthusiasm and try to realize those things that are better and finer.*";
P_HTM[5366]="*So samādhisampadaṃ ārādheti.**They become accomplished in immersion.*";
P_HTM[5367]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5368]="*So tāya samādhisampadāya na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5369]="*Samādhisampadāya ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.**They don’t become lazy and slack regarding their accomplishment in immersion, but generate enthusiasm and try to realize those things that are better and finer.*";
P_HTM[5370]="*So ñāṇadassanaṃ ārādheti.**They achieve knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5371]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena attamano hoti, no ca kho paripuṇṇasaṅkappo.**They’re happy with that, but they haven’t got all they wished for.*";
P_HTM[5372]="*So tena ñāṇadassanena na attānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.*";
P_HTM[5373]="*Ñāṇadassanena ca ye aññe dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca tesaṃ dhammānaṃ sacchikiriyāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, anolīnavuttiko ca hoti asāthaliko.**They don’t become lazy and slack regarding their knowledge and vision, but generate enthusiasm and try to realize those things that are better and finer.*";
P_HTM[5374]="*Katame ca, brāhmaṇa, dhammā ñāṇadassanena uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca?**And what are those things that are better and finer than knowledge and vision?*";
P_HTM[5375]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[5376]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5377]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[5380]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5381]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[5382]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5383]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5385]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5387]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5389]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[5390]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5391]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end.*";
P_HTM[5392]="*Ayampi kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammo ñāṇadassanena uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca.**This too is something better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Ime kho, brāhmaṇa, dhammā ñāṇadassanena uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca.**These are the things that are better and finer than knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5394]="*Seyyathāpi so, brāhmaṇa, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato sāraṃyeva chetvā ādāya pakkanto ‘sāran’ti jānamāno.**Suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. He’d cut out just the heartwood and depart knowing it was heartwood.*";
P_HTM[5395]="*Yañcassa sārena sārakaraṇīyaṃ tañcassa atthaṃ anubhavissati.**Whatever he needs to make from heartwood, he will succeed.*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**That’s what this person is like, I say.*";
P_HTM[5397]="*Iti kho, brāhmaṇa, nayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ lābhasakkārasilokānisaṃsaṃ, na sīlasampadānisaṃsaṃ, na samādhisampadānisaṃsaṃ, na ñāṇadassanānisaṃsaṃ.**And so, brahmin, this spiritual life is not lived for the sake of possessions, honor, and popularity, or for accomplishment in ethics, or for accomplishment in immersion, or for knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[5398]="*Yā ca kho ayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, akuppā cetovimutti—**Rather, the goal, heartwood, and final end of the spiritual life is the unshakable freedom of heart.”*";
P_HTM[5399]="*etadatthamidaṃ, brāhmaṇa, brahmacariyaṃ, etaṃ sāraṃ etaṃ pariyosānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5400]="*Evaṃ vutte, piṅgalakoccho brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the brahmin Piṅgalakoccha said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5401]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[5402]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5403]="*Cūḷasāropamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5404]="*Opammavaggo niṭṭhito tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5405]="*Moḷiyaphaggunariṭṭhañca nāmo,* **";
P_HTM[5406]="*Andhavane kathipuṇṇaṃ nivāpo;* **";
P_HTM[5407]="*Rāsikaṇerumahāgajanāmo,* **";
P_HTM[5408]="*Sārūpamo puna piṅgalakoccho.* **";
P_HTM[5409]="*31. Cūḷagosiṅgasutta**The Shorter Discourse at Gosiṅga*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5411]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nātike viharati giñjakāvasathe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house.*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca anuruddho āyasmā ca nandiyo āyasmā ca kimilo gosiṅgasālavanadāye viharanti.**Now at that time the venerables Anuruddha, Nandiya, and Kimbila were staying in the sal forest park at Gosiṅga.*";
P_HTM[5413]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkami.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to that park.*";
P_HTM[5414]="*Addasā kho dāyapālo bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The park keeper saw the Buddha coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[5415]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5416]="*“mā, samaṇa, etaṃ dāyaṃ pāvisi.**“Don’t come into this park, ascetic.*";
P_HTM[5417]="*Santettha tayo kulaputtā attakāmarūpā viharanti.**There are three gentlemen who love themselves staying here.*";
P_HTM[5418]="*Mā tesaṃ aphāsumakāsī”ti.**Don’t disturb them.”*";
P_HTM[5419]="*Assosi kho āyasmā anuruddho dāyapālassa bhagavatā saddhiṃ mantayamānassa.**Anuruddha heard the park keeper conversing with the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5420]="*Sutvāna dāyapālaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5421]="*“mā, āvuso dāyapāla, bhagavantaṃ vāresi.**“Don’t keep the Buddha out, good park keeper!*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Satthā no bhagavā anuppatto”ti.**Our Teacher, the Blessed One, has arrived.”*";
P_HTM[5423]="*Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho yenāyasmā ca nandiyo āyasmā ca kimilo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantañca nandiyaṃ āyasmantañca kimilaṃ etadavoca:**Then Anuruddha went to Nandiya and Kimbila, and said to them,*";
P_HTM[5424]="*“abhikkamathāyasmanto, abhikkamathāyasmanto, satthā no bhagavā anuppatto”ti.**“Come forth, venerables, come forth! Our Teacher, the Blessed One, has arrived!”*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Atha kho āyasmā ca anuruddho āyasmā ca nandiyo āyasmā ca kimilo bhagavantaṃ paccuggantvā—**Then Anuruddha, Nandiya, and Kimbila came out to greet the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5426]="*eko bhagavato pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesi, eko āsanaṃ paññapesi, eko pādodakaṃ upaṭṭhāpesi.**One received his bowl and robe, one spread out a seat, and one set out water for washing his feet.*";
P_HTM[5427]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**He sat on the seat spread out*";
P_HTM[5428]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā pāde pakkhālesi.**and washed his feet.*";
P_HTM[5429]="*Tepi kho āyasmanto bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Those venerables bowed and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[5430]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[5431]="*“Kacci vo, anuruddhā, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ, kacci piṇḍakena na kilamathā”ti?**“I hope you’re keeping well, Anuruddha and friends; I hope you’re alright. And I hope you’re having no trouble getting alms-food.”*";
P_HTM[5432]="*“Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā, yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā; na ca mayaṃ, bhante, piṇḍakena kilamāmā”ti.**“We’re alright, Blessed One, we’re getting by. And we have no trouble getting alms-food.”*";
P_HTM[5433]="*“Kacci pana vo, anuruddhā, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharathā”ti?**“I hope you’re living in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes?”*";
P_HTM[5434]="*“Taggha mayaṃ, bhante, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharāmā”ti.**“Indeed, sir, we live in harmony like this.”*";
P_HTM[5435]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana tumhe, anuruddhā, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharathā”ti?**“But how do you live this way?”*";
P_HTM[5436]="*“Idha mayhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ hoti:**“In this case, sir, I think,*";
P_HTM[5437]="*‘lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me,**‘I’m fortunate, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[5438]="*yohaṃ evarūpehi sabrahmacārīhi saddhiṃ viharāmī’ti.**to live together with spiritual companions such as these.’*";
P_HTM[5439]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, imesu āyasmantesu mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ āvi ceva raho ca;**I consistently treat these venerables with kindness by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private.*";
P_HTM[5440]="*mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ āvi ceva raho ca;* **";
P_HTM[5441]="*mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ āvi ceva raho ca.* **";
P_HTM[5442]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ hoti:**I think,*";
P_HTM[5443]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ nikkhipitvā imesaṃyeva āyasmantānaṃ cittassa vasena vatteyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I set aside my own ideas and just go along with these venerables’ ideas?’*";
P_HTM[5444]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhante, sakaṃ cittaṃ nikkhipitvā imesaṃyeva āyasmantānaṃ cittassa vasena vattāmi.**And that’s what I do.*";
P_HTM[5445]="*Nānā hi kho no, bhante, kāyā ekañca pana maññe cittan”ti.**Though we’re different in body, sir, we’re one in mind, it seems to me.”*";
P_HTM[5446]="*Āyasmāpi kho nandiyo … pe …**And the venerables Nandiya and Kimbila spoke likewise, and they added:*";
P_HTM[5447]="*āyasmāpi kho kimilo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5448]="*“mayhampi, bhante, evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5449]="*‘lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me,* **";
P_HTM[5450]="*yohaṃ evarūpehi sabrahmacārīhi saddhiṃ viharāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5451]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, imesu āyasmantesu mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ āvi ceva raho ca,* **";
P_HTM[5452]="*mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ āvi ceva raho ca,* **";
P_HTM[5453]="*mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ āvi ceva raho ca.* **";
P_HTM[5454]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5455]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ nikkhipitvā imesaṃyeva āyasmantānaṃ cittassa vasena vatteyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5456]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhante, sakaṃ cittaṃ nikkhipitvā imesaṃyeva āyasmantānaṃ cittassa vasena vattāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5457]="*Nānā hi kho no, bhante, kāyā ekañca pana maññe cittan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5458]="*“Evaṃ kho mayaṃ, bhante, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharāmā”ti.**“That’s how we live in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes.”*";
P_HTM[5459]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good, Anuruddha and friends!*";
P_HTM[5460]="*Kacci pana vo, anuruddhā, appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharathā”ti?**But I hope you’re living diligently, keen, and resolute?”*";
P_HTM[5461]="*“Taggha mayaṃ, bhante, appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharāmā”ti.**“Indeed, sir, we live diligently.”*";
P_HTM[5462]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana tumhe, anuruddhā, appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharathā”ti?**“But how do you live this way?”*";
P_HTM[5463]="*“Idha, bhante, amhākaṃ yo paṭhamaṃ gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamati so āsanāni paññapeti, pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, avakkārapātiṃ upaṭṭhāpeti.**“In this case, sir, whoever returns first from alms-round prepares the seats, and puts out the drinking water and the rubbish bin.*";
P_HTM[5464]="*Yo pacchā gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamati, sace hoti bhuttāvaseso sace ākaṅkhati bhuñjati, no ce ākaṅkhati appaharite vā chaḍḍeti, appāṇake vā udake opilāpeti.**If there’s anything left over, whoever returns last eats it if they like. Otherwise they throw it out where there is little that grows, or drop it into water that has no living creatures.*";
P_HTM[5465]="*So āsanāni paṭisāmeti, pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ paṭisāmeti, avakkārapātiṃ paṭisāmeti, bhattaggaṃ sammajjati.**Then they put away the seats, drinking water, and rubbish bin, and sweep the refectory.*";
P_HTM[5466]="*Yo passati pānīyaghaṭaṃ vā paribhojanīyaghaṭaṃ vā vaccaghaṭaṃ vā rittaṃ tucchaṃ so upaṭṭhāpeti.**If someone sees that the pot of water for washing, drinking, or the toilet is empty they set it up.*";
P_HTM[5467]="*Sacassa hoti avisayhaṃ, hatthavikārena dutiyaṃ āmantetvā hatthavilaṅghakena upaṭṭhāpema, na tveva mayaṃ, bhante, tappaccayā vācaṃ bhindāma.**If he can’t do it, he summons another with a wave of the hand, and they set it up by lifting it with their hands. But we don’t break into speech for that reason.*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Pañcāhikaṃ kho pana mayaṃ, bhante, sabbarattikaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sannisīdāma.**And every five days we sit together for the whole night and discuss the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5469]="*Evaṃ kho mayaṃ, bhante, appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharāmā”ti.**That’s how we live diligently, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[5470]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good, Anuruddha and friends!*";
P_HTM[5471]="*Atthi pana vo, anuruddhā, evaṃ appamattānaṃ ātāpīnaṃ pahitattānaṃ viharantānaṃ uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But as you live diligently like this, have you achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, a meditation at ease?”*";
P_HTM[5472]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5473]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāma.**Whenever we want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, we enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[5474]="*Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, amhākaṃ appamattānaṃ ātāpīnaṃ pahitattānaṃ viharantānaṃ uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti.**This is a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, a meditation at ease, that we have achieved while living diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[5475]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5476]="*Etassa pana vo, anuruddhā, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā atthañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But have you achieved any other superhuman distinction for going beyond and stilling that meditation?”*";
P_HTM[5477]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5478]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāma.**Whenever we want, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, we enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[5479]="*Etassa, bhante, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā ayamañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti.**This is another superhuman distinction that we have achieved for going beyond and stilling that meditation.”*";
P_HTM[5480]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5481]="*Etassa pana vo, anuruddhā, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā atthañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But have you achieved any other superhuman distinction for going beyond and stilling that meditation?”*";
P_HTM[5482]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5483]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhakā ca viharāma, satā ca sampajānā, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedema, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāma.**Whenever we want, with the fading away of rapture, we enter and remain in the third absorption, where we meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[5484]="*Etassa, bhante, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā ayamañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti.**This is another superhuman distinction that we have achieved for going beyond and stilling that meditation.”*";
P_HTM[5485]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5486]="*Etassa pana vo, anuruddhā, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā atthañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But have you achieved any other superhuman distinction for going beyond and stilling that meditation?”*";
P_HTM[5487]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāma.**Whenever we want, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, we enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[5489]="*Etassa, bhante, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā ayamañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti.**This is another superhuman distinction that we have achieved for going beyond and stilling that meditation.”*";
P_HTM[5490]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5491]="*Etassa pana vo, anuruddhā, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā atthañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But have you achieved any other superhuman distinction for going beyond and stilling that meditation?”*";
P_HTM[5492]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5493]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāma.**Whenever we want, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, we enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Etassa, bhante, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā ayamañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti.**This is another superhuman distinction that we have achieved for going beyond and stilling that meditation.”*";
P_HTM[5495]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5496]="*Etassa pana vo, anuruddhā, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā atthañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But have you achieved any other superhuman distinction for going beyond and stilling that meditation?”*";
P_HTM[5497]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5498]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāma … pe …**Whenever we want, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, we enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness. …*";
P_HTM[5499]="*sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāma … pe …**going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, we enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness. …*";
P_HTM[5500]="*sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāma.**going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, we enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[5501]="*Etassa, bhante, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā ayamañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti.**This is another superhuman distinction that we have achieved for going beyond and stilling that meditation.”*";
P_HTM[5502]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5503]="*Etassa pana vo, anuruddhā, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā atthañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?**But have you achieved any other superhuman distinction for going beyond and stilling that meditation?”*";
P_HTM[5504]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bhante.**“How could we not, sir?*";
P_HTM[5505]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāma sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharāma, paññāya ca no disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā.**Whenever we want, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, we enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, our defilements have come to an end.*";
P_HTM[5506]="*Etassa, bhante, vihārassa samatikkamāya etassa vihārassa paṭippassaddhiyā ayamañño uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro.**This is another superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, a meditation at ease, that we have achieved for going beyond and stilling that meditation.*";
P_HTM[5507]="*Imamhā ca mayaṃ, bhante, phāsuvihārā aññaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ uttaritaraṃ vā paṇītataraṃ vā na samanupassāmā”ti.**And we don’t see any better or finer way of meditating at ease than this.”*";
P_HTM[5508]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good!*";
P_HTM[5509]="*Imamhā phāsuvihārā uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā phāsuvihāro natthī”ti.**There is no better or finer way of meditating at ease than this.”*";
P_HTM[5510]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantañca anuruddhaṃ āyasmantañca nandiyaṃ āyasmantañca kimilaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired the venerables Anuruddha, Nandiya, and Kimbila with a Dhamma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[5511]="*Atha kho āyasmā ca anuruddho āyasmā ca nandiyo āyasmā ca kimilo bhagavantaṃ anusaṃyāyitvā tato paṭinivattitvā āyasmā ca nandiyo āyasmā ca kimilo āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:**The venerables then accompanied the Buddha for a little way before turning back. Nandiya and Kimbila said to Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[5512]="*“kiṃ nu kho mayaṃ āyasmato anuruddhassa evamārocimha:**“Did we ever tell you that we had*";
P_HTM[5513]="*‘imāsañca imāsañca vihārasamāpattīnaṃ mayaṃ lābhino’ti, yaṃ no āyasmā anuruddho bhagavato sammukhā yāva āsavānaṃ khayā pakāsetī”ti?**gained such and such meditations and attainments, up to the ending of defilements, as you revealed to the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[5514]="*“Na kho me āyasmanto evamārocesuṃ:**“The venerables did not tell me that they had*";
P_HTM[5515]="*‘imāsañca imāsañca vihārasamāpattīnaṃ mayaṃ lābhino’ti, api ca me āyasmantānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca vidito:**gained such meditations and attainments. But I discovered it by comprehending your minds,*";
P_HTM[5516]="*‘imāsañca imāsañca vihārasamāpattīnaṃ ime āyasmanto lābhino’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5517]="*Devatāpi me etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ:**and deities also told me.*";
P_HTM[5518]="*‘imāsañca imāsañca vihārasamāpattīnaṃ ime āyasmanto lābhino’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5519]="*Tamenaṃ bhagavatā pañhābhipuṭṭhena byākatan”ti.**I answered when the Buddha directly asked about it.”*";
P_HTM[5520]="*Atha kho dīgho parajano yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho dīgho parajano yakkho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the native spirit Dīgha Parajana went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5521]="*“lābhā vata, bhante, vajjīnaṃ, suladdhalābhā vajjipajāya,**“The Vajjis are lucky! The Vajjian people are so very lucky*";
P_HTM[5522]="*yattha tathāgato viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, ime ca tayo kulaputtā—**that the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha stays there, as well as these three gentlemen,*";
P_HTM[5523]="*āyasmā ca anuruddho, āyasmā ca nandiyo, āyasmā ca kimilo”ti.**the venerables Anuruddha, Nandiya, and Kimbila.”*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Dīghassa parajanassa yakkhassa saddaṃ sutvā bhummā devā saddamanussāvesuṃ:**Hearing the cry of Dīgha Parajana, the Earth Gods raised the cry …*";
P_HTM[5525]="*“lābhā vata, bho, vajjīnaṃ, suladdhalābhā vajjipajāya,* **";
P_HTM[5526]="*yattha tathāgato viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, ime ca tayo kulaputtā—* **";
P_HTM[5527]="*āyasmā ca anuruddho, āyasmā ca nandiyo, āyasmā ca kimilo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5528]="*Bhummānaṃ devānaṃ saddaṃ sutvā cātumahārājikā devā … pe …**Hearing the cry of the Earth Gods, the Gods of the Four Great Kings …*";
P_HTM[5529]="*tāvatiṃsā devā … pe …**the Gods of the Thirty-Three …*";
P_HTM[5530]="*yāmā devā … pe …**the Gods of Yama …*";
P_HTM[5531]="*tusitā devā … pe …**the Joyful Gods …*";
P_HTM[5532]="*nimmānaratī devā … pe …**the Gods Who Love to Create …*";
P_HTM[5533]="*paranimmitavasavattī devā … pe …**the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others …*";
P_HTM[5534]="*brahmakāyikā devā saddamanussāvesuṃ:**the Gods of Brahmā’s Host raised the cry,*";
P_HTM[5535]="*“lābhā vata, bho, vajjīnaṃ, suladdhalābhā vajjipajāya,**“The Vajjis are lucky! The Vajjian people are so very lucky*";
P_HTM[5536]="*yattha tathāgato viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, ime ca tayo kulaputtā—**that the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha stays there, as well as these three gentlemen,*";
P_HTM[5537]="*āyasmā ca anuruddho, āyasmā ca nandiyo, āyasmā ca kimilo”ti.**the venerables Anuruddha, Nandiya, and Kimbila.”*";
P_HTM[5538]="*Itiha te āyasmanto tena khaṇena tena layena tena muhuttena yāva brahmalokā viditā ahesuṃ.**And so at that moment, in that instant, those venerables were known as far as the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[5539]="*“Evametaṃ, dīgha, evametaṃ, dīgha.**“That’s so true, Dīgha! That’s so true!*";
P_HTM[5540]="*Yasmāpi, dīgha, kulā ete tayo kulaputtā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, tañcepi kulaṃ ete tayo kulaputte pasannacittaṃ anussareyya, tassapāssa kulassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If the family from which those three gentlemen went forth from the lay life to homelessness were to recollect those venerables with confident heart, that would be for that family’s lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5541]="*Yasmāpi, dīgha, kulaparivaṭṭā ete tayo kulaputtā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, so cepi kulaparivaṭṭo ete tayo kulaputte pasannacitto anussareyya, tassapāssa kulaparivaṭṭassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If the family circle …*";
P_HTM[5542]="*Yasmāpi, dīgha, gāmā ete tayo kulaputtā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, so cepi gāmo ete tayo kulaputte pasannacitto anussareyya, tassapāssa gāmassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**village …*";
P_HTM[5543]="*Yasmāpi, dīgha, nigamā ete tayo kulaputtā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, so cepi nigamo ete tayo kulaputte pasannacitto anussareyya, tassapāssa nigamassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**town …*";
P_HTM[5544]="*Yasmāpi, dīgha, nagarā ete tayo kulaputtā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, tañcepi nagaraṃ ete tayo kulaputte pasannacittaṃ anussareyya, tassapāssa nagarassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**city …*";
P_HTM[5545]="*Yasmāpi, dīgha, janapadā ete tayo kulaputtā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, so cepi janapado ete tayo kulaputte pasannacitto anussareyya, tassapāssa janapadassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**country …*";
P_HTM[5546]="*Sabbe cepi, dīgha, khattiyā ete tayo kulaputte pasannacittā anussareyyuṃ, sabbesānampāssa khattiyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**all the aristocrats …*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Sabbe cepi, dīgha, brāhmaṇā … pe …**all the brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5548]="*sabbe cepi, dīgha, vessā … pe …**all the merchants …*";
P_HTM[5549]="*sabbe cepi, dīgha, suddā ete tayo kulaputte pasannacittā anussareyyuṃ, sabbesānampāssa suddānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**all the workers were to recollect those venerables with confident heart, that would be for all those workers’ lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5550]="*Sadevako cepi, dīgha, loko samārako sabrahmako sassamaṇabrāhmaṇī pajā sadevamanussā ete tayo kulaputte pasannacittā anussareyya, sadevakassapāssa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**If the whole world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—were to recollect those venerables with confident heart, that would be for the whole world’s lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Passa, dīgha, yāva ete tayo kulaputtā bahujanahitāya paṭipannā bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya, atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti.**See, Dīgha, how those three gentlemen are practicing for the welfare and happiness of the people, out of compassion for the world, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans!”*";
P_HTM[5552]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5553]="*Attamano dīgho parajano yakkho bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, the native spirit Dīgha Parajana was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5554]="*Cūḷagosiṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5555]="*32. Mahāgosiṅgasutta**The Longer Discourse at Gosiṅga*";
P_HTM[5556]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5557]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gosiṅgasālavanadāye viharati sambahulehi abhiññātehi abhiññātehi therehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ—**At one time the Buddha was staying in the sal forest park at Gosiṅga, together with several well-known senior disciples, such as*";
P_HTM[5558]="*āyasmatā ca sāriputtena āyasmatā ca mahāmoggallānena āyasmatā ca mahākassapena āyasmatā ca anuruddhena āyasmatā ca revatena āyasmatā ca ānandena, aññehi ca abhiññātehi abhiññātehi therehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ.**the venerables Sāriputta, Mahāmoggallāna, Mahākassapa, Anuruddha, Revata, Ānanda, and others.*";
P_HTM[5559]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā mahākassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna came out of retreat, went to Venerable Mahākassapa, and said,*";
P_HTM[5560]="*“āyāmāvuso, kassapa, yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamissāma dhammassavanāyā”ti.**“Come, Reverend Kassapa, let’s go to Venerable Sāriputta to hear the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[5561]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosi.**“Yes, reverend,” Mahākassapa replied.*";
P_HTM[5562]="*Atha kho āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno āyasmā ca mahākassapo āyasmā ca anuruddho yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu dhammassavanāya.**Then, together with Venerable Anuruddha, they went to Sāriputta to hear the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantañca mahāmoggallānaṃ āyasmantañca mahākassapaṃ āyasmantañca anuruddhaṃ yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamante dhammassavanāya.**Seeing them, Venerable Ānanda*";
P_HTM[5564]="*Disvāna yenāyasmā revato tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavoca:**went to Venerable Revata, told him what was happening,*";
P_HTM[5565]="*“upasaṅkamantā kho amū, āvuso revata, sappurisā yenāyasmā sāriputto tena dhammassavanāya.**and invited him also.*";
P_HTM[5566]="*Āyāmāvuso revata, yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamissāma dhammassavanāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5567]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā revato āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi.* **";
P_HTM[5568]="*Atha kho āyasmā ca revato āyasmā ca ānando yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu dhammassavanāya.* **";
P_HTM[5569]="*Addasā kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantañca revataṃ āyasmantañca ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchante.**Sāriputta saw them coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[5570]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**and said to Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[5571]="*“etu kho āyasmā ānando.**“Come, Venerable Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Svāgataṃ āyasmato ānandassa bhagavato upaṭṭhākassa bhagavato santikāvacarassa.**Welcome to Ānanda, the Buddha’s attendant, who is so close to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5573]="*Ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso ānanda, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;**Ānanda, the sal forest park at Gosiṅga is lovely, the night is bright, the sal trees are in full blossom, and divine scents seem to float on the air.*";
P_HTM[5574]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso ānanda, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti?**What kind of mendicant would beautify this park?”*";
P_HTM[5575]="*“Idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo. Ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthā sabyañjanā; kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti, dhātā, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**“Reverend Sāriputta, it’s a mendicant who is very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[5576]="*So catassannaṃ parisānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti parimaṇḍalehi padabyañjanehi anuppabandhehi anusayasamugghātāya.**And they teach the four assemblies in order to uproot the underlying tendencies with well-rounded and systematic words and phrases.*";
P_HTM[5577]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Sāriputta said to Revata,*";
P_HTM[5579]="*“byākataṃ kho, āvuso revata, āyasmatā ānandena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**“Reverend Revata, Ānanda has answered by speaking from his heart.*";
P_HTM[5580]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ revataṃ pucchāma:**And now we ask you the same question.”*";
P_HTM[5581]="*‘ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso revata, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;* **";
P_HTM[5582]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso revata, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5583]="*“Idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu paṭisallānārāmo hoti paṭisallānarato, ajjhattaṃ cetosamathamanuyutto anirākatajjhāno, vipassanāya samannāgato, brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ.**“Reverend Sāriputta, it’s a mendicant who enjoys retreat and loves retreat. They’re committed to inner serenity of the heart, they don’t neglect absorption, they’re endowed with discernment, and they frequent empty huts.*";
P_HTM[5584]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5585]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Sāriputta said to Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[5586]="*“byākataṃ kho, āvuso anuruddha, āyasmatā revatena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**“Reverend Anuruddha, Revata has answered by speaking from his heart.*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ pucchāma:**And now we ask you the same question.”*";
P_HTM[5588]="*‘ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso anuruddha, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;* **";
P_HTM[5589]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso anuruddha, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5590]="*“Idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena sahassaṃ lokānaṃ voloketi.**“Reverend Sāriputta, it’s a mendicant who surveys the entire galaxy with clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human,*";
P_HTM[5591]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso sāriputta, cakkhumā puriso uparipāsādavaragato sahassaṃ nemimaṇḍalānaṃ volokeyya;**just as a person with good sight could survey a thousand wheel rims from the upper floor of a stilt longhouse.*";
P_HTM[5592]="*evameva kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena sahassaṃ lokānaṃ voloketi.* **";
P_HTM[5593]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5594]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Sāriputta said to Mahākassapa,*";
P_HTM[5595]="*“byākataṃ kho, āvuso kassapa, āyasmatā anuruddhena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**“Reverend Kassapa, Anuruddha has answered by speaking from his heart.*";
P_HTM[5596]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ pucchāma:**And now we ask you the same question.”*";
P_HTM[5597]="*‘ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso kassapa, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;* **";
P_HTM[5598]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso kassapa, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5599]="*“Idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu attanā ca āraññiko hoti āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca piṇḍapātiko hoti piṇḍapātikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca paṃsukūliko hoti paṃsukūlikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca tecīvariko hoti tecīvarikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca appiccho hoti appicchatāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca santuṭṭho hoti santuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca pavivitto hoti pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho hoti asaṃsaggassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca āraddhavīriyo hoti vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca sīlasampanno hoti sīlasampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca samādhisampanno hoti samādhisampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca paññāsampanno hoti paññāsampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca vimuttisampanno hoti vimuttisampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno hoti vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī.**“Reverend Sāriputta, it’s a mendicant who lives in the wilderness, eats only alms-food, wears rag robes, and owns just three robes; and they praise these things. They are of few wishes, content, secluded, aloof, and energetic; and they praise these things. They are accomplished in ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom; and they praise these things.*";
P_HTM[5600]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5601]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Sāriputta said to Mahāmoggallāna,*";
P_HTM[5602]="*“byākataṃ kho, āvuso moggallāna, āyasmatā mahākassapena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**“Reverend Moggallāna, Mahākassapa has answered by speaking from his heart.*";
P_HTM[5603]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ pucchāma:**And now we ask you the same question.”*";
P_HTM[5604]="*‘ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso moggallāna, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;* **";
P_HTM[5605]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5606]="*“Idhāvuso sāriputta, dve bhikkhū abhidhammakathaṃ kathenti, te aññamaññaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, aññamaññassa pañhaṃ puṭṭhā vissajjenti, no ca saṃsādenti, dhammī ca nesaṃ kathā pavattinī hoti.**“Reverend Sāriputta, it’s when two mendicants engage in discussion about the teaching. They question each other and answer each other’s questions without faltering, and their discussion on the teaching flows on.*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5608]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**Then Mahāmoggallāna said to Sāriputta,*";
P_HTM[5609]="*“byākataṃ kho, āvuso sāriputta, amhehi sabbeheva yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**“Each of us has spoken from our heart.*";
P_HTM[5610]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ pucchāma:**And now we ask you:*";
P_HTM[5611]="*‘ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;**Sāriputta, the sal forest park at Gosiṅga is lovely, the night is bright, the sal trees are in full blossom, and divine scents seem to float on the air.*";
P_HTM[5612]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti?**What kind of mendicant would beautify this park?”*";
P_HTM[5613]="*“Idhāvuso moggallāna, bhikkhu cittaṃ vasaṃ vatteti, no ca bhikkhu cittassa vasena vattati.**“Reverend Moggallāna, it’s when a mendicant masters their mind and is not mastered by it.*";
P_HTM[5614]="*So yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharati;**In the morning, they abide in whatever meditation or attainment they want.*";
P_HTM[5615]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharati;**At midday,*";
P_HTM[5616]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati sāyanhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā sāyanhasamayaṃ viharati.**and in the evening, they abide in whatever meditation or attainment they want.*";
P_HTM[5617]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso moggallāna, rañño vā rājamahāmattassa vā nānārattānaṃ dussānaṃ dussakaraṇḍako pūro assa.**Suppose that a ruler or their minister had a chest full of garments of different colors.*";
P_HTM[5618]="*So yaññadeva dussayugaṃ ākaṅkheyya pubbaṇhasamayaṃ pārupituṃ, taṃ tadeva dussayugaṃ pubbaṇhasamayaṃ pārupeyya;**In the morning, they’d don whatever pair of garments they wanted.*";
P_HTM[5619]="*yaññadeva dussayugaṃ ākaṅkheyya majjhanhikasamayaṃ pārupituṃ, taṃ tadeva dussayugaṃ majjhanhikasamayaṃ pārupeyya;**At midday,*";
P_HTM[5620]="*yaññadeva dussayugaṃ ākaṅkheyya sāyanhasamayaṃ pārupituṃ, taṃ tadeva dussayugaṃ sāyanhasamayaṃ pārupeyya.**and in the evening, they’d don whatever pair of garments they wanted.*";
P_HTM[5621]="*Evameva kho, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhu cittaṃ vasaṃ vatteti, no ca bhikkhu cittassa vasena vattati.**In the same way, a mendicant masters their mind and is not mastered by it.*";
P_HTM[5622]="*So yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharati;**In the morning, they abide in whatever meditation or attainment they want.*";
P_HTM[5623]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharati;**At midday,*";
P_HTM[5624]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati sāyanhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā sāyanhasamayaṃ viharati.**and in the evening, they abide in whatever meditation or attainment they want.*";
P_HTM[5625]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5626]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto te āyasmante etadavoca:**Then Sāriputta said to those venerables,*";
P_HTM[5627]="*“byākataṃ kho, āvuso, amhehi sabbeheva yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**“Each of us has spoken from the heart.*";
P_HTM[5628]="*Āyāmāvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocessāma.**Come, reverends, let’s go to the Buddha, and inform him about this.*";
P_HTM[5629]="*Yathā no bhagavā byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti.**As he answers, so we’ll remember it.”*";
P_HTM[5630]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te āyasmanto āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5631]="*Atha kho te āyasmanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then those venerables went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Venerable Sāriputta told the Buddha of how the mendicants had come to see him, and how he had asked Ānanda:*";
P_HTM[5632]="*“idha, bhante, āyasmā ca revato āyasmā ca ānando yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu dhammassavanāya.* **";
P_HTM[5633]="*Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, āyasmantañca revataṃ āyasmantañca ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchante.* **";
P_HTM[5634]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[5635]="*‘etu kho āyasmā ānando.* **";
P_HTM[5636]="*Svāgataṃ āyasmato ānandassa bhagavato upaṭṭhākassa bhagavato santikāvacarassa.* **";
P_HTM[5637]="*Ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso ānanda, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti;**“‘Ānanda, the sal forest park at Gosiṅga is lovely, the night is bright, the sal trees are in full blossom, and divine scents seem to float on the air.*";
P_HTM[5638]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso ānanda, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’ti?**What kind of mendicant would beautify this park?’*";
P_HTM[5639]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, āyasmā ānando maṃ etadavoca:**When I had spoken, Ānanda said to me:*";
P_HTM[5640]="*‘idhāvuso, sāriputta, bhikkhu bahussuto hoti sutadharo … pe …**‘Reverend Sāriputta, it’s a mendicant who is very learned …*";
P_HTM[5641]="*anusayasamugghātāya.* **";
P_HTM[5642]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.’”*";
P_HTM[5643]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[5644]="*Yathā taṃ ānandova sammā byākaramāno byākareyya.**Ānanda answered in the right way for him.*";
P_HTM[5645]="*Ānando hi, sāriputta, bahussuto sutadharo sutasannicayo. Ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthā sabyañjanā; kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti, dhātā, vacasā paricitā, manasānupekkhitā, diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**For Ānanda is very learned …”*";
P_HTM[5646]="*So catassannaṃ parisānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti parimaṇḍalehi padabyañjanehi anuppabandhehi anusayasamugghātāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5647]="*“Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavocaṃ:**“Next I asked Revata the same question.*";
P_HTM[5648]="*‘byākataṃ kho, āvuso revata, āyasmatā ānandena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5649]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ revataṃ pucchāma—* **";
P_HTM[5650]="*ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso revata, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā maññe gandhā sampavanti.* **";
P_HTM[5651]="*Kathaṃrūpena, āvuso revata, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5652]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, āyasmā revato maṃ etadavoca:**He said:*";
P_HTM[5653]="*‘idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu paṭisallānārāmo hoti paṭisallānarato, ajjhattaṃ cetosamathamanuyutto, anirākatajjhāno, vipassanāya samannāgato, brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ.**‘It’s a mendicant who enjoys retreat …*";
P_HTM[5654]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.’”*";
P_HTM[5655]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[5656]="*Yathā taṃ revatova sammā byākaramāno byākareyya.**Revata answered in the right way for him.*";
P_HTM[5657]="*Revato hi, sāriputta, paṭisallānārāmo paṭisallānarato, ajjhattaṃ cetosamathamanuyutto anirākatajjhāno, vipassanāya samannāgato brūhetā suññāgārānan”ti.**For Revata enjoys retreat …”*";
P_HTM[5658]="*“Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocaṃ:**“Next I asked Anuruddha the same question.*";
P_HTM[5659]="*‘byākataṃ kho, āvuso anuruddha, āyasmatā revatena … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5660]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso anuruddha, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5661]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, āyasmā anuruddho maṃ etadavoca:**He said:*";
P_HTM[5662]="*‘idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena sahassaṃ lokānaṃ voloketi.**‘It’s a mendicant who surveys the entire galaxy with clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human …*";
P_HTM[5663]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso sāriputta, cakkhumā puriso … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5664]="*evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.’”*";
P_HTM[5665]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta, yathā taṃ anuruddhova sammā byākaramāno byākareyya.**“Good, good, Sāriputta! Anuruddha answered in the right way for him.*";
P_HTM[5666]="*Anuruddho hi, sāriputta, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena sahassaṃ lokānaṃ voloketī”ti.**For Anuruddha surveys the entire galaxy with clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human.”*";
P_HTM[5667]="*“Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavocaṃ:**“Next I asked Mahākassapa the same question.*";
P_HTM[5668]="*‘byākataṃ kho, āvuso kassapa, āyasmatā anuruddhena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5669]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ pucchāma … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5670]="*kathaṃrūpena kho, āvuso kassapa, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5671]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, āyasmā mahākassapo maṃ etadavoca:**He said:*";
P_HTM[5672]="*‘idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu attanā ca āraññiko hoti āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca piṇḍapātiko hoti … pe … attanā ca paṃsukūliko hoti … pe … attanā ca tecīvariko hoti … pe … attanā ca appiccho hoti … pe … attanā ca santuṭṭho hoti … pe … attanā ca pavivitto hoti … pe … attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho hoti … pe … attanā ca āraddhavīriyo hoti … pe … attanā ca sīlasampanno hoti … pe … attanā ca samādhisampanno hoti … pe … attanā ca paññāsampanno hoti … attanā ca vimuttisampanno hoti … attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno hoti vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī.**‘It’s a mendicant who lives in the wilderness … and is accomplished in the knowledge and vision of freedom; and they praise these things.*";
P_HTM[5673]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.’”*";
P_HTM[5674]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[5675]="*Yathā taṃ kassapova sammā byākaramāno byākareyya.**Kassapa answered in the right way for him.*";
P_HTM[5676]="*Kassapo hi, sāriputta, attanā ca āraññiko āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca piṇḍapātiko piṇḍapātikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca paṃsukūliko paṃsukūlikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca tecīvariko tecīvarikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca appiccho appicchatāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca santuṭṭho santuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca pavivitto pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho asaṃsaggassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca āraddhavīriyo vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca sīlasampanno sīlasampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca samādhisampanno samādhisampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca paññāsampanno paññāsampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca vimuttisampanno vimuttisampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī, attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadāya ca vaṇṇavādī”ti.**For Kassapa lives in the wilderness … and is accomplished in the knowledge and vision of freedom; and he praises these things.”*";
P_HTM[5677]="*“Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ bhante āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavocaṃ:**“Next I asked Mahāmoggallāna the same question.*";
P_HTM[5678]="*‘byākataṃ kho, āvuso moggallāna, āyasmatā mahākassapena yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5679]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ pucchāma … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5680]="*kathaṃrūpena, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5681]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, āyasmā mahāmoggallāno maṃ etadavoca:**He said:*";
P_HTM[5682]="*‘idhāvuso sāriputta, dve bhikkhū abhidhammakathaṃ kathenti. Te aññamaññaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, aññamaññassa pañhaṃ puṭṭhā vissajjenti, no ca saṃsādenti, dhammī ca nesaṃ kathā pavattinī hoti.**‘It’s when two mendicants engage in discussion about the teaching …*";
P_HTM[5683]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.’”*";
P_HTM[5684]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta, yathā taṃ moggallānova sammā byākaramāno byākareyya.**“Good, good, Sāriputta! Moggallāna answered in the right way for him.*";
P_HTM[5685]="*Moggallāno hi, sāriputta, dhammakathiko”ti.**For Moggallāna is a Dhamma speaker.”*";
P_HTM[5686]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Moggallāna said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5687]="*“atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**“Next, I asked Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[5688]="*‘byākataṃ kho, āvuso sāriputta, amhehi sabbeheva yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ.**‘Each of us has spoken from our heart.*";
P_HTM[5689]="*Tattha dāni mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ pucchāma—**And now we ask you:*";
P_HTM[5690]="*ramaṇīyaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, gosiṅgasālavanaṃ, dosinā ratti, sabbaphāliphullā sālā, dibbā, maññe, gandhā sampavanti.**Sāriputta, the sal forest park at Gosiṅga is lovely, the night is bright, the sal trees are in full blossom, and divine scents seem to float on the air.*";
P_HTM[5691]="*Kathaṃrūpena, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’ti?**What kind of mendicant would beautify this park?’*";
P_HTM[5692]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto maṃ etadavoca:**When I had spoken, Sāriputta said to me:*";
P_HTM[5693]="*‘idhāvuso moggallāna, bhikkhu cittaṃ vasaṃ vatteti no ca bhikkhu cittassa vasena vattati.**‘Reverend Moggallāna, it’s when a mendicant masters their mind and is not mastered by it …*";
P_HTM[5694]="*So yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharati;* **";
P_HTM[5695]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharati;* **";
P_HTM[5696]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati sāyanhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā sāyanhasamayaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[5697]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso moggallāna, rañño vā rājamahāmattassa vā nānārattānaṃ dussānaṃ dussakaraṇḍako pūro assa.* **";
P_HTM[5698]="*So yaññadeva dussayugaṃ ākaṅkheyya pubbaṇhasamayaṃ pārupituṃ, taṃ tadeva dussayugaṃ pubbaṇhasamayaṃ pārupeyya;* **";
P_HTM[5699]="*yaññadeva dussayugaṃ ākaṅkheyya majjhanhikasamayaṃ pārupituṃ, taṃ tadeva dussayugaṃ majjhanhikasamayaṃ pārupeyya;* **";
P_HTM[5700]="*yaññadeva dussayugaṃ ākaṅkheyya sāyanhasamayaṃ pārupituṃ, taṃ tadeva dussayugaṃ sāyanhasamayaṃ pārupeyya.* **";
P_HTM[5701]="*Evameva kho, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhu cittaṃ vasaṃ vatteti, no ca bhikkhu cittassa vasena vattati.* **";
P_HTM[5702]="*So yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharati;* **";
P_HTM[5703]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharati;* **";
P_HTM[5704]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati sāyanhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā sāyanhasamayaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[5705]="*Evarūpena kho, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā’”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.’”*";
P_HTM[5706]="*“Sādhu sādhu, moggallāna.**“Good, good, Moggallāna!*";
P_HTM[5707]="*Yathā taṃ sāriputtova sammā byākaramāno byākareyya.**Sāriputta answered in the right way for him.*";
P_HTM[5708]="*Sāriputto hi, moggallāna, cittaṃ vasaṃ vatteti no ca sāriputto cittassa vasena vattati.**For Sāriputta masters his mind and is not mastered by it …”*";
P_HTM[5709]="*So yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ viharati;* **";
P_HTM[5710]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā majjhanhikasamayaṃ viharati;* **";
P_HTM[5711]="*yāya vihārasamāpattiyā ākaṅkhati sāyanhasamayaṃ viharituṃ, tāya vihārasamāpattiyā sāyanhasamayaṃ viharatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5712]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Sāriputta asked the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5713]="*“kassa nu kho, bhante, subhāsitan”ti?**“Sir, who has spoken well?”*";
P_HTM[5714]="*“Sabbesaṃ vo, sāriputta, subhāsitaṃ pariyāyena.**“You’ve all spoken well in your own way.*";
P_HTM[5715]="*Api ca mamapi suṇātha yathārūpena bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyya.**However, listen to me also as to what kind of mendicant would beautify this sal forest park at Gosiṅga.*";
P_HTM[5716]="*Idha, sāriputta, bhikkhu pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā:**It’s a mendicant who, after the meal, returns from alms-round, sits down cross-legged with their body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there, thinking:*";
P_HTM[5717]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ pallaṅkaṃ bhindissāmi yāva me nānupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccissatī’ti.**‘I will not break this sitting posture until my mind is freed from the defilements by not grasping!’*";
P_HTM[5718]="*Evarūpena kho, sāriputta, bhikkhunā gosiṅgasālavanaṃ sobheyyā”ti.**That’s the kind of mendicant who would beautify this park.”*";
P_HTM[5719]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5720]="*Attamanā te āyasmanto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, those venerables were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5721]="*Mahāgosiṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5722]="*33. Mahāgopālakasutta**The Longer Discourse on the Cowherd*";
P_HTM[5723]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5724]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5725]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5726]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[5727]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5728]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5729]="*“Ekādasahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako abhabbo gogaṇaṃ pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**“Mendicants, a cowherd with eleven factors can’t maintain and expand a herd of cattle.*";
P_HTM[5730]="*Katamehi ekādasahi?**What eleven?*";
P_HTM[5731]="*Idha, bhikkhave, gopālako na rūpaññū hoti, na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, na āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti, na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, na titthaṃ jānāti, na pītaṃ jānāti, na vīthiṃ jānāti, na gocarakusalo hoti anavasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti.**It’s when a cowherd doesn’t know form, is unskilled in characteristics, doesn’t pick out flies’ eggs, doesn’t dress wounds, doesn’t smoke out pests, doesn’t know the ford, doesn’t know satisfaction, doesn’t know the trail, is not skilled in pastures, milks dry, and doesn’t show extra respect to the bulls who are fathers and leaders of the herd.*";
P_HTM[5732]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako abhabbo gogaṇaṃ pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**A cowherd with these eleven factors can’t maintain and expand a herd of cattle.*";
P_HTM[5733]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjituṃ.**In the same way, a mendicant with eleven qualities can’t achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[5734]="*Katamehi ekādasahi?**What eleven?*";
P_HTM[5735]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaññū hoti, na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, na āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti, na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, na titthaṃ jānāti, na pītaṃ jānāti, na vīthiṃ jānāti, na gocarakusalo hoti, anavasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṃghapitaro saṃghapariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t know form, is unskilled in characteristics, doesn’t pick out flies’ eggs, doesn’t dress wounds, doesn’t smoke out pests, doesn’t know the ford, doesn’t know satisfaction, doesn’t know the trail, is not skilled in pastures, milks dry, and doesn’t show extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5736]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaññū hoti?**And how does a mendicant not know form?*";
P_HTM[5737]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘cattāri mahābhūtāni, catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāyarūpan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t truly understand that all form is the four primary elements, or form derived from the four primary elements.*";
P_HTM[5738]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na rūpaññū hoti. (1)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know form.*";
P_HTM[5739]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti?**And how is a mendicant not skilled in characteristics?*";
P_HTM[5740]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘kammalakkhaṇo bālo, kammalakkhaṇo paṇḍito’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t understand that a fool is characterized by their deeds, and an astute person is characterized by their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5741]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na lakkhaṇakusalo hoti. (2)**That’s how a mendicant isn’t skilled in characteristics.*";
P_HTM[5742]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti?**And how does a mendicant not pick out flies’ eggs?*";
P_HTM[5743]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ adhivāseti, nappajahati na vinodeti na byantī karoti na anabhāvaṃ gameti. Uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme adhivāseti, nappajahati na vinodeti na byantī karoti na anabhāvaṃ gameti.**It’s when a mendicant tolerates a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought that has arisen. They tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen. They don’t give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[5744]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti. (3)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t pick out flies’ eggs.*";
P_HTM[5745]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti?**And how does a mendicant not dress wounds?*";
P_HTM[5746]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā nimittaggāhī hoti anubyañjanaggāhī.**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[5747]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya na paṭipajjati, na rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye na saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**Since the faculty of sight is left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion become overwhelming. They don’t practice restraint, they don’t protect the faculty of sight, and they don’t achieve its restraint.*";
P_HTM[5748]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[5749]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[5750]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[5751]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[5752]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya nimittaggāhī hoti anubyañjanaggāhī.**know a thought with their mind, they get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[5753]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya na paṭipajjati, na rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye na saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**Since the faculty of the mind is left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion become overwhelming. They don’t practice restraint, they don’t protect the faculty of the mind, and they don’t achieve its restraint.*";
P_HTM[5754]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti. (4)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t dress wounds.*";
P_HTM[5755]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti?**And how does a mendicant not smoke out pests?*";
P_HTM[5756]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ na vitthārena paresaṃ desetā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t teach others the Dhamma in detail as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[5757]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na dhūmaṃ kattā hoti. (5)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t smoke out pests.*";
P_HTM[5758]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na titthaṃ jānāti?**And how does a mendicant not know the ford?*";
P_HTM[5759]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te kālena kālaṃ upasaṅkamitvā na paripucchati, na paripañhati:**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t from time to time go up to those mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines—and ask them questions:*";
P_HTM[5760]="*‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ?**‘Why, sir, does it say this?*";
P_HTM[5761]="*Imassa ko attho’ti?**What does that mean?’*";
P_HTM[5762]="*Tassa te āyasmanto avivaṭañceva na vivaranti, anuttānīkatañca na uttānīkaronti, anekavihitesu ca kaṅkhāṭhānīyesu dhammesu kaṅkhaṃ na paṭivinodenti.**Those venerables don’t clarify what is unclear, reveal what is obscure, and dispel doubt regarding the many doubtful matters.*";
P_HTM[5763]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na titthaṃ jānāti. (6)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know the ford.*";
P_HTM[5764]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na pītaṃ jānāti?**And how does a mendicant not know satisfaction?*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne na labhati atthavedaṃ, na labhati dhammavedaṃ, na labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, when the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One are being taught, finds no joy in the meaning and the teaching, and finds no joy connected with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5766]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na pītaṃ jānāti. (7)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know satisfaction.*";
P_HTM[5767]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vīthiṃ jānāti?**And how does a mendicant not know the trail?*";
P_HTM[5768]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t truly understand the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[5769]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na vīthiṃ jānāti. (8)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t know the trail.*";
P_HTM[5770]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na gocarakusalo hoti?**And how is a mendicant not skilled in pastures?*";
P_HTM[5771]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t truly understand the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[5772]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na gocarakusalo hoti. (9)**That’s how a mendicant is not skilled in pastures.*";
P_HTM[5773]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anavasesadohī hoti?**And how does a mendicant milk dry?*";
P_HTM[5774]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ saddhā gahapatikā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavārenti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi, tatra bhikkhu mattaṃ na jānāti paṭiggahaṇāya.**It’s when a mendicant is invited by a householder to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick, and that mendicant doesn’t know moderation in accepting.*";
P_HTM[5775]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anavasesadohī hoti. (10)**That’s how a mendicant milks dry.*";
P_HTM[5776]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti?**And how does a mendicant not show extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha?*";
P_HTM[5777]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā, tesu na mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca;**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t consistently treat senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha with kindness by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private.*";
P_HTM[5778]="*na mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca;* **";
P_HTM[5779]="*na mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca.* **";
P_HTM[5780]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te na atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti. (11)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t show extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5781]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjituṃ.**A mendicant with these eleven qualities can’t achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[5782]="*Ekādasahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako bhabbo gogaṇaṃ pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**A cowherd with eleven factors can maintain and expand a herd of cattle.*";
P_HTM[5783]="*Katamehi ekādasahi?**What eleven?*";
P_HTM[5784]="*Idha, bhikkhave, gopālako rūpaññū hoti, lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti, vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, titthaṃ jānāti, pītaṃ jānāti, vīthiṃ jānāti, gocarakusalo hoti, sāvasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti.**It’s when a cowherd knows form, is skilled in characteristics, picks out flies’ eggs, dresses wounds, smokes out pests, knows the ford, knows satisfaction, knows the trail, is skilled in pastures, doesn’t milk dry, and shows extra respect to the bulls who are fathers and leaders of the herd.*";
P_HTM[5785]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi aṅgehi samannāgato gopālako bhabbo gogaṇaṃ pariharituṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**A cowherd with these eleven factors can maintain and expand a herd of cattle.*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjituṃ.**In the same way, a mendicant with eleven qualities can achieve growth, improvement, and maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[5787]="*Katamehi ekādasahi?**What eleven?*";
P_HTM[5788]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaññū hoti, lakkhaṇakusalo hoti, āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti, vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti, dhūmaṃ kattā hoti, titthaṃ jānāti, pītaṃ jānāti, vīthiṃ jānāti, gocarakusalo hoti, sāvasesadohī ca hoti. Ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant knows form, is skilled in characteristics, picks out flies’ eggs, dresses wounds, smokes out pests, knows the ford, knows satisfaction, knows the trail, is skilled in pastures, doesn’t milk dry, and shows extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5789]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaññū hoti?**And how does a mendicant know form?*";
P_HTM[5790]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘cattāri mahābhūtāni, catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāyarūpan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant truly understands that all form is the four primary elements, or form derived from the four primary elements.*";
P_HTM[5791]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaññū hoti. (1)**That’s how a mendicant knows form.*";
P_HTM[5792]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lakkhaṇakusalo hoti?**And how is a mendicant skilled in characteristics?*";
P_HTM[5793]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kammalakkhaṇo bālo, kammalakkhaṇo paṇḍitoti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant understands that a fool is characterized by their deeds, and an astute person is characterized by their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5794]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lakkhaṇakusalo hoti. (2)**That’s how a mendicant is skilled in characteristics.*";
P_HTM[5795]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti?**And how does a mendicant pick out flies’ eggs?*";
P_HTM[5796]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti, pajahati vinodeti byantī karoti anabhāvaṃ gameti. Uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti, pajahati vinodeti byantī karoti anabhāvaṃ gameti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought that has arisen. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[5797]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsāṭikaṃ hāretā hoti. (3)**That’s how a mendicant picks out flies’ eggs.*";
P_HTM[5798]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti?**And how does a mendicant dress wounds?*";
P_HTM[5799]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[5800]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[5801]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[5802]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[5803]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[5804]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[5805]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[5806]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[5807]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇaṃ paṭicchādetā hoti. (4)**That’s how a mendicant dresses wounds.*";
P_HTM[5808]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhūmaṃ kattā hoti?**And how does a mendicant smoke out pests?*";
P_HTM[5809]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena paresaṃ desetā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant teaches others the Dhamma in detail as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[5810]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhūmaṃ kattā hoti. (5)**That’s how a mendicant smokes out pests.*";
P_HTM[5811]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu titthaṃ jānāti?**And how does a mendicant know the ford?*";
P_HTM[5812]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā te kālena kālaṃ upasaṅkamitvā paripucchati, paripañhati:**It’s when from time to time a mendicant goes up to those mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines—and asks them questions:*";
P_HTM[5813]="*‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ?**‘Why, sir, does it say this?*";
P_HTM[5814]="*Imassa ko attho’ti?**What does that mean?’*";
P_HTM[5815]="*Tassa te āyasmanto avivaṭañceva vivaranti, anuttānīkatañca uttānīkaronti, anekavihitesu ca kaṅkhāṭhānīyesu dhammesu kaṅkhaṃ paṭivinodenti.**Those venerables clarify what is unclear, reveal what is obscure, and dispel doubt regarding the many doubtful matters.*";
P_HTM[5816]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu titthaṃ jānāti. (6)**That’s how a mendicant knows the ford.*";
P_HTM[5817]="*Kathañca bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītaṃ jānāti?**And how does a mendicant know satisfaction?*";
P_HTM[5818]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, when the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One are being taught, finds joy in the meaning and the teaching, and finds joy connected with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5819]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītaṃ jānāti. (7)**That’s how a mendicant knows satisfaction.*";
P_HTM[5820]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vīthiṃ jānāti?**And how does a mendicant know the trail?*";
P_HTM[5821]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant truly understands the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[5822]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vīthiṃ jānāti. (8)**That’s how a mendicant knows the trail.*";
P_HTM[5823]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gocarakusalo hoti?**And how is a mendicant skilled in pastures?*";
P_HTM[5824]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro satipaṭṭhāne yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**It’s when a mendicant truly understands the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[5825]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gocarakusalo hoti. (9)**That’s how a mendicant is skilled in pastures.*";
P_HTM[5826]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sāvasesadohī hoti?**And how does a mendicant not milk dry?*";
P_HTM[5827]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ saddhā gahapatikā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavārenti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi.**It’s when a mendicant is invited by a householder to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick,*";
P_HTM[5828]="*Tatra bhikkhu mattaṃ jānāti paṭiggahaṇāya.**and that mendicant knows moderation in accepting.*";
P_HTM[5829]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sāvasesadohī hoti. (10)**That’s how a mendicant doesn’t milk dry.*";
P_HTM[5830]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā, te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti?**And how does a mendicant show extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha?*";
P_HTM[5831]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā tesu mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca;**It’s when a mendicant consistently treats senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha with kindness by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private.*";
P_HTM[5832]="*mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca;* **";
P_HTM[5833]="*mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpeti āvi ceva raho ca.* **";
P_HTM[5834]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā te atirekapūjāya pūjetā hoti. (11)**That’s how a mendicant shows extra respect to senior mendicants of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5835]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, ekādasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjitun”ti.**A mendicant with these eleven qualities can achieve growth, improvement, and maturity in this teaching and training.”*";
P_HTM[5836]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5837]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5838]="*Mahāgopālakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5839]="*34. Cūḷagopālakasutta**The Shorter Discourse on the Cowherd*";
P_HTM[5840]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5841]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati ukkacelāyaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā tīre.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis near Ukkacelā on the bank of the Ganges river.*";
P_HTM[5842]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5843]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[5844]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5845]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5846]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako duppaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye, asamavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, asamavekkhitvā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, atittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ suvidehānaṃ.**“Once upon a time, mendicants, there was an unintelligent Magadhan cowherd. In the last month of the rainy season, without inspecting the near shore or the far shore, he drove his cattle across a place with no ford on the Ganges river to the land of the Suvidehans on the northern shore.*";
P_HTM[5847]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, gāvo majjhegaṅgāya nadiyā sote āmaṇḍaliyaṃ karitvā tattheva anayabyasanaṃ āpajjiṃsu.**But the cattle bunched up in mid-stream and came to ruin right there.*";
P_HTM[5848]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5849]="*Tathā hi so, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako duppaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye, asamavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, asamavekkhitvā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, atittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ suvidehānaṃ.**Because the unintelligent cowherd failed to inspect the shores before driving the cattle across at a place with no ford.*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā akusalā imassa lokassa akusalā parassa lokassa, akusalā māradheyyassa akusalā amāradheyyassa, akusalā maccudheyyassa akusalā amaccudheyyassa, tesaṃ ye sotabbaṃ saddahātabbaṃ maññissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who are unskilled in this world and the other world, unskilled in Māra’s sovereignty and its opposite, and unskilled in Death’s sovereignty and its opposite. If anyone thinks they are worth listening to and trusting, it will be for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[5851]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako sappaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye, samavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, samavekkhitvā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, tittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ suvidehānaṃ.**Once upon a time, mendicants, there was an intelligent Magadhan cowherd. In the last month of the rainy season, after inspecting the near shore and the far shore, he drove his cattle across a ford on the Ganges river to the land of the Suvidehans on the northern shore.*";
P_HTM[5852]="*So paṭhamaṃ patāresi ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā.**First he drove across the bulls, the fathers and leaders of the herd.*";
P_HTM[5853]="*Te tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu.**They breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5854]="*Athāpare patāresi balavagāvo dammagāvo.**Then he drove across the strong and tractable cattle.*";
P_HTM[5855]="*Tepi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu.**They too breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5856]="*Athāpare patāresi vacchatare vacchatariyo.**Then he drove across the bullocks and heifers.*";
P_HTM[5857]="*Tepi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu.**They too breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5858]="*Athāpare patāresi vacchake kisābalake.**Then he drove across the calves and weak cattle.*";
P_HTM[5859]="*Tepi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu.**They too breasted the stream of the Ganges and safely reached the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5860]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, vacchako taruṇako tāvadeva jātako mātugoravakena vuyhamāno, sopi tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamāsi.**Once it happened that a baby calf had just been born. Urged on by its mother’s lowing, even it managed to breast the stream of the Ganges and safely reach the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5861]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5862]="*Tathā hi so, bhikkhave, māgadhako gopālako sappaññajātiko, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye, samavekkhitvā gaṅgāya nadiyā orimaṃ tīraṃ, samavekkhitvā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, tittheneva gāvo patāresi uttaraṃ tīraṃ suvidehānaṃ.**Because the intelligent cowherd inspected both shores before driving the cattle across at a ford.*";
P_HTM[5863]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kusalā imassa lokassa kusalā parassa lokassa, kusalā māradheyyassa kusalā amāradheyyassa, kusalā maccudheyyassa kusalā amaccudheyyassa, tesaṃ ye sotabbaṃ saddahātabbaṃ maññissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who are skilled in this world and the other world, skilled in Māra’s sovereignty and its opposite, and skilled in Death’s sovereignty and its opposite. If anyone thinks they are worth listening to and trusting, it will be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[5864]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye te usabhā gopitaro gopariṇāyakā te tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;**Just like the bulls, fathers and leaders of the herd, who crossed the Ganges to safety*";
P_HTM[5865]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, te tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṅgatā.**are the mendicants who are perfected, who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment. Having breasted Māra’s stream, they have safely crossed over to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5866]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, balavagāvo dammagāvo tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;**Just like the strong and tractable cattle who crossed the Ganges to safety*";
P_HTM[5867]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā, tepi tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti.**are the mendicants who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, are reborn spontaneously. They’re extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world. They too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5868]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, vacchatarā vacchatariyo tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;**Just like the bullocks and heifers who crossed the Ganges to safety*";
P_HTM[5869]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti, tepi tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti.**are the mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, are once-returners. They come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. They too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5870]="*Seyyathāpi te, bhikkhave, vacchakā kisābalakā tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamaṃsu;**Just like the calves and weak cattle who crossed the Ganges to safety*";
P_HTM[5871]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyanā, tepi tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti.**are the mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. They too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5872]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, vacchako taruṇako tāvadeva jātako mātugoravakena vuyhamāno tiriyaṃ gaṅgāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ agamāsi;**Just like the baby calf who had just been born, but, urged on by its mother’s lowing, still managed to cross the Ganges to safety*";
P_HTM[5873]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū dhammānusārino saddhānusārino, tepi tiriyaṃ mārassa sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gamissanti.**are the mendicants who are followers of principles, followers by faith. They too, having breasted Māra’s stream, will safely cross over to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5874]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, kusalo imassa lokassa kusalo parassa lokassa, kusalo māradheyyassa kusalo amāradheyyassa, kusalo maccudheyyassa kusalo amaccudheyyassa. Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, ye sotabbaṃ saddahātabbaṃ maññissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**Mendicants, I am skilled in this world and the other world, skilled in Māra’s sovereignty and its opposite, and skilled in Death’s sovereignty and its opposite. If anyone thinks I am worth listening to and trusting, it will be for their lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[5875]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5876]="*Idaṃ vatvā sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[5877]="*“Ayaṃ loko paro loko,**“This world and the other world*";
P_HTM[5878]="*jānatā suppakāsito;**have been clearly explained by one who knows;*";
P_HTM[5879]="*Yañca mārena sampattaṃ,**as well as Māra’s reach,*";
P_HTM[5880]="*appattaṃ yañca maccunā.**and what’s out of Death’s reach.*";
P_HTM[5881]="*Sabbaṃ lokaṃ abhiññāya,**Directly knowing the whole world,*";
P_HTM[5882]="*sambuddhena pajānatā;**the Buddha who understands*";
P_HTM[5883]="*Vivaṭaṃ amatadvāraṃ,**has flung open the door of the deathless,*";
P_HTM[5884]="*khemaṃ nibbānapattiyā.**for realizing the sanctuary, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[5885]="*Chinnaṃ pāpimato sotaṃ,**The Wicked One’s stream has been breasted,*";
P_HTM[5886]="*Viddhastaṃ vinaḷīkataṃ;**it’s smashed and gutted.*";
P_HTM[5887]="*Pāmojjabahulā hotha,**Be full of joy, mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Khemaṃ pattattha bhikkhavo”ti.**set your heart on the sanctuary!”*";
P_HTM[5889]="*Cūḷagopālakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5890]="*35. Cūḷasaccakasutta**The Shorter Discourse With Saccaka*";
P_HTM[5891]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5892]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Tena kho pana samayena saccako nigaṇṭhaputto vesāliyaṃ paṭivasati bhassappavādako paṇḍitavādo sādhusammato bahujanassa.**Now at that time Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, was staying in Vesālī. He was a debater and clever speaker regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[5894]="*So vesāliyaṃ parisati evaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati:**He was telling a crowd in Vesālī,*";
P_HTM[5895]="*“nāhaṃ taṃ passāmi samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā, saṅghiṃ gaṇiṃ gaṇācariyaṃ, api arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ paṭijānamānaṃ, yo mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddho na saṅkampeyya na sampakampeyya na sampavedheyya, yassa na kacchehi sedā mucceyyuṃ.**“If I was to take them on in debate, I don’t see any ascetic or brahmin—leader of an order or a community, or the teacher of a community, even one who claims to be a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha—who would not shake and rock and tremble, sweating from the armpits.*";
P_HTM[5896]="*Thūṇaṃ cepāhaṃ acetanaṃ vādena vādaṃ samārabheyyaṃ, sāpi mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddhā saṅkampeyya sampakampeyya sampavedheyya.**Even if I took on an insentient post in debate, it would shake and rock and tremble.*";
P_HTM[5897]="*Ko pana vādo manussabhūtassā”ti?**How much more then a human being!”*";
P_HTM[5898]="*Atha kho āyasmā assaji pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Venerable Assaji robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Vesālī for alms.*";
P_HTM[5899]="*Addasā kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto vesāliyaṃ jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno āyasmantaṃ assajiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**As Saccaka was going for a walk he saw Assaji coming off in the distance.*";
P_HTM[5900]="*Disvāna yenāyasmā assaji tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā assajinā saddhiṃ sammodi.**He approached him and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5901]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto āyasmantaṃ assajiṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Saccaka stood to one side and said to Assaji,*";
P_HTM[5902]="*“kathaṃ pana, bho assaji, samaṇo gotamo sāvake vineti, kathaṃbhāgā ca pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakesu anusāsanī bahulā pavattatī”ti?**“Master Assaji, how does the ascetic Gotama guide his disciples? And how does instruction to his disciples generally proceed?”*";
P_HTM[5903]="*“Evaṃ kho, aggivessana, bhagavā sāvake vineti, evaṃbhāgā ca pana bhagavato sāvakesu anusāsanī bahulā pavattati:**“Aggivessana, this is how the ascetic Gotama guides his disciples, and how instruction to his disciples generally proceeds:*";
P_HTM[5904]="*‘rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ, vedanā aniccā, saññā aniccā, saṅkhārā aniccā, viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ.**‘Form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[5905]="*Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, anattā, vedanā anattā, saññā anattā, saṅkhārā anattā, viññāṇaṃ anattā.**Form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are not-self.*";
P_HTM[5906]="*Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā, sabbe dhammā anattā’ti.**All conditions are impermanent. All things are not-self.’*";
P_HTM[5907]="*Evaṃ kho, aggivessana, bhagavā sāvake vineti, evaṃbhāgā ca pana bhagavato sāvakesu anusāsanī bahulā pavattatī”ti.**This is how the ascetic Gotama guides his disciples, and how instruction to his disciples generally proceeds.”*";
P_HTM[5908]="*“Dussutaṃ vata, bho assaji, assumha ye mayaṃ evaṃvādiṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ assumha.**“It’s sad to hear, Master Assaji, that the ascetic Gotama has such a doctrine.*";
P_HTM[5909]="*Appeva nāma mayaṃ kadāci karahaci tena bhotā gotamena saddhiṃ samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo, appeva nāma tasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā viveceyyāmā”ti.**Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet Master Gotama, and we can have a discussion. And hopefully I can dissuade him from this harmful misconception.”*";
P_HTM[5910]="*Tena kho pana samayena pañcamattāni licchavisatāni santhāgāre sannipatitāni honti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time around five hundred Licchavis were sitting together at the meeting hall on some business.*";
P_HTM[5911]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto yena te licchavī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te licchavī etadavoca:**Then Saccaka went up to them and said,*";
P_HTM[5912]="*“abhikkamantu bhonto licchavī, abhikkamantu bhonto licchavī, ajja me samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo bhavissati.**“Come forth, good Licchavīs, come forth! Today I am going to have a discussion with the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[5913]="*Sace me samaṇo gotamo tathā patiṭṭhissati yathā ca me ñātaññatarena sāvakena assajinā nāma bhikkhunā patiṭṭhitaṃ, seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso dīghalomikaṃ eḷakaṃ lomesu gahetvā ākaḍḍheyya parikaḍḍheyya samparikaḍḍheyya;**If he stands by the position stated to me by one of his well-known disciples—a mendicant named Assaji—I’ll take him on in debate and drag him to and fro and round about, like a strong man would drag a fleecy sheep to and fro and round about!*";
P_HTM[5914]="*evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ ākaḍḍhissāmi parikaḍḍhissāmi samparikaḍḍhissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5915]="*Seyyathāpi nāma balavā soṇḍikākammakāro mahantaṃ soṇḍikākiḷañjaṃ gambhīre udakarahade pakkhipitvā kaṇṇe gahetvā ākaḍḍheyya parikaḍḍheyya samparikaḍḍheyya;**Taking him on in debate, I’ll drag him to and fro and round about, like a strong brewer’s worker would toss a large brewer’s sieve into a deep lake, grab it by the corners, and drag it to and fro and round about!*";
P_HTM[5916]="*evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ ākaḍḍhissāmi parikaḍḍhissāmi samparikaḍḍhissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5917]="*Seyyathāpi nāma balavā soṇḍikādhutto vālaṃ kaṇṇe gahetvā odhuneyya niddhuneyya nipphoṭeyya;**Taking him on in debate, I’ll shake him down and about, and give him a beating, like a strong brewer’s mixer would grab a strainer by the corners and shake it down and about, and give it a beating!*";
P_HTM[5918]="*evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ odhunissāmi niddhunissāmi nipphoṭessāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5919]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kuñjaro saṭṭhihāyano gambhīraṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā sāṇadhovikaṃ nāma kīḷitajātaṃ kīḷati;**I’ll play a game of ear-washing with the ascetic Gotama, like a sixty-year-old elephant would plunge into a deep lotus pond and play a game of ear-washing!*";
P_HTM[5920]="*evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ sāṇadhovikaṃ maññe kīḷitajātaṃ kīḷissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5921]="*Abhikkamantu bhonto licchavī, abhikkamantu bhonto licchavī, ajja me samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo bhavissatī”ti.**Come forth, good Licchavīs, come forth! Today I am going to have a discussion with the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[5922]="*Tatrekacce licchavī evamāhaṃsu:**At that, some of the Licchavis said,*";
P_HTM[5923]="*“kiṃ samaṇo gotamo saccakassa nigaṇṭhaputtassa vādaṃ āropessati, atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropessatī”ti?**“How can the ascetic Gotama refute Saccaka’s doctrine, when it is Saccaka who will refute Gotama’s doctrine?”*";
P_HTM[5924]="*Ekacce licchavī evamāhaṃsu:**But some of the Licchavis said,*";
P_HTM[5925]="*“kiṃ so bhavamāno saccako nigaṇṭhaputto yo bhagavato vādaṃ āropessati, atha kho bhagavā saccakassa nigaṇṭhaputtassa vādaṃ āropessatī”ti?**“Who is Saccaka to refute the Buddha’s doctrine, when it is the Buddha who will refute Saccaka’s doctrine?”*";
P_HTM[5926]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto pañcamattehi licchavisatehi parivuto yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Saccaka, escorted by the five hundred Licchavis, went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[5927]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū abbhokāse caṅkamanti.**At that time several mendicants were walking meditation in the open air.*";
P_HTM[5928]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:**Then Saccaka went up to them and said,*";
P_HTM[5929]="*“kahaṃ nu kho, bho, etarahi so bhavaṃ gotamo viharati?**“Gentlemen, where is Master Gotama at present?*";
P_HTM[5930]="*Dassanakāmā hi mayaṃ taṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti.**For we want to see him.”*";
P_HTM[5931]="*“Esa, aggivessana, bhagavā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisinno”ti.**“Aggivessana, the Buddha has plunged deep into the Great Wood and is sitting at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation.”*";
P_HTM[5932]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto mahatiyā licchaviparisāya saddhiṃ mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Saccaka, together with a large group of Licchavis, went to see the Buddha in the Great Wood, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5933]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[5934]="*Tepi kho licchavī appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Before sitting down to one side, some of the Licchavīs bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5935]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Saccaka said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5936]="*“puccheyyāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ kiñcideva desaṃ, sace me bhavaṃ gotamo okāsaṃ karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti.**“I’d like to ask Master Gotama about a certain point, if you’d take the time to answer.”*";
P_HTM[5937]="*“Puccha, aggivessana, yadākaṅkhasī”ti.**“Ask what you wish, Aggivessana.”*";
P_HTM[5938]="*“Kathaṃ pana bhavaṃ gotamo sāvake vineti, kathaṃbhāgā ca pana bhoto gotamassa sāvakesu anusāsanī bahulā pavattatī”ti?**“How does the ascetic Gotama guide his disciples? And how does instruction to his disciples generally proceed?”*";
P_HTM[5939]="*“Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, sāvake vinemi, evaṃbhāgā ca pana me sāvakesu anusāsanī bahulā pavattati:**“This is how I guide my disciples, and how instruction to my disciples generally proceeds:*";
P_HTM[5940]="*‘rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ, vedanā aniccā, saññā aniccā, saṅkhārā aniccā, viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ.**‘Form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[5941]="*Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, anattā, vedanā anattā, saññā anattā, saṅkhārā anattā, viññāṇaṃ anattā.**Form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are not-self.*";
P_HTM[5942]="*Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā, sabbe dhammā anattā’ti.**All conditions are impermanent. All things are not-self.’*";
P_HTM[5943]="*Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, sāvake vinemi, evaṃbhāgā ca pana me sāvakesu anusāsanī bahulā pavattatī”ti.**This is how I guide my disciples, and how instruction to my disciples generally proceeds.”*";
P_HTM[5944]="*“Upamā maṃ, bho gotama, paṭibhātī”ti.**“A simile strikes me, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[5945]="*“Paṭibhātu taṃ, aggivessanā”ti bhagavā avoca.**“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5946]="*“Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, ye kecime bījagāmabhūtagāmā vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjanti, sabbe te pathaviṃ nissāya pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhāya.**“All the plants and seeds that achieve growth, increase, and maturity do so depending on the earth and grounded on the earth.*";
P_HTM[5947]="*Evamete bījagāmabhūtagāmā vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[5948]="*Seyyathāpi vā pana, bho gotama, ye kecime balakaraṇīyā kammantā karīyanti, sabbe te pathaviṃ nissāya pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhāya.**All the hard work that gets done depends on the earth and is grounded on the earth.*";
P_HTM[5949]="*Evamete balakaraṇīyā kammantā karīyanti.* **";
P_HTM[5950]="*Evameva kho, bho gotama, rūpattāyaṃ purisapuggalo rūpe patiṭṭhāya puññaṃ vā apuññaṃ vā pasavati, vedanattāyaṃ purisapuggalo vedanāyaṃ patiṭṭhāya puññaṃ vā apuññaṃ vā pasavati, saññattāyaṃ purisapuggalo saññāyaṃ patiṭṭhāya puññaṃ vā apuññaṃ vā pasavati, saṅkhārattāyaṃ purisapuggalo saṅkhāresu patiṭṭhāya puññaṃ vā apuññaṃ vā pasavati, viññāṇattāyaṃ purisapuggalo viññāṇe patiṭṭhāya puññaṃ vā apuññaṃ vā pasavatī”ti.**In the same way, an individual’s self is form. Grounded on form they make good and bad choices. An individual’s self is feeling … perception … choices … consciousness. Grounded on consciousness they make good and bad choices.”*";
P_HTM[5951]="*“Nanu tvaṃ, aggivessana, evaṃ vadesi:**“Aggivessana, are you not saying this:*";
P_HTM[5952]="*‘rūpaṃ me attā, vedanā me attā, saññā me attā, saṅkhārā me attā, viññāṇaṃ me attā’”ti?**‘Form is my self, feeling is my self, perception is my self, choices are my self, consciousness is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[5953]="*“Ahañhi, bho gotama, evaṃ vadāmi:**“Indeed, Master Gotama, that is what I am saying.*";
P_HTM[5954]="*‘rūpaṃ me attā, vedanā me attā, saññā me attā, saṅkhārā me attā, viññāṇaṃ me attā’ti, ayañca mahatī janatā”ti.**And this big crowd agrees with me!”*";
P_HTM[5955]="*“Kiñhi te, aggivessana, mahatī janatā karissati?**“What has this big crowd to do with you?*";
P_HTM[5956]="*Iṅgha tvaṃ, aggivessana, sakaññeva vādaṃ nibbeṭhehī”ti.**Please just explain your own statement.”*";
P_HTM[5957]="*“Ahañhi, bho gotama, evaṃ vadāmi:**“Then, Master Gotama, what I am saying is this:*";
P_HTM[5958]="*‘rūpaṃ me attā, vedanā me attā, saññā me attā, saṅkhārā me attā, viññāṇaṃ me attā’”ti.**‘Form is my self, feeling is my self, perception is my self, choices are my self, consciousness is my self’.”*";
P_HTM[5959]="*“Tena hi, aggivessana, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi, yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi.**“Well then, Aggivessana, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like.*";
P_HTM[5960]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[5961]="*vatteyya rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa sakasmiṃ vijite vaso—**Consider an anointed king such as Pasenadi of Kosala or Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha.*";
P_HTM[5962]="*ghātetāyaṃ vā ghātetuṃ, jāpetāyaṃ vā jāpetuṃ, pabbājetāyaṃ vā pabbājetuṃ, seyyathāpi rañño pasenadissa kosalassa, seyyathāpi vā pana rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassā”ti?**Would they have the power in their own realm to execute, fine, or banish those who are guilty?”*";
P_HTM[5963]="*“Vatteyya, bho gotama, rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa sakasmiṃ vijite vaso—**“An anointed king would have such power, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[5964]="*ghātetāyaṃ vā ghātetuṃ, jāpetāyaṃ vā jāpetuṃ, pabbājetāyaṃ vā pabbājetuṃ, seyyathāpi rañño pasenadissa kosalassa, seyyathāpi vā pana rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa.* **";
P_HTM[5965]="*Imesampi hi, bho gotama, saṃghānaṃ gaṇānaṃ—**Even federations such as the*";
P_HTM[5966]="*Seyyathidaṃ—vajjīnaṃ mallānaṃ—**Vajjis and Mallas*";
P_HTM[5967]="*vattati sakasmiṃ vijite vaso—**have such power in their own realm.*";
P_HTM[5968]="*ghātetāyaṃ vā ghātetuṃ, jāpetāyaṃ vā jāpetuṃ, pabbājetāyaṃ vā pabbājetuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5969]="*Kiṃ pana rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa, seyyathāpi rañño pasenadissa kosalassa, seyyathāpi vā pana rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa?**So of course an anointed king such as Pasenadi or Ajātasattu*";
P_HTM[5970]="*Vatteyya, bho gotama, vattituñca marahatī”ti.**would wield such power, as is their right.”*";
P_HTM[5971]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**“What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[5972]="*yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:**When you say,*";
P_HTM[5973]="*‘rūpaṃ me attā’ti, vattati te tasmiṃ rūpe vaso—**‘Form is my self,’ do you have power over that form to say:*";
P_HTM[5974]="*evaṃ me rūpaṃ hotu, evaṃ me rūpaṃ mā ahosī”ti?**‘May my form be like this! May it not be like that’?”*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Evaṃ vutte, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto tuṇhī ahosi.**When he said this, Saccaka kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5976]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ etadavoca:**The Buddha asked the question a second time,*";
P_HTM[5977]="*“taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana, yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:* **";
P_HTM[5978]="*‘rūpaṃ me attā’ti, vattati te tasmiṃ rūpe vaso—* **";
P_HTM[5979]="*evaṃ me rūpaṃ hotu, evaṃ me rūpaṃ mā ahosī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5980]="*Dutiyampi kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto tuṇhī ahosi.**but Saccaka still kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5981]="*Atha kho bhagavā saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ etadavoca:**So the Buddha said to Saccaka,*";
P_HTM[5982]="*“byākarohi dāni, aggivessana, na dāni te tuṇhībhāvassa kālo.**“Answer now, Aggivessana. Now is not the time for silence.*";
P_HTM[5983]="*Yo koci, aggivessana tathāgatena yāvatatiyaṃ sahadhammikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho na byākaroti, etthevassa sattadhā muddhā phalatī”ti.**If someone fails to answer a legitimate question when asked three times by the Buddha, their head explodes into seven pieces there and then.”*";
P_HTM[5984]="*Tena kho pana samayena vajirapāṇi yakkho āyasaṃ vajiraṃ ādāya ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ saccakassa nigaṇṭhaputtassa uparivehāsaṃ ṭhito hoti:**Now at that time the spirit Vajirapāṇi, taking up a burning iron thunderbolt, blazing and glowing, stood in the sky above Saccaka, thinking,*";
P_HTM[5985]="*“sacāyaṃ saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavatā yāvatatiyaṃ sahadhammikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho na byākarissati etthevassa sattadhā muddhaṃ phālessāmī”ti.**“If this Saccaka doesn’t answer when asked a third time, I’ll blow his head into seven pieces there and then!”*";
P_HTM[5986]="*Taṃ kho pana vajirapāṇiṃ yakkhaṃ bhagavā ceva passati saccako ca nigaṇṭhaputto.**And both the Buddha and Saccaka could see Vajirapāṇi.*";
P_HTM[5987]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhīto saṃviggo lomahaṭṭhajāto bhagavantaṃyeva tāṇaṃ gavesī bhagavantaṃyeva leṇaṃ gavesī bhagavantaṃyeva saraṇaṃ gavesī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Saccaka was terrified, shocked, and awestruck. Looking to the Buddha for shelter, protection, and refuge, he said,*";
P_HTM[5988]="*“pucchatu maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo, byākarissāmī”ti.**“Ask me, Master Gotama. I will answer.”*";
P_HTM[5989]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**“What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[5990]="*yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:**When you say,*";
P_HTM[5991]="*‘rūpaṃ me attā’ti, vattati te tasmiṃ rūpe vaso—**‘Form is my self,’ do you have power over that form to say:*";
P_HTM[5992]="*evaṃ me rūpaṃ hotu, evaṃ me rūpaṃ mā ahosī”ti?**‘May my form be like this! May it not be like that’?”*";
P_HTM[5993]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[5994]="*“Manasi karohi, aggivessana;**“Think about it, Aggivessana!*";
P_HTM[5995]="*manasi karitvā kho, aggivessana, byākarohi.**You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[5996]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[5997]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[5998]="*yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:**When you say,*";
P_HTM[5999]="*‘vedanā me attā’ti, vattati te tissaṃ vedanāyaṃ vaso—**‘Feeling is my self,’ do you have power over that feeling to say:*";
P_HTM[6000]="*evaṃ me vedanā hotu, evaṃ me vedanā mā ahosī”ti?**‘May my feeling be like this! May it not be like that’?”*";
P_HTM[6001]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6002]="*“Manasi karohi, aggivessana;**“Think about it, Aggivessana!*";
P_HTM[6003]="*manasi karitvā kho, aggivessana, byākarohi.**You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[6004]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[6005]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6006]="*yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:**When you say,*";
P_HTM[6007]="*‘saññā me attā’ti, vattati te tissaṃ saññāyaṃ vaso—**‘Perception is my self,’ do you have power over that perception to say:*";
P_HTM[6008]="*evaṃ me saññā hotu, evaṃ me saññā mā ahosī”ti?**‘May my perception be like this! May it not be like that’?”*";
P_HTM[6009]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6010]="*“Manasi karohi, aggivessana;**“Think about it, Aggivessana!*";
P_HTM[6011]="*manasi karitvā kho, aggivessana, byākarohi.**You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[6012]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[6013]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6014]="*yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:**When you say,*";
P_HTM[6015]="*‘saṅkhārā me attā’ti, vattati te tesu saṅkhāresu vaso—**‘Choices are my self,’ do you have power over those choices to say:*";
P_HTM[6016]="*evaṃ me saṅkhārā hontu, evaṃ me saṅkhārā mā ahesun”ti?**‘May my choices be like this! May they not be like that’?”*";
P_HTM[6017]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6018]="*“Manasi karohi, aggivessana;**“Think about it, Aggivessana!*";
P_HTM[6019]="*manasi karitvā kho, aggivessana, byākarohi.**You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[6020]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[6021]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6022]="*yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi:**When you say,*";
P_HTM[6023]="*‘viññāṇaṃ me attā’ti, vattati te tasmiṃ viññāṇe vaso—**‘Consciousness is my self,’ do you have power over that consciousness to say:*";
P_HTM[6024]="*evaṃ me viññāṇaṃ hotu, evaṃ me viññāṇaṃ mā ahosī”ti?**‘May my consciousness be like this! May it not be like that’?”*";
P_HTM[6025]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6026]="*“Manasi karohi, aggivessana;**“Think about it, Aggivessana!*";
P_HTM[6027]="*manasi karitvā kho, aggivessana, byākarohi.**You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[6028]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[6029]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6030]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[6031]="*“Aniccaṃ, bho gotama”.**“Impermanent.”*";
P_HTM[6032]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[6033]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bho gotama”.**“Suffering.”*";
P_HTM[6034]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[6035]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[6036]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6037]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**“What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6038]="*vedanā … pe …**Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[6039]="*saññā … pe …**perception …*";
P_HTM[6040]="*saṅkhārā … pe …**choices …*";
P_HTM[6041]="*taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana, viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[6042]="*“Aniccaṃ, bho gotama”.**“Impermanent.”*";
P_HTM[6043]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[6044]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bho gotama”.**“Suffering.”*";
P_HTM[6045]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[6046]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[6047]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6048]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**“What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6049]="*yo nu kho dukkhaṃ allīno dukkhaṃ upagato dukkhaṃ ajjhosito, dukkhaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati, api nu kho so sāmaṃ vā dukkhaṃ parijāneyya, dukkhaṃ vā parikkhepetvā vihareyyā”ti?**Consider someone who clings, holds, and attaches to suffering, regarding it thus: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’ Would such a person be able to completely understand suffering themselves, or live having wiped out suffering?”*";
P_HTM[6050]="*“Kiñhi siyā, bho gotama?**“How could they?*";
P_HTM[6051]="*No hidaṃ, bho gotamā”ti.**No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6052]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**“What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6053]="*nanu tvaṃ evaṃ sante dukkhaṃ allīno dukkhaṃ upagato dukkhaṃ ajjhosito, dukkhaṃ:**This being so, aren’t you someone who clings, holds, and attaches to suffering, regarding it thus: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[6054]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6055]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, bho gotama?**“How could I not?*";
P_HTM[6056]="*Evametaṃ, bho gotamā”ti.**Yes, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[6057]="*“Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya.**“Suppose, Aggivessana, there was a person in need of heartwood. Wandering in search of heartwood, they’d take a sharp axe and enter a forest.*";
P_HTM[6058]="*So tattha passeyya mahantaṃ kadalikkhandhaṃ ujuṃ navaṃ akukkukajātaṃ.**There they’d see a big banana tree, straight and young and grown free of defects.*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Tamenaṃ mūle chindeyya, mūle chetvā agge chindeyya, agge chetvā pattavaṭṭiṃ vinibbhujeyya.**They’d cut it down at the base, cut off the top, and unroll the coiled sheaths.*";
P_HTM[6060]="*So tattha pattavaṭṭiṃ vinibbhujanto pheggumpi nādhigaccheyya, kuto sāraṃ?**But they wouldn’t even find sapwood, much less heartwood.*";
P_HTM[6061]="*Evameva kho tvaṃ, aggivessana, mayā sakasmiṃ vāde samanuyuñjiyamāno samanugāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno ritto tuccho aparaddho.**In the same way, when pursued, pressed, and grilled by me on your own doctrine, you turn out to be void, hollow, and mistaken.*";
P_HTM[6062]="*Bhāsitā kho pana te esā, aggivessana, vesāliyaṃ parisati vācā:**But it was you who stated before the assembly of Vesālī:*";
P_HTM[6063]="*‘nāhaṃ taṃ passāmi samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā, saṃghiṃ gaṇiṃ gaṇācariyaṃ, api arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ paṭijānamānaṃ, yo mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddho na saṅkampeyya na sampakampeyya na sampavedheyya, yassa na kacchehi sedā mucceyyuṃ.**‘If I was to take them on in debate, I don’t see any ascetic or brahmin—leader of an order or a community, or the teacher of a community, even one who claims to be a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha—who would not shake and rock and tremble, sweating from the armpits.*";
P_HTM[6064]="*Thūṇaṃ cepāhaṃ acetanaṃ vādena vādaṃ samārabheyyaṃ sāpi mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddhā saṅkampeyya sampakampeyya sampavedheyya.**Even if I took on an insentient post in debate, it would shake and rock and tremble.*";
P_HTM[6065]="*Ko pana vādo manussabhūtassā’ti?**How much more then a human being!’*";
P_HTM[6066]="*Tuyhaṃ kho pana, aggivessana, appekaccāni sedaphusitāni nalāṭā muttāni, uttarāsaṅgaṃ vinibhinditvā bhūmiyaṃ patiṭṭhitāni.**But sweat is pouring from your forehead; it’s soaked through your robe and drips on the ground.*";
P_HTM[6067]="*Mayhaṃ kho pana, aggivessana, natthi etarahi kāyasmiṃ sedo”ti.**While I now have no sweat on my body.”*";
P_HTM[6068]="*Iti bhagavā tasmiṃ parisati suvaṇṇavaṇṇaṃ kāyaṃ vivari.**So the Buddha revealed his golden body to the assembly.*";
P_HTM[6069]="*Evaṃ vutte, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi.**When this was said, Saccaka sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[6070]="*Atha kho dummukho licchaviputto saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Knowing this, the Licchavi Dummukha said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6071]="*“upamā maṃ, bhagavā, paṭibhātī”ti.**“A simile strikes me, Blessed One.”*";
P_HTM[6072]="*“Paṭibhātu taṃ, dummukhā”ti bhagavā avoca.**“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6073]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhante, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre pokkharaṇī.**“Sir, suppose there was a lotus pond not far from a town or village,*";
P_HTM[6074]="*Tatrāssa kakkaṭako.**and a crab lived there.*";
P_HTM[6075]="*Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā kumārakā vā kumārikā vā tamhā gāmā vā nigamā vā nikkhamitvā yena sā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkameyyuṃ; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā taṃ kakkaṭakaṃ udakā uddharitvā thale patiṭṭhāpeyyuṃ.**Then several boys or girls would leave the town or village and go to the pond, where they’d pull out the crab and put it on dry land.*";
P_HTM[6076]="*Yaññadeva hi so, bhante, kakkaṭako aḷaṃ abhininnāmeyya taṃ tadeva te kumārakā vā kumārikā vā kaṭṭhena vā kathalena vā sañchindeyyuṃ sambhañjeyyuṃ sampalibhañjeyyuṃ.**Whenever that crab extended a claw, those boys or girls would snap, crack, and break it off with a stick or a stone.*";
P_HTM[6077]="*Evañhi so, bhante, kakkaṭako sabbehi aḷehi sañchinnehi sambhaggehi sampalibhaggehi abhabbo taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ puna otarituṃ, seyyathāpi pubbe.**And when that crab’s claws had all been snapped, cracked, and broken off it wouldn’t be able to return down into that lotus pond.*";
P_HTM[6078]="*Evameva kho, bhante, yāni saccakassa nigaṇṭhaputtassa visūkāyitāni visevitāni vipphanditāni tānipi sabbāni bhagavatā sañchinnāni sambhaggāni sampalibhaggāni;**In the same way, sir, the Buddha has snapped, cracked, and broken off all Saccaka’s tricks, dodges, and evasions.*";
P_HTM[6079]="*abhabbo ca dāni, bhante, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto puna bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamituṃ yadidaṃ vādādhippāyo”ti.**Now he can’t get near the Buddha again looking for a debate.”*";
P_HTM[6080]="*Evaṃ vutte, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto dummukhaṃ licchaviputtaṃ etadavoca:**But Saccaka said to him,*";
P_HTM[6081]="*“āgamehi tvaṃ, dummukha,āgamehi tvaṃ, dummukha, () na mayaṃ tayā saddhiṃ mantema, idha mayaṃ bhotā gotamena saddhiṃ mantema.**“Hold on, Dummukha, hold on! I wasn’t talking with you, I was talking with Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6082]="*Tiṭṭhatesā, bho gotama, amhākañceva aññesañca puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ vācā.**Master Gotama, leave aside that statement I made—as did various other ascetics and brahmins—*";
P_HTM[6083]="*Vilāpaṃ vilapitaṃ maññe.**it was, like, just a bit of nonsense.*";
P_HTM[6084]="*Kittāvatā ca nu kho bhoto gotamassa sāvako sāsanakaro hoti ovādapatikaro tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane viharatī”ti?**How do you define a disciple of Master Gotama who follows instructions and responds to advice; who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, gained assurance, and is independent of others in the Teacher’s instructions?”*";
P_HTM[6085]="*“Idha, aggivessana, mama sāvako yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati;**“It’s when one of my disciples truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[6086]="*yā kāci vedanā … pe …**They truly see any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[6087]="*yā kāci saññā … pe …**perception …*";
P_HTM[6088]="*ye keci saṅkhārā … pe …**choices …*";
P_HTM[6089]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā, yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Ettāvatā kho, aggivessana, mama sāvako sāsanakaro hoti ovādapatikaro tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane viharatī”ti.**That’s how to define one of my disciples who follows instructions and responds to advice; who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, gained assurance, and is independent of others in the Teacher’s instructions.”*";
P_HTM[6091]="*“Kittāvatā pana, bho gotama, bhikkhu arahaṃ hoti khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto”ti?**“But how do you define a mendicant who is a perfected one, with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment?”*";
P_HTM[6092]="*“Idha, aggivessana, bhikkhu yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādā vimutto hoti;**“It’s when one of my disciples truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ And having seen this with right understanding they’re freed by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[6093]="*yā kāci vedanā … pe …**They truly see any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[6094]="*yā kāci saññā … pe …**perception …*";
P_HTM[6095]="*ye keci saṅkhārā … pe …**choices …*";
P_HTM[6096]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādā vimutto hoti.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ And having seen this with right understanding they’re freed by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[6097]="*Ettāvatā kho, aggivessana, bhikkhu arahaṃ hoti khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto.**That’s how to define a mendicant who is a perfected one, with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment.*";
P_HTM[6098]="*Evaṃ vimuttacitto kho, aggivessana, bhikkhu tīhi anuttariyehi samannāgato hoti—**A mendicant whose mind is freed like this has three unsurpassable qualities:*";
P_HTM[6099]="*dassanānuttariyena, paṭipadānuttariyena, vimuttānuttariyena.**unsurpassable vision, practice, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[6100]="*Evaṃ vimuttacitto kho, aggivessana, bhikkhu tathāgataññeva sakkaroti garuṃ karoti māneti pūjeti—**They honor, respect, esteem, and venerate only the Realized One:*";
P_HTM[6101]="*buddho so bhagavā bodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, danto so bhagavā damathāya dhammaṃ deseti, santo so bhagavā samathāya dhammaṃ deseti, tiṇṇo so bhagavā taraṇāya dhammaṃ deseti, parinibbuto so bhagavā parinibbānāya dhammaṃ desetī”ti.**‘The Blessed One is awakened, tamed, serene, crossed over, and extinguished. And he teaches Dhamma for awakening, taming, serenity, crossing over, and extinguishment.’”*";
P_HTM[6102]="*Evaṃ vutte, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Saccaka said to him,*";
P_HTM[6103]="*“mayameva, bho gotama, dhaṃsī, mayaṃ pagabbā, ye mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ āsādetabbaṃ amaññimha.**“Master Gotama, it was rude and impudent of me to imagine I could attack you in debate.*";
P_HTM[6104]="*Siyā hi, bho gotama, hatthiṃ pabhinnaṃ āsajja purisassa sotthibhāvo, na tveva bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ āsajja siyā purisassa sotthibhāvo.**For a person might find safety after attacking a rutting elephant, but not after attacking Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6105]="*Siyā hi, bho gotama, pajjalitaṃ aggikkhandhaṃ āsajja purisassa sotthibhāvo, na tveva bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ āsajja siyā purisassa sotthibhāvo.**A person might find safety after attacking a blazing mass of fire, but not after attacking Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6106]="*Siyā hi, bho gotama, āsīvisaṃ ghoravisaṃ āsajja purisassa sotthibhāvo, na tveva bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ āsajja siyā purisassa sotthibhāvo.**They might find safety after attacking a poisonous viper, but not after attacking Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6107]="*Mayameva, bho gotama, dhaṃsī, mayaṃ pagabbā, ye mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ āsādetabbaṃ amaññimha.**It was rude and impudent of me to imagine I could attack you in debate.*";
P_HTM[6108]="*Adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti.**Would Master Gotama together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me?”*";
P_HTM[6109]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[6110]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā te licchavī āmantesi:**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Saccaka addressed those Licchavis,*";
P_HTM[6111]="*“suṇantu me bhonto licchavī, samaṇo me gotamo nimantito svātanāya saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**“Listen, gentlemen. I have invited the ascetic Gotama together with the Saṅgha of mendicants for tomorrow’s meal.*";
P_HTM[6112]="*Tena me abhihareyyātha yamassa patirūpaṃ maññeyyāthā”ti.**You may all bring me what you think is suitable.”*";
P_HTM[6113]="*Atha kho te licchavī tassā rattiyā accayena saccakassa nigaṇṭhaputtassa pañcamattāni thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāraṃ abhihariṃsu.**Then, when the night had passed, those Licchavis presented Saccaka with an offering of five hundred servings of food.*";
P_HTM[6114]="*Atha kho nigaṇṭhaputto sake ārāme paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi:**And Saccaka had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, saying,*";
P_HTM[6115]="*“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**“It’s time, Master Gotama, the meal is ready.”*";
P_HTM[6116]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena saccakassa nigaṇṭhaputtassa ārāmo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Saccaka’s park, where he sat on the seat spread out, together with the Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[6117]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then Saccaka served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[6118]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Saccaka took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[6119]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Saccaka said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6120]="*“yamidaṃ, bho gotama, dāne puññañca puññamahī ca taṃ dāyakānaṃ sukhāya hotū”ti.**“Master Gotama, may the merit and the growth of merit in this gift be for the happiness of the donors.”*";
P_HTM[6121]="*“Yaṃ kho, aggivessana, tādisaṃ dakkhiṇeyyaṃ āgamma avītarāgaṃ avītadosaṃ avītamohaṃ, taṃ dāyakānaṃ bhavissati.**“Aggivessana, whatever comes from giving to a recipient of a religious donation such as yourself—who is not free of greed, hate, and delusion—will accrue to the donors.*";
P_HTM[6122]="*Yaṃ kho, aggivessana, mādisaṃ dakkhiṇeyyaṃ āgamma vītarāgaṃ vītadosaṃ vītamohaṃ, taṃ tuyhaṃ bhavissatī”ti.**Whatever comes from giving to a recipient of a religious donation such as myself—who is free of greed, hate, and delusion—will accrue to you.”*";
P_HTM[6123]="*Cūḷasaccakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6124]="*36. Mahāsaccakasutta**The Longer Discourse With Saccaka*";
P_HTM[6125]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6126]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[6127]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ sunivattho hoti pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pavisitukāmo.**Now at that time in the morning the Buddha, being properly dressed, took his bowl and robe, wishing to enter Vesālī for alms.*";
P_HTM[6128]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā tenupasaṅkami.**Then as Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, was going for a walk he approached the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[6129]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Venerable Ānanda saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6130]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6131]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto āgacchati bhassappavādako paṇḍitavādo sādhusammato bahujanassa.**“Sir, Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, is coming. He’s a debater and clever speaker regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[6132]="*Eso kho, bhante, avaṇṇakāmo buddhassa, avaṇṇakāmo dhammassa, avaṇṇakāmo saṃghassa.**He wants to discredit the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6133]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā muhuttaṃ nisīdatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**Please, sir, sit for a moment out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[6134]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[6135]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Saccaka went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6136]="*“Santi, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kāyabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti, no cittabhāvanaṃ.**“Master Gotama, there are some ascetics and brahmins who live committed to the practice of developing physical endurance, without developing the mind.*";
P_HTM[6137]="*Phusanti hi te, bho gotama, sārīrikaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ.**They experience painful physical feelings.*";
P_HTM[6138]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bho gotama, sārīrikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭhassa sato ūrukkhambhopi nāma bhavissati, hadayampi nāma phalissati, uṇhampi lohitaṃ mukhato uggamissati, ummādampi pāpuṇissati cittakkhepaṃ.**This happened to someone once. Their thighs became paralyzed, their heart burst, hot blood gushed from their mouth, and they went mad and lost their mind.*";
P_HTM[6139]="*Tassa kho etaṃ, bho gotama, kāyanvayaṃ cittaṃ hoti, kāyassa vasena vattati.**Their mind was subject to the body, and the body had power over it.*";
P_HTM[6140]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6141]="*Abhāvitattā cittassa.**Because their mind was not developed.*";
P_HTM[6142]="*Santi pana, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā cittabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti, no kāyabhāvanaṃ.**There are some ascetics and brahmins who live committed to the practice of developing the mind, without developing physical endurance.*";
P_HTM[6143]="*Phusanti hi te, bho gotama, cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ.**They experience painful mental feelings.*";
P_HTM[6144]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bho gotama, cetasikāya dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭhassa sato ūrukkhambhopi nāma bhavissati, hadayampi nāma phalissati, uṇhampi lohitaṃ mukhato uggamissati, ummādampi pāpuṇissati cittakkhepaṃ.**This happened to someone once. Their thighs became paralyzed, their heart burst, hot blood gushed from their mouth, and they went mad and lost their mind.*";
P_HTM[6145]="*Tassa kho eso, bho gotama, cittanvayo kāyo hoti, cittassa vasena vattati.**Their body was subject to the mind, and the mind had power over it.*";
P_HTM[6146]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6147]="*Abhāvitattā kāyassa.**Because their physical endurance was not developed.*";
P_HTM[6148]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bho gotama, evaṃ hoti:**It occurs to me that*";
P_HTM[6149]="*‘addhā bhoto gotamassa sāvakā cittabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti, no kāyabhāvanan’”ti.**Master Gotama’s disciples must live committed to the practice of developing the mind, without developing physical endurance.”*";
P_HTM[6150]="*“Kinti pana te, aggivessana, kāyabhāvanā sutā”ti?**“But Aggivessana, what have you heard about the development of physical endurance?”*";
P_HTM[6151]="*“Seyyathidaṃ—**“Take, for example,*";
P_HTM[6152]="*nando vaccho, kiso saṅkicco, makkhali gosālo—**Nanda Vaccha, Kisa Saṅkicca, and Makkhali Gosāla.*";
P_HTM[6153]="*etehi, bho gotama, acelakā muttācārā hatthāpalekhanā naehibhaddantikā natiṭṭhabhaddantikā na abhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyanti,**They go naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal.*";
P_HTM[6154]="*te na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhanti na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhanti na eḷakamantaraṃ na daṇḍamantaraṃ na musalamantaraṃ na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ na gabbhiniyā na pāyamānāya na purisantaragatāya na saṅkittīsu na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivanti.**They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer.*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Te ekāgārikā vā honti ekālopikā, dvāgārikā vā honti dvālopikā … pe … sattāgārikā vā honti sattālopikā.**They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls.*";
P_HTM[6156]="*Ekissāpi dattiyā yāpenti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpenti … pe … sattahipi dattīhi yāpenti.**They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day.*";
P_HTM[6157]="*Ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhārenti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhārenti … pe … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhārenti. Iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyuttā viharantī”ti.**They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating food at set intervals.”*";
P_HTM[6158]="*“Kiṃ pana te, aggivessana, tāvatakeneva yāpentī”ti?**“But Aggivessana, do they get by on so little?”*";
P_HTM[6159]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6160]="*Appekadā, bho gotama, uḷārāni uḷārāni khādanīyāni khādanti, uḷārāni uḷārāni bhojanāni bhuñjanti, uḷārāni uḷārāni sāyanīyāni sāyanti, uḷārāni uḷārāni pānāni pivanti.**Sometimes they eat a variety of luxury foods and drink a variety of luxury beverages.*";
P_HTM[6161]="*Te imaṃ kāyaṃ balaṃ gāhenti nāma, brūhenti nāma, medenti nāmā”ti.**They gather their body’s strength, build it up, and get fat.”*";
P_HTM[6162]="*“Yaṃ kho te, aggivessana, purimaṃ pahāya pacchā upacinanti, evaṃ imassa kāyassa ācayāpacayo hoti.**“What they earlier gave up, they later got back. That is how there is the increase and decrease of this body.*";
P_HTM[6163]="*Kinti pana te, aggivessana, cittabhāvanā sutā”ti?**But Aggivessana, what have you heard about development of the mind?”*";
P_HTM[6164]="*Cittabhāvanāya kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavatā puṭṭho samāno na sampāyāsi.**When Saccaka was questioned by the Buddha about development of the mind, he was unable to answer.*";
P_HTM[6165]="*Atha kho bhagavā saccakaṃ nigaṇṭhaputtaṃ etadavoca:**So the Buddha said to Saccaka,*";
P_HTM[6166]="*“yāpi kho te esā, aggivessana, purimā kāyabhāvanā bhāsitā sāpi ariyassa vinaye no dhammikā kāyabhāvanā.**“The development of physical endurance that you have described is not the legitimate development of physical endurance in the noble one’s training.*";
P_HTM[6167]="*Kāyabhāvanampi kho tvaṃ, aggivessana, na aññāsi, kuto pana tvaṃ cittabhāvanaṃ jānissasi?**And since you don’t even understand the development of physical endurance, how can you possibly understand the development of the mind?*";
P_HTM[6168]="*Api ca, aggivessana, yathā abhāvitakāyo ca hoti abhāvitacitto ca, bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto ca.**Still, as to how someone is undeveloped in physical endurance and mind, and how someone is developed in physical endurance and mind,*";
P_HTM[6169]="*Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[6170]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Saccaka.*";
P_HTM[6171]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[6172]="*“Kathañca, aggivessana, abhāvitakāyo ca hoti abhāvitacitto ca?**“And how is someone undeveloped in physical endurance and mind?*";
P_HTM[6173]="*Idha, aggivessana, assutavato puthujjanassa uppajjati sukhā vedanā.**Take an uneducated ordinary person who has a pleasant feeling.*";
P_HTM[6174]="*So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno sukhasārāgī ca hoti sukhasārāgitañca āpajjati.**When they experience pleasant feeling they become full of lust for it.*";
P_HTM[6175]="*Tassa sā sukhā vedanā nirujjhati.**Then that pleasant feeling ceases.*";
P_HTM[6176]="*Sukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.**And when it ceases, a painful feeling arises.*";
P_HTM[6177]="*So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati.**When they experience painful feeling, they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[6178]="*Tassa kho esā, aggivessana, uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā cittassa.**Because their physical endurance is undeveloped, pleasant feelings occupy the mind. And because their mind is undeveloped, painful feelings occupy the mind.*";
P_HTM[6179]="*Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, evaṃ ubhatopakkhaṃ uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati abhāvitattā cittassa, evaṃ kho, aggivessana, abhāvitakāyo ca hoti abhāvitacitto ca.**Someone whose mind is occupied by both pleasant and painful feelings like this is undeveloped in physical endurance and in mind.*";
P_HTM[6180]="*Kathañca, aggivessana, bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto ca?**And how is someone developed in physical endurance and mind?*";
P_HTM[6181]="*Idha, aggivessana, sutavato ariyasāvakassa uppajjati sukhā vedanā.**Take an educated noble disciple who has a pleasant feeling.*";
P_HTM[6182]="*So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na sukhasārāgī ca hoti, na sukhasārāgitañca āpajjati.**When they experience pleasant feeling they don’t become full of lust for it.*";
P_HTM[6183]="*Tassa sā sukhā vedanā nirujjhati.**Then that pleasant feeling ceases.*";
P_HTM[6184]="*Sukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.**And when it ceases, painful feeling arises.*";
P_HTM[6185]="*So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati na kilamati na paridevati na urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**When they experience painful feelings they don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion.*";
P_HTM[6186]="*Tassa kho esā, aggivessana, uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā cittassa.**Because their physical endurance is developed, pleasant feelings don’t occupy the mind. And because their mind is developed, painful feelings don’t occupy the mind.*";
P_HTM[6187]="*Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, evaṃ ubhatopakkhaṃ uppannāpi sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā kāyassa, uppannāpi dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati bhāvitattā cittassa. Evaṃ kho, aggivessana, bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto cā”ti.**Someone whose mind is not occupied by both pleasant and painful feelings like this is developed in physical endurance and in mind.”*";
P_HTM[6188]="*“Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ bhoto gotamassa.**“I am quite confident that Master Gotama*";
P_HTM[6189]="*Bhavañhi gotamo bhāvitakāyo ca hoti bhāvitacitto cā”ti.**is developed in physical endurance and in mind.”*";
P_HTM[6190]="*“Addhā kho te ayaṃ, aggivessana, āsajja upanīya vācā bhāsitā,**“Your words are clearly invasive and intrusive, Aggivessana.*";
P_HTM[6191]="*api ca te ahaṃ byākarissāmi.**Nevertheless, I will answer you.*";
P_HTM[6192]="*Yato kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, taṃ vata me uppannā vā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassati, uppannā vā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti.**Ever since I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness, it has not been possible for any pleasant or painful feeling to occupy my mind.”*";
P_HTM[6193]="*“Na hi nūna bhoto gotamassa uppajjati tathārūpā sukhā vedanā yathārūpā uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭheyya; na hi nūna bhoto gotamassa uppajjati tathārūpā dukkhā vedanā yathārūpā uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭheyyā”ti.**“Surely you must have had feelings so pleasant or so painful that they could occupy your mind?”*";
P_HTM[6194]="*“Kiñhi no siyā, aggivessana?**“How could I not, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6195]="*Idha me, aggivessana, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[6196]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[6197]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[6198]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[6199]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, aparena samayena daharova samāno, susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā, akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ.**Some time later, while still black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life—though my mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces—I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[6200]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**Once I had gone forth I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6201]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso kālāma, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend Kālāma, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[6202]="*Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, āḷāro kālāmo maṃ etadavoca:**Āḷāra Kālāma replied,*";
P_HTM[6203]="*‘viharatāyasmā,**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[6204]="*tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own tradition with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6205]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[6206]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi theravādañca, ‘jānāmi passāmī’ti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[6207]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6208]="*‘na kho āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti,**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Āḷāra Kālāma declares: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[6209]="*addhā āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharatī’ti.**Surely he meditates knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[6210]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6211]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, to what extent do you say you’ve realized this teaching with your own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6212]="*Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, āḷāro kālāmo ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, he declared the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[6213]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6214]="*‘na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Āḷāra Kālāma who has faith,*";
P_HTM[6215]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi vīriyaṃ, mayhampatthi vīriyaṃ;**energy,*";
P_HTM[6216]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi sati, mayhampatthi sati;**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[6217]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi samādhi, mayhampatthi samādhi;**immersion,*";
P_HTM[6218]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi paññā, mayhampatthi paññā;**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[6219]="*yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ āḷāro kālāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Āḷāra Kālāma says he has realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6220]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6221]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6222]="*‘ettāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, have you realized this teaching with your own insight up to this point, and declare having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[6223]="*‘Ettāvatā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemī’ti.**‘I have, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[6224]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6225]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[6226]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[6227]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi;**So the teaching that I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6228]="*yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi.**So the teaching that I know, you know, and the teaching you know, I know.*";
P_HTM[6230]="*Iti yādiso ahaṃ tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso ahaṃ.**I am like you and you are like me.*";
P_HTM[6231]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, ubhova santā imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharāmā’ti.**Come now, reverend! We should both lead this community together.’*";
P_HTM[6232]="*Iti kho, aggivessana, āḷāro kālāmo ācariyo me samāno attano antevāsiṃ maṃ samānaṃ attanā samasamaṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my teacher Āḷāra Kālāma placed me, his student, on the same position as him, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[6233]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6234]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva ākiñcaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of nothingness.’*";
P_HTM[6235]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[6236]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6237]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[6238]="*Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, udako rāmaputto maṃ etadavoca:**Uddaka replied,*";
P_HTM[6239]="*‘viharatāyasmā,**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[6240]="*tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own tradition with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6241]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[6242]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi theravādañca, ‘jānāmi passāmī’ti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[6243]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6244]="*‘na kho rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi.**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Rāma declared: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[6245]="*Addhā rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ vihāsī’ti.**Surely he meditated knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[6246]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6247]="*‘kittāvatā no āvuso rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, to what extent did Rāma say he’d realized this teaching with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6248]="*Evaṃ vutte, aggivessana, udako rāmaputto nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, Uddaka, son of Rāma, declared the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6250]="*‘na kho rāmasseva ahosi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Rāma who had faith,*";
P_HTM[6251]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi vīriyaṃ, mayhampatthi vīriyaṃ;**energy,*";
P_HTM[6252]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi sati, mayhampatthi sati;**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[6253]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi samādhi, mayhampatthi samādhi;**immersion,*";
P_HTM[6254]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi paññā, mayhampatthi paññā;**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[6255]="*yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Rāma said he had realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6256]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6257]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, aggivessana, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6258]="*‘ettāvatā no āvuso rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, had Rāma realized this teaching with his own insight up to this point, and declared having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[6259]="*‘Ettāvatā kho āvuso rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti.**‘He had, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[6260]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6261]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[6262]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi, taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi, taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi.**The teaching that Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it, you have realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it. The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6264]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi.**So the teaching that Rāma directly knew, you know, and the teaching you know, Rāma directly knew.*";
P_HTM[6265]="*Iti yādiso rāmo ahosi tādiso tuvaṃ; yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso rāmo ahosi.**Rāma was like you and you are like Rāma.*";
P_HTM[6266]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, tuvaṃ imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharā’ti.**Come now, reverend! You should lead this community.’*";
P_HTM[6267]="*Iti kho, aggivessana, udako rāmaputto sabrahmacārī me samāno ācariyaṭṭhāne ca maṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my spiritual companion Uddaka, son of Rāma, placed me in the position of a teacher, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[6268]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6269]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’*";
P_HTM[6270]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[6271]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, kiṅkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno magadhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena uruvelā senānigamo tadavasariṃ.**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. Traveling stage by stage in the Magadhan lands, I arrived at Senanigama near Uruvelā.*";
P_HTM[6272]="*Tatthaddasaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ, pāsādikañca vanasaṇḍaṃ, nadiñca sandantiṃ setakaṃ supatitthaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ, samantā ca gocaragāmaṃ.**There I saw a delightful park, a lovely grove with a flowing river that was clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby was a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[6273]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6274]="*‘ramaṇīyo vata bho bhūmibhāgo, pāsādiko ca vanasaṇḍo, nadī ca sandati setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā, samantā ca gocaragāmo.**‘This park is truly delightful, a lovely grove with a flowing river that’s clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby there’s a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[6275]="*Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāyā’ti.**This is good enough for a gentleman who wishes to put forth effort in meditation.’*";
P_HTM[6276]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tattheva nisīdiṃ**So I sat down right there, thinking:*";
P_HTM[6277]="*‘alamidaṃ padhānāyā’ti.**‘This is good enough for meditation.’*";
P_HTM[6278]="*Apissumaṃ, aggivessana, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**And then these three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6279]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying in water.*";
P_HTM[6280]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[6281]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[6282]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6283]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, udake nikkhittaṃ, uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log lying in the water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[6284]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6285]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[6286]="*“Aduñhi, bho gotama, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, tañca pana udake nikkhittaṃ.**Because it’s a green, sappy log, and it’s lying in the water.*";
P_HTM[6287]="*Yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[6288]="*“Evameva kho, aggivessana, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi avūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho, so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti, na suppaṭippassaddho, opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. They haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[6289]="*No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6290]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, aggivessana, paṭhamā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the first example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6291]="*Aparāpi kho maṃ, aggivessana, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**Then a second example occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6292]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water.*";
P_HTM[6293]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[6294]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[6295]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6296]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ, uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[6297]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6298]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[6299]="*“Aduñhi, bho gotama, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, kiñcāpi ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Because it’s still a green, sappy log, despite the fact that it’s lying on dry land far from water.*";
P_HTM[6300]="*Yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[6301]="*“Evameva kho, aggivessana, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti, na suppaṭippassaddho, opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. But they haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[6302]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, aggivessana, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā**This was the second example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6303]="*Aparāpi kho maṃ, aggivessana, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**Then a third example occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6304]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ, ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a dried up, withered log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water.*";
P_HTM[6305]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[6306]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[6307]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana,**What do you think, Aggivessana?*";
P_HTM[6308]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ, ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ, uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that dried up, withered log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[6309]="*“Evaṃ, bho gotama”.**“Yes, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[6310]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6311]="*“Aduñhi, bho gotama, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ, tañca pana ārakā udakā thale nikkhittan”ti.**Because it’s a dried up, withered log, and it’s lying on dry land far from water.”*";
P_HTM[6312]="*“Evameva kho, aggivessana, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho, so ca ajjhattaṃ suppahīno hoti suppaṭippassaddho, opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. And they have internally given up and stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion, they are capable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[6313]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, aggivessana, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the third example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6314]="*Imā kho maṃ, aggivessana, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**These are the three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6315]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6316]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ dantebhi dantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇheyyaṃ abhinippīḷeyyaṃ abhisantāpeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind.’*";
P_HTM[6317]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, dantebhi dantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhāmi abhinippīḷemi abhisantāpemi.**So that’s what I did,*";
P_HTM[6318]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, dantebhi dantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti.**until sweat ran from my armpits.*";
P_HTM[6319]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, balavā puriso dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ sīse vā gahetvā khandhe vā gahetvā abhiniggaṇheyya abhinippīḷeyya abhisantāpeyya;**It was like when a strong man grabs a weaker man by the head or throat or shoulder and squeezes, squashes, and tortures them.*";
P_HTM[6320]="*evameva kho me, aggivessana, dantebhi dantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti.**In the same way, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, I squeezed, squashed, and tortured mind with mind until sweat ran from my armpits.*";
P_HTM[6321]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6322]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6323]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6324]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I practice the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6325]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti.**But then winds came out my ears making a loud noise,*";
P_HTM[6327]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kammāragaggariyā dhamamānāya adhimatto saddo hoti;**like the puffing of a blacksmith’s bellows.*";
P_HTM[6328]="*evameva kho me, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6329]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā. Sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6330]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6331]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6332]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6333]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6334]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti.**But then strong winds ground my head,*";
P_HTM[6335]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, balavā puriso tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya;**like a strong man was drilling into my head with a sharp point.*";
P_HTM[6336]="*evameva kho me, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti.* **";
P_HTM[6337]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā. Sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6338]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6339]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6340]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6341]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6342]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā honti.**But then I got a severe headache,*";
P_HTM[6343]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīse sīsaveṭhaṃ dadeyya;**like a strong man was tightening a tough leather strap around my head.*";
P_HTM[6344]="*evameva kho me, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā honti.* **";
P_HTM[6345]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā. Sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6346]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6347]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6348]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6349]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6350]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.**But then strong winds carved up my belly,*";
P_HTM[6351]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya;**like a deft butcher or their apprentice was slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver.*";
P_HTM[6352]="*evameva kho me, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.* **";
P_HTM[6353]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā. Sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6354]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6355]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6356]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6357]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6358]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti.**But then there was an intense burning in my body,*";
P_HTM[6359]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ;**like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[6360]="*evameva kho me, aggivessana, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6361]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, aggivessana, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā. Sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6362]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā dukkhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such painful feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6363]="*Apissu maṃ, aggivessana, devatā disvā evamāhaṃsu:**Then some deities saw me and said,*";
P_HTM[6364]="*‘kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is dead.’*";
P_HTM[6365]="*Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:**Others said,*";
P_HTM[6366]="*‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, api ca kālaṃ karotī’ti.**‘He’s not dead, but he’s dying.’*";
P_HTM[6367]="*Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:**Others said,*";
P_HTM[6368]="*‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, napi kālaṃ karoti, arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo, vihāro tveva so arahato evarūpo hotī’ti.**‘He’s not dead or dying. The ascetic Gotama is a perfected one, for that is how the perfected ones live.’*";
P_HTM[6369]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6370]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I practice completely cutting off food?’*";
P_HTM[6371]="*Atha kho maṃ, aggivessana, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**But deities came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[6372]="*‘mā kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajji.**‘Good sir, don’t practice totally cutting off food.*";
P_HTM[6373]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjissasi, tassa te mayaṃ dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāressāma, tāya tvaṃ yāpessasī’ti.**If you do, we’ll infuse divine nectar into your pores and you will live on that.’*";
P_HTM[6374]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[6375]="*‘ahañceva kho pana sabbaso ajajjitaṃ paṭijāneyyaṃ, imā ca me devatā dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāreyyuṃ, tāya cāhaṃ yāpeyyaṃ, taṃ mamassa musā’ti.**‘If I claim to be completely fasting while these deities are infusing divine nectar in my pores, that would be a lie on my part.’*";
P_HTM[6376]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tā devatā paccācikkhāmi, ‘halan’ti vadāmi.**So I dismissed those deities, saying, ‘There’s no need.’*";
P_HTM[6377]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6378]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ, pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā hareṇukayūsan’ti.**‘Why don’t I just take a little bit of food each time, a cup of broth made from mung beans, lentils, chickpeas, or green gram.’*";
P_HTM[6379]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ, pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ.**So that’s what I did,*";
P_HTM[6380]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato, pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.**until my body became extremely emaciated.*";
P_HTM[6381]="*Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty-year-old or a corpse,*";
P_HTM[6382]="*Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,*";
P_HTM[6383]="*Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako uṇṇatāvanato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,*";
P_HTM[6384]="*Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn.*";
P_HTM[6385]="*Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti; evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well.*";
P_HTM[6386]="*Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-gourd in the wind and sun.*";
P_HTM[6387]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmīti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmīti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, yāvassu me, aggivessana, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly.*";
P_HTM[6388]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmīti tattheva avakujjo papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face down right there.*";
P_HTM[6389]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, imameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anumajjāmi. Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, pāṇinā gattāni anumajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā papatanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out.*";
P_HTM[6390]="*Apissu maṃ, aggivessana, manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: ‘kāḷo samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Then some people saw me and said: ‘The ascetic Gotama is black.’*";
P_HTM[6391]="*Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, sāmo samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Some said: ‘He’s not black, he’s brown.’*";
P_HTM[6392]="*Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, napi sāmo, maṅguracchavi samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Some said: ‘He’s neither black nor brown. The ascetic Gotama has tawny skin.’*";
P_HTM[6393]="*Yāvassu me, aggivessana, tāva parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto upahato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**That’s how far the pure, bright complexion of my skin had been ruined by taking so little food.*";
P_HTM[6394]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[6395]="*‘ye kho keci atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayiṃsu, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo.**‘Whatever ascetics and brahmins have experienced painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion—whether in the past, future, or present—this is as far as it goes, no-one has done more than this.*";
P_HTM[6396]="*Yepi hi keci anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayissanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[6397]="*Yepi hi keci etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[6398]="*Na kho panāhaṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya adhigacchāmi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ.**But I have not achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones by this severe, grueling work.*";
P_HTM[6399]="*Siyā nu kho añño maggo bodhāyā’ti?**Could there be another path to awakening?’*";
P_HTM[6400]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6401]="*‘abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ pitu sakkassa kammante sītāya jambucchāyāya nisinno vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitā.**‘I recall sitting in the cool shade of the rose-apple tree while my father the Sakyan was off working. Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6402]="*Siyā nu kho eso maggo bodhāyā’ti?**Could that be the path to awakening?’*";
P_HTM[6403]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, satānusāri viññāṇaṃ ahosi:**Stemming from that memory came the realization:*";
P_HTM[6404]="*‘eseva maggo bodhāyā’ti.**‘That is the path to awakening!’*";
P_HTM[6405]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6406]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi, yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti?**‘Why am I afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities?’*";
P_HTM[6407]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[6408]="*‘na kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi, yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti.**‘I’m not afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities.’*";
P_HTM[6409]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, aggivessana, etadahosi:**Then I thought,*";
P_HTM[6410]="*‘na kho taṃ sukaraṃ sukhaṃ adhigantuṃ evaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyena, yannūnāhaṃ oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ odanakummāsan’ti.**‘I can’t achieve that pleasure with a body so excessively emaciated. Why don’t I eat some solid food, some rice and porridge?’*";
P_HTM[6411]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ.**So I ate some solid food.*";
P_HTM[6412]="*Tena kho pana maṃ, aggivessana, samayena pañca bhikkhū paccupaṭṭhitā honti:**Now at that time the five mendicants were attending on me, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6413]="*‘yaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ adhigamissati, taṃ no ārocessatī’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama will tell us of any truth that he realizes.’*";
P_HTM[6414]="*Yato kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ, atha me te pañca bhikkhū nibbijja pakkamiṃsu:**But when I ate some solid food, they left disappointed in me, saying,*";
P_HTM[6415]="*‘bāhulliko samaṇo gotamo, padhānavibbhanto, āvatto bāhullāyā’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama has become indulgent; he has strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.’*";
P_HTM[6416]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāretvā, balaṃ gahetvā, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**After eating solid food and gathering my strength, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6417]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6418]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered and remained in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6419]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6420]="*Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihāsiṃ, sato ca sampajāno. Sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedesiṃ yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**And with the fading away of rapture, I entered and remained in the third absorption, where I meditated with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[6421]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6422]="*Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**With the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, I entered and remained in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[6423]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6424]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[6425]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi.**I recollected my many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[6426]="*Ayaṃ kho me, aggivessana, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā;**This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[6427]="*avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[6428]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6429]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[6430]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi … pe …**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[6431]="*ayaṃ kho me, aggivessana, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā;**This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[6432]="*avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[6433]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6434]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6435]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ.**I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[6436]="*‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ.**I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[6437]="*Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha.**Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[6438]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi.**When it was freed, I knew it was freed.*";
P_HTM[6439]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsiṃ.**I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[6440]="*Ayaṃ kho me, aggivessana, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā vijjā adhigatā;**This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[6441]="*avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[6442]="*Evarūpāpi kho me, aggivessana, uppannā sukhā vedanā cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**But even such pleasant feeling did not occupy my mind.*";
P_HTM[6443]="*Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, aggivessana, anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ desetā.**Aggivessana, I recall teaching the Dhamma to an assembly of many hundreds,*";
P_HTM[6444]="*Apissu maṃ ekameko evaṃ maññati:**and each person thinks*";
P_HTM[6445]="*‘mamevārabbha samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’ti.**that I am teaching the Dhamma especially for them.*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Na kho panetaṃ, aggivessana, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ;**But it should not be seen like this.*";
P_HTM[6447]="*yāvadeva viññāpanatthāya tathāgato paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**The Realized One teaches others only so that they can understand.*";
P_HTM[6448]="*So kho ahaṃ, aggivessana, tassāyeva kathāya pariyosāne, tasmiṃyeva purimasmiṃ samādhinimitte ajjhattameva cittaṃ saṇṭhapemi sannisādemi ekodiṃ karomi samādahāmi, yena sudaṃ niccakappaṃ viharāmī”ti.**When that talk is finished, I still, settle, unify, and immerse my mind in samādhi internally, using the same meditation subject as a foundation of immersion that I used before, which is my usual meditation.”*";
P_HTM[6449]="*“Okappaniyametaṃ bhoto gotamassa yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“I’d believe that of Master Gotama, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6450]="*Abhijānāti kho pana bhavaṃ gotamo divā supitā”ti?**But do you ever recall sleeping during the day?”*";
P_HTM[6451]="*“Abhijānāmahaṃ, aggivessana, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapetvā dakkhiṇena passena sato sampajāno niddaṃ okkamitā”ti.**“I do recall that in the last month of the summer, I have spread out my outer robe folded in four and lain down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware.”*";
P_HTM[6452]="*“Etaṃ kho, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammohavihārasmiṃ vadantī”ti?**“Some ascetics and brahmins call that a deluded abiding.”*";
P_HTM[6453]="*“Na kho, aggivessana, ettāvatā sammūḷho vā hoti asammūḷho vā.**“That’s not how to define whether someone is deluded or not.*";
P_HTM[6454]="*Api ca, aggivessana, yathā sammūḷho ca hoti asammūḷho ca,**But as to how to define whether someone is deluded or not,*";
P_HTM[6455]="*taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[6456]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Saccaka.*";
P_HTM[6457]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[6458]="*“Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā appahīnā, tamahaṃ ‘sammūḷho’ti vadāmi.**“Whoever has not given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death—is deluded, I say.*";
P_HTM[6459]="*Āsavānañhi, aggivessana, appahānā sammūḷho hoti.**For it’s not giving up the defilements that makes you deluded.*";
P_HTM[6460]="*Yassa kassaci, aggivessana, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā pahīnā, tamahaṃ ‘asammūḷho’ti vadāmi.**Whoever has given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death—is not deluded, I say.*";
P_HTM[6461]="*Āsavānañhi, aggivessana, pahānā asammūḷho hoti.**For it’s giving up the defilements that makes you not deluded.*";
P_HTM[6462]="*Tathāgatassa kho, aggivessana, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**The Realized One has given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death. He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[6463]="*Seyyathāpi, aggivessana, tālo matthakacchinno abhabbo puna virūḷhiyā;**Just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth,*";
P_HTM[6464]="*evameva kho, aggivessana, tathāgatassa ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā”ti.**in the same way, the Realized One has given up the defilements so they are unable to arise in the future.”*";
P_HTM[6465]="*Evaṃ vutte, saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Saccaka said to him,*";
P_HTM[6466]="*“acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6467]="*Yāvañcidaṃ bhoto gotamassa evaṃ āsajja āsajja vuccamānassa, upanītehi vacanappathehi samudācariyamānassa, chavivaṇṇo ceva pariyodāyati, mukhavaṇṇo ca vippasīdati, yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**When Master Gotama is repeatedly attacked with inappropriate and intrusive criticism, the complexion of his skin brightens and the color of his face becomes clear, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6468]="*Abhijānāmahaṃ, bho gotama, pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ vādena vādaṃ samārabhitā.**I recall taking on Pūraṇa Kassapa in debate.*";
P_HTM[6469]="*Sopi mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddho aññenaññaṃ paṭicari, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmesi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsi.**He dodged the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[6470]="*Bhoto pana gotamassa evaṃ āsajja āsajja vuccamānassa, upanītehi vacanappathehi samudācariyamānassa, chavivaṇṇo ceva pariyodāyati, mukhavaṇṇo ca vippasīdati, yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**But when Master Gotama is repeatedly attacked with inappropriate and intrusive criticism, the complexion of his skin brightens and the color of his face becomes clear, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Abhijānāmahaṃ, bho gotama, makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ … pe …**I recall taking on Makkhali Gosāla,*";
P_HTM[6472]="*ajitaṃ kesakambalaṃ …**Ajita Kesakambala,*";
P_HTM[6473]="*pakudhaṃ kaccāyanaṃ …**Pakudha Kaccāyana,*";
P_HTM[6474]="*sañjayaṃ belaṭṭhaputtaṃ …**Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta,*";
P_HTM[6475]="*nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ vādena vādaṃ samārabhitā.**and Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta in debate.*";
P_HTM[6476]="*Sopi mayā vādena vādaṃ samāraddho aññenaññaṃ paṭicari, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmesi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsi.**They all dodged the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[6477]="*Bhoto pana gotamassa evaṃ āsajja āsajja vuccamānassa, upanītehi vacanappathehi samudācariyamānassa, chavivaṇṇo ceva pariyodāyati, mukhavaṇṇo ca vippasīdati, yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**But when Master Gotama is repeatedly attacked with inappropriate and intrusive criticism, the complexion of his skin brightens and the color of his face becomes clear, just like a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6478]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma.**Well, now, Master Gotama, I must go.*";
P_HTM[6479]="*Bahukiccā mayaṃ, bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[6480]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, aggivessana, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, Aggivessana, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[6481]="*Atha kho saccako nigaṇṭhaputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti.**Then Saccaka, the son of Jain parents, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[6482]="*Mahāsaccakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6483]="*37. Cūḷataṇhāsaṅkhayasutta**The Shorter Discourse on the Ending of Craving*";
P_HTM[6484]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6485]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother.*";
P_HTM[6486]="*Atha kho sakko devānamindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho sakko devānamindo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**And then Sakka, lord of gods, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6487]="*“kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimutto hoti accantaniṭṭho accantayogakkhemī accantabrahmacārī accantapariyosāno seṭṭho devamanussānan”ti?**“Sir, how do you briefly define a mendicant who is freed through the ending of craving, who has reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal, and is best among gods and humans?”*";
P_HTM[6488]="*“Idha, devānaminda, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti:**“Lord of Gods, it’s when a mendicant has heard:*";
P_HTM[6489]="*‘sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā’ti.**‘Nothing is worth insisting on.’*";
P_HTM[6490]="*Evañcetaṃ, devānaminda, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti:**When a mendicant has heard that*";
P_HTM[6491]="*‘sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā’ti.**nothing is worth insisting on,*";
P_HTM[6492]="*So sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhijānāti; sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhiññāya sabbaṃ dhammaṃ parijānāti; sabbaṃ dhammaṃ pariññāya yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti—**they directly know all things. Directly knowing all things, they completely understand all things. Having completely understood all things, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—*";
P_HTM[6493]="*sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so tāsu vedanāsu aniccānupassī viharati, virāgānupassī viharati, nirodhānupassī viharati, paṭinissaggānupassī viharati.**they meditate observing impermanence, dispassion, cessation, and letting go in those feelings.*";
P_HTM[6494]="*So tāsu vedanāsu aniccānupassī viharanto, virāgānupassī viharanto, nirodhānupassī viharanto, paṭinissaggānupassī viharanto na kiñci loke upādiyati.**Meditating in this way, they don’t grasp at anything in the world.*";
P_HTM[6495]="*Anupādiyaṃ na paritassati, aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati:**Not grasping, they’re not anxious. Not being anxious, they personally become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[6496]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[6497]="*Ettāvatā kho, devānaminda, bhikkhu saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimutto hoti accantaniṭṭho accantayogakkhemī accantabrahmacārī accantapariyosāno seṭṭho devamanussānan”ti.**That’s how I briefly define a mendicant who is freed through the ending of craving, who has reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal, and is best among gods and humans.”*";
P_HTM[6498]="*Atha kho sakko devānamindo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi.**Then Sakka, lord of gods, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there.*";
P_HTM[6499]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti.**Now, at that time Venerable Mahāmoggallāna was sitting not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6500]="*Atha kho āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa etadahosi:**He thought,*";
P_HTM[6501]="*“kiṃ nu kho so yakkho bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhisamecca anumodi udāhu no;**“Did that spirit comprehend what the Buddha said when he agreed with him, or not?*";
P_HTM[6502]="*yannūnāhaṃ taṃ yakkhaṃ jāneyyaṃ—**Why don’t I find out?”*";
P_HTM[6503]="*yadi vā so yakkho bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhisamecca anumodi yadi vā no”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6504]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde antarahito devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi.**And then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Eastern Monastery and reappeared among the gods of the Thirty-Three.*";
P_HTM[6505]="*Tena kho pana samayena sakko devānamindo ekapuṇḍarīke uyyāne dibbehi pañcahi tūriyasatehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti.**Now at that time Sakka was amusing himself in the Single Lotus Park, supplied and provided with a divine orchestra.*";
P_HTM[6506]="*Addasā kho sakko devānamindo āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Seeing Mahāmoggallāna coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6507]="*Disvāna tāni dibbāni pañca tūriyasatāni paṭippaṇāmetvā yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**he dismissed the orchestra, approached Mahāmoggallāna, and said,*";
P_HTM[6508]="*“ehi kho, mārisa moggallāna, svāgataṃ, mārisa moggallāna.**“Come, my good Moggallāna! Welcome, good sir!*";
P_HTM[6509]="*Cirassaṃ kho, mārisa moggallāna, imaṃ pariyāyaṃ akāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya.**It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.*";
P_HTM[6510]="*Nisīda, mārisa moggallāna, idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti.**Sit, my good Moggallāna, this seat is for you.”*";
P_HTM[6511]="*Nisīdi kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno paññatte āsane.**Mahāmoggallāna sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[6512]="*Sakkopi kho devānamindo aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**while Sakka took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[6513]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Mahāmoggallāna said to him,*";
P_HTM[6514]="*“yathā kathaṃ pana kho, kosiya, bhagavā saṃkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ abhāsi?**“Kosiya, how did the Buddha briefly explain freedom through the ending of craving?*";
P_HTM[6515]="*Sādhu mayampi etissā kathāya bhāgino assāma savanāyā”ti.**Please share this talk with me so that I can also get to hear it.”*";
P_HTM[6516]="*“Mayaṃ kho, mārisa moggallāna, bahukiccā bahukaraṇīyā—**“My good Moggallāna, I have many duties, and much to do,*";
P_HTM[6517]="*appeva sakena karaṇīyena, api ca devānaṃyeva tāvatiṃsānaṃ karaṇīyena.**not only for myself, but also for the Gods of the Thirty-Three.*";
P_HTM[6518]="*Api ca, mārisa moggallāna, sussutaṃyeva hoti suggahitaṃ sumanasikataṃ sūpadhāritaṃ, yaṃ no khippameva antaradhāyati.**Besides, I quickly forget even things I’ve properly heard, learned, attended, and memorized.*";
P_HTM[6519]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, mārisa moggallāna, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi.**Once upon a time, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons.*";
P_HTM[6520]="*Tasmiṃ kho pana, mārisa moggallāna, saṅgāme devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājiniṃsu.**In that battle the gods won and the demons lost.*";
P_HTM[6521]="*So kho ahaṃ, mārisa moggallāna, taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā vijitasaṅgāmo tato paṭinivattitvā vejayantaṃ nāma pāsādaṃ māpesiṃ.**When I returned from that battle as a conqueror, I created the Palace of Victory.*";
P_HTM[6522]="*Vejayantassa kho, mārisa moggallāna, pāsādassa ekasataṃ niyyūhaṃ.**The Palace of Victory has a hundred towers.*";
P_HTM[6523]="*Ekekasmiṃ niyyūhe satta satta kūṭāgārasatāni.**Each tower has seven hundred chambers.*";
P_HTM[6524]="*Ekamekasmiṃ kūṭāgāre satta satta accharāyo.**Each chamber has seven nymphs.*";
P_HTM[6525]="*Ekamekissā accharāya satta satta paricārikāyo.**Each nymph has seven maids.*";
P_HTM[6526]="*Iccheyyāsi no tvaṃ, mārisa moggallāna, vejayantassa pāsādassa rāmaṇeyyakaṃ daṭṭhun”ti?**Would you like to see the lovely Palace of Victory?”*";
P_HTM[6527]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno tuṇhībhāvena.**Mahāmoggallāna consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[6528]="*Atha kho sakko ca devānamindo vessavaṇo ca mahārājā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ purakkhatvā yena vejayanto pāsādo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**Then, putting Venerable Mahāmoggallāna in front, Sakka, lord of gods, and Vessavaṇa, the Great King, went to the Palace of Victory.*";
P_HTM[6529]="*Addasaṃsu kho sakkassa devānamindassa paricārikāyo āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ;**When they saw Moggallāna coming off in the distance, Sakka’s maids,*";
P_HTM[6530]="*disvā ottappamānā hirīyamānā sakaṃ sakaṃ ovarakaṃ pavisiṃsu.**being prudent and discreet, each went to her own bedroom.*";
P_HTM[6531]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suṇisā sasuraṃ disvā ottappati hirīyati;**They were just like a daughter-in-law who is prudent and discreet when they see their father-in-law.*";
P_HTM[6532]="*evameva sakkassa devānamindassa paricārikāyo āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ disvā ottappamānā hirīyamānā sakaṃ sakaṃ ovarakaṃ pavisiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[6533]="*Atha kho sakko ca devānamindo vessavaṇo ca mahārājā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ vejayante pāsāde anucaṅkamāpenti anuvicarāpenti:**Then Sakka and Vessavaṇa encouraged Moggallāna to wander and explore the palace, saying,*";
P_HTM[6534]="*“idampi, mārisa moggallāna, passa vejayantassa pāsādassa rāmaṇeyyakaṃ;**“See, in the palace, my good Moggallāna, this lovely thing!*";
P_HTM[6535]="*idampi, mārisa moggallāna, passa vejayantassa pāsādassa rāmaṇeyyakan”ti.**And that lovely thing!”*";
P_HTM[6536]="*“Sobhati idaṃ āyasmato kosiyassa, yathā taṃ pubbe katapuññassa.**“That looks nice for Venerable Kosiya, just like for someone who has made merit in the past.*";
P_HTM[6537]="*Manussāpi kiñcideva rāmaṇeyyakaṃ disvā evamāhaṃsu:**Humans, when they see something lovely, also say:*";
P_HTM[6538]="*‘sobhati vata bho yathā devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānan’ti.**‘It looks nice enough for the Gods of the Thirty-Three!’*";
P_HTM[6539]="*Tayidaṃ āyasmato kosiyassa sobhati, yathā taṃ pubbe katapuññassā”ti.**That looks nice for Venerable Kosiya, just like for someone who has made merit in the past.”*";
P_HTM[6540]="*Atha kho āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa etadahosi:**Then Moggallāna thought,*";
P_HTM[6541]="*“atibāḷhaṃ kho ayaṃ yakkho pamatto viharati.**“This spirit lives much too negligently.*";
P_HTM[6542]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ yakkhaṃ saṃvejeyyan”ti.**Why don’t I stir up a sense of urgency in him?”*";
P_HTM[6543]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi yathā vejayantaṃ pāsādaṃ pādaṅguṭṭhakena saṅkampesi sampakampesi sampavedhesi.**Then Moggallāna used his psychic power to make the Palace of Victory shake and rock and tremble with his big toe.*";
P_HTM[6544]="*Atha kho sakko ca devānamindo, vessavaṇo ca mahārājā, devā ca tāvatiṃsā acchariyabbhutacittajātā ahesuṃ:**Then Sakka, Vessavaṇa, and the Gods of the Thirty-Three, their minds full of wonder and amazement, thought,*";
P_HTM[6545]="*“acchariyaṃ vata, bho, abbhutaṃ vata, bho.**“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6546]="*Samaṇassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā, yatra hi nāma dibbabhavanaṃ pādaṅguṭṭhakena saṅkampessati sampakampessati sampavedhessatī”ti.**The ascetic has such power and might that he makes the god’s home shake and rock and tremble with his big toe!”*";
P_HTM[6547]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ saṃviggaṃ lomahaṭṭhajātaṃ viditvā sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca:**Knowing that Sakka was shocked and awestruck, Moggallāna said to him,*";
P_HTM[6548]="*“yathā kathaṃ pana kho, kosiya, bhagavā saṃkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ abhāsi?**“Kosiya, how did the Buddha briefly explain freedom through the ending of craving?*";
P_HTM[6549]="*Sādhu mayampi etissā kathāya bhāgino assāma savanāyā”ti.**Please share this talk with me so that I can also get to hear it.”*";
P_HTM[6550]="*“Idhāhaṃ, mārisa moggallāna, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho ahaṃ, mārisa moggallāna, bhagavantaṃ etadavocaṃ:**“My dear Moggallāna, I approached the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6551]="*‘kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimutto hoti accantaniṭṭho accantayogakkhemī accantabrahmacārī accantapariyosāno seṭṭho devamanussānan’ti?**‘Sir, how do you briefly define a mendicant who is freed with the ending of craving, who has reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal, and is best among gods and humans?’*";
P_HTM[6552]="*Evaṃ vutte, mārisa moggallāna, bhagavā maṃ etadavoca:**When I had spoken the Buddha said to me:*";
P_HTM[6553]="*‘idha, devānaminda, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti:**‘Lord of Gods, it’s when a mendicant has heard:*";
P_HTM[6554]="*“sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā”ti.**“Nothing is worth insisting on”*";
P_HTM[6555]="*Evañcetaṃ, devānaminda, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti**When a mendicant has heard that*";
P_HTM[6556]="*“sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā”ti.**nothing is worth insisting on,*";
P_HTM[6557]="*So sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhiññāya sabbaṃ dhammaṃ parijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ pariññāya yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā.**they directly know all things. Directly knowing all things, they completely understand all things. Having completely understood all things, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—*";
P_HTM[6558]="*So tāsu vedanāsu aniccānupassī viharati, virāgānupassī viharati, nirodhānupassī viharati, paṭinissaggānupassī viharati.**they meditate observing impermanence, dispassion, cessation, and letting go in those feelings.*";
P_HTM[6559]="*So tāsu vedanāsu aniccānupassī viharanto, virāgānupassī viharanto, nirodhānupassī viharanto, paṭinissaggānupassī viharanto na kiñci loke upādiyati,**Meditating in this way, they don’t grasp at anything in the world.*";
P_HTM[6560]="*anupādiyaṃ na paritassati, aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati:**Not grasping, they’re not anxious. Not being anxious, they personally become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[6561]="*“khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti pajānāti.**They understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[6562]="*Ettāvatā kho, devānaminda, bhikkhu saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimutto hoti accantaniṭṭho accantayogakkhemī accantabrahmacārī accantapariyosāno seṭṭho devamanussānan’ti.**That’s how I briefly define a mendicant who is freed through the ending of craving, who has reached the ultimate end, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual life, the ultimate goal, and is best among gods and humans.’*";
P_HTM[6563]="*Evaṃ kho me, mārisa moggallāna, bhagavā saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ abhāsī”ti.**That’s how the Buddha briefly explained freedom through the ending of craving to me.”*";
P_HTM[6564]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno sakkassa devānamindassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—devesu tāvatiṃsesu antarahito pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde pāturahosi.**Moggallāna approved and agreed with what Sakka said. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from among the Gods of the Thirty-Three and reappeared in the Eastern Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6565]="*Atha kho sakkassa devānamindassa paricārikāyo acirapakkante āyasmante mahāmoggallāne sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Soon after Moggallāna left, Sakka’s maids said to him,*";
P_HTM[6566]="*“eso nu te, mārisa, so bhagavā satthā”ti?**“Good sir, was that the Blessed One, your Teacher?”*";
P_HTM[6567]="*“Na kho me, mārisa, so bhagavā satthā.**“No, it was not.*";
P_HTM[6568]="*Sabrahmacārī me eso āyasmā mahāmoggallāno”ti.**That was my spiritual companion Venerable Mahāmoggallāna.”*";
P_HTM[6569]="*“Lābhā te, mārisa, suladdhaṃ te, mārisa**“You’re fortunate, good sir, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[6570]="*yassa te sabrahmacārī evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo.**to have a spiritual companion of such power and might!*";
P_HTM[6571]="*Aho nūna te so bhagavā satthā”ti.**We can’t believe that’s not the Blessed One, your Teacher!”*";
P_HTM[6572]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Mahāmoggallāna went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6573]="*“abhijānāti no, bhante, bhagavā ahu ñātaññatarassa mahesakkhassa yakkhassa saṃkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ bhāsitā”ti?**“Sir, do you recall briefly explaining freedom through the ending of craving to a certain well-known and illustrious spirit?”*";
P_HTM[6574]="*“Abhijānāmahaṃ, moggallāna, idha sakko devānamindo yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, moggallāna, sakko devānamindo maṃ etadavoca:**“I do, Moggallāna.” And the Buddha retold all that happened when Sakka came to visit him, adding:*";
P_HTM[6575]="*‘kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu saṃkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimutto hoti accantaniṭṭho accantayogakkhemī accantabrahmacārī accantapariyosāno seṭṭho devamanussānan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6576]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, moggallāna, sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavocaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6577]="*‘idha devānaminda, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti* **";
P_HTM[6578]="*“sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6579]="*Evaṃ cetaṃ, devānaminda, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti* **";
P_HTM[6580]="*“sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6581]="*So sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhiññāya sabbaṃ dhammaṃ parijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ pariññāya yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā.* **";
P_HTM[6582]="*So tāsu vedanāsu aniccānupassī viharati, virāgānupassī viharati, nirodhānupassī viharati, paṭinissaggānupassī viharati.* **";
P_HTM[6583]="*So tāsu vedanāsu aniccānupassī viharanto, virāgānupassī viharanto, nirodhānupassī viharanto,* **";
P_HTM[6584]="*paṭinissaggānupassī viharanto na kiñci loke upādiyati,* **";
P_HTM[6585]="*anupādiyaṃ na paritassati, aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati:* **";
P_HTM[6586]="*“khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti pajānāti.* **";
P_HTM[6587]="*Ettāvatā kho, devānaminda, bhikkhu saṃkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimutto hoti accantaniṭṭho accantayogakkhemī accantabrahmacārī accantapariyosāno seṭṭho devamanussānan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6588]="*Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, moggallāna, abhijānāmi sakkassa devānamindassa saṃkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ bhāsitā”ti.**“That’s how I recall briefly explaining freedom through the ending of craving to Sakka, lord of gods.”*";
P_HTM[6589]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6590]="*Attamano āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6591]="*Cūḷataṇhāsaṅkhayasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6592]="*38. Mahātaṇhāsaṅkhayasutta**The Longer Discourse on the Ending of Craving*";
P_HTM[6593]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6594]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6595]="*Tena kho pana samayena sātissa nāma bhikkhuno kevaṭṭaputtassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti:**Now at that time a mendicant called Sāti, the fisherman’s son, had the following harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[6596]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati anaññan”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it is this very same consciousness that roams and transmigrates, not another.”*";
P_HTM[6597]="*Assosuṃ kho sambahulā bhikkhū:**Several mendicants heard about this.*";
P_HTM[6598]="*“sātissa kira nāma bhikkhuno kevaṭṭaputtassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6599]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6600]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**They went up to Sāti and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6601]="*“saccaṃ kira te, āvuso sāti, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:**“Is it really true, Reverend Sāti, that you have such a harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[6602]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’”ti?**‘As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it is this very same consciousness that roams and transmigrates, not another’?”*";
P_HTM[6603]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan”ti.**“Absolutely, reverends. As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it is this very same consciousness that roams and transmigrates, not another.”*";
P_HTM[6604]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetukāmā samanuyuñjanti samanugāhanti samanubhāsanti:**Then, wishing to dissuade Sāti from his view, the mendicants pursued, pressed, and grilled him,*";
P_HTM[6605]="*“mā evaṃ, āvuso sāti, avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**“Don’t say that, Sāti! Don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for misrepresentation of the Buddha is not good. And the Buddha would not say that.*";
P_HTM[6606]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso sāti, paṭiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā, aññatra paccayā natthi viññāṇassa sambhavo”ti.**In many ways the Buddha has said that consciousness is dependently originated, since consciousness does not arise without a cause.”*";
P_HTM[6607]="*Evampi kho sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto tehi bhikkhūhi samanuyuñjiyamāno samanugāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno tadeva pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati:**But even though the mendicants pressed him in this way, Sāti obstinately stuck to his misconception and insisted on stating it.*";
P_HTM[6608]="*“evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati anaññan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6609]="*Yato kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When they weren’t able to dissuade Sāti from his view, the mendicants went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6610]="*“sātissa nāma, bhante, bhikkhuno kevaṭṭaputtassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6611]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6612]="*Assumha kho mayaṃ, bhante, sātissa kira nāma bhikkhuno kevaṭṭaputtassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6613]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6614]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yena sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etadavocumha:* **";
P_HTM[6615]="*‘saccaṃ kira te, āvuso sāti, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6616]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan”’ti?* **";
P_HTM[6617]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto amhe etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[6618]="*‘evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6619]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetukāmā samanuyuñjimha samanugāhimha samanubhāsimha:* **";
P_HTM[6620]="*‘mā evaṃ, āvuso sāti, avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[6621]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso sāti, paṭiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā, aññatra paccayā natthi viññāṇassa sambhavo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6622]="*Evampi kho, bhante, sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto amhehi samanuyuñjiyamāno samanugāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno tadeva pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmasā abhinivissa voharati:* **";
P_HTM[6623]="*‘evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6624]="*Yato kho mayaṃ, bhante, nāsakkhimha sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha mayaṃ etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocemā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6625]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[6626]="*“ehi tvaṃ bhikkhu, mama vacanena sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell the mendicant Sāti that*";
P_HTM[6627]="*‘satthā taṃ, āvuso sāti, āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons him.”*";
P_HTM[6628]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yena sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Sāti and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6629]="*“satthā taṃ, āvuso sāti, āmantetī”ti.**“Reverend Sāti, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[6630]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” Sāti replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6631]="*“saccaṃ kira te, sāti, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ:**“Is it really true, Sāti, that you have such a harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[6632]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan’”ti?**‘As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it is this very same consciousness that roams and transmigrates, not another’?”*";
P_HTM[6633]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā tadevidaṃ viññāṇaṃ sandhāvati saṃsarati, anaññan”ti.**“Absolutely, sir. As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it is this very same consciousness that roams and transmigrates, not another.”*";
P_HTM[6634]="*“Katamaṃ taṃ, sāti, viññāṇan”ti?**“Sāti, what is that consciousness?”*";
P_HTM[6635]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, vado vedeyyo tatra tatra kalyāṇapāpakānaṃ kammānaṃ vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedetī”ti.**“Sir, it is he who speaks and feels and experiences the results of good and bad deeds in all the different realms.”*";
P_HTM[6636]="*“Kassa nu kho nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mayā evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi?**“Silly man, who on earth have you ever known me to teach in that way?*";
P_HTM[6637]="*Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, anekapariyāyena paṭiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ vuttaṃ, aññatra paccayā natthi viññāṇassa sambhavoti?**Haven’t I said in many ways that consciousness is dependently originated, since consciousness does not arise without a cause?*";
P_HTM[6638]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, moghapurisa, attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhasi, attānañca khaṇasi, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavasi.**But still you misrepresent me by your wrong grasp, harm yourself, and make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[6639]="*Tañhi te, moghapurisa, bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**This will be for your lasting harm and suffering.”*";
P_HTM[6640]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[6641]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[6642]="*api nāyaṃ sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto usmīkatopi imasmiṃ dhammavinaye”ti?**Has this mendicant Sāti kindled even a spark of wisdom in this teaching and training?”*";
P_HTM[6643]="*“Kiñhi siyā, bhante?**“How could that be, sir?*";
P_HTM[6644]="*No hetaṃ, bhante”ti.**No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6645]="*Evaṃ vutte, sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi.**When this was said, Sāti sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[6646]="*Atha kho bhagavā sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā sātiṃ bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**Knowing this, the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[6647]="*“paññāyissasi kho tvaṃ, moghapurisa, etena sakena pāpakena diṭṭhigatena.**“Silly man, you will be known by your own harmful misconception.*";
P_HTM[6648]="*Idhāhaṃ bhikkhū paṭipucchissāmī”ti.**I’ll question the mendicants about this.”*";
P_HTM[6649]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[6650]="*“tumhepi me, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha yathāyaṃ sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhati, attānañca khaṇati, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatī”ti?**“Mendicants, do you understand my teachings as Sāti does, when he misrepresents me by his wrong grasp, harms himself, and makes much bad karma?”*";
P_HTM[6651]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[6652]="*Anekapariyāyena hi no, bhante, paṭiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā, aññatra paccayā natthi viññāṇassa sambhavo”ti.**For in many ways the Buddha has told us that consciousness is dependently originated, since consciousness does not arise without a cause.”*";
P_HTM[6653]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[6654]="*Sādhu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha.**It’s good that you understand my teaching like this.*";
P_HTM[6655]="*Anekapariyāyena hi vo, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppannaṃ viññāṇaṃ vuttaṃ mayā, aññatra paccayā natthi viññāṇassa sambhavo”ti.**For in many ways I have told you that consciousness is dependently originated, since consciousness does not arise without a cause.*";
P_HTM[6656]="*Atha ca panāyaṃ sāti bhikkhu kevaṭṭaputto attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhati, attānañca khaṇati, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**But still this Sāti misrepresents me by his wrong grasp, harms himself, and makes much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[6657]="*Tañhi tassa moghapurisassa bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for his lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[6658]="*“Yaṃ yadeva, bhikkhave, paccayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, tena teneva viññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**Consciousness is reckoned according to the specific conditions dependent upon which it arises.*";
P_HTM[6659]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, cakkhuviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**Consciousness that arises dependent on the eye and sights is reckoned as eye consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6660]="*sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, sotaviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**Consciousness that arises dependent on the ear and sounds is reckoned as ear consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6661]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, ghānaviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**Consciousness that arises dependent on the nose and smells is reckoned as nose consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6662]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, jivhāviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**Consciousness that arises dependent on the tongue and tastes is reckoned as tongue consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6663]="*kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, kāyaviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**Consciousness that arises dependent on the body and touches is reckoned as body consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6664]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, manoviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**Consciousness that arises dependent on the mind and thoughts is reckoned as mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6665]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yaṃ yadeva paccayaṃ paṭicca aggi jalati tena teneva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**It’s like fire, which is reckoned according to the specific conditions dependent upon which it burns.*";
P_HTM[6666]="*Kaṭṭhañca paṭicca aggi jalati, kaṭṭhaggitveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on logs is reckoned as a log fire.*";
P_HTM[6667]="*sakalikañca paṭicca aggi jalati, sakalikaggitveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on twigs is reckoned as a twig fire.*";
P_HTM[6668]="*tiṇañca paṭicca aggi jalati, tiṇaggitveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on grass is reckoned as a grass fire.*";
P_HTM[6669]="*gomayañca paṭicca aggi jalati, gomayaggitveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on cow-dung is reckoned as a cow-dung fire.*";
P_HTM[6670]="*thusañca paṭicca aggi jalati, thusaggitveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on husks is reckoned as a husk fire.*";
P_HTM[6671]="*saṅkārañca paṭicca aggi jalati, saṅkāraggitveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**A fire that burns dependent on rubbish is reckoned as a rubbish fire.*";
P_HTM[6672]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yaṃ yadeva paccayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, tena teneva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**In the same way, consciousness is reckoned according to the specific conditions dependent upon which it arises. …*";
P_HTM[6673]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, cakkhuviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;* **";
P_HTM[6674]="*sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, sotaviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati,* **";
P_HTM[6675]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, ghānaviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati,* **";
P_HTM[6676]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, jivhāviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6677]="*Kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, kāyaviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6678]="*Manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati viññāṇaṃ, manoviññāṇantveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[6679]="*Bhūtamidanti, bhikkhave, passathā”ti?**Mendicants, do you see that this has come to be?”*";
P_HTM[6680]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6681]="*“Tadāhārasambhavanti, bhikkhave, passathā”ti?**“Do you see that it originated with that as fuel?”*";
P_HTM[6682]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6683]="*“Tadāhāranirodhā yaṃ bhūtaṃ, taṃ nirodhadhammanti, bhikkhave, passathā”ti?**“Do you see that when that fuel ceases, what has come to be is liable to cease?”*";
P_HTM[6684]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6685]="*“Bhūtamidaṃ nossūti, bhikkhave, kaṅkhato uppajjati vicikicchā”ti?**“Does doubt arise when you’re uncertain whether or not this has come to be?”*";
P_HTM[6686]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6687]="*“Tadāhārasambhavaṃ nossūti, bhikkhave, kaṅkhato uppajjati vicikicchā”ti?**“Does doubt arise when you’re uncertain whether or not this has originated with that as fuel?”*";
P_HTM[6688]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6689]="*“Tadāhāranirodhā yaṃ bhūtaṃ, taṃ nirodhadhammaṃ nossūti, bhikkhave, kaṅkhato uppajjati vicikicchā”ti?**“Does doubt arise when you’re uncertain whether or not when that fuel ceases, what has come to be is liable to cease?”*";
P_HTM[6690]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6691]="*“Bhūtamidanti, bhikkhave, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato yā vicikicchā sā pahīyatī”ti?**“Is doubt given up in someone who truly sees with right understanding that this has come to be?”*";
P_HTM[6692]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6693]="*“Tadāhārasambhavanti, bhikkhave, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato yā vicikicchā sā pahīyatī”ti?**“Is doubt given up in someone who truly sees with right understanding that this has originated with that as fuel?”*";
P_HTM[6694]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6695]="*“Tadāhāranirodhā yaṃ bhūtaṃ, taṃ nirodhadhammanti, bhikkhave, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato yā vicikicchā sā pahīyatī”ti?**“Is doubt given up in someone who truly sees with right understanding that when that fuel ceases, what has come to be is liable to cease?”*";
P_HTM[6696]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6697]="*“Bhūtamidanti, bhikkhave, itipi vo ettha nibbicikicchā”ti?**“Are you free of doubt as to whether this has come to be?”*";
P_HTM[6698]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6699]="*“Tadāhārasambhavanti, bhikkhave, itipi vo ettha nibbicikicchā”ti?**“Are you free of doubt as to whether this has originated with that as fuel?”*";
P_HTM[6700]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6701]="*“Tadāhāranirodhā yaṃ bhūtaṃ taṃ nirodhadhammanti, bhikkhave, itipi vo ettha nibbicikicchā”ti?**“Are you free of doubt as to whether when that fuel ceases, what has come to be is liable to cease?”*";
P_HTM[6702]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6703]="*“Bhūtamidanti, bhikkhave, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhan”ti?**“Have you truly seen clearly with right understanding that this has come to be?”*";
P_HTM[6704]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6705]="*“Tadāhārasambhavanti, bhikkhave, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhan”ti?**“Have you truly seen clearly with right understanding that this has originated with that as fuel?”*";
P_HTM[6706]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6707]="*“Tadāhāranirodhā yaṃ bhūtaṃ taṃ nirodhadhammanti, bhikkhave, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhan”ti?**“Have you truly seen clearly with right understanding that when that fuel ceases, what has come to be is liable to cease?”*";
P_HTM[6708]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6709]="*“Imañce tumhe, bhikkhave, diṭṭhiṃ evaṃ parisuddhaṃ evaṃ pariyodātaṃ allīyetha kelāyetha dhanāyetha mamāyetha, api nu me tumhe, bhikkhave, kullūpamaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājāneyyātha nittharaṇatthāya no gahaṇatthāyā”ti?**“Pure and bright as this view is, mendicants, if you cherish it, fancy it, treasure it, and treat it as your own, would you be understanding how the Dhamma is similar to a raft: for crossing over, not for holding on?”*";
P_HTM[6710]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6711]="*“Imañce tumhe, bhikkhave, diṭṭhiṃ evaṃ parisuddhaṃ evaṃ pariyodātaṃ na allīyetha na kelāyetha na dhanāyetha na mamāyetha, api nu me tumhe, bhikkhave, kullūpamaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājāneyyātha nittharaṇatthāya no gahaṇatthāyā”ti?**“Pure and bright as this view is, mendicants, if you don’t cherish it, fancy it, treasure it, and treat it as your own, would you be understanding how the Dhamma is similar to a raft: for crossing over, not for holding on?”*";
P_HTM[6712]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6713]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā, sambhavesīnaṃ vā anuggahāya.**“Mendicants, there are these four fuels. They maintain sentient beings that have been born and help those that are about to be born.*";
P_HTM[6714]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6715]="*Kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ.**Solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention the third, and consciousness the fourth.*";
P_HTM[6716]="*Ime ca, bhikkhave, cattāro āhārā kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā?**What is the source, origin, birthplace, and root of these four fuels?*";
P_HTM[6717]="*Ime cattāro āhārā taṇhānidānā taṇhāsamudayā taṇhājātikā taṇhāpabhavā.**Craving.*";
P_HTM[6718]="*Taṇhā cāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā?**And what is the source of craving?*";
P_HTM[6719]="*Taṇhā vedanānidānā vedanāsamudayā vedanājātikā vedanāpabhavā.**Feeling.*";
P_HTM[6720]="*Vedanā cāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā?**And what is the source of feeling?*";
P_HTM[6721]="*Vedanā phassanidānā phassasamudayā phassajātikā phassapabhavā.**Contact.*";
P_HTM[6722]="*Phasso cāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃnidāno kiṃsamudayo kiṃjātiko kiṃpabhavo?**And what is the source of contact?*";
P_HTM[6723]="*Phasso saḷāyatananidāno saḷāyatanasamudayo saḷāyatanajātiko saḷāyatanapabhavo.**The six sense fields.*";
P_HTM[6724]="*Saḷāyatanañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃnidānaṃ kiṃsamudayaṃ kiṃjātikaṃ kiṃpabhavaṃ?**And what is the source of the six sense fields?*";
P_HTM[6725]="*Saḷāyatanaṃ nāmarūpanidānaṃ nāmarūpasamudayaṃ nāmarūpajātikaṃ nāmarūpapabhavaṃ.**Name and form.*";
P_HTM[6726]="*Nāmarūpañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃnidānaṃ kiṃsamudayaṃ kiṃjātikaṃ kiṃpabhavaṃ?**And what is the source of name and form?*";
P_HTM[6727]="*Nāmarūpaṃ viññāṇanidānaṃ viññāṇasamudayaṃ viññāṇajātikaṃ viññāṇapabhavaṃ.**Consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6728]="*Viññāṇañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, kiṃnidānaṃ kiṃsamudayaṃ kiṃjātikaṃ kiṃpabhavaṃ?**And what is the source of consciousness?*";
P_HTM[6729]="*Viññāṇaṃ saṅkhāranidānaṃ saṅkhārasamudayaṃ saṅkhārajātikaṃ saṅkhārapabhavaṃ.**Choices.*";
P_HTM[6730]="*Saṅkhārā cime, bhikkhave, kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā?**And what is the source of choices?*";
P_HTM[6731]="*Saṅkhārā avijjānidānā avijjāsamudayā avijjājātikā avijjāpabhavā.**Ignorance.*";
P_HTM[6732]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā,**So, ignorance is a condition for choices.*";
P_HTM[6733]="*saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ,**Choices are a condition for consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6734]="*viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ,**Consciousness is a condition for name and form.*";
P_HTM[6735]="*nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ,**Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields.*";
P_HTM[6736]="*saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso,**The six sense fields are conditions for contact.*";
P_HTM[6737]="*phassapaccayā vedanā,**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[6738]="*vedanāpaccayā taṇhā,**Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[6739]="*taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ,**Craving is a condition for grasping.*";
P_HTM[6740]="*upādānapaccayā bhavo,**Grasping is a condition for continued existence.*";
P_HTM[6741]="*bhavapaccayā jāti,**Continued existence is a condition for rebirth.*";
P_HTM[6742]="*jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti.**Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be.*";
P_HTM[6743]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.*";
P_HTM[6744]="*Jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇanti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;**‘Rebirth is a condition for old age and death.’ That’s what I said.*";
P_HTM[6745]="*jātipaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, jarāmaraṇaṃ, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?**Is that how you see this or not?”*";
P_HTM[6746]="*“Jātipaccayā, bhante, jarāmaraṇaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6747]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—**“That’s how we see it.”*";
P_HTM[6748]="*jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6749]="*“Bhavapaccayā jātīti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;**“‘Continued existence is a condition for rebirth.’ …*";
P_HTM[6750]="*bhavapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, jāti, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6751]="*“Bhavapaccayā, bhante, jāti;* **";
P_HTM[6752]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6753]="*bhavapaccayā jātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6754]="*“Upādānapaccayā bhavoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6755]="*upādānapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, bhavo, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6756]="*“Upādānapaccayā, bhante, bhavo;* **";
P_HTM[6757]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6758]="*upādānapaccayā bhavo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6759]="*“Taṇhāpaccayā upādānanti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, taṇhāpaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, upādānaṃ, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6760]="*“Taṇhāpaccayā, bhante, upādānaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6761]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6762]="*taṇhāpaccayā upādānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6763]="*“Vedanāpaccayā taṇhāti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6764]="*vedanāpaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, taṇhā, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6765]="*“Vedanāpaccayā, bhante, taṇhā;* **";
P_HTM[6766]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6767]="*vedanāpaccayā taṇhā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6768]="*“Phassapaccayā vedanāti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6769]="*phassapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, vedanā, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6770]="*“Phassapaccayā, bhante, vedanā;* **";
P_HTM[6771]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6772]="*phassapaccayā vedanā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6773]="*“Saḷāyatanapaccayā phassoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6774]="*saḷāyatanapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, phasso, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6775]="*“Saḷāyatanapaccayā, bhante, phasso;* **";
P_HTM[6776]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6777]="*saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6778]="*“Nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatananti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6779]="*nāmarūpapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, saḷāyatanaṃ, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6780]="*“Nāmarūpapaccayā, bhante, saḷāyatanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6781]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6782]="*nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6783]="*“Viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpanti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6784]="*viññāṇapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, nāmarūpaṃ, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6785]="*“Viññāṇapaccayā, bhante, nāmarūpaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6786]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6787]="*viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6788]="*“Saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇanti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6789]="*saṅkhārapaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6790]="*“Saṅkhārapaccayā, bhante, viññāṇaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6791]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6792]="*saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6793]="*“Avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārāti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;**‘Ignorance is a condition for choices.’ That’s what I said.*";
P_HTM[6794]="*avijjāpaccayā nu kho, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?**Is that how you see this or not?”*";
P_HTM[6795]="*“Avijjāpaccayā, bhante, saṅkhārā;* **";
P_HTM[6796]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—**“That’s how we see it.”*";
P_HTM[6797]="*avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6798]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[6799]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, tumhepi evaṃ vadetha, ahampi evaṃ vadāmi—**So both you and I say this.*";
P_HTM[6800]="*imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati, yadidaṃ—**When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises. That is:*";
P_HTM[6801]="*avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā,**Ignorance is a condition for choices.*";
P_HTM[6802]="*saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ,**Choices are a condition for consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6803]="*viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ,**Consciousness is a condition for name and form.*";
P_HTM[6804]="*nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ,**Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields.*";
P_HTM[6805]="*saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso,**The six sense fields are conditions for contact.*";
P_HTM[6806]="*phassapaccayā vedanā,**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[6807]="*vedanāpaccayā taṇhā,**Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[6808]="*taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ,**Craving is a condition for grasping.*";
P_HTM[6809]="*upādānapaccayā bhavo,**Grasping is a condition for continued existence.*";
P_HTM[6810]="*bhavapaccayā jāti,**Continued existence is a condition for rebirth.*";
P_HTM[6811]="*jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti.**Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be.*";
P_HTM[6812]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.*";
P_HTM[6813]="*Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho,**When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease.*";
P_HTM[6814]="*saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho,**When choices cease, consciousness ceases.*";
P_HTM[6815]="*viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho,**When consciousness ceases, name and form cease.*";
P_HTM[6816]="*nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho,**When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease.*";
P_HTM[6817]="*saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho,**When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases.*";
P_HTM[6818]="*phassanirodhā vedanānirodho,**When contact ceases, feeling ceases.*";
P_HTM[6819]="*vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho,**When feeling ceases, craving ceases.*";
P_HTM[6820]="*taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho,**When craving ceases, grasping ceases.*";
P_HTM[6821]="*upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho,**When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases.*";
P_HTM[6822]="*bhavanirodhā jātinirodho,**When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases.*";
P_HTM[6823]="*jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti.**When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[6824]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.*";
P_HTM[6825]="*Jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;**‘When rebirth ceases, old age and death cease.’ That’s what I said.*";
P_HTM[6826]="*jātinirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, jarāmaraṇanirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?**Is that how you see this or not?”*";
P_HTM[6827]="*“Jātinirodhā, bhante, jarāmaraṇanirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6828]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—**“That’s how we see it.”*";
P_HTM[6829]="*jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6830]="*“Bhavanirodhā jātinirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;**‘When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases.’ …*";
P_HTM[6831]="*bhavanirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, jātinirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6832]="*“Bhavanirodhā, bhante, jātinirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6833]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6834]="*bhavanirodhā jātinirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6835]="*“Upādānanirodhā bhavanirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6836]="*upādānanirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, bhavanirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6837]="*“Upādānanirodhā, bhante, bhavanirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6838]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6839]="*upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6840]="*“Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6841]="*taṇhānirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, upādānanirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6842]="*“Taṇhānirodhā, bhante, upādānanirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6843]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6844]="*taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6845]="*“Vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6846]="*vedanānirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, taṇhānirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6847]="*“Vedanānirodhā, bhante, taṇhānirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6848]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6849]="*vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6850]="*“Phassanirodhā vedanānirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6851]="*phassanirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, vedanānirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6852]="*“Phassanirodhā, bhante, vedanānirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6853]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6854]="*phassanirodhā vedanānirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6855]="*“Saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6856]="*saḷāyatananirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, phassanirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotīti?* **";
P_HTM[6857]="*Saḷāyatananirodhā, bhante, phassanirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6858]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6859]="*saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6860]="*“Nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6861]="*nāmarūpanirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, saḷāyatananirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6862]="*“Nāmarūpanirodhā, bhante, saḷāyatananirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6863]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6864]="*nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6865]="*“Viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6866]="*viññāṇanirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, nāmarūpanirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6867]="*“Viññāṇanirodhā, bhante, nāmarūpanirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6868]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6869]="*viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6870]="*“Saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6871]="*saṅkhāranirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, viññāṇanirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6872]="*“Saṅkhāranirodhā, bhante, viññāṇanirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6873]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6874]="*saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6875]="*“Avijjānirodhā saṅkhāranirodhoti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ;**‘When ignorance ceases, choices cease.’ That’s what I said.*";
P_HTM[6876]="*avijjānirodhā nu kho, bhikkhave, saṅkhāranirodho, no vā, kathaṃ vā ettha hotī”ti?**Is that how you see this or not?”*";
P_HTM[6877]="*“Avijjānirodhā, bhante, saṅkhāranirodho;* **";
P_HTM[6878]="*evaṃ no ettha hoti—**“That’s how we see it.”*";
P_HTM[6879]="*avijjānirodhā saṅkhāranirodho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6880]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[6881]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, tumhepi evaṃ vadetha, ahampi evaṃ vadāmi—**So both you and I say this.*";
P_HTM[6882]="*imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti, imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhati, yadidaṃ—**When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that ceases. That is:*";
P_HTM[6883]="*avijjānirodhā saṅkhāranirodho,**When ignorance ceases, choices cease.*";
P_HTM[6884]="*saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho,**When choices cease, consciousness ceases.*";
P_HTM[6885]="*viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho,**When consciousness ceases, name and form cease.*";
P_HTM[6886]="*nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho,**When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease.*";
P_HTM[6887]="*saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho,**When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases.*";
P_HTM[6888]="*phassanirodhā vedanānirodho,**When contact ceases, feeling ceases.*";
P_HTM[6889]="*vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho,**When feeling ceases, craving ceases.*";
P_HTM[6890]="*taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho,**When craving ceases, grasping ceases.*";
P_HTM[6891]="*upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho,**When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases.*";
P_HTM[6892]="*bhavanirodhā jātinirodho,**When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases.*";
P_HTM[6893]="*jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti.**When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[6894]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.*";
P_HTM[6895]="*Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā pubbantaṃ vā paṭidhāveyyātha:**Knowing and seeing in this way, mendicants, would you turn back to the past, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6896]="*‘ahesumha nu kho mayaṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, nanu kho ahesumha atītamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ nu kho ahesumha atītamaddhānaṃ, kathaṃ nu kho ahesumha atītamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ hutvā kiṃ ahesumha nu kho mayaṃ atītamaddhānan’”ti?**‘Did we exist in the past? Did we not exist in the past? What were we in the past? How were we in the past? After being what, what did we become in the past?’?”*";
P_HTM[6897]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6898]="*“Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā aparantaṃ vā paṭidhāveyyātha—**“Knowing and seeing in this way, mendicants, would you turn forward to the future, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6899]="*bhavissāma nu kho mayaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, nanu kho bhavissāma anāgatamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ nu kho bhavissāma anāgatamaddhānaṃ, kathaṃ nu kho bhavissāma anāgatamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ hutvā kiṃ bhavissāma nu kho mayaṃ anāgatamaddhānan”ti?**‘Will we exist in the future? Will we not exist in the future? What will we be in the future? How will we be in the future? After being what, what will we become in the future?’?”*";
P_HTM[6900]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6901]="*“Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā etarahi vā paccuppannamaddhānaṃ ajjhattaṃ kathaṅkathī assatha—**“Knowing and seeing in this way, mendicants, would you be undecided about the present, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6902]="*ahaṃ nu khosmi, no nu khosmi, kiṃ nu khosmi, kathaṃ nu khosmi, ayaṃ nu kho satto kuto āgato, so kuhiṃ gāmī bhavissatī”ti?**‘Am I? Am I not? What am I? How am I? This sentient being—where did it come from? And where will it go?’?”*";
P_HTM[6903]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6904]="*“Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā evaṃ vadeyyātha—**“Knowing and seeing in this way, would you say,*";
P_HTM[6905]="*satthā no garu, satthugāravena ca mayaṃ evaṃ vademā”ti?**‘Our teacher is respected. We speak like this out of respect for our teacher.’?”*";
P_HTM[6906]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6907]="*“Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā evaṃ vadeyyātha—**“Knowing and seeing in this way, would you say,*";
P_HTM[6908]="*samaṇo evamāha, samaṇā ca nāma mayaṃ evaṃ vademā”ti?**‘Our ascetic says this. It’s only because of him that we say this’?”*";
P_HTM[6909]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6910]="*“Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā aññaṃ satthāraṃ uddiseyyāthā”ti?**“Knowing and seeing in this way, would you acknowledge another teacher?”*";
P_HTM[6911]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6912]="*“Api nu tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā yāni tāni puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ vata kotūhalamaṅgalāni tāni sārato paccāgaccheyyāthā”ti?**“Knowing and seeing in this way, would you believe that the observances and noisy, superstitious rites of the various ascetics and brahmins are the most important things?”*";
P_HTM[6913]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6914]="*“Nanu, bhikkhave, yadeva tumhākaṃ sāmaṃ ñātaṃ sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sāmaṃ viditaṃ, tadeva tumhe vadethā”ti.**“Are you not speaking only of what you have known and seen and realized for yourselves?”*";
P_HTM[6915]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6916]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave, upanītā kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, iminā sandiṭṭhikena dhammena akālikena ehipassikena opaneyyikena paccattaṃ veditabbena viññūhi.**“Good, mendicants! You have been guided by me with this teaching that’s visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[6917]="*Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhi—**For when I said that this teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves,*";
P_HTM[6918]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttanti.**this is what I was referring to.*";
P_HTM[6919]="*Tiṇṇaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sannipātā gabbhassāvakkanti hoti.**Mendicants, when three things come together an embryo is conceived.*";
P_HTM[6920]="*Idha mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca na utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca na paccupaṭṭhito hoti, neva tāva gabbhassāvakkanti hoti.**In a case where the mother and father come together, but the mother is not in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, and the spirit being reborn is not present, the embryo is not conceived.*";
P_HTM[6921]="*Idha mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca na paccupaṭṭhito hoti, neva tāva gabbhassāvakkanti hoti.**In a case where the mother and father come together, the mother is in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, but the spirit being reborn is not present, the embryo is not conceived.*";
P_HTM[6922]="*Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca paccupaṭṭhito hoti—evaṃ tiṇṇaṃ sannipātā gabbhassāvakkanti hoti.**But when these three things come together—the mother and father come together, the mother is in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, and the spirit being reborn is present—an embryo is conceived.*";
P_HTM[6923]="*Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, mātā nava vā dasa vā māse gabbhaṃ kucchinā pariharati mahatā saṃsayena garubhāraṃ.**The mother nurtures the embryo in her womb for nine or ten months at great risk to her heavy burden.*";
P_HTM[6924]="*Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, mātā navannaṃ vā dasannaṃ vā māsānaṃ accayena vijāyati mahatā saṃsayena garubhāraṃ.**When nine or ten months have passed, the mother gives birth at great risk to her heavy burden.*";
P_HTM[6925]="*Tamenaṃ jātaṃ samānaṃ sakena lohitena poseti.**When the infant is born she nourishes it with her own blood.*";
P_HTM[6926]="*Lohitañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye yadidaṃ mātuthaññaṃ.**For mother’s milk is regarded as blood in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[6927]="*Sa kho so, bhikkhave, kumāro vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya**That boy grows up and his faculties mature.*";
P_HTM[6928]="*yāni tāni kumārakānaṃ kīḷāpanakāni tehi kīḷati, seyyathidaṃ—vaṅkakaṃ ghaṭikaṃ mokkhacikaṃ ciṅgulakaṃ pattāḷhakaṃ rathakaṃ dhanukaṃ.**He accordingly plays childish games such as toy plows, tipcat, somersaults, pinwheels, toy measures, toy carts, and toy bows.*";
P_HTM[6929]="*Sa kho so, bhikkhave, kumāro vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya**That boy grows up and his faculties mature further.*";
P_HTM[6930]="*pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti—**He accordingly amuses himself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[6931]="*cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[6932]="*sotaviññeyyehi saddehi …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[6933]="*ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[6934]="*jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[6935]="*kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi.**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[6936]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe sārajjati, appiyarūpe rūpe byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati parittacetaso.**When they see a sight with their eyes, if it’s pleasant they desire it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body unestablished and their heart restricted.*";
P_HTM[6937]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[6938]="*So evaṃ anurodhavirodhaṃ samāpanno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**Being so full of favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it.*";
P_HTM[6939]="*Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī.**This gives rise to relishing.*";
P_HTM[6940]="*Yā vedanāsu nandī tadupādānaṃ, tassupādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti.**Relishing feelings is grasping. Their grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be.*";
P_HTM[6941]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.*";
P_HTM[6942]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[6943]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[6944]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[6945]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[6946]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme sārajjati, appiyarūpe dhamme byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati parittacetaso.**When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they desire it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body unestablished and their heart restricted.*";
P_HTM[6947]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[6948]="*So evaṃ anurodhavirodhaṃ samāpanno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**Being so full of favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it.*";
P_HTM[6949]="*Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī.**This gives rise to relishing.*";
P_HTM[6950]="*Yā vedanāsu nandī tadupādānaṃ, tassupādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti.**Relishing feelings is grasping. Their grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be.*";
P_HTM[6951]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.*";
P_HTM[6952]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**But consider when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[6953]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[6954]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ;**He proclaims a teaching that is good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, with the right meaning and phrasing.*";
P_HTM[6955]="*kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He reveals an entirely full and pure spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[6956]="*Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto.**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some good family.*";
P_HTM[6957]="*So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati.**They gain faith in the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[6958]="*So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:**and reflect,*";
P_HTM[6959]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[6960]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[6961]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā, kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’”ti.**Why don’t I cut off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[6962]="*So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā, kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[6963]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[6964]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati.**They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving.*";
P_HTM[6965]="*Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti, ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.**They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[6966]="*Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa.**They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words.*";
P_HTM[6967]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī, samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[6968]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[6969]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena, sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[6970]="*So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid injuring plants and seeds.*";
P_HTM[6971]="*ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato, virato vikālabhojanā.**They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[6972]="*Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.*";
P_HTM[6973]="*mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, perfumes, and makeup.*";
P_HTM[6974]="*uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid high and luxurious beds.*";
P_HTM[6975]="*jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid receiving gold and money,*";
P_HTM[6976]="*āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**raw grains,*";
P_HTM[6977]="*āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**raw meat,*";
P_HTM[6978]="*itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**women and girls,*";
P_HTM[6979]="*dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**male and female bondservants,*";
P_HTM[6980]="*ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**goats and sheep,*";
P_HTM[6981]="*kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**chickens and pigs,*";
P_HTM[6982]="*hatthigavāssavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**elephants, cows, horses, and mares,*";
P_HTM[6983]="*khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**and fields and land.*";
P_HTM[6984]="*dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid running errands and messages;*";
P_HTM[6985]="*kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti,**buying and selling;*";
P_HTM[6986]="*tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti,**falsifying weights, metals, or measures;*";
P_HTM[6987]="*ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti,**bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;*";
P_HTM[6988]="*chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti.**mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.*";
P_HTM[6989]="*So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[6990]="*Seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti sapattabhārova ḍeti;**They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden.*";
P_HTM[6991]="*evameva bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena, kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[6992]="*So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[6993]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they see a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[6994]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[6995]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[6996]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[6997]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[6998]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[6999]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[7000]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[7001]="*So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[7002]="*So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti.**They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.*";
P_HTM[7003]="*So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato,**When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness,*";
P_HTM[7004]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati—araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[7005]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya, parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[7006]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[7007]="*byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will.*";
P_HTM[7008]="*thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī, sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[7009]="*uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[7010]="*vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[7011]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe,**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[7012]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[7013]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[7014]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[7015]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[7016]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe na sārajjati, appiyarūpe rūpe na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso.**When they see a sight with their eyes, if it’s pleasant they don’t desire it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart.*";
P_HTM[7017]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[7018]="*So evaṃ anurodhavirodhavippahīno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti, sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**Having given up favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they don’t approve, welcome, or keep clinging to it.*";
P_HTM[7019]="*Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato yā vedanāsu nandī sā nirujjhati.**As a result, relishing of feelings ceases.*";
P_HTM[7020]="*Tassa nandīnirodhā upādānanirodho, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti.**When their relishing ceases, grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[7021]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.*";
P_HTM[7022]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[7023]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[7024]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[7025]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[7026]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme na sārajjati, appiyarūpe dhamme na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso,**When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they don’t desire it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart.*";
P_HTM[7027]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[7028]="*So evaṃ anurodhavirodhavippahīno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti, sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**Having given up favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they don’t approve, welcome, or keep clinging to it.*";
P_HTM[7029]="*Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato yā vedanāsu nandī sā nirujjhati.**As a result, relishing of feelings ceases.*";
P_HTM[7030]="*Tassa nandīnirodhā upādānanirodho, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti.**When their relishing ceases, grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[7031]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.*";
P_HTM[7032]="*Imaṃ kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ dhāretha, sātiṃ pana bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ mahātaṇhājālataṇhāsaṅghāṭappaṭimukkan”ti.**Mendicants, you should memorize that brief statement on freedom through the ending of craving. But the mendicant Sāti, the fisherman’s son, is caught in a vast net of craving, a tangle of craving.”*";
P_HTM[7033]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7034]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7035]="*Mahātaṇhāsaṅkhayasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7036]="*39. Mahāassapurasutta**The Longer Discourse at Assapura*";
P_HTM[7037]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7038]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅgesu viharati assapuraṃ nāma aṅgānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Aṅgas, near the Aṅgan town named Assapura.*";
P_HTM[7039]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[7040]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[7041]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7042]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7043]="*“Samaṇā samaṇāti vo, bhikkhave, jano sañjānāti.**“Mendicants, people label you as ascetics.*";
P_HTM[7044]="*Tumhe ca pana ‘ke tumhe’ti puṭṭhā samānā ‘samaṇāmhā’ti paṭijānātha;**And when they ask you what you are, you claim to be ascetics.*";
P_HTM[7045]="*tesaṃ vo, bhikkhave, evaṃsamaññānaṃ sataṃ evaṃpaṭiññānaṃ sataṃ ‘ye dhammā samaṇakaraṇā ca brāhmaṇakaraṇā ca te dhamme samādāya vattissāma, evaṃ no ayaṃ amhākaṃ samaññā ca saccā bhavissati paṭiññā ca bhūtā.**Given this label and this claim, you should train like this: ‘We will undertake and follow the things that make one an ascetic and a brahmin. That way our label will be accurate and our claim correct.*";
P_HTM[7046]="*Yesañca mayaṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjāma, tesaṃ te kārā amhesu mahapphalā bhavissanti mahānisaṃsā, amhākañcevāyaṃ pabbajjā avañjhā bhavissati saphalā saudrayā’ti.**Any robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick that we use will be very fruitful and beneficial for the donor. And our going forth will not be wasted, but will be fruitful and fertile.’*";
P_HTM[7047]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7048]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā samaṇakaraṇā ca brāhmaṇakaraṇā ca?**And what are the things that make one an ascetic and a brahmin?*";
P_HTM[7049]="*‘Hirottappena samannāgatā bhavissāmā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**You should train like this: ‘We will have conscience and prudence.’*";
P_HTM[7050]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7051]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**‘We have conscience and prudence. Just this much is enough. We have achieved the goal of life as an ascetic. There is nothing more to do.’ And you might rest content with just that much.*";
P_HTM[7052]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:**I declare this to you, mendicants, I announce this to you:*";
P_HTM[7053]="*‘mā vo sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi, sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.**‘You who seek to be true ascetics, do not lose sight of the goal of the ascetic life while there is still more to do.’*";
P_HTM[7054]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7055]="*‘Parisuddho no kāyasamācāro bhavissati uttāno vivaṭo na ca chiddavā saṃvuto ca.**You should train like this: ‘Our bodily behavior will be pure, clear, open, neither inconsistent nor secretive.*";
P_HTM[7056]="*Tāya ca pana parisuddhakāyasamācāratāya nevattānukkaṃsessāma na paraṃ vambhessāmā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**And we won’t glorify ourselves or put others down on account of our pure bodily behavior.’*";
P_HTM[7057]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7058]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro;**‘We have conscience and prudence, and our bodily behavior is pure.*";
P_HTM[7059]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**Just this much is enough …’*";
P_HTM[7060]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:**I declare this to you, mendicants, I announce this to you:*";
P_HTM[7061]="*‘mā vo sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi, sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.**‘You who seek to be true ascetics, do not lose sight of the goal of the ascetic life while there is still more to do.’*";
P_HTM[7062]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7063]="*‘Parisuddho no vacīsamācāro bhavissati uttāno vivaṭo na ca chiddavā saṃvuto ca.**You should train like this: ‘Our verbal behavior …*";
P_HTM[7064]="*Tāya ca pana parisuddhavacīsamācāratāya nevattānukkaṃsessāma na paraṃ vambhessāmā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7065]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:* **";
P_HTM[7066]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro;* **";
P_HTM[7067]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.* **";
P_HTM[7068]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:* **";
P_HTM[7069]="*‘mā vo sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi, sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.* **";
P_HTM[7070]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[7071]="*‘Parisuddho no manosamācāro bhavissati uttāno vivaṭo na ca chiddavā saṃvuto ca.**mental behavior …*";
P_HTM[7072]="*Tāya ca pana parisuddhamanosamācāratāya nevattānukkaṃsessāma na paraṃ vambhessāmā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7073]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:* **";
P_HTM[7074]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro, parisuddho manosamācāro;* **";
P_HTM[7075]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.* **";
P_HTM[7076]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:* **";
P_HTM[7077]="*‘mā vo sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi, sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.* **";
P_HTM[7078]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[7079]="*‘Parisuddho no ājīvo bhavissati uttāno vivaṭo na ca chiddavā saṃvuto ca.**livelihood will be pure, clear, open, neither inconsistent nor secretive.*";
P_HTM[7080]="*Tāya ca pana parisuddhājīvatāya nevattānukkaṃsessāma na paraṃ vambhessāmā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**And we won’t glorify ourselves or put others down on account of our pure livelihood.’*";
P_HTM[7081]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7082]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro, parisuddho manosamācāro, parisuddho ājīvo;**‘We have conscience and prudence, our bodily, verbal, and mental behavior is pure, and our livelihood is pure.*";
P_HTM[7083]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**Just this much is enough. We have achieved the goal of life as an ascetic. There is nothing more to do.’ And you might rest content with just that much.*";
P_HTM[7084]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:**I declare this to you, mendicants, I announce this to you:*";
P_HTM[7085]="*‘mā vo sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi, sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.**‘You who seek to be true ascetics, do not lose sight of the goal of the ascetic life while there is still more to do.’*";
P_HTM[7086]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7087]="*‘Indriyesu guttadvārā bhavissāma;**You should train yourselves like this: ‘We will restrain our sense doors.*";
P_HTM[7088]="*cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When we see a sight with our eyes, we won’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[7089]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjissāma, rakkhissāma cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjissāma.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, we will practice restraint, we will protect the faculty of sight, and we will achieve its restraint.*";
P_HTM[7090]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When we hear a sound with our ears …*";
P_HTM[7091]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**When we smell an odor with our nose …*";
P_HTM[7092]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**When we taste a flavor with our tongue …*";
P_HTM[7093]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**When we feel a touch with our body …*";
P_HTM[7094]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When we know a thought with our mind, we won’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[7095]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjissāma, rakkhissāma manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjissāmā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, we will practice restraint, we will protect the faculty of mind, and we will achieve its restraint.’*";
P_HTM[7096]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7097]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro, parisuddho manosamācāro, parisuddho ājīvo, indriyesumha guttadvārā;**‘We have conscience and prudence, our bodily, verbal, and mental behavior is pure, our livelihood is pure, and our sense doors are restrained.*";
P_HTM[7098]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**Just this much is enough …’*";
P_HTM[7099]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:* **";
P_HTM[7100]="*‘mā vo sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi, sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.* **";
P_HTM[7101]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7102]="*‘Bhojane mattaññuno bhavissāma, paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āharissāma,**You should train yourselves like this: ‘We will not eat too much. We will only eat after reflecting properly on our food.*";
P_HTM[7103]="*neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā, brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāma navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāma, yātrā ca no bhavissati, anavajjatā ca, phāsu vihāro cā’ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**We will eat not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to sustain this body, to avoid harm, and to support spiritual practice. In this way, we shall put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and we will live blamelessly and at ease.’*";
P_HTM[7104]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7105]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro, parisuddho manosamācāro, parisuddho ājīvo, indriyesumha guttadvārā, bhojane mattaññuno;**‘We have conscience and prudence, our bodily, verbal, and mental behavior is pure, our livelihood is pure, our sense doors are restrained, and we don’t eat too much.*";
P_HTM[7106]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**Just this much is enough …’*";
P_HTM[7107]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:* **";
P_HTM[7108]="*‘mā vo, sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.* **";
P_HTM[7109]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7110]="*‘Jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā bhavissāma, divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodhessāma.**You should train yourselves like this: ‘We will be dedicated to wakefulness. When practicing walking and sitting meditation by day, we will purify our mind from obstacles.*";
P_HTM[7111]="*Rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodhessāma.**In the evening, we will continue to practice walking and sitting meditation.*";
P_HTM[7112]="*Rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappessāma pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā.**In the middle of the night, we will lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up.*";
P_HTM[7113]="*Rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodhessāmā’ti, evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**In the last part of the night, we will get up and continue to practice walking and sitting meditation, purifying our mind from obstacles.’*";
P_HTM[7114]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7115]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro, parisuddho manosamācāro, parisuddho ājīvo, indriyesumha guttadvārā, bhojane mattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā;**‘We have conscience and prudence, our bodily, verbal, and mental behavior is pure, our livelihood is pure, our sense doors are restrained, we don’t eat too much, and we are dedicated to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[7116]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti, tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**Just this much is enough …’*";
P_HTM[7117]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:* **";
P_HTM[7118]="*‘mā vo, sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.* **";
P_HTM[7119]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7120]="*‘Satisampajaññena samannāgatā bhavissāma, abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī’ti, evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**You should train yourselves like this: ‘We will have situational awareness and mindfulness. We will act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.’*";
P_HTM[7121]="*Siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Now, mendicants, you might think,*";
P_HTM[7122]="*‘hirottappenamha samannāgatā, parisuddho no kāyasamācāro, parisuddho vacīsamācāro, parisuddho manosamācāro, parisuddho ājīvo, indriyesumha guttadvārā, bhojane mattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā, satisampajaññena samannāgatā;**‘We have conscience and prudence, our bodily, verbal, and mental behavior is pure, our livelihood is pure, our sense doors are restrained, we don’t eat too much, we are dedicated to wakefulness, and we have mindfulness and situational awareness.*";
P_HTM[7123]="*alamettāvatā katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci uttariṃ karaṇīyan’ti tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhiṃ āpajjeyyātha.**Just this much is enough …’*";
P_HTM[7124]="*Ārocayāmi vo, bhikkhave, paṭivedayāmi vo, bhikkhave:* **";
P_HTM[7125]="*‘mā vo, sāmaññatthikānaṃ sataṃ sāmaññattho parihāyi sati uttariṃ karaṇīye’.* **";
P_HTM[7126]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, uttariṃ karaṇīyaṃ?**What more is there to do?*";
P_HTM[7127]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati—araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanappatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**Take a mendicant who frequents a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[7128]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[7129]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[7130]="*byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will.*";
P_HTM[7131]="*thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati, ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[7132]="*uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati, ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[7133]="*vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati, akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[7134]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso iṇaṃ ādāya kammante payojeyya.**Suppose a man who has gotten into debt were to apply himself to work,*";
P_HTM[7135]="*Tassa te kammantā samijjheyyuṃ.**and his efforts proved successful.*";
P_HTM[7136]="*So yāni ca porāṇāni iṇamūlāni tāni ca byantī kareyya, siyā cassa uttariṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ dārabharaṇāya.**He would pay off the original loan and have enough left over to support his partner.*";
P_HTM[7137]="*Tassa evamassa:**Thinking about this,*";
P_HTM[7138]="*‘ahaṃ kho pubbe iṇaṃ ādāya kammante payojesiṃ, tassa me te kammantā samijjhiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[7139]="*Sohaṃ yāni ca porāṇāni iṇamūlāni tāni ca byantī akāsiṃ, atthi ca me uttariṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ dārabharaṇāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7140]="*So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ.**he’d be filled with joy and happiness.*";
P_HTM[7141]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso ābādhiko assa dukkhito bāḷhagilāno, bhattañcassa nacchādeyya, na cassa kāye balamattā.**Suppose a person was sick, suffering, and gravely ill. They’d lose their appetite and get physically weak.*";
P_HTM[7142]="*So aparena samayena tamhā ābādhā mucceyya, bhattañcassa chādeyya, siyā cassa kāye balamattā.**But after some time they’d recover from that illness, and regain their appetite and their strength.*";
P_HTM[7143]="*Tassa evamassa:**Thinking about this,*";
P_HTM[7144]="*‘ahaṃ kho pubbe ābādhiko ahosiṃ dukkhito bāḷhagilāno, bhattañca me nacchādesi, na ca me āsi kāye balamattā, somhi etarahi tamhā ābādhā mutto, bhattañca me chādeti, atthi ca me kāye balamattā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7145]="*So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ.**they’d be filled with joy and happiness.*";
P_HTM[7146]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso bandhanāgāre baddho assa.**Suppose a person was imprisoned in a jail.*";
P_HTM[7147]="*So aparena samayena tamhā bandhanā mucceyya sotthinā abbhayena, na cassa kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo.**But after some time they were released from jail, safe and sound, with no loss of wealth.*";
P_HTM[7148]="*Tassa evamassa:**Thinking about this,*";
P_HTM[7149]="*‘ahaṃ kho pubbe bandhanāgāre baddho ahosiṃ, somhi etarahi tamhā bandhanā mutto, sotthinā abbhayena, natthi ca me kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7150]="*So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ.**they’d be filled with joy and happiness.*";
P_HTM[7151]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso dāso assa anattādhīno parādhīno na yenakāmaṅgamo.**Suppose a person was a bondservant. They belonged to someone else and were unable to go where they wished.*";
P_HTM[7152]="*So aparena samayena tamhā dāsabyā mucceyya attādhīno aparādhīno bhujisso yenakāmaṅgamo.**But after some time they’d be freed from servitude and become their own master, an emancipated individual able to go where they wished.*";
P_HTM[7153]="*Tassa evamassa:**Thinking about this,*";
P_HTM[7154]="*‘ahaṃ kho pubbe dāso ahosiṃ anattādhīno parādhīno na yenakāmaṅgamo, somhi etarahi tamhā dāsabyā mutto attādhīno aparādhīno bhujisso yenakāmaṅgamo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7155]="*So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ.**they’d be filled with joy and happiness.*";
P_HTM[7156]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sadhano sabhogo kantāraddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya.**Suppose there was a person with wealth and property who was traveling along a desert road.*";
P_HTM[7157]="*So aparena samayena tamhā kantārā nitthareyya sotthinā abbhayena, na cassa kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo.**But after some time they crossed over the desert, safe and sound, with no loss of wealth.*";
P_HTM[7158]="*Tassa evamassa:**Thinking about this,*";
P_HTM[7159]="*‘ahaṃ kho pubbe sadhano sabhogo kantāraddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7160]="*Somhi etarahi tamhā kantārā nitthiṇṇo sotthinā abbhayena, natthi ca me kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7161]="*So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ.**they’d be filled with joy and happiness.*";
P_HTM[7162]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathā iṇaṃ yathā rogaṃ yathā bandhanāgāraṃ yathā dāsabyaṃ yathā kantāraddhānamaggaṃ, ime pañca nīvaraṇe appahīne attani samanupassati.**In the same way, as long as these five hindrances are not given up inside themselves, a mendicant regards them as a debt, a disease, a prison, slavery, and a desert crossing.*";
P_HTM[7163]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, āṇaṇyaṃ yathā ārogyaṃ yathā bandhanāmokkhaṃ yathā bhujissaṃ yathā khemantabhūmiṃ; evameva bhikkhu ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahīne attani samanupassati.**But when these five hindrances are given up inside themselves, a mendicant regards this as freedom from debt, good health, release from prison, emancipation, and sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[7164]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe,**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[7165]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi, savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[7166]="*So imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of seclusion.*";
P_HTM[7167]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho nhāpako vā nhāpakantevāsī vā kaṃsathāle nhānīyacuṇṇāni ākiritvā udakena paripphosakaṃ paripphosakaṃ sanneyya. Sāyaṃ nhānīyapiṇḍi snehānugatā snehaparetā santarabāhirā, phuṭā snehena na ca pagghariṇī.**It’s like when a deft bathroom attendant or their apprentice pours bath powder into a bronze dish, sprinkling it little by little with water. They knead it until the ball of bath powder is soaked and saturated with moisture, spread through inside and out; yet no moisture oozes out.*";
P_HTM[7168]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with rapture and bliss born of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of seclusion.*";
P_HTM[7169]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[7170]="*So imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion.*";
P_HTM[7171]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, udakarahado ubbhidodako. Tassa nevassa puratthimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na pacchimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na uttarāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na dakkhiṇāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, devo ca na kālena kālaṃ sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya. Atha kho tamhāva udakarahadā sītā vāridhārā ubbhijjitvā tameva udakarahadaṃ sītena vārinā abhisandeyya parisandeyya paripūreyya paripphareyya, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato udakarahadassa sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ assa.**It’s like a deep lake fed by spring water. There’s no inlet to the east, west, north, or south, and no rainfall to replenish it from time to time. But the stream of cool water welling up in the lake drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads throughout the lake. There’s no part of the lake that’s not spread through with cool water.*";
P_HTM[7172]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion.*";
P_HTM[7173]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[7174]="*So imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture.*";
P_HTM[7175]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni antonimuggaposīni, tāni yāva caggā yāva ca mūlā sītena vārinā abhisannāni parisannāni paripūrāni paripphuṭāni, nāssa kiñci sabbāvataṃ uppalānaṃ vā padumānaṃ vā puṇḍarīkānaṃ vā sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ assa.**It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. From the tip to the root they’re drenched, steeped, filled, and soaked with cool water. There’s no part of them that’s not soaked with cool water.*";
P_HTM[7176]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture.*";
P_HTM[7177]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[7178]="*So imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind.*";
P_HTM[7179]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso odātena vatthena sasīsaṃ pārupetvā nisinno assa, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa odātena vatthena apphuṭaṃ assa.**It’s like someone sitting wrapped from head to foot with white cloth. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread over with white cloth.*";
P_HTM[7180]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, they sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind.*";
P_HTM[7181]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[7182]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ, dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[7183]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sakamhā gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ gaccheyya, tamhāpi gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ gaccheyya, so tamhā gāmā sakaṃyeva gāmaṃ paccāgaccheyya. Tassa evamassa: ‘ahaṃ kho sakamhā gāmā amuṃ gāmaṃ agacchiṃ, tatrapi evaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ evaṃ nisīdiṃ evaṃ abhāsiṃ evaṃ tuṇhī ahosiṃ; tamhāpi gāmā amuṃ gāmaṃ agacchiṃ, tatrapi evaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ evaṃ nisīdiṃ evaṃ abhāsiṃ evaṃ tuṇhī ahosiṃ; somhi tamhā gāmā sakaṃyeva gāmaṃ paccāgato’ti.**Suppose a person was to leave their home village and go to another village. From that village they’d go to yet another village. And from that village they’d return to their home village. They’d think: ‘I went from my home village to another village. There I stood like this, sat like that, spoke like this, or kept silent like that. From that village I went to yet another village. There too I stood like this, sat like that, spoke like this, or kept silent like that. And from that village I returned to my home village.’*";
P_HTM[7184]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**In the same way, a mendicant recollects their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[7185]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[7186]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate, yathākammūpage satte pajānāti … pe …**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[7187]="*seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dve agārā sadvārā. Tattha cakkhumā puriso majjhe ṭhito passeyya manusse gehaṃ pavisantepi nikkhamantepi, anucaṅkamantepi anuvicarantepi.**Suppose there were two houses with doors. A person with good eyesight standing in between them would see people entering and leaving a house and wandering to and fro.*";
P_HTM[7188]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti … pe ….**In the same way, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[7189]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[7190]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[7191]="*‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[7192]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[7193]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti:**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[7194]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[7195]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, pabbatasaṅkhepe udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo.**Suppose that in a mountain glen there was a lake that was transparent, clear, and unclouded. A person with good eyesight standing on the bank would see the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying still.*";
P_HTM[7196]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso tīre ṭhito passeyya sippisambukampi sakkharakathalampi macchagumbampi, carantampi tiṭṭhantampi.* **";
P_HTM[7197]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[7198]="*‘ayaṃ kho udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo. Tatrime sippisambukāpi sakkharakathalāpi macchagumbāpi carantipi tiṭṭhantipī’ti’.**‘This lake is transparent, clear, and unclouded. And here are the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying still.’*";
P_HTM[7199]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe …**In the same way, a mendicant truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[7200]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[7201]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘samaṇo’ itipi ‘brāhmaṇo’itipi ‘nhātako’itipi ‘vedagū’itipi ‘sottiyo’itipi ‘ariyo’itipi ‘arahaṃ’itipi.**This mendicant is called an ‘ascetic’, a ‘brahmin’, a ‘bathed initiate’, a ‘knowledge master’, a ‘scholar’, a ‘noble one’, and a ‘perfected one’.*";
P_HTM[7202]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samaṇo hoti?**And how is a mendicant an ascetic?*";
P_HTM[7203]="*Samitāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṅkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They have quelled the bad, unskillful qualities that are corrupted, leading to future lives, hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[7204]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samaṇo hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is an ascetic.*";
P_HTM[7205]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu brāhmaṇo hoti?**And how is a mendicant a brahmin?*";
P_HTM[7206]="*Bāhitāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṅkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They have barred out the bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7207]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu brāhmaṇo hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[7208]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nhātako hoti?**And how is a mendicant a bathed initiate?*";
P_HTM[7209]="*Nhātāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṃkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They have bathed off the bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7210]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nhātako hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a bathed initiate.*";
P_HTM[7211]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedagū hoti?**And how is a mendicant a knowledge master?*";
P_HTM[7212]="*Viditāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṅkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They have known the bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7213]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedagū hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a knowledge master.*";
P_HTM[7214]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sottiyo hoti?**And how is a mendicant a scholar?*";
P_HTM[7215]="*Nissutāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṅkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They have scoured off the bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7216]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sottiyo hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a scholar.*";
P_HTM[7217]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyo hoti?**And how is a mendicant a noble one?*";
P_HTM[7218]="*Ārakāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṅkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They are far away from the bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7219]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyo hoti.**That’s how a mendicant is a noble one.*";
P_HTM[7220]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ hoti?**And how is a mendicant a perfected one?*";
P_HTM[7221]="*Ārakāssa honti pāpakā akusalā dhammā, saṅkilesikā, ponobbhavikā, sadarā, dukkhavipākā, āyatiṃ, jātijarāmaraṇiyā.**They are far away from the bad, unskillful qualities that are corrupted, leading to future lives, hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[7222]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ hotī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant is a perfected one.”*";
P_HTM[7223]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7224]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7225]="*Mahāassapurasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7226]="*40. Cūḷaassapurasutta**The Shorter Discourse at Assapura*";
P_HTM[7227]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7228]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅgesu viharati assapuraṃ nāma aṅgānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Aṅgas, near the Aṅgan town named Assapura.*";
P_HTM[7229]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[7230]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[7231]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7232]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7233]="*“Samaṇā samaṇāti vo, bhikkhave, jano sañjānāti.**“Mendicants, people label you as ascetics.*";
P_HTM[7234]="*Tumhe ca pana ‘ke tumhe’ti puṭṭhā samānā ‘samaṇāmhā’ti paṭijānātha.**And when they ask you what you are, you claim to be ascetics.*";
P_HTM[7235]="*Tesaṃ vo, bhikkhave, evaṃsamaññānaṃ sataṃ evaṃpaṭiññānaṃ sataṃ:**Given this label and this claim, you should train like this: ‘We will practice in the way that is proper for an ascetic. That way our label will be accurate and our claim correct.*";
P_HTM[7236]="*‘yā samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadā taṃ paṭipajjissāma;* **";
P_HTM[7237]="*evaṃ no ayaṃ amhākaṃ samaññā ca saccā bhavissati paṭiññā ca bhūtā;* **";
P_HTM[7238]="*yesañca mayaṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjāma, tesaṃ te kārā amhesu mahapphalā bhavissanti mahānisaṃsā, amhākañcevāyaṃ pabbajjā avañjhā bhavissati saphalā saudrayā’ti.**Any robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick that we use will be very fruitful and beneficial for the donor. And our going forth will not be wasted, but will be fruitful and fertile.’*";
P_HTM[7239]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7240]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti?**And how does a mendicant not practice in the way that is proper for an ascetic?*";
P_HTM[7241]="*Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno abhijjhālussa abhijjhā appahīnā hoti, byāpannacittassa byāpādo appahīno hoti, kodhanassa kodho appahīno hoti, upanāhissa upanāho appahīno hoti, makkhissa makkho appahīno hoti, paḷāsissa paḷāso appahīno hoti, issukissa issā appahīnā hoti, maccharissa macchariyaṃ appahīnaṃ hoti, saṭhassa sāṭheyyaṃ appahīnaṃ hoti, māyāvissa māyā appahīnā hoti, pāpicchassa pāpikā icchā appahīnā hoti, micchādiṭṭhikassa micchādiṭṭhi appahīnā hoti—**There are some mendicants who have not given up covetousness, ill will, irritability, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deviousness, deceit, bad desires, and wrong view.*";
P_HTM[7242]="*imesaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, samaṇamalānaṃ samaṇadosānaṃ samaṇakasaṭānaṃ āpāyikānaṃ ṭhānānaṃ duggativedaniyānaṃ appahānā ‘na samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno’ti vadāmi.**These stains, defects, and dregs of an ascetic are grounds for rebirth in places of loss, and are experienced in bad places. As long as they have not given these up, they do not practice in the way that is proper for an ascetic, I say.*";
P_HTM[7243]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, matajaṃ nāma āvudhajātaṃ ubhatodhāraṃ pītanisitaṃ.**I say that such a mendicant’s going forth may be compared to the kind of weapon called ‘death-dealer’—double-edged, hardened, and keen—covered and wrapped in the outer robe.*";
P_HTM[7244]="*Tadassa saṅghāṭiyā sampārutaṃ sampaliveṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7245]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa bhikkhuno pabbajjaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[7246]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅghāṭikassa saṅghāṭidhāraṇamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**I say that you don’t deserve the label ‘outer robe wearer’ just because you wear an outer robe.*";
P_HTM[7247]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, acelakassa acelakamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘naked ascetic’ just because you go naked.*";
P_HTM[7248]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, rajojallikassa rajojallikamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘dust and dirt wearer’ just because you’re caked in dust and dirt.*";
P_HTM[7249]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, udakorohakassa udakorohaṇamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘water immerser’ just because you immerse yourself in water.*";
P_HTM[7250]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlikassa rukkhamūlikamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘tree root dweller’ just because you stay at the root of a tree.*";
P_HTM[7251]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, abbhokāsikassa abbhokāsikamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘open air dweller’ just because you stay in the open air.*";
P_HTM[7252]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ubbhaṭṭhakassa ubbhaṭṭhakamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘stander’ just because you continually stand.*";
P_HTM[7253]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyāyabhattikassa pariyāyabhattikamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘interval eater’ just because you eat food at set intervals.*";
P_HTM[7254]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, mantajjhāyakassa mantajjhāyakamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘reciter’ just because you recite scriptures.*";
P_HTM[7255]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, jaṭilakassa jaṭādhāraṇamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**You don’t deserve the label ‘matted-hair ascetic’ just because you have matted hair.*";
P_HTM[7256]="*Saṅghāṭikassa ce, bhikkhave, saṅghāṭidhāraṇamattena abhijjhālussa abhijjhā pahīyetha, byāpannacittassa byāpādo pahīyetha, kodhanassa kodho pahīyetha, upanāhissa upanāho pahīyetha, makkhissa makkho pahīyetha, paḷāsissa paḷāso pahīyetha, issukissa issā pahīyetha, maccharissa macchariyaṃ pahīyetha, saṭhassa sāṭheyyaṃ pahīyetha, māyāvissa māyā pahīyetha, pāpicchassa pāpikā icchā pahīyetha, micchādiṭṭhikassa micchādiṭṭhi pahīyetha, tamenaṃ mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā jātameva naṃ saṅghāṭikaṃ kareyyuṃ, saṅghāṭikattameva samādapeyyuṃ:**Imagine that just by wearing an outer robe someone with covetousness, ill will, irritability, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deviousness, deceit, bad desires, and wrong view could give up these things. If that were the case, your friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would make you an outer robe wearer as soon as you were born. They’d encourage you:*";
P_HTM[7257]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, bhadramukha, saṅghāṭiko hohi, saṅghāṭikassa te sato saṅghāṭidhāraṇamattena abhijjhālussa abhijjhā pahīyissati, byāpannacittassa byāpādo pahīyissati, kodhanassa kodho pahīyissati, upanāhissa upanāho pahīyissati, makkhissa makkho pahīyissati, paḷāsissa paḷāso pahīyissati, issukissa issā pahīyissati, maccharissa macchariyaṃ pahīyissati, saṭhassa sāṭheyyaṃ pahīyissati, māyāvissa māyā pahīyissati, pāpicchassa pāpikā icchā pahīyissati, micchādiṭṭhikassa micchādiṭṭhi pahīyissatī’ti.**‘Please, my dear, wear an outer robe! By doing so you will give up covetousness, ill will, irritability, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deviousness, deceit, bad desires, and wrong view.’*";
P_HTM[7258]="*Yasmā ca kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅghāṭikampi idhekaccaṃ passāmi abhijjhāluṃ byāpannacittaṃ kodhanaṃ upanāhiṃ makkhiṃ paḷāsiṃ issukiṃ macchariṃ saṭhaṃ māyāviṃ pāpicchaṃ micchādiṭṭhikaṃ, tasmā na saṅghāṭikassa saṅghāṭidhāraṇamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**But sometimes I see someone with these bad qualities who is an outer robe wearer. That’s why I say that you don’t deserve the label ‘outer robe wearer’ just because you wear an outer robe.*";
P_HTM[7259]="*Acelakassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**Imagine that just by going naked …*";
P_HTM[7260]="*rajojallikassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**wearing dust and dirt …*";
P_HTM[7261]="*udakorohakassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**immersing in water …*";
P_HTM[7262]="*rukkhamūlikassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**staying at the root of a tree …*";
P_HTM[7263]="*abbhokāsikassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**staying in the open air …*";
P_HTM[7264]="*ubbhaṭṭhakassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**standing continually …*";
P_HTM[7265]="*pariyāyabhattikassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**eating at set intervals …*";
P_HTM[7266]="*mantajjhāyakassa ce, bhikkhave … pe …**reciting scriptures …*";
P_HTM[7267]="*jaṭilakassa ce, bhikkhave, jaṭādhāraṇamattena abhijjhālussa abhijjhā pahīyetha, byāpannacittassa byāpādo pahīyetha, kodhanassa kodho pahīyetha, upanāhissa upanāho pahīyetha, makkhissa makkho pahīyetha, paḷāsissa paḷāso pahīyetha, issukissa issā pahīyetha, maccharissa macchariyaṃ pahīyetha, saṭhassa sāṭheyyaṃ pahīyetha, māyāvissa māyā pahīyetha, pāpicchassa pāpikā icchā pahīyetha, micchādiṭṭhikassa micchādiṭṭhi pahīyetha, tamenaṃ mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā jātameva naṃ jaṭilakaṃ kareyyuṃ, jaṭilakattameva samādapeyyuṃ:**having matted hair someone with covetousness, ill will, irritability, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deviousness, deceit, bad desires, and wrong view could give up these things. If that were the case, your friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would make you a matted-hair ascetic as soon as you were born. They’d encourage you:*";
P_HTM[7268]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, bhadramukha, jaṭilako hohi, jaṭilakassa te sato jaṭādhāraṇamattena abhijjhālussa abhijjhā pahīyissati byāpannacittassa byāpādo pahīyissati, kodhanassa kodho pahīyissati … pe … pāpicchassa pāpikā icchā pahīyissati micchādiṭṭhikassa micchādiṭṭhi pahīyissatī’ti.**‘Please, my dear, become a matted-hair ascetic! By doing so you will give up covetousness, ill will, irritability, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deviousness, deceit, bad desires, and wrong view.’*";
P_HTM[7269]="*Yasmā ca kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, jaṭilakampi idhekaccaṃ passāmi abhijjhāluṃ byāpannacittaṃ kodhanaṃ upanāhiṃ makkhiṃ palāsiṃ issukiṃ macchariṃ saṭhaṃ māyāviṃ pāpicchaṃ micchādiṭṭhiṃ, tasmā na jaṭilakassa jaṭādhāraṇamattena sāmaññaṃ vadāmi.**But sometimes I see someone with these bad qualities who is a matted-hair ascetic. That’s why I say that you don’t deserve the label ‘matted-hair ascetic’ just because you have matted hair.*";
P_HTM[7270]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti?**And how does a mendicant practice in the way that is proper for an ascetic?*";
P_HTM[7271]="*Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno abhijjhālussa abhijjhā pahīnā hoti, byāpannacittassa byāpādo pahīno hoti, kodhanassa kodho pahīno hoti, upanāhissa upanāho pahīno hoti, makkhissa makkho pahīno hoti, paḷāsissa paḷāso pahīno hoti, issukissa issā pahīnā hoti, maccharissa macchariyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, saṭhassa sāṭheyyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, māyāvissa māyā pahīnā hoti, pāpicchassa pāpikā icchā pahīnā hoti, micchādiṭṭhikassa micchādiṭṭhi pahīnā hoti—**There are some mendicants who have given up covetousness, ill will, irritability, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deviousness, deceit, bad desires, and wrong view.*";
P_HTM[7272]="*imesaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, samaṇamalānaṃ samaṇadosānaṃ samaṇakasaṭānaṃ āpāyikānaṃ ṭhānānaṃ duggativedaniyānaṃ pahānā ‘samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno’ti vadāmi.**These stains, defects, and dregs of an ascetic are grounds for rebirth in places of loss, and are experienced in bad places. When they have given these up, they are practicing in the way that is proper for an ascetic, I say.*";
P_HTM[7273]="*So sabbehi imehi pāpakehi akusalehi dhammehi visuddhamattānaṃ samanupassati ().**They see themselves purified from all these bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7274]="*Tassa sabbehi imehi pāpakehi akusalehi dhammehi visuddhamattānaṃ samanupassato () pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati.**Seeing this, joy springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[7275]="*So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[7276]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[7277]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[7278]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[7279]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā.**Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with smooth banks, delightful.*";
P_HTM[7280]="*Puratthimāya cepi disāya puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito.**Then along comes a person—whether from the east, west, north, or south—struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched.*";
P_HTM[7281]="*So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ āgamma vineyya udakapipāsaṃ vineyya ghammapariḷāhaṃ … pe … pacchimāya cepi disāya puriso āgaccheyya … pe … uttarāya cepi disāya puriso āgaccheyya … pe … dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya puriso āgaccheyya. Yato kuto cepi naṃ puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto, kilanto tasito pipāsito. So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ āgamma vineyya udakapipāsaṃ, vineyya ghammapariḷāhaṃ.**No matter what direction they come from, when they arrive at that lotus pond they would alleviate their thirst and heat exhaustion.*";
P_HTM[7282]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, khattiyakulā cepi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma, evaṃ mettaṃ karuṇaṃ muditaṃ upekkhaṃ bhāvetvā labhati ajjhattaṃ vūpasamaṃ. Ajjhattaṃ vūpasamā ‘samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno’ti vadāmi. Brāhmaṇakulā cepi … pe … vessakulā cepi … pe … suddakulā cepi … pe … yasmā kasmā cepi kulā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma, evaṃ mettaṃ karuṇaṃ muditaṃ upekkhaṃ bhāvetvā labhati ajjhattaṃ vūpasamaṃ.**In the same way, suppose someone has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness—whether from a family of aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, or workers—and has arrived at the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One. Having developed love, compassion, rejoicing, and equanimity in this way they gain inner peace.*";
P_HTM[7283]="*Ajjhattaṃ vūpasamā ‘samaṇasāmīcippaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno’ti vadāmi.**Because of that inner peace they are practicing the way proper for an ascetic, I say.*";
P_HTM[7284]="*Khattiyakulā cepi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti.**And suppose someone has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness—whether from a family of aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, or workers—*";
P_HTM[7285]="*So ca āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**and they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[7286]="*Āsavānaṃ khayā samaṇo hoti. Brāhmaṇakulā cepi … pe … vessakulā cepi … suddakulā cepi … yasmā kasmā cepi kulā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. Āsavānaṃ khayā samaṇo hotī”ti.**They’re an ascetic because of the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[7287]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7288]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7289]="*Cūḷaassapurasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7290]="*Mahāyamakavaggo niṭṭhito catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[7291]="*Giñjakasālavanaṃ pariharituṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7292]="*Paññavato puna saccakanisedho;* **";
P_HTM[7293]="*Mukhavaṇṇapasīdanatāpindo,* **";
P_HTM[7294]="*Kevaṭṭaassapurajaṭilena.* **";
P_HTM[7295]="*41. Sāleyyakasutta**The People of Sālā*";
P_HTM[7296]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7297]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena sālā nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Sālā.*";
P_HTM[7298]="*Assosuṃ kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Sālā heard,*";
P_HTM[7299]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ sālaṃ anuppatto.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—while wandering in the land of the Kosalans has arrived at Sālā, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7300]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[7301]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7302]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[7303]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ;**He proclaims a teaching that is good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, with the right meaning and phrasing.*";
P_HTM[7304]="*kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He reveals an entirely full and pure spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[7305]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[7306]="*Atha kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then the brahmins and householders of Sālā went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. Seated to one side they said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7307]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti?**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell?*";
P_HTM[7308]="*Ko pana, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti?**And what is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm?”*";
P_HTM[7309]="*“Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**“Unprincipled and immoral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7310]="*Dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti.**Principled and moral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”*";
P_HTM[7311]="*“Na kho mayaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāma.**“We don’t understand the detailed meaning of Master Gotama’s brief statement.*";
P_HTM[7312]="*Sādhu no bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu, yathā mayaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, vitthārena atthaṃ ājāneyyāmā”ti.**Master Gotama, please teach us this matter in detail so we can understand the meaning.”*";
P_HTM[7313]="*“Tena hi, gahapatayo, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, householders, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[7314]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7315]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7316]="*“Tividhaṃ kho, gahapatayo, kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**“Householders, unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body, fourfold by way of speech, and threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[7317]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti?**And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct threefold by way of body?*";
P_HTM[7318]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, luddo lohitapāṇi hatappahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu.**It’s when a certain person kills living creatures. They’re violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[7319]="*Adinnādāyī kho pana hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ, gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti.**They steal. With the intention to commit theft, they take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[7320]="*Kāmesumicchācārī kho pana hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā piturakkhitā mātāpiturakkhitā bhāturakkhitā bhaginirakkhitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sassāmikā saparidaṇḍā antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti.**They commit sexual misconduct. They have sexual relations with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They have sexual relations with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal.*";
P_HTM[7321]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**This is how unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body.*";
P_HTM[7322]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti?**And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct fourfold by way of speech?*";
P_HTM[7323]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco musāvādī hoti. Sabhāgato vā parisāgato vā, ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā, abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: na jānāmī’ti, ‘apassaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti. Iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti.**It’s when a certain person lies. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ So they deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason.*";
P_HTM[7324]="*Pisuṇavāco kho pana hoti. Ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti samaggānaṃ vā bhettā, bhinnānaṃ vā anuppadātā, vaggārāmo vaggarato vagganandī vaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They speak divisively. They repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. And so they divide those who are harmonious, supporting division, delighting in division, loving division, speaking words that promote division.*";
P_HTM[7325]="*Pharusavāco kho pana hoti. Yā sā vācā aṇḍakā kakkasā parakaṭukā parābhisajjanī kodhasāmantā asamādhisaṃvattanikā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They speak harshly. They use the kinds of words that are cruel, nasty, hurtful, offensive, bordering on anger, not leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[7326]="*Samphappalāpī kho pana hoti. Akālavādī abhūtavādī anatthavādī adhammavādī avinayavādī. Anidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti akālena anapadesaṃ apariyantavatiṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ.**They talk nonsense. Their speech is untimely, and is neither factual nor beneficial. It has nothing to do with the teaching or the training. Their words have no value, and are untimely, unreasonable, rambling, and pointless.*";
P_HTM[7327]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**This is how unprincipled and immoral conduct is fourfold by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[7328]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti?**And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct threefold by way of mind?*";
P_HTM[7329]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ abhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti.**It's when a certain person is covetous. They covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’*";
P_HTM[7330]="*Byāpannacitto kho pana hoti paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā vajjhantu vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā ahesun’ti.**They have ill will and hateful intentions: ‘May these sentient beings be killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or annihilated!’*";
P_HTM[7331]="*Micchādiṭṭhiko kho pana hoti viparītadassano:**They have wrong view. Their perspective is distorted:*";
P_HTM[7332]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ natthi yiṭṭhaṃ natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko natthi paro loko, natthi mātā natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.**‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[7333]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**This is how unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[7334]="*Evaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**That’s how unprincipled and immoral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7335]="*Tividhaṃ kho, gahapatayo, kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**Householders, principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of body, fourfold by way of speech, and threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[7336]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti?**And how is principled and moral conduct threefold by way of body?*";
P_HTM[7337]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**It’s when a certain person gives up killing living creatures. They renounce the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[7338]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ, gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, taṃ nādinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti.**They give up stealing. They don’t, with the intention to commit theft, take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[7339]="*Kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā piturakkhitā mātāpiturakkhitā bhāturakkhitā bhaginirakkhitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sassāmikā saparidaṇḍā antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu na cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti.**They give up sexual misconduct. They don’t have sexual relations with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They don’t have sexual relations with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal.*";
P_HTM[7340]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**This is how principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of body.*";
P_HTM[7341]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti?**And how is principled and moral conduct fourfold by way of speech?*";
P_HTM[7342]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti. Sabhāgato vā parisāgato vā, ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā, abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti. Iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā na sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti.**It’s when a certain person gives up lying. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I see.’ So they don’t deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason.*";
P_HTM[7343]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[7344]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā—tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable, and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[7345]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti. Kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[7346]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**This is how principled and moral conduct is fourfold by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[7347]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti?**And how is principled and moral conduct threefold by way of mind?*";
P_HTM[7348]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ nābhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti.**It's when a certain person is not covetous. They don’t covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’*";
P_HTM[7349]="*Abyāpannacitto kho pana hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā abyābajjhā anīghā sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti.**They have a kind heart and loving intentions: ‘May these sentient beings live free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy!’*";
P_HTM[7350]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko kho pana hoti aviparītadassano:**They have right view, an undistorted perspective:*";
P_HTM[7351]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ atthi yiṭṭhaṃ atthi hutaṃ, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, atthi ayaṃ loko atthi paro loko, atthi mātā atthi pitā, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.**‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There is obligation to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[7352]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**This is how principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[7353]="*Evaṃ dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**This is how principled and moral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7354]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:**A person of principled and moral conduct might wish:*";
P_HTM[7355]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of well-to-do aristocrats!’*";
P_HTM[7356]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.**It’s possible that this might happen.*";
P_HTM[7357]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[7358]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.**Because they have principled and moral conduct.*";
P_HTM[7359]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:**A person of principled and moral conduct might wish:*";
P_HTM[7360]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ … pe …**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of well-to-do brahmins …*";
P_HTM[7361]="*gahapatimahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;**well-to-do householders …*";
P_HTM[7362]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7363]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7364]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7365]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7366]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;**the Gods of the Four Great Kings …*";
P_HTM[7367]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7368]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7369]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7370]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7371]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tāvatiṃsānaṃ devānaṃ … pe …**the Gods of the Thirty-Three …*";
P_HTM[7372]="*yāmānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Yama …*";
P_HTM[7373]="*tusitānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Joyful Gods …*";
P_HTM[7374]="*nimmānaratīnaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods Who Love to Create …*";
P_HTM[7375]="*paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others …*";
P_HTM[7376]="*brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;**the Gods of Brahmā’s Host …*";
P_HTM[7377]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7378]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7379]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7380]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7381]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā ābhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;**the Radiant Gods …*";
P_HTM[7382]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā ābhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7383]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7384]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7385]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7386]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parittābhānaṃ devānaṃ … pe …**the Gods of Limited Radiance …*";
P_HTM[7387]="*appamāṇābhānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Limitless Radiance …*";
P_HTM[7388]="*ābhassarānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Streaming Radiance …*";
P_HTM[7389]="*parittasubhānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Limited Glory …*";
P_HTM[7390]="*appamāṇasubhānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Limitless Glory …*";
P_HTM[7391]="*subhakiṇhānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods Replete with Glory …*";
P_HTM[7392]="*vehapphalānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Abundant Fruit …*";
P_HTM[7393]="*avihānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Aviha …*";
P_HTM[7394]="*atappānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Atappa …*";
P_HTM[7395]="*sudassānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods Fair to See …*";
P_HTM[7396]="*sudassīnaṃ devānaṃ …**the Fair Seeing Gods …*";
P_HTM[7397]="*akaniṭṭhānaṃ devānaṃ …**the Gods of Akaniṭṭha …*";
P_HTM[7398]="*ākāsānañcāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ …**the gods of the dimension of infinite space …*";
P_HTM[7399]="*viññāṇañcāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ …**the gods of the dimension of infinite consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7400]="*ākiñcaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ …**the gods of the dimension of nothingness …*";
P_HTM[7401]="*nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;**the gods of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’*";
P_HTM[7402]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.**It’s possible that this might happen.*";
P_HTM[7403]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[7404]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.**Because they have principled and moral conduct.*";
P_HTM[7405]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:**A person of principled and moral conduct might wish:*";
P_HTM[7406]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti;**‘If only I might realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[7407]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya.**It’s possible that this might happen.*";
P_HTM[7408]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[7409]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī”ti.**Because they have principled and moral conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7410]="*Evaṃ vutte, sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Sālā said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7411]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[7412]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[7413]="*Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[7414]="*Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[7415]="*Sāleyyakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7416]="*42. Verañjakasutta**The People of Verañja*";
P_HTM[7417]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7418]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7419]="*Tena kho pana samayena verañjakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time the brahmins and householders of Verañja were residing in Sāvatthī on some business.*";
P_HTM[7420]="*Assosuṃ kho verañjakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Verañja heard:*";
P_HTM[7421]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—is staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7422]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation …” …*";
P_HTM[7423]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’.* **";
P_HTM[7424]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.* **";
P_HTM[7425]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ; kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.* **";
P_HTM[7426]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7427]="*Atha kho verañjakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho verañjakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7428]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti?* **";
P_HTM[7429]="*Ko pana, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7430]="*“Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[7431]="*Dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7432]="*“Na kho mayaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāma.* **";
P_HTM[7433]="*Sādhu no bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā mayaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, vitthārena atthaṃ ājāneyyāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7434]="*“Tena hi, gahapatayo, suṇātha sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7435]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho verañjakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavato paccassosuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7436]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[7437]="*“Tividhaṃ kho, gahapatayo, kāyena adhammacārī visamacārī hoti, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacārī visamacārī hoti, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacārī visamacārī hoti.**“Householders, a person of unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body, fourfold by way of speech, and threefold by way of mind. …” …*";
P_HTM[7438]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena adhammacārī visamacārī hoti?**(The remainder of this discourse is identical with MN 41.)*";
P_HTM[7439]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti. Luddo lohitapāṇi hatappahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu.* **";
P_HTM[7440]="*Adinnādāyī kho pana hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ … taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7441]="*Kāmesumicchācārī kho pana hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā … tathārūpāsu cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7442]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena adhammacārī visamacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7443]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacārī visamacārī hoti?* **";
P_HTM[7444]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco musāvādī hoti. Sabhāgato vā … sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7445]="*Pisuṇavāco kho pana hoti. Ito sutvā amutra akkhātā … vaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7446]="*Pharusavāco kho pana hoti. Yā sā vācā aṇḍakā kakkasā … tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7447]="*Samphappalāpī kho pana hoti. Akālavādī … apariyantavatiṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7448]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya adhammacārī visamacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7449]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacārī visamacārī hoti?* **";
P_HTM[7450]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti … pe … taṃ mamassā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7451]="*Byāpannacitto kho pana hoti paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā … mā vā ahesun’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7452]="*Micchādiṭṭhiko kho pana hoti viparītadassano:* **";
P_HTM[7453]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ … sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7454]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā adhammacārī visamacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7455]="*Evaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[7456]="*Tividhaṃ kho, gahapatayo, kāyena dhammacārī samacārī hoti, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacārī samacārī hoti, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacārī samacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7457]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena dhammacārī samacārī hoti?* **";
P_HTM[7458]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.* **";
P_HTM[7459]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa … taṃ nādinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7460]="*Kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya … tathārūpāsu na cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7461]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ kāyena dhammacārī samacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7462]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacārī samacārī hoti?* **";
P_HTM[7463]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti. Sabhāgato vā … pe … na sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7464]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya … samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7465]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya … tathārūpaṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7466]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya … kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7467]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, catubbidhaṃ vācāya dhammacārī samacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7468]="*Kathañca, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacārī samacārī hoti?* **";
P_HTM[7469]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ nābhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa, taṃ mamassā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7470]="*Abyāpannacitto kho pana hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā abyābajjhā anīghā sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7471]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko kho pana hoti aviparītadassano:* **";
P_HTM[7472]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ … sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7473]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapatayo, tividhaṃ manasā dhammacārī samacārī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7474]="*Evaṃ dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, gahapatayo, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[7475]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7476]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7477]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7478]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7479]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7480]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7481]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7482]="*gahapatimahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7483]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7484]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7485]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7486]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7487]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7488]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7489]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7490]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7491]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7492]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tāvatiṃsānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7493]="*yāmānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7494]="*tusitānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7495]="*nimmānaratīnaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7496]="*paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7497]="*brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7498]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7499]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7500]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7501]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7502]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā ābhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7503]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā ābhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7504]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7505]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7506]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7507]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parittābhānaṃ devānaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7508]="*appamāṇābhānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7509]="*ābhassarānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7510]="*parittasubhānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7511]="*appamāṇasubhānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7512]="*subhakiṇhānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7513]="*vehapphalānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7514]="*avihānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7515]="*atappānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7516]="*sudassānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7517]="*sudassīnaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7518]="*akaniṭṭhānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7519]="*ākāsānañcāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7520]="*viññāṇañcāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7521]="*ākiñcaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[7522]="*nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7523]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7524]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7525]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī.* **";
P_HTM[7526]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, gahapatayo, dhammacārī samacārī:* **";
P_HTM[7527]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7528]="*ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, ‘yaṃ so āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya.* **";
P_HTM[7529]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7530]="*Tathā hi so dhammacārī samacārī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7531]="*Evaṃ vutte, verañjakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7532]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.* **";
P_HTM[7533]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.* **";
P_HTM[7534]="*Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.* **";
P_HTM[7535]="*Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7536]="*Verañjakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7537]="*43. Mahāvedallasutta**The Great Classification*";
P_HTM[7538]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7539]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7540]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita came out of retreat, went to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7541]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[7542]="*“‘Duppañño duppañño’ti, āvuso, vuccati.**“Reverend, they speak of ‘a witless person’.*";
P_HTM[7543]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, duppaññoti vuccatī”ti?**How is a witless person defined?”*";
P_HTM[7544]="*“‘Nappajānāti nappajānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā duppaññoti vuccati.**“Reverend, they’re called witless because they don’t understand.*";
P_HTM[7545]="*Kiñca nappajānāti?**And what don’t they understand?*";
P_HTM[7546]="*‘Idaṃ dukkhan’ti nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti nappajānāti.**They don’t understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[7547]="*‘Nappajānāti nappajānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā duppaññoti vuccatī”ti.**They’re called witless because they don’t understand.”*";
P_HTM[7548]="*“Sādhāvuso”ti kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi:**Saying “Good, reverend,” Mahākoṭṭhita approved and agreed with what Sāriputta said. Then he asked another question:*";
P_HTM[7549]="*“‘Paññavā paññavā’ti, āvuso, vuccati.**“They speak of ‘a wise person’.*";
P_HTM[7550]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, paññavāti vuccatī”ti?**How is a wise person defined?”*";
P_HTM[7551]="*“‘Pajānāti pajānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā paññavāti vuccati.**“They’re called wise because they understand.*";
P_HTM[7552]="*Kiñca pajānāti?**And what do they understand?*";
P_HTM[7553]="*‘Idaṃ dukkhan’ti pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[7554]="*‘Pajānāti pajānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā paññavāti vuccatī”ti.**They’re called wise because they understand.”*";
P_HTM[7555]="*“‘Viññāṇaṃ viññāṇan’ti, āvuso, vuccati.**“They speak of ‘consciousness’.*";
P_HTM[7556]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, viññāṇanti vuccatī”ti?**How is consciousness defined?”*";
P_HTM[7557]="*“‘Vijānāti vijānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā viññāṇanti vuccati.**“It’s called consciousness because it cognizes.*";
P_HTM[7558]="*Kiñca vijānāti?**And what does it cognize?*";
P_HTM[7559]="*Sukhantipi vijānāti, dukkhantipi vijānāti, adukkhamasukhantipi vijānāti.**It cognizes ‘pleasure’ and ‘pain’ and ‘neutral’.*";
P_HTM[7560]="*‘Vijānāti vijānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā viññāṇanti vuccatī”ti.**It’s called consciousness because it cognizes.”*";
P_HTM[7561]="*“Yā cāvuso, paññā yañca viññāṇaṃ—**“Wisdom and consciousness—*";
P_HTM[7562]="*ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā udāhu visaṃsaṭṭhā?**are these things mixed or separate?*";
P_HTM[7563]="*Labbhā ca panimesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetun”ti?**And can we completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them?”*";
P_HTM[7564]="*“Yā cāvuso, paññā yañca viññāṇaṃ—**“Wisdom and consciousness—*";
P_HTM[7565]="*ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā, no visaṃsaṭṭhā.**these things are mixed, not separate.*";
P_HTM[7566]="*Na ca labbhā imesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetuṃ.**And you can never completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them.*";
P_HTM[7567]="*Yaṃ hāvuso, pajānāti taṃ vijānāti, yaṃ vijānāti taṃ pajānāti.**For you understand what you cognize, and you cognize what you understand.*";
P_HTM[7568]="*Tasmā ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā, no visaṃsaṭṭhā.**That’s why these things are mixed, not separate.*";
P_HTM[7569]="*Na ca labbhā imesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetun”ti.**And you can never completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[7570]="*“Yā cāvuso, paññā yañca viññāṇaṃ—**“Wisdom and consciousness—*";
P_HTM[7571]="*imesaṃ dhammānaṃ saṃsaṭṭhānaṃ no visaṃsaṭṭhānaṃ kiṃ nānākaraṇan”ti?**what is the difference between these things that are mixed, not separate?”*";
P_HTM[7572]="*“Yā cāvuso, paññā yañca viññāṇaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[7573]="*imesaṃ dhammānaṃ saṃsaṭṭhānaṃ no visaṃsaṭṭhānaṃ paññā bhāvetabbā, viññāṇaṃ pariññeyyaṃ.**“The difference between these things is that wisdom should be developed, while consciousness should be completely understood.”*";
P_HTM[7574]="*Idaṃ nesaṃ nānākaraṇan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7575]="*“‘Vedanā vedanā’ti, āvuso, vuccati.**“They speak of this thing called ‘feeling’.*";
P_HTM[7576]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, vedanāti vuccatī”ti?**How is feeling defined?”*";
P_HTM[7577]="*“‘Vedeti vedetī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā vedanāti vuccati.**“It’s called feeling because it feels.*";
P_HTM[7578]="*Kiñca vedeti?**And what does it feel?*";
P_HTM[7579]="*Sukhampi vedeti, dukkhampi vedeti, adukkhamasukhampi vedeti.**It feels pleasure, pain, and neutral.*";
P_HTM[7580]="*‘Vedeti vedetī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā vedanāti vuccatī”ti.**It’s called feeling because it feels.”*";
P_HTM[7581]="*“‘Saññā saññā’ti, āvuso, vuccati.**“They speak of this thing called ‘perception’.*";
P_HTM[7582]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, saññāti vuccatī”ti?**How is perception defined?”*";
P_HTM[7583]="*“‘Sañjānāti sañjānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā saññāti vuccati.**“It’s called perception because it perceives.*";
P_HTM[7584]="*Kiñca sañjānāti?**And what does it perceive?*";
P_HTM[7585]="*Nīlakampi sañjānāti, pītakampi sañjānāti, lohitakampi sañjānāti, odātampi sañjānāti.**It perceives blue, yellow, red, and white.*";
P_HTM[7586]="*‘Sañjānāti sañjānātī’ti kho, āvuso, tasmā saññāti vuccatī”ti.**It’s called perception because it perceives.”*";
P_HTM[7587]="*“Yā cāvuso, vedanā yā ca saññā yañca viññāṇaṃ—**“Feeling, perception, and consciousness—*";
P_HTM[7588]="*ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā udāhu visaṃsaṭṭhā?**are these things mixed or separate?*";
P_HTM[7589]="*Labbhā ca panimesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetun”ti?**And can we completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them?”*";
P_HTM[7590]="*“Yā cāvuso, vedanā yā ca saññā yañca viññāṇaṃ—**“Feeling, perception, and consciousness—*";
P_HTM[7591]="*ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā, no visaṃsaṭṭhā.**these things are mixed, not separate.*";
P_HTM[7592]="*Na ca labbhā imesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetuṃ.**And you can never completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them.*";
P_HTM[7593]="*Yaṃ hāvuso, vedeti taṃ sañjānāti, yaṃ sañjānāti taṃ vijānāti.**For you perceive what you feel, and you cognize what you perceive.*";
P_HTM[7594]="*Tasmā ime dhammā saṃsaṭṭhā no visaṃsaṭṭhā.**That’s why these things are mixed, not separate.*";
P_HTM[7595]="*Na ca labbhā imesaṃ dhammānaṃ vinibbhujitvā vinibbhujitvā nānākaraṇaṃ paññāpetun”ti.**And you can never completely dissect them so as to describe the difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[7596]="*“Nissaṭṭhena hāvuso, pañcahi indriyehi parisuddhena manoviññāṇena kiṃ neyyan”ti?**“What can be known by purified mind consciousness released from the five senses?”*";
P_HTM[7597]="*“Nissaṭṭhena, āvuso, pañcahi indriyehi parisuddhena manoviññāṇena ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ neyyaṃ, ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ neyyaṃ, ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ neyyan”ti.**“Aware that ‘space is infinite’ it can know the dimension of infinite space. Aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’ it can know the dimension of infinite consciousness. Aware that ‘there is nothing at all’ it can know the dimension of nothingness.”*";
P_HTM[7598]="*“Neyyaṃ panāvuso, dhammaṃ kena pajānātī”ti?**“How do you understand something that can be known?”*";
P_HTM[7599]="*“Neyyaṃ kho, āvuso, dhammaṃ paññācakkhunā pajānātī”ti.**“You understand something that can be known with the eye of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[7600]="*“Paññā panāvuso, kimatthiyā”ti?**“What is the purpose of wisdom?”*";
P_HTM[7601]="*“Paññā kho, āvuso, abhiññatthā pariññatthā pahānatthā”ti.**“The purpose of wisdom is direct knowledge, complete understanding, and giving up.”*";
P_HTM[7602]="*“Kati panāvuso, paccayā sammādiṭṭhiyā uppādāyā”ti?**“How many conditions are there for the arising of right view?”*";
P_HTM[7603]="*“Dve kho, āvuso, paccayā sammādiṭṭhiyā uppādāya—**“There are two conditions for the arising of right view:*";
P_HTM[7604]="*parato ca ghoso, yoniso ca manasikāro.**the words of another and proper attention.*";
P_HTM[7605]="*Ime kho, āvuso, dve paccayā sammādiṭṭhiyā uppādāyā”ti.**These are the two conditions for the arising of right view.”*";
P_HTM[7606]="*“Katihi panāvuso, aṅgehi anuggahitā sammādiṭṭhi cetovimuttiphalā ca hoti cetovimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca, paññāvimuttiphalā ca hoti paññāvimuttiphalānisaṃsā cā”ti?**“When right view is supported by how many factors does it have freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom as its fruit and benefit?”*";
P_HTM[7607]="*“Pañcahi kho, āvuso, aṅgehi anuggahitā sammādiṭṭhi cetovimuttiphalā ca hoti cetovimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca, paññāvimuttiphalā ca hoti paññāvimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca.**“When right view is supported by five factors it has freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom as its fruit and benefit.*";
P_HTM[7608]="*Idhāvuso, sammādiṭṭhi sīlānuggahitā ca hoti, sutānuggahitā ca hoti, sākacchānuggahitā ca hoti, samathānuggahitā ca hoti, vipassanānuggahitā ca hoti.**It’s when right view is supported by ethics, learning, discussion, serenity, and discernment.*";
P_HTM[7609]="*Imehi kho, āvuso, pañcahaṅgehi anuggahitā sammādiṭṭhi cetovimuttiphalā ca hoti cetovimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca, paññāvimuttiphalā ca hoti paññāvimuttiphalānisaṃsā cā”ti.**When right view is supported by these five factors it has freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom as its fruit and benefit.”*";
P_HTM[7610]="*“Kati panāvuso, bhavā”ti?**“How many states of existence are there?”*";
P_HTM[7611]="*“Tayome, āvuso, bhavā—**“Reverend, there are these three states of existence.*";
P_HTM[7612]="*kāmabhavo, rūpabhavo, arūpabhavo”ti.**Existence in the sensual realm, the realm of luminous form, and the formless realm.”*";
P_HTM[7613]="*“Kathaṃ panāvuso, āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti hotī”ti?**“But how is there rebirth into a new state of existence in the future?”*";
P_HTM[7614]="*“Avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ kho, āvuso, sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ tatratatrābhinandanā—**“It’s because of sentient beings—hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving—taking pleasure in various different realms.*";
P_HTM[7615]="*evaṃ āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti hotī”ti.**That’s how there is rebirth into a new state of existence in the future.”*";
P_HTM[7616]="*“Kathaṃ panāvuso, āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti na hotī”ti?**“But how is there no rebirth into a new state of existence in the future?”*";
P_HTM[7617]="*“Avijjāvirāgā kho, āvuso, vijjuppādā taṇhānirodhā—**“It’s when ignorance fades away, knowledge arises, and craving ceases.*";
P_HTM[7618]="*evaṃ āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti na hotī”ti.**That’s how there is no rebirth into a new state of existence in the future.”*";
P_HTM[7619]="*“Katamaṃ panāvuso, paṭhamaṃ jhānan”ti?**“But what, reverend, is the first absorption?”*";
P_HTM[7620]="*“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati—**“Reverend, it’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[7621]="*idaṃ vuccati, āvuso, paṭhamaṃ jhānan”ti.**This is called the first absorption.”*";
P_HTM[7622]="*“Paṭhamaṃ panāvuso, jhānaṃ katiaṅgikan”ti?**“But how many factors does the first absorption have?”*";
P_HTM[7623]="*“Paṭhamaṃ kho, āvuso, jhānaṃ pañcaṅgikaṃ.**“The first absorption has five factors.*";
P_HTM[7624]="*Idhāvuso, paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa bhikkhuno vitakko ca vattati, vicāro ca pīti ca sukhañca cittekaggatā ca.**When a mendicant has entered the first absorption, placing the mind, keeping it connected, rapture, bliss, and unification of mind are present.*";
P_HTM[7625]="*Paṭhamaṃ kho, āvuso, jhānaṃ evaṃ pañcaṅgikan”ti.**That’s how the first absorption has five factors.”*";
P_HTM[7626]="*“Paṭhamaṃ panāvuso, jhānaṃ kataṅgavippahīnaṃ kataṅgasamannāgatan”ti?**“But how many factors has the first absorption given up and how many does it possess?”*";
P_HTM[7627]="*“Paṭhamaṃ kho, āvuso, jhānaṃ pañcaṅgavippahīnaṃ, pañcaṅgasamannāgataṃ.**“The first absorption has given up five factors and possesses five factors.*";
P_HTM[7628]="*Idhāvuso, paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa bhikkhuno kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā hoti;**When a mendicant has entered the first absorption, sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt are given up.*";
P_HTM[7629]="*vitakko ca vattati, vicāro ca pīti ca sukhañca cittekaggatā ca.**Placing the mind, keeping it connected, rapture, bliss, and unification of mind are present.*";
P_HTM[7630]="*Paṭhamaṃ kho, āvuso, jhānaṃ evaṃ pañcaṅgavippahīnaṃ pañcaṅgasamannāgatan”ti.**That’s how the first absorption has given up five factors and possesses five factors.”*";
P_HTM[7631]="*“Pañcimāni, āvuso, indriyāni nānāvisayāni nānāgocarāni, na aññamaññassa gocaravisayaṃ paccanubhonti, seyyathidaṃ—**“Reverend, these five faculties have different scopes and different ranges, and don’t experience each others’ scope and range. That is,*";
P_HTM[7632]="*cakkhundriyaṃ, sotindriyaṃ, ghānindriyaṃ, jivhindriyaṃ, kāyindriyaṃ.**the faculties of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, and body.*";
P_HTM[7633]="*Imesaṃ kho, āvuso, pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ nānāvisayānaṃ nānāgocarānaṃ, na aññamaññassa gocaravisayaṃ paccanubhontānaṃ, kiṃ paṭisaraṇaṃ, ko ca nesaṃ gocaravisayaṃ paccanubhotī”ti?**What do these five faculties, with their different scopes and ranges, have recourse to? What experiences their scopes and ranges?”*";
P_HTM[7634]="*“Pañcimāni, āvuso, indriyāni nānāvisayāni nānāgocarāni, na aññamaññassa gocaravisayaṃ paccanubhonti, seyyathidaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[7635]="*cakkhundriyaṃ, sotindriyaṃ, ghānindriyaṃ, jivhindriyaṃ, kāyindriyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7636]="*Imesaṃ kho, āvuso, pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ nānāvisayānaṃ nānāgocarānaṃ, na aññamaññassa gocaravisayaṃ paccanubhontānaṃ, mano paṭisaraṇaṃ, mano ca nesaṃ gocaravisayaṃ paccanubhotī”ti.**“These five faculties, with their different scopes and ranges, have recourse to the mind. And the mind experiences their scopes and ranges.”*";
P_HTM[7637]="*“Pañcimāni, āvuso, indriyāni, seyyathidaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[7638]="*cakkhundriyaṃ, sotindriyaṃ, ghānindriyaṃ, jivhindriyaṃ, kāyindriyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7639]="*Imāni kho, āvuso, pañcindriyāni kiṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhantī”ti?**“These five faculties depend on what to continue?”*";
P_HTM[7640]="*“Pañcimāni, āvuso, indriyāni, seyyathidaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[7641]="*cakkhundriyaṃ, sotindriyaṃ, ghānindriyaṃ, jivhindriyaṃ, kāyindriyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7642]="*Imāni kho, āvuso, pañcindriyāni āyuṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhantī”ti.**“These five faculties depend on life to continue.”*";
P_HTM[7643]="*“Āyu panāvuso, kiṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī”ti?**“But what does life depend on to continue?”*";
P_HTM[7644]="*“Āyu usmaṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī”ti.**“Life depends on warmth to continue.”*";
P_HTM[7645]="*“Usmā panāvuso, kiṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī”ti?**“But what does warmth depend on to continue?”*";
P_HTM[7646]="*“Usmā āyuṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī”ti.**“Warmth depends on life to continue.”*";
P_HTM[7647]="*“Idāneva kho mayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ evaṃ ājānāma:**“Just now I understood you to say:*";
P_HTM[7648]="*‘āyu usmaṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī’ti.**‘Life depends on warmth to continue.’*";
P_HTM[7649]="*Idāneva pana mayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ evaṃ ājānāma:**But I also understood you to say:*";
P_HTM[7650]="*‘usmā āyuṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī’ti.**‘Warmth depends on life to continue.’*";
P_HTM[7651]="*Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[7652]="*“Tena hāvuso, upamaṃ te karissāmi;**“Well then, reverend, I shall give you a simile.*";
P_HTM[7653]="*upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti.**For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said.*";
P_HTM[7654]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, telappadīpassa jhāyato acciṃ paṭicca ābhā paññāyati, ābhaṃ paṭicca acci paññāyati;**Suppose there was an oil lamp burning. The light appears dependent on the flame, and the flame appears dependent on the light.*";
P_HTM[7655]="*evameva kho, āvuso, āyu usmaṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhati, usmā āyuṃ paṭicca tiṭṭhatī”ti.**In the same way, life depends on warmth to continue, and warmth depends on life to continue.”*";
P_HTM[7656]="*“Teva nu kho, āvuso, āyusaṅkhārā, te vedaniyā dhammā udāhu aññe āyusaṅkhārā aññe vedaniyā dhammā”ti?**“Are the life forces the same things as the phenomena that are felt? Or are they different things?”*";
P_HTM[7657]="*“Na kho, āvuso, teva āyusaṅkhārā te vedaniyā dhammā.**“The life forces are not the same things as the phenomena that are felt.*";
P_HTM[7658]="*Te ca hāvuso, āyusaṅkhārā abhaviṃsu te vedaniyā dhammā, na yidaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa bhikkhuno vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyetha.**For if the life forces and the phenomena that are felt were the same things, a mendicant who had attained the cessation of perception and feeling would not emerge from it.*";
P_HTM[7659]="*Yasmā ca kho, āvuso, aññe āyusaṅkhārā aññe vedaniyā dhammā, tasmā saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa bhikkhuno vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyatī”ti.**But because the life forces and the phenomena that are felt are different things, a mendicant who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling can emerge from it.”*";
P_HTM[7660]="*“Yadā nu kho, āvuso, imaṃ kāyaṃ kati dhammā jahanti; athāyaṃ kāyo ujjhito avakkhitto seti, yathā kaṭṭhaṃ acetanan”ti?**“How many things must this body lose before it lies forsaken, tossed aside like an insentient log?”*";
P_HTM[7661]="*“Yadā kho, āvuso, imaṃ kāyaṃ tayo dhammā jahanti—āyu usmā ca viññāṇaṃ; athāyaṃ kāyo ujjhito avakkhitto seti, yathā kaṭṭhaṃ acetanan”ti.**“This body must lose three things before it lies forsaken, tossed aside like an insentient log: vitality, warmth, and consciousness.”*";
P_HTM[7662]="*“Yvāyaṃ, āvuso, mato kālaṅkato, yo cāyaṃ bhikkhu saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno—imesaṃ kiṃ nānākaraṇan”ti?**“What’s the difference between someone who has passed away and a mendicant who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling?”*";
P_HTM[7663]="*“Yvāyaṃ, āvuso, mato kālaṅkato tassa kāyasaṅkhārā niruddhā paṭippassaddhā, vacīsaṅkhārā niruddhā paṭippassaddhā, cittasaṅkhārā niruddhā paṭippassaddhā, āyu parikkhīṇo, usmā vūpasantā, indriyāni paribhinnāni.**“When someone dies, their physical, verbal, and mental processes have ceased and stilled; their vitality is spent; their warmth is dissipated; and their faculties have disintegrated.*";
P_HTM[7664]="*Yo cāyaṃ bhikkhu saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno tassapi kāyasaṅkhārā niruddhā paṭippassaddhā, vacīsaṅkhārā niruddhā paṭippassaddhā, cittasaṅkhārā niruddhā paṭippassaddhā, āyu na parikkhīṇo, usmā avūpasantā, indriyāni vippasannāni.**When a mendicant has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, their physical, verbal, and mental processes have ceased and stilled. But their vitality is not spent; their warmth is not dissipated; and their faculties are very clear.*";
P_HTM[7665]="*Yvāyaṃ, āvuso, mato kālaṅkato, yo cāyaṃ bhikkhu saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno—idaṃ nesaṃ nānākaraṇan”ti.**That’s the difference between someone who has passed away and a mendicant who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7666]="*“Kati panāvuso, paccayā adukkhamasukhāya cetovimuttiyā samāpattiyā”ti?**“How many conditions are necessary to attain the neutral release of the heart?”*";
P_HTM[7667]="*“Cattāro kho, āvuso, paccayā adukkhamasukhāya cetovimuttiyā samāpattiyā.**“Four conditions are necessary to attain the neutral release of the heart.*";
P_HTM[7668]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[7669]="*Ime kho, āvuso, cattāro paccayā adukkhamasukhāya cetovimuttiyā samāpattiyā”ti.**These four conditions are necessary to attain the neutral release of the heart.”*";
P_HTM[7670]="*“Kati panāvuso, paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā samāpattiyā”ti?**“How many conditions are necessary to attain the signless release of the heart?”*";
P_HTM[7671]="*“Dve kho, āvuso, paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā samāpattiyā—**“Two conditions are necessary to attain the signless release of the heart:*";
P_HTM[7672]="*sabbanimittānañca amanasikāro, animittāya ca dhātuyā manasikāro.**not focusing on any signs, and focusing on the signless.*";
P_HTM[7673]="*Ime kho, āvuso, dve paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā samāpattiyā”ti.**These two conditions are necessary to attain the signless release of the heart.”*";
P_HTM[7674]="*“Kati panāvuso, paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā ṭhitiyā”ti?**“How many conditions are necessary to remain in the signless release of the heart?”*";
P_HTM[7675]="*“Tayo kho, āvuso, paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā ṭhitiyā—**“Three conditions are necessary to remain in the signless release of the heart:*";
P_HTM[7676]="*sabbanimittānañca amanasikāro, animittāya ca dhātuyā manasikāro, pubbe ca abhisaṅkhāro.**not focusing on any signs, focusing on the signless, and a previous determination.*";
P_HTM[7677]="*Ime kho, āvuso, tayo paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā ṭhitiyā”ti.**These three conditions are necessary to remain in the signless release of the heart.”*";
P_HTM[7678]="*“Kati panāvuso, paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā vuṭṭhānāyā”ti?**“How many conditions are necessary to emerge from the signless release of the heart?”*";
P_HTM[7679]="*“Dve kho, āvuso, paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā vuṭṭhānāya—**“Two conditions are necessary to emerge from the signless release of the heart:*";
P_HTM[7680]="*sabbanimittānañca manasikāro, animittāya ca dhātuyā amanasikāro.**focusing on all signs, and not focusing on the signless.*";
P_HTM[7681]="*Ime kho, āvuso, dve paccayā animittāya cetovimuttiyā vuṭṭhānāyā”ti.**These two conditions are necessary to emerge from the signless release of the heart.”*";
P_HTM[7682]="*“Yā cāyaṃ, āvuso, appamāṇā cetovimutti, yā ca ākiñcaññā cetovimutti, yā ca suññatā cetovimutti, yā ca animittā cetovimutti—ime dhammā nānātthā ceva nānābyañjanā ca udāhu ekatthā byañjanameva nānan”ti?**“The limitless heart’s release, and the heart’s release through nothingness, and the heart’s release through emptiness, and the signless heart’s release: do these things differ in both meaning and phrasing? Or do they mean the same thing, and differ only in the phrasing?”*";
P_HTM[7683]="*“Yā cāyaṃ, āvuso, appamāṇā cetovimutti, yā ca ākiñcaññā cetovimutti, yā ca suññatā cetovimutti, yā ca animittā cetovimutti—atthi kho, āvuso, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma ime dhammā nānātthā ceva nānābyañjanā ca;**“There is a way in which these things differ in both meaning and phrasing.*";
P_HTM[7684]="*atthi ca kho, āvuso, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma ime dhammā ekatthā, byañjanameva nānaṃ.**But there’s also a way in which they mean the same thing, and differ only in the phrasing.*";
P_HTM[7685]="*Katamo cāvuso, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma ime dhammā nānātthā ceva nānābyañjanā ca?**And what’s the way in which these things differ in both meaning and phrasing?*";
P_HTM[7686]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**Firstly, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[7687]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[7688]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …**They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[7689]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[7690]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, appamāṇā cetovimutti.**This is called the limitless heart’s release.*";
P_HTM[7691]="*Katamā cāvuso, ākiñcaññā cetovimutti?**And what is the heart’s release through nothingness?*";
P_HTM[7692]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma natthi kiñcīti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[7693]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, ākiñcaññā cetovimutti.**This is called the heart’s release through nothingness.*";
P_HTM[7694]="*Katamā cāvuso, suññatā cetovimutti?**And what is the heart’s release through emptiness?*";
P_HTM[7695]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, and reflects like this:*";
P_HTM[7696]="*‘suññamidaṃ attena vā attaniyena vā’ti.**‘This is empty of a self or what belongs to a self.’*";
P_HTM[7697]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, suññatā cetovimutti.**This is called the heart’s release through emptiness.*";
P_HTM[7698]="*Katamā cāvuso, animittā cetovimutti?**And what is the signless heart’s release?*";
P_HTM[7699]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu sabbanimittānaṃ amanasikārā animittaṃ cetosamādhiṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, not focusing on any signs, enters and remains in the signless immersion of the heart.*";
P_HTM[7700]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, animittā cetovimutti.**This is called the signless heart’s release.*";
P_HTM[7701]="*Ayaṃ kho, āvuso, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma ime dhammā nānātthā ceva nānābyañjanā ca.**This is the way in which these things differ in both meaning and phrasing.*";
P_HTM[7702]="*Katamo cāvuso, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma ime dhammā ekatthā byañjanameva nānaṃ?**And what’s the way in which they mean the same thing, and differ only in the phrasing?*";
P_HTM[7703]="*Rāgo kho, āvuso, pamāṇakaraṇo, doso pamāṇakaraṇo, moho pamāṇakaraṇo.**Greed, hate, and delusion are makers of limits.*";
P_HTM[7704]="*Te khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**A mendicant who has ended the defilements has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[7705]="*Yāvatā kho, āvuso, appamāṇā cetovimuttiyo, akuppā tāsaṃ cetovimutti aggamakkhāyati.**The unshakable heart’s release is said to be the best kind of limitless heart’s release.*";
P_HTM[7706]="*Sā kho panākuppā cetovimutti suññā rāgena, suññā dosena, suññā mohena.**That unshakable heart’s release is empty of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[7707]="*Rāgo kho, āvuso, kiñcano, doso kiñcano, moho kiñcano.**Greed is something, hate is something, and delusion is something.*";
P_HTM[7708]="*Te khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**A mendicant who has ended the defilements has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[7709]="*Yāvatā kho, āvuso, ākiñcaññā cetovimuttiyo, akuppā tāsaṃ cetovimutti aggamakkhāyati.**The unshakable heart’s release is said to be the best kind of heart’s release through nothingness.*";
P_HTM[7710]="*Sā kho panākuppā cetovimutti suññā rāgena, suññā dosena, suññā mohena.**That unshakable heart’s release is empty of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[7711]="*Rāgo kho, āvuso, nimittakaraṇo, doso nimittakaraṇo, moho nimittakaraṇo.**Greed, hate, and delusion are makers of signs.*";
P_HTM[7712]="*Te khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**A mendicant who has ended the defilements has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[7713]="*Yāvatā kho, āvuso, animittā cetovimuttiyo, akuppā tāsaṃ cetovimutti aggamakkhāyati.**The unshakable heart’s release is said to be the best kind of signless heart’s release.*";
P_HTM[7714]="*Sā kho panākuppā cetovimutti suññā rāgena, suññā dosena, suññā mohena.**That unshakable heart’s release is empty of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[7715]="*Ayaṃ kho, āvuso, pariyāyo yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma ime dhammā ekatthā byañjanameva nānan”ti.**This is the way in which they mean the same thing, and differ only in the phrasing.”*";
P_HTM[7716]="*Idamavocāyasmā sāriputto.**This is what Venerable Sāriputta said.*";
P_HTM[7717]="*Attamano āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita was happy with what Sāriputta said.*";
P_HTM[7718]="*Mahāvedallasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7719]="*44. Cūḷavedallasutta**The Shorter Classification*";
P_HTM[7720]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7721]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[7722]="*Atha kho visākho upāsako yena dhammadinnā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho visākho upāsako dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca:**Then the layman Visākha went to see the nun Dhammadinnā, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to her:*";
P_HTM[7723]="*“‘sakkāyo sakkāyo’ti, ayye, vuccati.**“Ma’am, they speak of this thing called ‘identity’.*";
P_HTM[7724]="*Katamo nu kho, ayye, sakkāyo vutto bhagavatā”ti?**What is this identity that the Buddha spoke of?”*";
P_HTM[7725]="*“Pañca kho ime, āvuso visākha, upādānakkhandhā sakkāyo vutto bhagavatā,**“Visākha, the Buddha said that these five grasping aggregates are identity.*";
P_HTM[7726]="*seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho.**That is: form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[7727]="*Ime kho, āvuso visākha, pañcupādānakkhandhā sakkāyo vutto bhagavatā”ti.**The Buddha said that these five grasping aggregates are identity.”*";
P_HTM[7728]="*“Sādhayye”ti kho visākho upāsako dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi:**Saying “Good, ma’am,” Visākha approved and agreed with what Dhammadinnā said. Then he asked another question:*";
P_HTM[7729]="*“‘sakkāyasamudayo sakkāyasamudayo’ti, ayye, vuccati.**“Ma’am, they speak of this thing called ‘the origin of identity’.*";
P_HTM[7730]="*Katamo nu kho, ayye, sakkāyasamudayo vutto bhagavatā”ti?**What is the origin of identity that the Buddha spoke of?”*";
P_HTM[7731]="*“Yāyaṃ, āvuso visākha, taṇhā ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—**“It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and greed, taking pleasure in various different realms. That is,*";
P_HTM[7732]="*kāmataṇhā bhavataṇhā vibhavataṇhā;**craving for sensual pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to end existence.*";
P_HTM[7733]="*ayaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyasamudayo vutto bhagavatā”ti.**The Buddha said that this is the origin of identity.”*";
P_HTM[7734]="*“‘Sakkāyanirodho sakkāyanirodho’ti, ayye, vuccati.**“Ma’am, they speak of this thing called ‘the cessation of identity’.*";
P_HTM[7735]="*Katamo nu kho, ayye, sakkāyanirodho vutto bhagavatā”ti?**What is the cessation of identity that the Buddha spoke of?”*";
P_HTM[7736]="*“Yo kho, āvuso visākha, tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo;**“It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not adhering to it.*";
P_HTM[7737]="*ayaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyanirodho vutto bhagavatā”ti.**The Buddha said that this is the cessation of identity.”*";
P_HTM[7738]="*“‘Sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti, ayye, vuccati.**“Ma’am, they speak of the practice that leads to the cessation of identity.*";
P_HTM[7739]="*Katamā nu kho, ayye, sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā vuttā bhagavatā”ti?**What is the practice that leads to the cessation of identity that the Buddha spoke of?”*";
P_HTM[7740]="*“Ayameva kho, āvuso visākha, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā vuttā bhagavatā, seyyathidaṃ—**“The practice that leads to the cessation of identity that the Buddha spoke of is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[7741]="*sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo sammāsati sammāsamādhī”ti.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[7742]="*“Taññeva nu kho, ayye, upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā udāhu aññatra pañcahupādānakkhandhehi upādānan”ti?**“But ma’am, is that grasping the exact same thing as the five grasping aggregates? Or is grasping one thing and the five grasping aggregates another?”*";
P_HTM[7743]="*“Na kho, āvuso visākha, taññeva upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā, nāpi aññatra pañcahupādānakkhandhehi upādānaṃ.**“That grasping is not the exact same thing as the five grasping aggregates. Nor is grasping one thing and the five grasping aggregates another.*";
P_HTM[7744]="*Yo kho, āvuso visākha, pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgo taṃ tattha upādānan”ti.**The desire and greed for the five grasping aggregates is the grasping there.”*";
P_HTM[7745]="*“Kathaṃ panāyye, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti?**“But ma’am, how does identity view come about?”*";
P_HTM[7746]="*“Idhāvuso visākha, assutavā puthujjano, ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto,**“It’s when an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[7747]="*rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ.**They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form.*";
P_HTM[7748]="*Vedanaṃ … pe …**They regard feeling …*";
P_HTM[7749]="*saññaṃ …**perception …*";
P_HTM[7750]="*saṅkhāre …**choices …*";
P_HTM[7751]="*viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā viññāṇaṃ, viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ.**consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness.*";
P_HTM[7752]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti.**That’s how identity view comes about.”*";
P_HTM[7753]="*“Kathaṃ panāyye, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti?**“But ma’am, how does identity view not come about?”*";
P_HTM[7754]="*“Idhāvuso visākha, sutavā ariyasāvako, ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido sappurisadhamme suvinīto,**“It’s when an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[7755]="*na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā rūpaṃ, na rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ.**They don’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form.*";
P_HTM[7756]="*Na vedanaṃ … pe …**They don’t regard feeling …*";
P_HTM[7757]="*na saññaṃ …**perception …*";
P_HTM[7758]="*na saṅkhāre … pe …**choices …*";
P_HTM[7759]="*na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā viññāṇaṃ, na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ.**consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness.*";
P_HTM[7760]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti.**That’s how identity view does not come about.”*";
P_HTM[7761]="*“Katamo panāyye, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo”ti?**“But ma’am, what is the noble eightfold path?”*";
P_HTM[7762]="*“Ayameva kho, āvuso visākha, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**“It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[7763]="*sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo sammāsati sammāsamādhī”ti.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[7764]="*“Ariyo panāyye, aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhato udāhu asaṅkhato”ti?**“But ma’am, is the noble eightfold path conditioned or unconditioned?”*";
P_HTM[7765]="*“Ariyo kho, āvuso visākha, aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhato”ti.**“The noble eightfold path is conditioned.”*";
P_HTM[7766]="*“Ariyena nu kho, ayye, aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena tayo khandhā saṅgahitā udāhu tīhi khandhehi ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅgahito”ti?**“Are the three practice categories included in the noble eightfold path? Or is the noble eightfold path included in the three practice categories?”*";
P_HTM[7767]="*“Na kho, āvuso visākha, ariyena aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena tayo khandhā saṅgahitā; tīhi ca kho, āvuso visākha, khandhehi ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅgahito.**“The three practice categories are not included in the noble eightfold path. Rather, the noble eightfold path is included in the three practice categories.*";
P_HTM[7768]="*Yā cāvuso visākha, sammāvācā yo ca sammākammanto yo ca sammāājīvo ime dhammā sīlakkhandhe saṅgahitā.**Right speech, right action, and right livelihood: these things are included in the category of ethics.*";
P_HTM[7769]="*Yo ca sammāvāyāmo yā ca sammāsati yo ca sammāsamādhi ime dhammā samādhikkhandhe saṅgahitā.**Right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion: these things are included in the category of immersion.*";
P_HTM[7770]="*Yā ca sammādiṭṭhi yo ca sammāsaṅkappo, ime dhammā paññākkhandhe saṅgahitā”ti.**Right view and right thought: these things are included in the category of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[7771]="*“Katamo panāyye, samādhi, katame dhammā samādhinimittā, katame dhammā samādhiparikkhārā, katamā samādhibhāvanā”ti?**“But ma’am, what is immersion? What things are the foundations of immersion? What things are the prerequisites for immersion? What is the development of immersion?”*";
P_HTM[7772]="*“Yā kho, āvuso visākha, cittassa ekaggatā ayaṃ samādhi;**“Unification of the mind is immersion.*";
P_HTM[7773]="*cattāro satipaṭṭhānā samādhinimittā;**The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the foundations of immersion.*";
P_HTM[7774]="*cattāro sammappadhānā samādhiparikkhārā.**The four right efforts are the prerequisites for immersion.*";
P_HTM[7775]="*Yā tesaṃyeva dhammānaṃ āsevanā bhāvanā bahulīkammaṃ, ayaṃ ettha samādhibhāvanā”ti.**The cultivation, development, and making much of these very same things is the development of immersion.”*";
P_HTM[7776]="*“Kati panāyye, saṅkhārā”ti?**“How many processes are there?”*";
P_HTM[7777]="*“Tayome, āvuso visākha, saṅkhārā—**“There are these three processes.*";
P_HTM[7778]="*kāyasaṅkhāro, vacīsaṅkhāro, cittasaṅkhāro”ti.**Physical, verbal, and mental processes.”*";
P_HTM[7779]="*“Katamo panāyye, kāyasaṅkhāro, katamo vacīsaṅkhāro, katamo cittasaṅkhāro”ti?**“But ma’am, what is the physical process? What’s the verbal process? What’s the mental process?”*";
P_HTM[7780]="*“Assāsapassāsā kho, āvuso visākha, kāyasaṅkhāro, vitakkavicārā vacīsaṅkhāro, saññā ca vedanā ca cittasaṅkhāro”ti.**“Breathing is a physical process. Placing the mind and keeping it connected are verbal processes. Perception and feeling are mental processes.”*";
P_HTM[7781]="*“Kasmā panāyye, assāsapassāsā kāyasaṅkhāro, kasmā vitakkavicārā vacīsaṅkhāro, kasmā saññā ca vedanā ca cittasaṅkhāro”ti?**“But ma’am, why is breathing a physical process? Why are placing the mind and keeping it connected verbal processes? Why are perception and feeling mental processes?”*";
P_HTM[7782]="*“Assāsapassāsā kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikā ete dhammā kāyappaṭibaddhā, tasmā assāsapassāsā kāyasaṅkhāro.**“Breathing is physical. It’s tied up with the body, that’s why breathing is a physical process.*";
P_HTM[7783]="*Pubbe kho, āvuso visākha, vitakketvā vicāretvā pacchā vācaṃ bhindati, tasmā vitakkavicārā vacīsaṅkhāro.**First you place the mind and keep it connected, then you break into speech. That’s why placing the mind and keeping it connected are verbal processes.*";
P_HTM[7784]="*Saññā ca vedanā ca cetasikā ete dhammā cittappaṭibaddhā, tasmā saññā ca vedanā ca cittasaṅkhāro”ti.**Perception and feeling are mental. They’re tied up with the mind, that’s why perception and feeling are mental processes.”*";
P_HTM[7785]="*“Kathaṃ panāyye, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpatti hotī”ti?**“But ma’am, how does someone attain the cessation of perception and feeling?”*";
P_HTM[7786]="*“Na kho, āvuso visākha, saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjantassa bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti:**“A mendicant who is entering such an attainment does not think:*";
P_HTM[7787]="*‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjissan’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno’ti vā.**‘I will enter the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I am entering the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I have entered the cessation of perception and feeling.’*";
P_HTM[7788]="*Atha khvāssa pubbeva tathā cittaṃ bhāvitaṃ hoti yaṃ taṃ tathattāya upanetī”ti.**Rather, their mind has been previously developed so as to lead to such a state.”*";
P_HTM[7789]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjantassa panāyye, bhikkhuno katame dhammā paṭhamaṃ nirujjhanti—yadi vā kāyasaṅkhāro, yadi vā vacīsaṅkhāro, yadi vā cittasaṅkhāro”ti?**“But ma’am, which cease first for a mendicant who is entering the cessation of perception and feeling: physical, verbal, or mental processes?”*";
P_HTM[7790]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjantassa kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuno paṭhamaṃ nirujjhati vacīsaṅkhāro, tato kāyasaṅkhāro, tato cittasaṅkhāro”ti.**“Verbal processes cease first, then physical, then mental.”*";
P_HTM[7791]="*“Kathaṃ panāyye, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ hotī”ti?**“But ma’am, how does someone emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling?”*";
P_HTM[7792]="*“Na kho, āvuso visākha, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahantassa bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti:**“A mendicant who is emerging from such an attainment does not think:*";
P_HTM[7793]="*‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahissan’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahāmī’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhito’ti vā.**‘I will emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I am emerging from the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I have emerged from the cessation of perception and feeling.’*";
P_HTM[7794]="*Atha khvāssa pubbeva tathā cittaṃ bhāvitaṃ hoti yaṃ taṃ tathattāya upanetī”ti.**Rather, their mind has been previously developed so as to lead to such a state.”*";
P_HTM[7795]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahantassa panāyye, bhikkhuno katame dhammā paṭhamaṃ uppajjanti—yadi vā kāyasaṅkhāro, yadi vā vacīsaṅkhāro, yadi vā cittasaṅkhāro”ti?**“But ma’am, which arise first for a mendicant who is emerging from the cessation of perception and feeling: physical, verbal, or mental processes?”*";
P_HTM[7796]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahantassa kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuno paṭhamaṃ uppajjati cittasaṅkhāro, tato kāyasaṅkhāro, tato vacīsaṅkhāro”ti.**“Mental processes arise first, then physical, then verbal.”*";
P_HTM[7797]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitaṃ panāyye, bhikkhuṃ kati phassā phusantī”ti?**“But ma’am, when a mendicant has emerged from the attainment of the cessation of perception and feeling, how many kinds of contact do they experience?”*";
P_HTM[7798]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuṃ tayo phassā phusanti—suññato phasso, animitto phasso, appaṇihito phasso”ti.**“They experience three kinds of contact: emptiness, signless, and undirected contacts.”*";
P_HTM[7799]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitassa panāyye, bhikkhuno kiṃninnaṃ cittaṃ hoti kiṃpoṇaṃ kiṃpabbhāran”ti?**“But ma’am, when a mendicant has emerged from the attainment of the cessation of perception and feeling, what does their mind slant, slope, and incline to?”*";
P_HTM[7800]="*“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitassa kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuno vivekaninnaṃ cittaṃ hoti, vivekapoṇaṃ vivekapabbhāran”ti.**“Their mind slants, slopes, and inclines to seclusion.”*";
P_HTM[7801]="*“Kati panāyye, vedanā”ti?**“But ma’am, how many feelings are there?”*";
P_HTM[7802]="*“Tisso kho imā, āvuso visākha, vedanā—**“There are three feelings:*";
P_HTM[7803]="*sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā”ti.**pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7804]="*“Katamā panāyye, sukhā vedanā, katamā dukkhā vedanā, katamā adukkhamasukhā vedanā”ti?**“What are these three feelings?”*";
P_HTM[7805]="*“Yaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā sukhaṃ sātaṃ vedayitaṃ—**“Anything felt physically or mentally as pleasant or enjoyable.*";
P_HTM[7806]="*ayaṃ sukhā vedanā.**This is pleasant feeling.*";
P_HTM[7807]="*Yaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā dukkhaṃ asātaṃ vedayitaṃ—**Anything felt physically or mentally as painful or unpleasant.*";
P_HTM[7808]="*ayaṃ dukkhā vedanā.**This is painful feeling.*";
P_HTM[7809]="*Yaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā neva sātaṃ nāsātaṃ vedayitaṃ—**Anything felt physically or mentally as neither pleasurable nor painful.*";
P_HTM[7810]="*ayaṃ adukkhamasukhā vedanā”ti.**This is neutral feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7811]="*“Sukhā panāyye, vedanā kiṃsukhā kiṃdukkhā, dukkhā vedanā kiṃsukhā kiṃdukkhā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā kiṃsukhā kiṃdukkhā”ti?**“What is pleasant and what is painful in each of the three feelings?”*";
P_HTM[7812]="*“Sukhā kho, āvuso visākha, vedanā ṭhitisukhā vipariṇāmadukkhā;**“Pleasant feeling is pleasant when it remains and painful when it perishes.*";
P_HTM[7813]="*dukkhā vedanā ṭhitidukkhā vipariṇāmasukhā;**Painful feeling is painful when it remains and pleasant when it perishes.*";
P_HTM[7814]="*adukkhamasukhā vedanā ñāṇasukhā aññāṇadukkhā”ti.**Neutral feeling is pleasant when there is knowledge, and painful when there is ignorance.”*";
P_HTM[7815]="*“Sukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ anusayo anuseti, dukkhāya vedanāya kiṃ anusayo anuseti, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya kiṃ anusayo anusetī”ti?**“What underlying tendencies underlie each of the three feelings?”*";
P_HTM[7816]="*“Sukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya rāgānusayo anuseti, dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo anuseti, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo anusetī”ti.**“The underlying tendency for greed underlies pleasant feeling. The underlying tendency for repulsion underlies painful feeling. The underlying tendency for ignorance underlies neutral feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7817]="*“Sabbāya nu kho, ayye, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo anuseti, sabbāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo anuseti, sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo anusetī”ti?**“Do these underlying tendencies always underlie these feelings?”*";
P_HTM[7818]="*“Na kho, āvuso visākha, sabbāya sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo anuseti, na sabbāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo anuseti, na sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo anusetī”ti.**“No, they do not.”*";
P_HTM[7819]="*“Sukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ pahātabbaṃ, dukkhāya vedanāya kiṃ pahātabbaṃ, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya kiṃ pahātabban”ti?**“What should be given up in regard to each of these three feelings?”*";
P_HTM[7820]="*“Sukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya rāgānusayo pahātabbo, dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo pahātabbo, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo pahātabbo”ti.**“The underlying tendency to greed should be given up when it comes to pleasant feeling. The underlying tendency to repulsion should be given up when it comes to painful feeling. The underlying tendency to ignorance should be given up when it comes to neutral feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7821]="*“Sabbāya nu kho, ayye, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo pahātabbo, sabbāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo pahātabbo, sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo pahātabbo”ti?**“Should these underlying tendencies be given up regarding all instances of these feelings?”*";
P_HTM[7822]="*“Na kho, āvuso visākha, sabbāya sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo pahātabbo, na sabbāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo pahātabbo, na sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo pahātabbo.**“No, not in all instances.*";
P_HTM[7823]="*Idhāvuso visākha, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[7824]="*Rāgaṃ tena pajahati, na tattha rāgānusayo anuseti.**With this they give up greed, and the underlying tendency to greed does not lie within that.*";
P_HTM[7825]="*Idhāvuso visākha, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**And take a mendicant who reflects:*";
P_HTM[7826]="*‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ tadāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharissāmi yadariyā etarahi āyatanaṃ upasampajja viharantī’ti?**‘Oh, when will I enter and remain in the same dimension that the noble ones enter and remain in today?’*";
P_HTM[7827]="*Iti anuttaresu vimokkhesu pihaṃ upaṭṭhāpayato uppajjati pihāppaccayā domanassaṃ.**Nursing such a longing for the supreme liberations gives rise to sadness due to longing.*";
P_HTM[7828]="*Paṭighaṃ tena pajahati, na tattha paṭighānusayo anuseti.**With this they give up repulsion, and the underlying tendency to repulsion does not lie within that.*";
P_HTM[7829]="*Idhāvuso visākha, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā, dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Take a mendicant who, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[7830]="*Avijjaṃ tena pajahati, na tattha avijjānusayo anusetī”ti.**With this they give up ignorance, and the underlying tendency to ignorance does not lie within that.”*";
P_HTM[7831]="*“Sukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“But ma’am, what is the counterpart of pleasant feeling?”*";
P_HTM[7832]="*“Sukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya dukkhā vedanā paṭibhāgo”ti.**“Painful feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7833]="*“Dukkhāya pannāyye, vedanāya kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“What is the counterpart of painful feeling?”*";
P_HTM[7834]="*“Dukkhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya sukhā vedanā paṭibhāgo”ti.**“Pleasant feeling.”*";
P_HTM[7835]="*“Adukkhamasukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“What is the counterpart of neutral feeling?”*";
P_HTM[7836]="*“Adukkhamasukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya avijjā paṭibhāgo”ti.**“Ignorance.”*";
P_HTM[7837]="*“Avijjāya panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“What is the counterpart of ignorance?”*";
P_HTM[7838]="*“Avijjāya kho, āvuso visākha, vijjā paṭibhāgo”ti.**“Knowledge.”*";
P_HTM[7839]="*“Vijjāya panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“What is the counterpart of knowledge?”*";
P_HTM[7840]="*“Vijjāya kho, āvuso visākha, vimutti paṭibhāgo”ti.**“Freedom.”*";
P_HTM[7841]="*“Vimuttiyā panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“What is the counterpart of freedom?”*";
P_HTM[7842]="*“Vimuttiyā kho, āvuso visākha, nibbānaṃ paṭibhāgo”ti.**“Extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[7843]="*“Nibbānassa panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?**“What is the counterpart of extinguishment?”*";
P_HTM[7844]="*“Accayāsi, āvuso visākha, pañhaṃ, nāsakkhi pañhānaṃ pariyantaṃ gahetuṃ.**“Your question goes too far, Visākha. You couldn’t figure out the limit of questions.*";
P_HTM[7845]="*Nibbānogadhañhi, āvuso visākha, brahmacariyaṃ, nibbānaparāyanaṃ nibbānapariyosānaṃ.**For extinguishment is the culmination, destination, and end of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[7846]="*Ākaṅkhamāno ca tvaṃ, āvuso visākha, bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ puccheyyāsi, yathā ca te bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsī”ti.**If you wish, go to the Buddha and ask him this question. You should remember it in line with his answer.”*";
P_HTM[7847]="*Atha kho visākho upāsako dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**And then the layman Visākha approved and agreed with what the nun Dhammadinnā said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled her, keeping her on his right. Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[7848]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho visākho upāsako yāvatako ahosi dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[7849]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā visākhaṃ upāsakaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[7850]="*“paṇḍitā, visākha, dhammadinnā bhikkhunī, mahāpaññā, visākha, dhammadinnā bhikkhunī.**“The nun Dhammadinnā is astute, Visākha, she has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[7851]="*Mañcepi tvaṃ, visākha, etamatthaṃ puccheyyāsi, ahampi taṃ evamevaṃ byākareyyaṃ, yathā taṃ dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā byākataṃ.**If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the same way as the nun Dhammadinnā.*";
P_HTM[7852]="*Eso cevetassa attho. Evañca naṃ dhārehī”ti.**That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”*";
P_HTM[7853]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7854]="*Attamano visākho upāsako bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, the layman Visākha was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7855]="*Cūḷavedallasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7856]="*45. Cūḷadhammasamādānasutta**The Shorter Discourse on Taking Up Practices*";
P_HTM[7857]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7858]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7859]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[7860]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[7861]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7862]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7863]="*“cattārimāni, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānāni.**“Mendicants, there are these four ways of taking up practices.*";
P_HTM[7864]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7865]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ;**There is a way of taking up practices that is pleasant now but results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[7866]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ;**There is a way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[7867]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ;**There is a way of taking up practices that is painful now but results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7868]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ.**There is a way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7869]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now but results in future pain?*";
P_HTM[7870]="*Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[7871]="*‘natthi kāmesu doso’ti.**‘There’s nothing wrong with sensual pleasures.’*";
P_HTM[7872]="*Te kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjanti.**They throw themselves into sensual pleasures,*";
P_HTM[7873]="*Te kho moḷibaddhāhi paribbājikāhi paricārenti.**cavorting with female wanderers with fancy hair-dos.*";
P_HTM[7874]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say,*";
P_HTM[7875]="*‘kiṃsu nāma te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kāmesu anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānā kāmānaṃ pahānamāhaṃsu, kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapenti?**‘What future danger do those ascetics and brahmins see in sensual pleasures that they speak of giving up sensual pleasures, and advocate the complete understanding of sensual pleasures?*";
P_HTM[7876]="*Sukho imissā paribbājikāya taruṇāya mudukāya lomasāya bāhāya samphasso’ti te kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjanti.**Pleasant is the touch of this female wanderer’s arm, tender, soft, and downy!’ And they throw themselves into sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[7877]="*Te kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjitvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7878]="*Te tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti.**And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings.*";
P_HTM[7879]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say,*";
P_HTM[7880]="*‘idaṃ kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kāmesu anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānā kāmānaṃ pahānamāhaṃsu, kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapenti, ime hi mayaṃ kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayāmā’ti.**‘This is that future danger that those ascetics and brahmins saw. For it is because of sensual pleasures that I’m feeling painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings.’*";
P_HTM[7881]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse māluvāsipāṭikā phaleyya.**Suppose that in the last month of summer a camel’s foot creeper pod were to burst open*";
P_HTM[7882]="*Atha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, māluvābījaṃ aññatarasmiṃ sālamūle nipateyya.**and a seed were to fall at the root of a sal tree.*";
P_HTM[7883]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, yā tasmiṃ sāle adhivatthā devatā sā bhītā saṃviggā santāsaṃ āpajjeyya.**Then the deity haunting that sal tree would become apprehensive and nervous.*";
P_HTM[7884]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tasmiṃ sāle adhivatthāya devatāya mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā ārāmadevatā vanadevatā rukkhadevatā osadhitiṇavanappatīsu adhivatthā devatā saṅgamma samāgamma evaṃ samassāseyyuṃ:**But their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin—deities of the parks, forests, trees, and those who haunt the herbs, grass, and big trees—would come together to reassure them,*";
P_HTM[7885]="*‘mā bhavaṃ bhāyi, mā bhavaṃ bhāyi;**‘Do not fear, sir, do not fear!*";
P_HTM[7886]="*appeva nāmetaṃ māluvābījaṃ moro vā gileyya, mago vā khādeyya, davaḍāho vā ḍaheyya, vanakammikā vā uddhareyyuṃ, upacikā vā uṭṭhaheyyuṃ, abījaṃ vā panassā’ti.**Hopefully that seed will be swallowed by a peacock, or eaten by a deer, or burnt by a forest fire, or picked up by a lumberjack, or eaten by termites, or it may not even be fertile.’*";
P_HTM[7887]="*Atha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, māluvābījaṃ neva moro gileyya, na mago khādeyya, na davaḍāho ḍaheyya, na vanakammikā uddhareyyuṃ, na upacikā uṭṭhaheyyuṃ, bījañca panassa taṃ pāvussakena meghena abhippavuṭṭhaṃ sammadeva viruheyya.**But none of these things happened. And the seed was fertile, so that when the clouds soaked it with rain, it sprouted.*";
P_HTM[7888]="*Sāssa māluvālatā taruṇā mudukā lomasā vilambinī, sā taṃ sālaṃ upaniseveyya.**And the creeper wound its tender, soft, and downy tendrils around that sal tree.*";
P_HTM[7889]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tasmiṃ sāle adhivatthāya devatāya evamassa:**Then the deity thought,*";
P_HTM[7890]="*‘kiṃsu nāma te bhonto mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā ārāmadevatā vanadevatā rukkhadevatā osadhitiṇavanappatīsu adhivatthā devatā māluvābīje anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānā saṅgamma samāgamma evaṃ samassāsesuṃ:**‘What future danger did my friends see when they said:*";
P_HTM[7891]="*“mā bhavaṃ bhāyi mā bhavaṃ bhāyi,**‘Do not fear, sir, do not fear!*";
P_HTM[7892]="*appeva nāmetaṃ māluvābījaṃ moro vā gileyya, mago vā khādeyya, davaḍāho vā ḍaheyya, vanakammikā vā uddhareyyuṃ, upacikā vā uṭṭhaheyyuṃ, abījaṃ vā panassā”ti;**Hopefully that seed will be swallowed by a peacock, or eaten by a deer, or burnt by a forest fire, or picked up by a lumberjack, or eaten by termites, or it may not even be fertile.’*";
P_HTM[7893]="*sukho imissā māluvālatāya taruṇāya mudukāya lomasāya vilambiniyā samphasso’ti.**Pleasant is the touch of this creeper’s tender, soft, and downy tendrils.’*";
P_HTM[7894]="*Sā taṃ sālaṃ anuparihareyya.**Then the creeper enfolded the sal tree,*";
P_HTM[7895]="*Sā taṃ sālaṃ anupariharitvā upari viṭabhiṃ kareyya.**made a canopy over it,*";
P_HTM[7896]="*Upari viṭabhiṃ karitvā oghanaṃ janeyya.**draped a curtain around it,*";
P_HTM[7897]="*Oghanaṃ janetvā ye tassa sālassa mahantā mahantā khandhā te padāleyya.**and split apart all the main branches.*";
P_HTM[7898]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tasmiṃ sāle adhivatthāya devatāya evamassa:**Then the deity thought,*";
P_HTM[7899]="*‘idaṃ kho te bhonto mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā ārāmadevatā vanadevatā rukkhadevatā osadhitiṇavanappatīsu adhivatthā devatā māluvābīje anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānā saṅgamma samāgamma evaṃ samassāsesuṃ:**‘This is the future danger that my friends saw!*";
P_HTM[7900]="*“mā bhavaṃ bhāyi mā bhavaṃ bhāyi, appeva nāmetaṃ māluvābījaṃ moro vā gileyya, mago vā khādeyya, davaḍāho vā ḍaheyya, vanakammikā vā uddhareyyuṃ, upacikā vā uṭṭhaheyyuṃ abījaṃ vā panassā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7901]="*Yañcāhaṃ māluvābījahetu dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayāmī’ti.**It’s because of that camel’s foot creeper seed that I’m feeling painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings.’*";
P_HTM[7902]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, santi eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino ‘natthi kāmesu doso’ti.**In the same way, there are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view: ‘There’s nothing wrong with sensual pleasures’ …*";
P_HTM[7903]="*Te kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[7904]="*Te moḷibaddhāhi paribbājikāhi paricārenti.* **";
P_HTM[7905]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:* **";
P_HTM[7906]="*‘kiṃsu nāma te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kāmesu anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānā kāmānaṃ pahānamāhaṃsu, kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapenti?* **";
P_HTM[7907]="*Sukho imissā paribbājikāya taruṇāya mudukāya lomasāya bāhāya samphasso’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7908]="*Te kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[7909]="*Te kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjitvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[7910]="*Te tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti.* **";
P_HTM[7911]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:* **";
P_HTM[7912]="*‘idaṃ kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kāmesu anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānā kāmānaṃ pahānamāhaṃsu, kāmānaṃ pariññaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[7913]="*Ime hi mayaṃ kāmahetu kāmanidānaṃ dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7914]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ.**This is called the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now but results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[7915]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain?*";
P_HTM[7916]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco acelako hoti muttācāro hatthāpalekhano, naehibhaddantiko, natiṭṭhabhaddantiko, nābhihaṭaṃ, na uddissakataṃ, na nimantanaṃ sādiyati,**It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal.*";
P_HTM[7917]="*so na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, na saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ, na maṃsaṃ, na suraṃ, na merayaṃ, na thusodakaṃ pivati.**They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer.*";
P_HTM[7918]="*So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … pe … sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko.**They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls.*";
P_HTM[7919]="*Ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti.**They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day.*";
P_HTM[7920]="*Ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti. Iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating food at set intervals.*";
P_HTM[7921]="*So sākabhakkho vā hoti, sāmākabhakkho vā hoti, nīvārabhakkho vā hoti, daddulabhakkho vā hoti, haṭabhakkho vā hoti, kaṇabhakkho vā hoti, ācāmabhakkho vā hoti, piññākabhakkho vā hoti, tiṇabhakkho vā hoti, gomayabhakkho vā hoti, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī.**They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit.*";
P_HTM[7922]="*So sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi dhāreti, kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhampi dhāreti,**They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings.*";
P_HTM[7923]="*kesamassulocakopi hoti, kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto,**They tear out their hair and beard, committed to this practice.*";
P_HTM[7924]="*ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti, āsanapaṭikkhitto,**They stand forever, refusing seats.*";
P_HTM[7925]="*ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto,**They squat, committed to persisting in the squatting position.*";
P_HTM[7926]="*kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti, kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti,**They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed.*";
P_HTM[7927]="*sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**They’re committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening.*";
P_HTM[7928]="*Iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**And so they live committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body.*";
P_HTM[7929]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[7930]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ.**This is called the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[7931]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is painful now but results in future pleasure?*";
P_HTM[7932]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pakatiyā tibbarāgajātiko hoti, so abhikkhaṇaṃ rāgajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;**It’s when someone is ordinarily full of acute greed, hate, and delusion. They often feel the pain and sadness that greed, hate, and delusion bring.*";
P_HTM[7933]="*pakatiyā tibbadosajātiko hoti, so abhikkhaṇaṃ dosajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[7934]="*pakatiyā tibbamohajātiko hoti, so abhikkhaṇaṃ mohajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[7935]="*So sahāpi dukkhena, sahāpi domanassena, assumukhopi rudamāno paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati.**They lead the full and pure spiritual life in pain and sadness, weeping, with tearful faces.*";
P_HTM[7936]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7937]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ.**This is called the way of taking up practices that is painful now but results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7938]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure?*";
P_HTM[7939]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pakatiyā na tibbarāgajātiko hoti, so na abhikkhaṇaṃ rāgajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;**It’s when someone is not ordinarily full of acute greed, hate, and delusion. They rarely feel the pain and sadness that greed, hate, and delusion bring.*";
P_HTM[7940]="*pakatiyā na tibbadosajātiko hoti, so na abhikkhaṇaṃ dosajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[7941]="*pakatiyā na tibbamohajātiko hoti, so na abhikkhaṇaṃ mohajaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[7942]="*So vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[7943]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**second absorption …*";
P_HTM[7944]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[7945]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[7946]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[7947]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ.**This is called the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7948]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri dhammasamādānānī”ti.**These are the four ways of taking up practices.”*";
P_HTM[7949]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7950]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7951]="*Cūḷadhammasamādānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7952]="*46. Mahādhammasamādānasutta**The Great Discourse on Taking Up Practices*";
P_HTM[7953]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7954]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7955]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[7956]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[7957]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7958]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7959]="*“yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, sattā evaṅkāmā evaṃchandā evaṃadhippāyā:**“Mendicants, sentient beings typically have the wish, desire, and hope:*";
P_HTM[7960]="*‘aho vata aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyeyyuṃ, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍheyyun’ti.**‘Oh, if only unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things would decrease, and likable, desirable, and agreeable things would increase!’*";
P_HTM[7961]="*Tesaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṅkāmānaṃ evaṃchandānaṃ evaṃadhippāyānaṃ aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti.**But exactly the opposite happens to them.*";
P_HTM[7962]="*Tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, kaṃ hetuṃ paccethā”ti?**What do you take to be the reason for this?”*";
P_HTM[7963]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā, bhagavaṃnettikā, bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaññeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho; bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[7964]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[7965]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7966]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7967]="*“Idha, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano, ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto,**“Take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[7968]="*sevitabbe dhamme na jānāti asevitabbe dhamme na jānāti, bhajitabbe dhamme na jānāti abhajitabbe dhamme na jānāti.**They don’t know what practices they should cultivate and foster, and what practices they shouldn’t cultivate and foster.*";
P_HTM[7969]="*So sevitabbe dhamme ajānanto asevitabbe dhamme ajānanto, bhajitabbe dhamme ajānanto abhajitabbe dhamme ajānanto, asevitabbe dhamme sevati sevitabbe dhamme na sevati, abhajitabbe dhamme bhajati bhajitabbe dhamme na bhajati.**So they cultivate and foster practices they shouldn’t, and don’t cultivate and foster practices they should.*";
P_HTM[7970]="*Tassa asevitabbe dhamme sevato sevitabbe dhamme asevato, abhajitabbe dhamme bhajato bhajitabbe dhamme abhajato aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti.**When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things increase, and likable, desirable, and agreeable things decrease.*";
P_HTM[7971]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[7972]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ aviddasuno.**Because that’s what it’s like for someone who doesn’t know.*";
P_HTM[7973]="*Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako, ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido sappurisadhamme suvinīto,**But an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[7974]="*sevitabbe dhamme jānāti asevitabbe dhamme jānāti, bhajitabbe dhamme jānāti abhajitabbe dhamme jānāti.**They know what practices they should cultivate and foster, and what practices they shouldn’t cultivate and foster.*";
P_HTM[7975]="*So sevitabbe dhamme jānanto asevitabbe dhamme jānanto, bhajitabbe dhamme jānanto abhajitabbe dhamme jānanto, asevitabbe dhamme na sevati sevitabbe dhamme sevati, abhajitabbe dhamme na bhajati bhajitabbe dhamme bhajati.**So they cultivate and foster practices they should, and don’t cultivate and foster practices they shouldn’t.*";
P_HTM[7976]="*Tassa asevitabbe dhamme asevato sevitabbe dhamme sevato, abhajitabbe dhamme abhajato bhajitabbe dhamme bhajato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things decrease, and likable, desirable, and agreeable things increase.*";
P_HTM[7977]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[7978]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ viddasuno.**Because that’s what it’s like for someone who knows.*";
P_HTM[7979]="*Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānāni.**Mendicants, there are these four ways of taking up practices.*";
P_HTM[7980]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7981]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ;**There is a way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[7982]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ;**There is a way of taking up practices that is pleasant now but results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[7983]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ;**There is a way of taking up practices that is painful now but results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7984]="*atthi, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ.**There is a way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7985]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ, taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain, an ignoramus, without knowing this, doesn’t truly understand:*";
P_HTM[7986]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākan’ti.**‘This is the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain.’*";
P_HTM[7987]="*Taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto taṃ sevati, taṃ na parivajjeti.**So instead of avoiding that practice, they cultivate it.*";
P_HTM[7988]="*Tassa taṃ sevato, taṃ aparivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti.**When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things increase, and likable, desirable, and agreeable things decrease.*";
P_HTM[7989]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[7990]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ aviddasuno. (1)**Because that’s what it’s like for someone who doesn’t know.*";
P_HTM[7991]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pain, an ignoramus …*";
P_HTM[7992]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7993]="*Taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto taṃ sevati, taṃ na parivajjeti.**cultivates it …*";
P_HTM[7994]="*Tassa taṃ sevato, taṃ aparivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti.**and disagreeable things increase …*";
P_HTM[7995]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[7996]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ aviddasuno. (2)* **";
P_HTM[7997]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ, taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pleasure, an ignoramus …*";
P_HTM[7998]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7999]="*Taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto taṃ na sevati, taṃ parivajjeti.**doesn’t cultivate it …*";
P_HTM[8000]="*Tassa taṃ asevato, taṃ parivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti.**and disagreeable things increase …*";
P_HTM[8001]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[8002]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ aviddasuno. (3)* **";
P_HTM[8003]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ, taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure, an ignoramus …*";
P_HTM[8004]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8005]="*Taṃ avidvā avijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto taṃ na sevati, taṃ parivajjeti.**doesn’t cultivate it …*";
P_HTM[8006]="*Tassa taṃ asevato, taṃ parivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā parihāyanti.**and disagreeable things increase …*";
P_HTM[8007]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8008]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ aviddasuno. (4)**Because that’s what it’s like for someone who doesn’t know.*";
P_HTM[8009]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain, a wise person, knowing this, truly understands:*";
P_HTM[8010]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākan’ti.**‘This is the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain.’*";
P_HTM[8011]="*Taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanto taṃ na sevati, taṃ parivajjeti.**So instead of cultivating that practice, they avoid it.*";
P_HTM[8012]="*Tassa taṃ asevato, taṃ parivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things decrease, and likable, desirable, and agreeable things increase.*";
P_HTM[8013]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8014]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ viddasuno. (1)**Because that’s what it’s like for someone who knows.*";
P_HTM[8015]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pain, a wise person …*";
P_HTM[8016]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8017]="*Taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanto taṃ na sevati, taṃ parivajjeti.**doesn’t cultivate it …*";
P_HTM[8018]="*Tassa taṃ asevato, taṃ parivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**and agreeable things increase …*";
P_HTM[8019]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[8020]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ viddasuno. (2)* **";
P_HTM[8021]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pleasure, a wise person …*";
P_HTM[8022]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8023]="*Taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanto taṃ sevati, taṃ na parivajjeti.**cultivates it …*";
P_HTM[8024]="*Tassa taṃ sevato, taṃ aparivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**and agreeable things increase …*";
P_HTM[8025]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[8026]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ viddasuno. (3)* **";
P_HTM[8027]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti:**When it comes to the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure, a wise person, knowing this, truly understands:*";
P_HTM[8028]="*‘idaṃ kho dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākan’ti.**‘This is the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure.’*";
P_HTM[8029]="*Taṃ vidvā vijjāgato yathābhūtaṃ pajānanto taṃ sevati, taṃ na parivajjeti.**So instead of avoiding that practice, they cultivate it.*";
P_HTM[8030]="*Tassa taṃ sevato, taṃ aparivajjayato, aniṭṭhā akantā amanāpā dhammā parihāyanti, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**When they do so, unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable things decrease, and likable, desirable, and agreeable things increase.*";
P_HTM[8031]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8032]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti yathā taṃ viddasuno. (4)**Because that’s what it’s like for someone who knows.*";
P_HTM[8033]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain?*";
P_HTM[8034]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena pāṇātipātī hoti, pāṇātipātapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;**It’s when someone in pain and sadness kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view. Because of these things they experience pain and sadness.*";
P_HTM[8035]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena adinnādāyī hoti, adinnādānapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8036]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena kāmesu micchācārī hoti, kāmesu micchācārapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8037]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena musāvādī hoti, musāvādapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8038]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena pisuṇavāco hoti, pisuṇavācāpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8039]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena pharusavāco hoti, pharusavācāpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8040]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena samphappalāpī hoti, samphappalāpapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8041]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena abhijjhālu hoti, abhijjhāpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8042]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena byāpannacitto hoti, byāpādapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8043]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena micchādiṭṭhi hoti, micchādiṭṭhipaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[8044]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**And when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[8045]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ. (1)**This is called the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[8046]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now but results in future pain?*";
P_HTM[8047]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena pāṇātipātī hoti, pāṇātipātapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;**It’s when someone with pleasure and happiness kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view. Because of these things they experience pleasure and happiness.*";
P_HTM[8048]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena adinnādāyī hoti, adinnādānapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8049]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena kāmesumicchācārī hoti, kāmesumicchācārapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8050]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena musāvādī hoti, musāvādapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8051]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena pisuṇavāco hoti, pisuṇavācāpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8052]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena pharusavāco hoti, pharusavācāpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8053]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena samphappalāpī hoti, samphappalāpapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8054]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena abhijjhālu hoti, abhijjhāpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8055]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena byāpannacitto hoti, byāpādapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8056]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena micchādiṭṭhi hoti, micchādiṭṭhipaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[8057]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**But when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[8058]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ. (2)**This is called the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now but results in future pain.*";
P_HTM[8059]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is painful now but results in future pleasure?*";
P_HTM[8060]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;**It’s when someone in pain and sadness doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. Because of these things they experience pain and sadness.*";
P_HTM[8061]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8062]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8063]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8064]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8065]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8066]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā veramaṇīpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8067]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena anabhijjhālu hoti, anabhijjhāpaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8068]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena abyāpannacitto hoti, abyāpādapaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8069]="*sahāpi dukkhena sahāpi domanassena sammādiṭṭhi hoti, sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[8070]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**But when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[8071]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ. (3)**This is called the way of taking up practices that is painful now but results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[8072]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ?**And what is the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure?*";
P_HTM[8073]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;**It’s when someone with pleasure and happiness doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. Because of these things they experience pleasure and happiness.*";
P_HTM[8074]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8075]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8076]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8077]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8078]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8079]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā veramaṇīpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8080]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena anabhijjhālu hoti, anabhijjhāpaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8081]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena abyāpannacitto hoti, abyāpādapaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti;* **";
P_HTM[8082]="*sahāpi sukhena sahāpi somanassena sammādiṭṭhi hoti, sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[8083]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**And when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[8084]="*Idaṃ, vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ.**This is called the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure.*";
P_HTM[8085]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri dhammasamādānāni. (4)**These are the four ways of taking up practices.*";
P_HTM[8086]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, tittakālābu visena saṃsaṭṭho.**Suppose there was some bitter gourd mixed with poison.*";
P_HTM[8087]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo.**Then a man would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain.*";
P_HTM[8088]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him:*";
P_HTM[8089]="*‘ambho purisa, ayaṃ tittakālābu visena saṃsaṭṭho,**‘Here, mister, this is bitter gourd mixed with poison.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*sace ākaṅkhasi piva.**Drink it if you like.*";
P_HTM[8091]="*Tassa te pivato ceva nacchādessati vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana maraṇaṃ vā nigacchasi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’ti.**If you drink it, the color, aroma, and flavor will be unappetizing, and it will result in death or deadly pain.’*";
P_HTM[8092]="*So taṃ appaṭisaṅkhāya piveyya, nappaṭinissajjeyya.**He wouldn’t reject it. Without reflection, he’d drink it.*";
P_HTM[8093]="*Tassa taṃ pivato ceva nacchādeyya vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**The color, aroma, and flavor would be unappetizing, and it would result in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[8094]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ vadāmi, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ. (1)**This is comparable to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain, I say.*";
P_HTM[8095]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, āpānīyakaṃso vaṇṇasampanno gandhasampanno rasasampanno.**Suppose there was a bronze cup of beverage that had a nice color, aroma, and flavor.*";
P_HTM[8096]="*So ca kho visena saṃsaṭṭho.**But it was mixed with poison.*";
P_HTM[8097]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo.**Then a man would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain.*";
P_HTM[8098]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him:*";
P_HTM[8099]="*‘ambho purisa, ayaṃ āpānīyakaṃso vaṇṇasampanno gandhasampanno rasasampanno.**‘Here, mister, this bronze cup of beverage has a nice color, aroma, and flavor.*";
P_HTM[8100]="*So ca kho visena saṃsaṭṭho,**But it’s mixed with poison.*";
P_HTM[8101]="*sace ākaṅkhasi piva.**Drink it if you like.*";
P_HTM[8102]="*Tassa te pivatohi kho chādessati vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana maraṇaṃ vā nigacchasi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’ti.**If you drink it, the color, aroma, and flavor will be appetizing, but it will result in death or deadly pain.’*";
P_HTM[8103]="*So taṃ appaṭisaṅkhāya piveyya, nappaṭinissajjeyya.**He wouldn’t reject it. Without reflection, he’d drink it.*";
P_HTM[8104]="*Tassa taṃ pivatohi kho chādeyya vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**The color, aroma, and flavor would be appetizing, but it would result in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[8105]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ vadāmi, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhaṃ āyatiṃ dukkhavipākaṃ. (2)**This is comparable to the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pain, I say.*";
P_HTM[8106]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, pūtimuttaṃ nānābhesajjehi saṃsaṭṭhaṃ.**Suppose there was some fermented urine mixed with different medicines.*";
P_HTM[8107]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya paṇḍukarogī.**Then a man with jaundice would come along.*";
P_HTM[8108]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him:*";
P_HTM[8109]="*‘ambho purisa, idaṃ pūtimuttaṃ nānābhesajjehi saṃsaṭṭhaṃ, sace ākaṅkhasi piva.**‘Here, mister, this is fermented urine mixed with different medicines. Drink it if you like.*";
P_HTM[8110]="*Tassa te pivatohi kho nacchādessati vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana sukhī bhavissasī’ti.**If you drink it, the color, aroma, and flavor will be unappetizing, but after drinking it you will be happy.’*";
P_HTM[8111]="*So taṃ paṭisaṅkhāya piveyya, nappaṭinissajjeyya.**He wouldn’t reject it. After reflection, he’d drink it.*";
P_HTM[8112]="*Tassa taṃ pivatohi kho nacchādeyya vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana sukhī assa.**The color, aroma, and flavor would be unappetizing, but after drinking it he would be happy.*";
P_HTM[8113]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ vadāmi, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhaṃ āyatiṃ sukhavipākaṃ. (3)**This is comparable to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pleasure, I say.*";
P_HTM[8114]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dadhi ca madhu ca sappi ca phāṇitañca ekajjhaṃ saṃsaṭṭhaṃ.**Suppose there was some curds, honey, ghee, and molasses all mixed together.*";
P_HTM[8115]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya lohitapakkhandiko.**Then a man with dysentery would come along.*";
P_HTM[8116]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him:*";
P_HTM[8117]="*‘ambho purisa, idaṃ dadhi ca madhu ca sappi ca phāṇitañca ekajjhaṃ saṃsaṭṭhaṃ, sace ākaṅkhasi piva.**‘Here, mister, this is curds, honey, ghee, and molasses all mixed together. Drink it if you like.*";
P_HTM[8118]="*Tassa te pivato ceva chādessati vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana sukhī bhavissasī’ti.**If you drink it, the color, aroma, and flavor will be appetizing, and after drinking it you will be happy.’*";
P_HTM[8119]="*So taṃ paṭisaṅkhāya piveyya, nappaṭinissajjeyya.**He wouldn’t reject it. After reflection, he’d drink it.*";
P_HTM[8120]="*Tassa taṃ pivato ceva chādeyya vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana sukhī assa.**The color, aroma, and flavor would be appetizing, and after drinking it he would be happy.*";
P_HTM[8121]="*Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ vadāmi, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ. (4)**This is comparable to the way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure, I say.*";
P_HTM[8122]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve ādicco nabhaṃ abbhussakkamāno sabbaṃ ākāsagataṃ tamagataṃ abhivihacca bhāsate ca tapate ca virocate ca;**It’s like the time after the rainy season when the sky is clear and cloudless. And when the sun rises, it dispels all the darkness from the sky as it shines and glows and radiates.*";
P_HTM[8123]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannasukhañceva āyatiñca sukhavipākaṃ tadaññe puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇaparappavāde abhivihacca bhāsate ca tapate ca virocate cā”ti.**In the same way, this way of taking up practices that is pleasant now and results in future pleasure dispels the doctrines of the various other ascetics and brahmins as it shines and glows and radiates.”*";
P_HTM[8124]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8125]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8126]="*Mahādhammasamādānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8127]="*47. Vīmaṃsakasutta**The Inquirer*";
P_HTM[8128]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8129]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[8130]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[8131]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[8132]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[8133]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[8134]="*“vīmaṃsakena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā parassa cetopariyāyaṃ ajānantena tathāgate samannesanā kātabbā ‘sammāsambuddho vā no vā’ iti viññāṇāyā”ti.**“Mendicants, a mendicant who is an inquirer, unable to comprehend another’s mind, should scrutinize the Realized One to see whether he is a fully awakened Buddha or not.”*";
P_HTM[8135]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā, bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā; sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho; bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[8136]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[8137]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[8138]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[8139]="*“Vīmaṃsakena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā parassa cetopariyāyaṃ ajānantena dvīsu dhammesu tathāgato samannesitabbo cakkhusotaviññeyyesu dhammesu:**“Mendicants, a mendicant who is an inquirer, unable to comprehend another’s mind, should scrutinize the Realized One for two things—things that can be seen and heard:*";
P_HTM[8140]="*‘ye saṅkiliṭṭhā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti vā te tathāgatassa no vā’ti?**‘Can anything corrupt be seen or heard in the Realized One or not?’*";
P_HTM[8141]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing him they find that*";
P_HTM[8142]="*‘ye saṅkiliṭṭhā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, na te tathāgatassa saṃvijjantī’ti. (1)**nothing corrupt can be seen or heard in the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[8143]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8144]="*‘ye saṅkiliṭṭhā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, na te tathāgatassa saṃvijjantī’ti, tato naṃ uttariṃ samannesati:**They scrutinize further:*";
P_HTM[8145]="*‘ye vītimissā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti vā te tathāgatassa no vā’ti?**‘Can anything mixed be seen or heard in the Realized One or not?’*";
P_HTM[8146]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing him they find that*";
P_HTM[8147]="*‘ye vītimissā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, na te tathāgatassa saṃvijjantī’ti. (2)**nothing mixed can be seen or heard in the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[8148]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8149]="*‘ye vītimissā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, na te tathāgatassa saṃvijjantī’ti, tato naṃ uttariṃ samannesati:**They scrutinize further:*";
P_HTM[8150]="*‘ye vodātā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti vā te tathāgatassa no vā’ti?**‘Can anything clean be seen or heard in the Realized One or not?’*";
P_HTM[8151]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing him they find that*";
P_HTM[8152]="*‘ye vodātā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti te tathāgatassā’ti. (3)**clean things can be seen and heard in the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[8153]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8154]="*‘ye vodātā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti te tathāgatassā’ti, tato naṃ uttariṃ samannesati:**They scrutinize further:*";
P_HTM[8155]="*‘dīgharattaṃ samāpanno ayamāyasmā imaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ, udāhu ittarasamāpanno’ti?**‘Did the venerable attain this skillful state a long time ago, or just recently?’*";
P_HTM[8156]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing him they find that*";
P_HTM[8157]="*‘dīgharattaṃ samāpanno ayamāyasmā imaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ, nāyamāyasmā ittarasamāpanno’ti. (4)**the venerable attained this skillful state a long time ago, not just recently.*";
P_HTM[8158]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8159]="*‘dīgharattaṃ samāpanno ayamāyasmā imaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ, nāyamāyasmā ittarasamāpanno’ti, tato naṃ uttariṃ samannesati:**They scrutinize further:*";
P_HTM[8160]="*‘ñattajjhāpanno ayamāyasmā bhikkhu yasappatto, saṃvijjantassa idhekacce ādīnavā’ti?**‘Are certain dangers found in that venerable mendicant who has achieved fame and renown?’*";
P_HTM[8161]="*Na tāva, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno idhekacce ādīnavā saṃvijjanti yāva na ñattajjhāpanno hoti yasappatto.**For, mendicants, so long as a mendicant has not achieved fame and renown, certain dangers are not found in them.*";
P_HTM[8162]="*Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ñattajjhāpanno hoti yasappatto, athassa idhekacce ādīnavā saṃvijjanti.**But when they achieve fame and renown, those dangers appear.*";
P_HTM[8163]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing him they find that*";
P_HTM[8164]="*‘ñattajjhāpanno ayamāyasmā bhikkhu yasappatto, nāssa idhekacce ādīnavā saṃvijjantī’ti. (5)**those dangers are not found in that venerable mendicant who has achieved fame and renown.*";
P_HTM[8165]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8166]="*‘ñattajjhāpanno ayamāyasmā bhikkhu yasappatto, nāssa idhekacce ādīnavā saṃvijjantī’ti, tato naṃ uttariṃ samannesati:**They scrutinize further:*";
P_HTM[8167]="*‘abhayūparato ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā bhayūparato;**‘Is this venerable securely stopped or insecurely stopped?*";
P_HTM[8168]="*vītarāgattā kāme na sevati khayā rāgassā’ti?**Is the reason they don’t indulge in sensual pleasures that they’re free of greed because greed has ended?’*";
P_HTM[8169]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing him they find that*";
P_HTM[8170]="*‘abhayūparato ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā bhayūparato;**that venerable is securely stopped, not insecurely stopped.*";
P_HTM[8171]="*vītarāgattā kāme na sevati khayā rāgassā’ti. (6)**The reason they don’t indulge in sensual pleasures is that they’re free of greed because greed has ended.*";
P_HTM[8172]="*Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ pare evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If others should ask that mendicant,*";
P_HTM[8173]="*‘ke panāyasmato ākārā, ke anvayā, yenāyasmā evaṃ vadesi—**‘But what reason and evidence does the venerable have for saying this?’*";
P_HTM[8174]="*abhayūparato ayamāyasmā, nāyamāyasmā bhayūparato;* **";
P_HTM[8175]="*vītarāgattā kāme na sevati khayā rāgassā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8176]="*Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:**Answering rightly, the mendicant should say,*";
P_HTM[8177]="*‘tathā hi pana ayamāyasmā saṅghe vā viharanto eko vā viharanto, ye ca tattha sugatā ye ca tattha duggatā, ye ca tattha gaṇamanusāsanti, ye ca idhekacce āmisesu sandissanti, ye ca idhekacce āmisena anupalittā, nāyamāyasmā taṃ tena avajānāti.**‘Because, whether that venerable is staying in a community or alone, some people there are in a good state or a sorry state, some instruct a group, and some indulge in material pleasures, while others remain unsullied. Yet that venerable doesn’t look down on them for that.*";
P_HTM[8178]="*Sammukhā kho pana metaṃ bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—**Also, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[8179]="*abhayūparatohamasmi, nāhamasmi bhayūparato, vītarāgattā kāme na sevāmi khayā rāgassā’ti.**“I am securely stopped, not insecurely stopped. The reason I don’t indulge in sensual pleasures is that I’m free of greed because greed has ended.”’*";
P_HTM[8180]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, tathāgatova uttariṃ paṭipucchitabbo:**Next, they should ask the Realized One himself about this,*";
P_HTM[8181]="*‘ye saṅkiliṭṭhā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti vā te tathāgatassa no vā’ti?**‘Can anything corrupt be seen or heard in the Realized One or not?’*";
P_HTM[8182]="*Byākaramāno, bhikkhave, tathāgato evaṃ byākareyya:**The Realized One would answer,*";
P_HTM[8183]="*‘ye saṅkiliṭṭhā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, na te tathāgatassa saṃvijjantī’ti. (1)**‘Nothing corrupt can be seen or heard in the Realized One.’*";
P_HTM[8184]="*‘Ye vītimissā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti vā te tathāgatassa no vā’ti?**‘Can anything mixed be seen or heard in the Realized One or not?’*";
P_HTM[8185]="*Byākaramāno, bhikkhave, tathāgato evaṃ byākareyya:**The Realized One would answer,*";
P_HTM[8186]="*‘ye vītimissā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, na te tathāgatassa saṃvijjantī’ti. (2)**‘Nothing mixed can be seen or heard in the Realized One.’*";
P_HTM[8187]="*‘Ye vodātā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti vā te tathāgatassa no vā’ti?**‘Can anything clean be seen or heard in the Realized One or not?’*";
P_HTM[8188]="*Byākaramāno, bhikkhave, tathāgato evaṃ byākareyya:**The Realized One would answer,*";
P_HTM[8189]="*‘ye vodātā cakkhusotaviññeyyā dhammā, saṃvijjanti te tathāgatassa;**‘Clean things can be seen and heard in the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[8190]="*etaṃ pathohamasmi, etaṃ gocaro, no ca tena tammayo’ti. (3)**I am that range and that territory, but I do not identify with that.’*";
P_HTM[8191]="*Evaṃvādiṃ kho, bhikkhave, satthāraṃ arahati sāvako upasaṅkamituṃ dhammassavanāya.**A disciple ought to approach a teacher who has such a doctrine in order to listen to the teaching.*";
P_HTM[8192]="*Tassa satthā dhammaṃ deseti uttaruttariṃ paṇītapaṇītaṃ kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgaṃ.**The teacher explains Dhamma with its higher and higher stages, with its better and better stages, with its dark and bright sides.*";
P_HTM[8193]="*Yathā yathā kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno satthā dhammaṃ deseti uttaruttariṃ paṇītapaṇītaṃ kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgaṃ tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme abhiññāya idhekaccaṃ dhammaṃ dhammesu niṭṭhaṃ gacchati, satthari pasīdati:**When they directly know a certain principle of those teachings, in accordance with how they were taught, the mendicant comes to a conclusion about the teachings. They have confidence in the teacher:*";
P_HTM[8194]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno saṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha! The teaching is well explained! The Saṅgha is practicing well!’*";
P_HTM[8195]="*Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ pare evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If others should ask that mendicant,*";
P_HTM[8196]="*‘ke panāyasmato ākārā, ke anvayā, yenāyasmā evaṃ vadesi—**‘But what reason and evidence does the venerable have for saying this?’*";
P_HTM[8197]="*sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno saṅgho’ti?* **";
P_HTM[8198]="*Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya:**Answering rightly, the mendicant should say,*";
P_HTM[8199]="*‘idhāhaṃ, āvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃ dhammassavanāya.**‘Reverends, I approached the Buddha to listen to the teaching.*";
P_HTM[8200]="*Tassa me bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti uttaruttariṃ paṇītapaṇītaṃ kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgaṃ.**He explained Dhamma with its higher and higher stages, with its better and better stages, with its dark and bright sides.*";
P_HTM[8201]="*Yathā yathā me, āvuso, bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti uttaruttariṃ paṇītapaṇītaṃ kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgaṃ tathā tathāhaṃ tasmiṃ dhamme abhiññāya idhekaccaṃ dhammaṃ dhammesu niṭṭhamagamaṃ, satthari pasīdiṃ—**When I directly knew a certain principle of those teachings, in accordance with how I was taught, I came to a conclusion about the teachings. I had confidence in the Teacher:*";
P_HTM[8202]="*sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā, dhammo, suppaṭipanno saṅgho’ti.**“The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha! The teaching is well explained! The Saṅgha is practicing well!”’*";
P_HTM[8203]="*Yassa kassaci, bhikkhave, imehi ākārehi imehi padehi imehi byañjanehi tathāgate saddhā niviṭṭhā hoti mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ākāravatī saddhā dassanamūlikā, daḷhā;**When someone’s faith is settled, rooted, and planted in the Realized One in this manner, with these words and phrases, it’s said to be grounded faith that’s based on evidence.*";
P_HTM[8204]="*asaṃhāriyā samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ.**It is firm, and cannot be shifted by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.*";
P_HTM[8205]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tathāgate dhammasamannesanā hoti.**This is how to scrutinize the Realized One’s qualities.*";
P_HTM[8206]="*Evañca pana tathāgato dhammatāsusamanniṭṭho hotī”ti.**But the Realized One has already been properly searched in this way by nature.”*";
P_HTM[8207]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8208]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8209]="*Vīmaṃsakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8210]="*48. Kosambiyasutta**The Mendicants of Kosambi*";
P_HTM[8211]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8212]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8213]="*Tena kho pana samayena kosambiyaṃ bhikkhū bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharanti.**Now at that time the mendicants of Kosambi were arguing, quarreling, and fighting, continually wounding each other with barbed words.*";
P_HTM[8214]="*Te na ceva aññamaññaṃ saññāpenti na ca saññattiṃ upenti, na ca aññamaññaṃ nijjhāpenti, na ca nijjhattiṃ upenti.**They couldn’t persuade each other or be persuaded, nor could they convince each other or be convinced.*";
P_HTM[8215]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what was happening.*";
P_HTM[8216]="*“idha, bhante, kosambiyaṃ bhikkhū bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharanti, te na ceva aññamaññaṃ saññāpenti, na ca saññattiṃ upenti, na ca aññamaññaṃ nijjhāpenti, na ca nijjhattiṃ upentī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8217]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[8218]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena te bhikkhū āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell those mendicants that*";
P_HTM[8219]="*‘satthā vo āyasmante āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons them.*";
P_HTM[8220]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to those monks and said,*";
P_HTM[8221]="*“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti.**“Venerables, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[8222]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” those monks replied. They went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them,*";
P_HTM[8223]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharatha,**“Is it really true, mendicants, that you have been arguing, quarreling, and fighting, continually wounding each other with barbed words?*";
P_HTM[8224]="*te na ceva aññamaññaṃ saññāpetha, na ca saññattiṃ upetha, na ca aññamaññaṃ nijjhāpetha, na ca nijjhattiṃ upethā”ti?**And that you can’t persuade each other or be persuaded, nor can you convince each other or be convinced?”*";
P_HTM[8225]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir,” they said.*";
P_HTM[8226]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[8227]="*yasmiṃ tumhe samaye bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharatha, api nu tumhākaṃ tasmiṃ samaye mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ … pe … mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho cā”ti?**When you’re arguing, quarreling, and fighting, continually wounding each other with barbed words, are you treating your spiritual companions with kindness by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private?”*";
P_HTM[8228]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[8229]="*“Iti kira, bhikkhave, yasmiṃ tumhe samaye bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharatha, neva tumhākaṃ tasmiṃ samaye mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, na mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ … pe … na mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca.**“So it seems that when you’re arguing you are not treating each other with kindness.*";
P_HTM[8230]="*Atha kiñcarahi tumhe, moghapurisā, kiṃ jānantā kiṃ passantā bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharatha, te na ceva aññamaññaṃ saññāpetha, na ca saññattiṃ upetha, na ca aññamaññaṃ nijjhāpetha, na ca nijjhattiṃ upetha?**So what exactly do you know and see, you foolish men, that you behave in such a way?*";
P_HTM[8231]="*Tañhi tumhākaṃ, moghapurisā, bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**This will be for your lasting harm and suffering.”*";
P_HTM[8232]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[8233]="*“chayime, bhikkhave, dhammā sāraṇīyā piyakaraṇā garukaraṇā saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these six warm-hearted qualities make for fondness and respect, conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling.*";
P_HTM[8234]="*Katame cha?**What six?*";
P_HTM[8235]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca.**Firstly, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with bodily kindness, both in public and in private.*";
P_HTM[8236]="*Ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (1)**This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling.*";
P_HTM[8237]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca.**Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with verbal kindness …*";
P_HTM[8238]="*Ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (2)* **";
P_HTM[8239]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca.**Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with mental kindness …*";
P_HTM[8240]="*Ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (3)* **";
P_HTM[8241]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te lābhā dhammikā dhammaladdhā antamaso pattapariyāpannamattampi, tathārūpehi lābhehi appaṭivibhattabhogī hoti sīlavantehi sabrahmacārīhi sādhāraṇabhogī.**Furthermore, a mendicant shares without reservation any material possessions they have gained by legitimate means, even the food placed in the alms-bowl, using them in common with their ethical spiritual companions …*";
P_HTM[8242]="*Ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (4)* **";
P_HTM[8243]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni samādhisaṃvattanikāni tathārūpesu sīlesu sīlasāmaññagato viharati sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca.**Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the precepts shared with their spiritual companions, both in public and in private. Those precepts are unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. …*";
P_HTM[8244]="*Ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (5)* **";
P_HTM[8245]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhisāmaññagato viharati sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca.**Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the view shared with their spiritual companions, both in public and in private. That view is noble and emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[8246]="*Ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (6)**This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling.*";
P_HTM[8247]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha sāraṇīyā dhammā piyakaraṇā garukaraṇā saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattanti.**These six warm-hearted qualities make for fondness and respect, conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling.*";
P_HTM[8248]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, channaṃ sāraṇīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ etaṃ aggaṃ etaṃ saṅgāhikaṃ etaṃ saṅghāṭanikaṃ—yadidaṃ yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**Of these six warm-hearted qualities, the chief is the view that is noble and emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete ending of suffering. It holds and binds everything together.*";
P_HTM[8249]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kūṭāgārassa etaṃ aggaṃ etaṃ saṅgāhikaṃ etaṃ saṅghāṭanikaṃ yadidaṃ kūṭaṃ;**It’s like a bungalow. The roof-peak is the chief point, which holds and binds everything together.*";
P_HTM[8250]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ sāraṇīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ etaṃ aggaṃ etaṃ saṅgāhikaṃ etaṃ saṅghāṭanikaṃ yadidaṃ yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya.**In the same way, of these six warm-hearted qualities, the chief is the view that is noble and emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete ending of suffering. It holds and binds everything together.*";
P_HTM[8251]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya?**And how does the view that is noble and emancipating lead one who practices it to the complete ending of suffering?*";
P_HTM[8252]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a mendicant has gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, and reflects like this,*";
P_HTM[8253]="*‘atthi nu kho me taṃ pariyuṭṭhānaṃ ajjhattaṃ appahīnaṃ, yenāhaṃ pariyuṭṭhānena pariyuṭṭhitacitto yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyyaṃ na passeyyan’ti?**‘Is there anything that I’m overcome with internally and haven’t given up, because of which I might not accurately know and see?’*";
P_HTM[8254]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhito hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**If a mendicant is overcome with sensual desire, it’s their mind that’s overcome.*";
P_HTM[8255]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu byāpādapariyuṭṭhito hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**If a mendicant is overcome with ill will,*";
P_HTM[8256]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhito hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**dullness and drowsiness,*";
P_HTM[8257]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhito hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**restlessness and remorse,*";
P_HTM[8258]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhito hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**doubt,*";
P_HTM[8259]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu idhalokacintāya pasuto hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**pursuing speculation about this world,*";
P_HTM[8260]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paralokacintāya pasuto hoti, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**pursuing speculation about the next world,*";
P_HTM[8261]="*Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhaṇḍanajāto kalahajāto vivādāpanno aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudanto viharati, pariyuṭṭhitacittova hoti.**or arguing, quarreling, and fighting, continually wounding others with barbed words, it’s their mind that’s overcome.*";
P_HTM[8262]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8263]="*‘natthi kho me taṃ pariyuṭṭhānaṃ ajjhattaṃ appahīnaṃ, yenāhaṃ pariyuṭṭhānena pariyuṭṭhitacitto yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyyaṃ na passeyyaṃ.**‘There is nothing that I’m overcome with internally and haven’t given up, because of which I might not accurately know and see.*";
P_HTM[8264]="*Suppaṇihitaṃ me mānasaṃ saccānaṃ bodhāyā’ti.**My mind is properly disposed for awakening to the truths.’*";
P_HTM[8265]="*Idamassa paṭhamaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (1)**This is the first knowledge they have achieved that is noble and transcendent, and is not shared with ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[8266]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects,*";
P_HTM[8267]="*‘imaṃ nu kho ahaṃ diṭṭhiṃ āsevanto bhāvento bahulīkaronto labhāmi paccattaṃ samathaṃ, labhāmi paccattaṃ nibbutin’ti?**‘When I develop, cultivate, and make much of this view, do I personally gain serenity and quenching?’*";
P_HTM[8268]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8269]="*‘imaṃ kho ahaṃ diṭṭhiṃ āsevanto bhāvento bahulīkaronto labhāmi paccattaṃ samathaṃ, labhāmi paccattaṃ nibbutin’ti.**‘When I develop, cultivate, and make much of this view, I personally gain serenity and quenching.’*";
P_HTM[8270]="*Idamassa dutiyaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (2)**This is their second knowledge …*";
P_HTM[8271]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects,*";
P_HTM[8272]="*‘yathārūpāyāhaṃ diṭṭhiyā samannāgato, atthi nu kho ito bahiddhā añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgato’ti?**‘Are there any ascetics or brahmins outside of the Buddhist community who have the same kind of view that I have?’*";
P_HTM[8273]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8274]="*‘yathārūpāyāhaṃ diṭṭhiyā samannāgato, natthi ito bahiddhā añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgato’ti.**‘There are no ascetics or brahmins outside of the Buddhist community who have the same kind of view that I have.’*";
P_HTM[8275]="*Idamassa tatiyaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (3)**This is their third knowledge …*";
P_HTM[8276]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects,*";
P_HTM[8277]="*‘yathārūpāya dhammatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya dhammatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘Do I have the same nature as a person accomplished in view?’*";
P_HTM[8278]="*Kathaṃrūpāya ca, bhikkhave, dhammatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato?**And what, mendicants, is the nature of a person accomplished in view?*";
P_HTM[8279]="*Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa:**This is the nature of a person accomplished in view.*";
P_HTM[8280]="*‘kiñcāpi tathārūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, yathārūpāya āpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyati, atha kho naṃ khippameva satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu deseti vivarati uttānīkaroti;**Though they may fall into a kind of offense for which rehabilitation has been laid down, they quickly disclose, clarify, and reveal it to the Teacher or a sensible spiritual companion.*";
P_HTM[8281]="*desetvā vivaritvā uttānīkatvā āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjati’.**And having revealed it they restrain themselves in the future.*";
P_HTM[8282]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako hatthena vā pādena vā aṅgāraṃ akkamitvā khippameva paṭisaṃharati;**Suppose there was a little baby boy. If he puts his hand or foot on a burning coal, he quickly pulls it back.*";
P_HTM[8283]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, dhammatā esā diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa:**In the same way, this is the nature of a person accomplished in view.*";
P_HTM[8284]="*‘kiñcāpi tathārūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati yathārūpāya āpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyati, atha kho naṃ khippameva satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu deseti vivarati uttānīkaroti;**Though they may still fall into a kind of offense for which rehabilitation has been laid down, they quickly reveal it to the Teacher or a sensible spiritual companion.*";
P_HTM[8285]="*desetvā vivaritvā uttānīkatvā āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjati’.**And having revealed it they restrain themselves in the future.*";
P_HTM[8286]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8287]="*‘yathārūpāya dhammatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya dhammatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘I have the same nature as a person accomplished in view.’*";
P_HTM[8288]="*Idamassa catutthaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (4)**This is their fourth knowledge …*";
P_HTM[8289]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects,*";
P_HTM[8290]="*‘yathārūpāya dhammatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya dhammatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘Do I have the same nature as a person accomplished in view?’*";
P_HTM[8291]="*Kathaṃrūpāya ca, bhikkhave, dhammatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato?**And what, mendicants, is the nature of a person accomplished in view?*";
P_HTM[8292]="*Dhammatā esā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa:**This is the nature of a person accomplished in view.*";
P_HTM[8293]="*‘kiñcāpi yāni tāni sabrahmacārīnaṃ uccāvacāni kiṅkaraṇīyāni tattha ussukkaṃ āpanno hoti, atha khvāssa tibbāpekkhā hoti adhisīlasikkhāya adhicittasikkhāya adhipaññāsikkhāya’.**Though they might manage a diverse spectrum of duties for their spiritual companions, they still feel a keen regard for the training in higher ethics, higher mind, and higher wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8294]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gāvī taruṇavacchā thambañca ālumpati vacchakañca apacinati;**Suppose there was a cow with a baby calf. She keeps the calf close as she grazes.*";
P_HTM[8295]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, dhammatā esā diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa:**In the same way, this is the nature of a person accomplished in view.*";
P_HTM[8296]="*‘kiñcāpi yāni tāni sabrahmacārīnaṃ uccāvacāni kiṅkaraṇīyāni tattha ussukkaṃ āpanno hoti, atha khvāssa tibbāpekkhā hoti adhisīlasikkhāya adhicittasikkhāya adhipaññāsikkhāya’.**Though they might manage a diverse spectrum of duties for their spiritual companions, they still feel a keen regard for the training in higher ethics, higher mind, and higher wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8297]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8298]="*‘yathārūpāya dhammatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya dhammatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘I have the same nature as a person accomplished in view.’*";
P_HTM[8299]="*Idamassa pañcamaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (5)**This is their fifth knowledge …*";
P_HTM[8300]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects,*";
P_HTM[8301]="*‘yathārūpāya balatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya balatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘Do I have the same strength as a person accomplished in view?’*";
P_HTM[8302]="*Kathaṃrūpāya ca, bhikkhave, balatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato?**And what, mendicants, is the strength of a person accomplished in view?*";
P_HTM[8303]="*Balatā esā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa yaṃ tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasikatvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti.**The strength of a person accomplished in view is that, when the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One are being taught, they pay heed, pay attention, engage wholeheartedly, and lend an ear.*";
P_HTM[8304]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8305]="*‘yathārūpāya balatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya balatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘I have the same strength as a person accomplished in view.’*";
P_HTM[8306]="*Idamassa chaṭṭhaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (6)**This is their sixth knowledge …*";
P_HTM[8307]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects,*";
P_HTM[8308]="*‘yathārūpāya balatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya balatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘Do I have the same strength as a person accomplished in view?’*";
P_HTM[8309]="*Kathaṃrūpāya ca, bhikkhave, balatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato?**And what, mendicants, is the strength of a person accomplished in view?*";
P_HTM[8310]="*Balatā esā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa yaṃ tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ.**The strength of a person accomplished in view is that, when the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One are being taught, they find joy in the meaning and the teaching, and find joy connected with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[8311]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[8312]="*‘yathārūpāya balatāya diṭṭhisampanno puggalo samannāgato, ahampi tathārūpāya balatāya samannāgato’ti.**‘I have the same strength as a person accomplished in view.’*";
P_HTM[8313]="*Idamassa sattamaṃ ñāṇaṃ adhigataṃ hoti ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ asādhāraṇaṃ puthujjanehi. (7)**This is the seventh knowledge they have achieved that is noble and transcendent, and is not shared with ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[8314]="*Evaṃ sattaṅgasamannāgatassa kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa dhammatā susamanniṭṭhā hoti sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya.**When a noble disciple has these seven factors, they have properly investigated their own nature with respect to the realization of the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[8315]="*Evaṃ sattaṅgasamannāgato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpattiphalasamannāgato hotī”ti.**A noble disciple with these seven factors has the fruit of stream-entry.”*";
P_HTM[8316]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8317]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8318]="*Kosambiyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8319]="*49. Brahmanimantanikasutta**On the Invitation of Brahmā*";
P_HTM[8320]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8321]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[8322]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[8323]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[8324]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[8325]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[8326]="*“Ekamidāhaṃ, bhikkhave, samayaṃ ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ viharāmi subhagavane sālarājamūle.**“At one time, mendicants, I was staying near Ukkaṭṭhā, in the Subhaga Forest at the root of a magnificent sal tree.*";
P_HTM[8327]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena bakassa brahmuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti:**Now at that time Baka the Brahmā had the following harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[8328]="*‘idaṃ niccaṃ, idaṃ dhuvaṃ, idaṃ sassataṃ, idaṃ kevalaṃ, idaṃ acavanadhammaṃ, idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjati, ito ca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ natthī’ti.**‘This is permanent, this is everlasting, this is eternal, this is whole, this is imperishable. For this is where there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn. And there’s no other escape beyond this.’*";
P_HTM[8329]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bakassa brahmuno cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—**Then I knew what Baka the Brahmā was thinking.*";
P_HTM[8330]="*seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—ukkaṭṭhāyaṃ subhagavane sālarājamūle antarahito tasmiṃ brahmaloke pāturahosiṃ.**As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, I vanished from the Subhaga Forest and reappeared in that Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[8331]="*Addasā kho maṃ, bhikkhave, bako brahmā dūratova āgacchantaṃ;**Baka saw me coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[8332]="*disvāna maṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[8333]="*‘ehi kho, mārisa, svāgataṃ, mārisa.**‘Come, good sir! Welcome, good sir!*";
P_HTM[8334]="*Cirassaṃ kho, mārisa, imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya.**It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.*";
P_HTM[8335]="*Idañhi, mārisa, niccaṃ, idaṃ dhuvaṃ, idaṃ sassataṃ, idaṃ kevalaṃ, idaṃ acavanadhammaṃ, idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjati. Ito ca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ natthī’ti.**For this is permanent, this is everlasting, this is eternal, this is complete, this is imperishable. For this is where there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn. And there’s no other escape beyond this.’*";
P_HTM[8336]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bakaṃ brahmānaṃ etadavocaṃ:**When he had spoken, I said to him,*";
P_HTM[8337]="*‘avijjāgato vata bho bako brahmā, avijjāgato vata bho bako brahmā;**‘Alas, Baka the Brahmā is lost in ignorance! Alas, Baka the Brahmā is lost in ignorance!*";
P_HTM[8338]="*yatra hi nāma aniccaṃyeva samānaṃ niccanti vakkhati, addhuvaṃyeva samānaṃ dhuvanti vakkhati, asassataṃyeva samānaṃ sassatanti vakkhati, akevalaṃyeva samānaṃ kevalanti vakkhati, cavanadhammaṃyeva samānaṃ acavanadhammanti vakkhati;**Because what is actually impermanent, not lasting, transient, incomplete, and perishable, he says is permanent, everlasting, eternal, complete, and imperishable.*";
P_HTM[8339]="*yattha ca pana jāyati jīyati mīyati cavati upapajjati tañca vakkhati:**And where there is being born, growing old, dying, passing away, and being reborn, he says that*";
P_HTM[8340]="*“idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjatī”ti;**there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn.*";
P_HTM[8341]="*santañca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ “natthaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇan”ti vakkhatī’ti.**And although there is another escape beyond this, he says that there’s no other escape beyond this.’*";
P_HTM[8342]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, māro pāpimā aññataraṃ brahmapārisajjaṃ anvāvisitvā maṃ etadavoca:**Then Māra the Wicked took possession of a member of Brahmā’s retinue and said this to me,*";
P_HTM[8343]="*‘bhikkhu bhikkhu, metamāsado metamāsado, eso hi, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānaṃ.**‘Mendicant, mendicant! Don’t attack this one! Don’t attack this one! For this is Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those yet to be born.*";
P_HTM[8344]="*Ahesuṃ kho ye, bhikkhu, tayā pubbe samaṇabrāhmaṇā lokasmiṃ pathavīgarahakā pathavījigucchakā, āpagarahakā āpajigucchakā, tejagarahakā tejajigucchakā, vāyagarahakā vāyajigucchakā, bhūtagarahakā bhūtajigucchakā, devagarahakā devajigucchakā, pajāpatigarahakā pajāpatijigucchakā, brahmagarahakā brahmajigucchakā—**There have been ascetics and brahmins before you, mendicant, who criticized and loathed earth, water, air, fire, creatures, gods, the Creator, and Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[8345]="*te kāyassa bhedā pāṇupacchedā hīne kāye patiṭṭhitā ahesuṃ.**When their bodies broke up and their breath was cut off they were reborn in a lower realm.*";
P_HTM[8346]="*Ye pana, bhikkhu, tayā pubbe samaṇabrāhmaṇā lokasmiṃ pathavīpasaṃsakā pathavābhinandino, āpapasaṃsakā āpābhinandino, tejapasaṃsakā tejābhinandino, vāyapasaṃsakā vāyābhinandino, bhūtapasaṃsakā bhūtābhinandino, devapasaṃsakā devābhinandino, pajāpatipasaṃsakā pajāpatābhinandino, brahmapasaṃsakā brahmābhinandino—**There have been ascetics and brahmins before you, mendicant, who praised and approved earth, water, air, fire, creatures, gods, the Creator, and Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[8347]="*te kāyassa bhedā pāṇupacchedā paṇīte kāye patiṭṭhitā.**When their bodies broke up and their breath was cut off they were reborn in a higher realm.*";
P_HTM[8348]="*Taṃ tāhaṃ, bhikkhu, evaṃ vadāmi:**So, mendicant, I tell you this:*";
P_HTM[8349]="*“iṅgha tvaṃ, mārisa, yadeva te brahmā āha tadeva tvaṃ karohi, mā tvaṃ brahmuno vacanaṃ upātivattittho”.**please, good sir, do exactly what Brahmā says. Don’t go beyond the word of Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[8350]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, brahmuno vacanaṃ upātivattissasi, seyyathāpi nāma puriso siriṃ āgacchantiṃ daṇḍena paṭippaṇāmeyya, seyyathāpi vā pana, bhikkhu, puriso narakappapāte papatanto hatthehi ca pādehi ca pathaviṃ virādheyya, evaṃ sampadamidaṃ, bhikkhu, tuyhaṃ bhavissati.**If you do, then the consequence for you will be like that of a person who, when Lady Luck approaches, wards her off with a staff, or someone who shoves away the ground as they fall down the chasm into hell.*";
P_HTM[8351]="*Iṅgha tvaṃ, mārisa, yadeva te brahmā āha tadeva tvaṃ karohi, mā tvaṃ brahmuno vacanaṃ upātivattittho.**Please, dear sir, do exactly what Brahmā says. Don’t go beyond the word of Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[8352]="*Nanu tvaṃ, bhikkhu, passasi brahmaparisaṃ sannipatitan’ti?**Do you not see the assembly of Brahmā gathered here?’*";
P_HTM[8353]="*Iti kho maṃ, bhikkhave, māro pāpimā brahmaparisaṃ upanesi.**And that is how Māra the Wicked presented the assembly of Brahmā to me as an example.*";
P_HTM[8354]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavocaṃ:**When he had spoken, I said to Māra,*";
P_HTM[8355]="*‘jānāmi kho tāhaṃ, pāpima; mā tvaṃ maññittho:**‘I know you, Wicked One. Do not think,*";
P_HTM[8356]="*“na maṃ jānātī”ti.**“He does not know me.”*";
P_HTM[8357]="*Māro tvamasi, pāpima.**You are Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[8358]="*Yo ceva, pāpima, brahmā, yā ca brahmaparisā, ye ca brahmapārisajjā, sabbeva tava hatthagatā sabbeva tava vasaṅgatā.**And Brahmā, Brahmā’s assembly, and Brahmā’s retinue have all fallen into your hands; they’re under your sway.*";
P_HTM[8359]="*Tuyhañhi, pāpima, evaṃ hoti:**And you think,*";
P_HTM[8360]="*“esopi me assa hatthagato, esopi me assa vasaṅgato”ti.**“Maybe this one, too, has fallen into my hands; maybe he’s under my sway!”*";
P_HTM[8361]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, pāpima, neva tava hatthagato neva tava vasaṅgato’ti.**But I haven’t fallen into your hands; I’m not under your sway.’*";
P_HTM[8362]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, bako brahmā maṃ etadavoca:**When I had spoken, Baka the Brahmā said to me,*";
P_HTM[8363]="*‘ahañhi, mārisa, niccaṃyeva samānaṃ “niccan”ti vadāmi, dhuvaṃyeva samānaṃ “dhuvan”ti vadāmi, sassataṃyeva samānaṃ “sassatan”ti vadāmi, kevalaṃyeva samānaṃ “kevalan”ti vadāmi, acavanadhammaṃyeva samānaṃ “acavanadhamman”ti vadāmi, yattha ca pana na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjati tadevāhaṃ vadāmi:**‘But, good sir, what I say is permanent, everlasting, eternal, complete, and imperishable is in fact permanent, everlasting, eternal, complete, and imperishable. And where I say there’s no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn there is in fact*";
P_HTM[8364]="*“idañhi na jāyati na jīyati na mīyati na cavati na upapajjatī”ti.**no being born, growing old, dying, passing away, or being reborn.*";
P_HTM[8365]="*Asantañca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ “natthaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇan”ti vadāmi.**And when I say there’s no other escape beyond this there is in fact no other escape beyond this.*";
P_HTM[8366]="*Ahesuṃ kho, bhikkhu, tayā pubbe samaṇabrāhmaṇā lokasmiṃ yāvatakaṃ tuyhaṃ kasiṇaṃ āyu tāvatakaṃ tesaṃ tapokammameva ahosi.**There have been ascetics and brahmins in the world before you, mendicant, whose self-mortification lasted as long as your entire life.*";
P_HTM[8367]="*Te kho evaṃ jāneyyuṃ santañca panaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ “atthaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇan”ti, asantaṃ vā aññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ “natthaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇan”ti.**When there was another escape beyond this they knew it, and when there was no other escape beyond this, they knew it.*";
P_HTM[8368]="*Taṃ tāhaṃ, bhikkhu, evaṃ vadāmi:**So, mendicant, I tell you this:*";
P_HTM[8369]="*“na cevaññaṃ uttari nissaraṇaṃ dakkhissasi, yāvadeva ca pana kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī bhavissasi.**you will never find another escape beyond this, and you will eventually get weary and frustrated.*";
P_HTM[8370]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pathaviṃ ajjhosissasi, opasāyiko me bhavissasi vatthusāyiko, yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāhiteyyo.**If you attach to earth, you will lie close to me, in my domain, vulnerable and expendable.*";
P_HTM[8371]="*Sace āpaṃ …**If you attach to water …*";
P_HTM[8372]="*tejaṃ …**fire …*";
P_HTM[8373]="*vāyaṃ …**air …*";
P_HTM[8374]="*bhūte …**creatures …*";
P_HTM[8375]="*deve …**gods …*";
P_HTM[8376]="*pajāpatiṃ …**the Creator …*";
P_HTM[8377]="*brahmaṃ ajjhosissasi, opasāyiko me bhavissasi vatthusāyiko, yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāhiteyyo”’ti.**Brahmā, you will lie close to me, in my domain, vulnerable and expendable.’*";
P_HTM[8378]="*‘Ahampi kho evaṃ, brahme, jānāmi:**‘Brahmā, I too know that*";
P_HTM[8379]="*“sace pathaviṃ ajjhosissāmi, opasāyiko te bhavissāmi vatthusāyiko, yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāhiteyyo.**if I attach to earth, I will lie close to you, in your domain, vulnerable and expendable.*";
P_HTM[8380]="*Sace āpaṃ …**If I attach to water …*";
P_HTM[8381]="*tejaṃ …**fire …*";
P_HTM[8382]="*vāyaṃ …**air …*";
P_HTM[8383]="*bhūte …**creatures …*";
P_HTM[8384]="*deve …**gods …*";
P_HTM[8385]="*pajāpatiṃ …**the Creator …*";
P_HTM[8386]="*brahmaṃ ajjhosissāmi, opasāyiko te bhavissāmi vatthusāyiko, yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāhiteyyo”ti api ca te ahaṃ, brahme, gatiñca pajānāmi, jutiñca pajānāmi:**Brahmā, I will lie close to you, in your domain, vulnerable and expendable. And in addition, Brahmā, I understand your range and your light:*";
P_HTM[8387]="*“evaṃ mahiddhiko bako brahmā, evaṃ mahānubhāvo bako brahmā, evaṃ mahesakkho bako brahmā”ti.**“That’s how powerful is Baka the Brahmā, how illustrious and mighty.”’*";
P_HTM[8388]="*Yathākathaṃ pana me tvaṃ, mārisa, gatiñca pajānāsi, jutiñca pajānāsi:**‘But in what way do you understand my range and my light?’*";
P_HTM[8389]="*“evaṃ mahiddhiko bako brahmā, evaṃ mahānubhāvo bako brahmā, evaṃ mahesakkho bako brahmā”’ti?* **";
P_HTM[8390]="*‘Yāvatā candimasūriyā,**‘A galaxy extends a thousand times as far*";
P_HTM[8391]="*Pariharanti disā bhanti virocanā;**as the moon and sun revolve*";
P_HTM[8392]="*Tāva sahassadhā loko,**and the shining ones light up the quarters.*";
P_HTM[8393]="*Ettha te vattate vaso.**And there you wield your power.*";
P_HTM[8394]="*Paroparañca jānāsi,**You know the high and low,*";
P_HTM[8395]="*atho rāgavirāginaṃ;**the passionate and dispassionate,*";
P_HTM[8396]="*Itthabhāvaññathābhāvaṃ,**and the coming and going of sentient beings*";
P_HTM[8397]="*sattānaṃ āgatiṃ gatinti.**from this realm to another.*";
P_HTM[8398]="*Evaṃ kho te ahaṃ, brahme, gatiñca pajānāmi jutiñca pajānāmi:**That’s how I understand your range and your light.*";
P_HTM[8399]="*“evaṃ mahiddhiko bako brahmā, evaṃ mahānubhāvo bako brahmā, evaṃ mahesakkho bako brahmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8400]="*Atthi kho, brahme, añño kāyo, taṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi;**But there is another realm that you don’t know or see.*";
P_HTM[8401]="*tamahaṃ jānāmi passāmi.**But I know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[8402]="*Atthi kho, brahme, ābhassarā nāma kāyo yato tvaṃ cuto idhūpapanno.**There is the realm named after the gods of streaming radiance. You passed away from there and were reborn here.*";
P_HTM[8403]="*Tassa te aticiranivāsena sā sati pamuṭṭhā, tena taṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi;**You’ve dwelt here so long that you’ve forgotten about that, so you don’t know it or see it.*";
P_HTM[8404]="*tamahaṃ jānāmi passāmi.**But I know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[8405]="*Evampi kho ahaṃ, brahme, neva te samasamo abhiññāya, kuto nīceyyaṃ?**So Brahmā, I am not your equal in knowledge, still less your inferior.*";
P_HTM[8406]="*Atha kho ahameva tayā bhiyyo.**Rather, I know more than you.*";
P_HTM[8407]="*Atthi kho, brahme, subhakiṇho nāma kāyo, vehapphalo nāma kāyo, abhibhū nāma kāyo, taṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi;**There is the realm named after the gods replete with glory … the realm named after the gods of abundant fruit … the realm named after the Overlord, which you don’t know or see.*";
P_HTM[8408]="*tamahaṃ jānāmi passāmi.**But I know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[8409]="*Evampi kho ahaṃ, brahme, neva te samasamo abhiññāya, kuto nīceyyaṃ?**So Brahmā, I am not your equal in knowledge, still less your inferior.*";
P_HTM[8410]="*Atha kho ahameva tayā bhiyyo.**Rather, I know more than you.*";
P_HTM[8411]="*Pathaviṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme, pathavito abhiññāya yāvatā pathaviyā pathavattena ananubhūtaṃ tadabhiññāya pathaviṃ nāpahosiṃ, pathaviyā nāpahosiṃ, pathavito nāpahosiṃ, pathaviṃ meti nāpahosiṃ, pathaviṃ nābhivadiṃ.**Having directly known earth as earth, and having directly known that which does not fall within the scope of experience based on earth, I did not identify with earth, I did not identify regarding earth, I did not identify as earth, I did not identify ‘earth is mine’, I did not enjoy earth.*";
P_HTM[8412]="*Evampi kho ahaṃ, brahme, neva te samasamo abhiññāya, kuto nīceyyaṃ?**So Brahmā, I am not your equal in knowledge, still less your inferior.*";
P_HTM[8413]="*Atha kho ahameva tayā bhiyyo.**Rather, I know more than you.*";
P_HTM[8414]="*Āpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**Having directly known water …*";
P_HTM[8415]="*tejaṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**fire …*";
P_HTM[8416]="*vāyaṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**air …*";
P_HTM[8417]="*bhūte kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**creatures …*";
P_HTM[8418]="*deve kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**gods …*";
P_HTM[8419]="*pajāpatiṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**the Creator …*";
P_HTM[8420]="*brahmaṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**Brahmā …*";
P_HTM[8421]="*ābhassare kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**the gods of streaming radiance …*";
P_HTM[8422]="*subhakiṇhe kho ahaṃ, brahme …**the gods replete with glory …*";
P_HTM[8423]="*… pe …* **";
P_HTM[8424]="*vehapphale kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**the gods of abundant fruit …*";
P_HTM[8425]="*abhibhuṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme … pe …**the Overlord …*";
P_HTM[8426]="*sabbaṃ kho ahaṃ, brahme, sabbato abhiññāya yāvatā sabbassa sabbattena ananubhūtaṃ tadabhiññāya sabbaṃ nāpahosiṃ sabbasmiṃ nāpahosiṃ sabbato nāpahosiṃ sabbaṃ meti nāpahosiṃ, sabbaṃ nābhivadiṃ.**Having directly known all as all, and having directly known that which does not fall within the scope of experience based on all, I did not identify with all, I did not identify regarding all, I did not identify as all, I did not identify ‘all is mine’, I did not enjoy all.*";
P_HTM[8427]="*Evampi kho ahaṃ, brahme, neva te samasamo abhiññāya, kuto nīceyyaṃ?**So Brahmā, I am not your equal in knowledge, still less your inferior.*";
P_HTM[8428]="*Atha kho ahameva tayā bhiyyo’ti.**Rather, I know more than you.’*";
P_HTM[8429]="*‘Sace kho, mārisa, sabbassa sabbattena ananubhūtaṃ, tadabhiññāya mā heva te rittakameva ahosi, tucchakameva ahosīti.**‘Well, good sir, if you have directly known that which is not within the scope of experience based on all, may your words not turn out to be void and hollow!*";
P_HTM[8430]="*Viññāṇaṃ anidassanaṃ anantaṃ sabbato pabhaṃ, taṃ pathaviyā pathavattena ananubhūtaṃ, āpassa āpattena ananubhūtaṃ, tejassa tejattena ananubhūtaṃ, vāyassa vāyattena ananubhūtaṃ, bhūtānaṃ bhūtattena ananubhūtaṃ, devānaṃ devattena ananubhūtaṃ, pajāpatissa pajāpatittena ananubhūtaṃ, brahmānaṃ brahmattena ananubhūtaṃ, ābhassarānaṃ ābhassarattena ananubhūtaṃ, subhakiṇhānaṃ subhakiṇhattena ananubhūtaṃ, vehapphalānaṃ vehapphalattena ananubhūtaṃ, abhibhussa abhibhuttena ananubhūtaṃ, sabbassa sabbattena ananubhūtaṃ.**Consciousness that is invisible, infinite, radiant all round—that’s what is not within the scope of experience based on earth, water, fire, air, creatures, gods, the Creator, Brahmā, the gods of streaming radiance, the gods replete with glory, the gods of abundant fruit, the Overlord, and the all.*";
P_HTM[8431]="*Handa carahi te, mārisa, passa antaradhāyāmī’ti.**Well look now, good sir, I will vanish from you!’*";
P_HTM[8432]="*‘Handa carahi me tvaṃ, brahme, antaradhāyassu, sace visahasī’ti.**‘All right, then, Brahmā, vanish from me—if you can.’*";
P_HTM[8433]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, bako brahmā:**Then Baka the Brahmā said,*";
P_HTM[8434]="*‘antaradhāyissāmi samaṇassa gotamassa, antaradhāyissāmi samaṇassa gotamassā’ti nevassu me sakkoti antaradhāyituṃ.**‘I will vanish from the ascetic Gotama! I will vanish from the ascetic Gotama!’ But he was unable to vanish from me.*";
P_HTM[8435]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bakaṃ brahmānaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I said to him,*";
P_HTM[8436]="*‘handa carahi te brahme antaradhāyāmī’ti.**‘Well look now, Brahmā, I will vanish from you!’*";
P_HTM[8437]="*‘Handa carahi me tvaṃ, mārisa, antaradhāyassu sace visahasī’ti.**‘All right, then, good sir, vanish from me—if you can.’*";
P_HTM[8438]="*Atha kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsiṃ:**Then I used my psychic power to will that*";
P_HTM[8439]="*‘ettāvatā brahmā ca brahmaparisā ca brahmapārisajjā ca saddañca me sossanti, na ca maṃ dakkhantī’ti.**my voice would extend so that Brahmā, his assembly, and his retinue would hear me, but they would not see me.*";
P_HTM[8440]="*Antarahito imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsiṃ:**And while invisible I recited this verse:*";
P_HTM[8441]="*‘Bhavevāhaṃ bhayaṃ disvā,**‘Seeing the danger in continued existence—*";
P_HTM[8442]="*bhavañca vibhavesinaṃ;**that life in any existence will cease to be—*";
P_HTM[8443]="*Bhavaṃ nābhivadiṃ kiñci,**I didn’t welcome any kind of existence,*";
P_HTM[8444]="*nandiñca na upādiyin’ti.**and didn’t grasp at relishing.’*";
P_HTM[8445]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, brahmā ca brahmaparisā ca brahmapārisajjā ca acchariyabbhutacittajātā ahesuṃ:**Then Brahmā, his assembly, and his retinue, their minds full of wonder and amazement, thought,*";
P_HTM[8446]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[8447]="*Samaṇassa gotamassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā, na ca vata no ito pubbe diṭṭho vā, suto vā, añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃ mahiddhiko evaṃ mahānubhāvo yathāyaṃ samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito.**The ascetic Gotama has such psychic power and might! We’ve never before seen or heard of any other ascetic or brahmin with psychic power and might like the ascetic Gotama, who has gone forth from the Sakyan clan.*";
P_HTM[8448]="*Bhavarāmāya vata, bho, pajāya bhavaratāya bhavasammuditāya samūlaṃ bhavaṃ udabbahī’ti.**Though people enjoy continued existence, loving it so much, he has extracted it down to its root.’*";
P_HTM[8449]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, māro pāpimā aññataraṃ brahmapārisajjaṃ anvāvisitvā maṃ etadavoca:**Then Māra the Wicked took possession of a member of Brahmā’s retinue and said this to me,*";
P_HTM[8450]="*‘sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, evaṃ pajānāsi, sace tvaṃ evaṃ anubuddho, mā sāvake upanesi, mā pabbajite;**‘If such is your understanding, good sir, do not present it to your disciples or those gone forth!*";
P_HTM[8451]="*mā sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desesi, mā pabbajitānaṃ;**Do not teach this Dhamma to your disciples or those gone forth!*";
P_HTM[8452]="*mā sāvakesu gedhimakāsi, mā pabbajitesu.**Do not wish this for your disciples or those gone forth!*";
P_HTM[8453]="*Ahesuṃ kho, bhikkhu, tayā pubbe samaṇabrāhmaṇā lokasmiṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā paṭijānamānā.**There have been ascetics and brahmins before you, mendicant, who claimed to be perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas.*";
P_HTM[8454]="*Te sāvake upanesuṃ pabbajite, sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desesuṃ pabbajitānaṃ, sāvakesu gedhimakaṃsu pabbajitesu, te sāvake upanetvā pabbajite, sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desetvā pabbajitānaṃ, sāvakesu gedhitacittā pabbajitesu,**They presented, taught, and wished this for their disciples and those gone forth.*";
P_HTM[8455]="*kāyassa bhedā pāṇupacchedā hīne kāye patiṭṭhitā.**When their bodies broke up and their breath was cut off they were reborn in a lower realm.*";
P_HTM[8456]="*Ahesuṃ ye pana, bhikkhu, tayā pubbe samaṇabrāhmaṇā lokasmiṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā paṭijānamānā.**But there have also been other ascetics and brahmins before you, mendicant, who claimed to be perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas.*";
P_HTM[8457]="*Te na sāvake upanesuṃ na pabbajite, na sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desesuṃ na pabbajitānaṃ, na sāvakesu gedhimakaṃsu na pabbajitesu, te na sāvake upanetvā na pabbajite, na sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desetvā na pabbajitānaṃ, na sāvakesu gedhitacittā na pabbajitesu,**They did not present, teach, or wish this for their disciples and those gone forth.*";
P_HTM[8458]="*kāyassa bhedā pāṇupacchedā paṇīte kāye patiṭṭhitā.**When their bodies broke up and their breath was cut off they were reborn in a higher realm.*";
P_HTM[8459]="*Taṃ tāhaṃ, bhikkhu, evaṃ vadāmi—**So, mendicant, I tell you this:*";
P_HTM[8460]="*iṅgha tvaṃ, mārisa, appossukko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāramanuyutto viharassu, anakkhātaṃ kusalañhi, mārisa, mā paraṃ ovadāhī’ti.**please, good sir, remain passive, dwelling in blissful meditation in the present life, for this is better left unsaid. Good sir, do not instruct others.’*";
P_HTM[8461]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavocaṃ:**When he had spoken, I said to Māra,*";
P_HTM[8462]="*‘jānāmi kho tāhaṃ, pāpima, mā tvaṃ maññittho:**‘I know you, Wicked One. Do not think,*";
P_HTM[8463]="*“na maṃ jānātī”ti.**“He doesn’t know me.”*";
P_HTM[8464]="*Māro tvamasi, pāpima.**You are Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[8465]="*Na maṃ tvaṃ, pāpima, hitānukampī evaṃ vadesi;**You don’t speak to me like this out of compassion,*";
P_HTM[8466]="*ahitānukampī maṃ tvaṃ, pāpima, evaṃ vadesi.**but with no compassion.*";
P_HTM[8467]="*Tuyhañhi, pāpima, evaṃ hoti:**For you think,*";
P_HTM[8468]="*“yesaṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desessati, te me visayaṃ upātivattissantī”ti.**“Those who the ascetic Gotama teaches will go beyond my reach.”*";
P_HTM[8469]="*Asammāsambuddhāva pana te, pāpima, samānā sammāsambuddhāmhāti paṭijāniṃsu.**Those who formerly claimed to be fully awakened Buddhas were not in fact fully awakened Buddhas.*";
P_HTM[8470]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, pāpima, sammāsambuddhova samāno sammāsambuddhomhīti paṭijānāmi.**But I am.*";
P_HTM[8471]="*Desentopi hi, pāpima, tathāgato sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ tādisova adesentopi hi, pāpima, tathāgato sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ tādisova.**The Realized One remains as such whether or not he teaches disciples.*";
P_HTM[8472]="*Upanentopi hi, pāpima, tathāgato sāvake tādisova, anupanentopi hi, pāpima, tathāgato sāvake tādisova.**The Realized One remains as such whether or not he presents the teaching to disciples.*";
P_HTM[8473]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8474]="*Tathāgatassa, pāpima, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā—**Because the Realized One has given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[8475]="*te pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[8476]="*Seyyathāpi, pāpima, tālo matthakacchinno abhabbo puna virūḷhiyā;**Just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth,*";
P_HTM[8477]="*evameva kho, pāpima, tathāgatassa ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā—**the Realized One has given up the defilements—corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[8478]="*te pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā’ti.**He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them so they are unable to arise in the future.’”*";
P_HTM[8479]="*Iti hidaṃ mārassa ca anālapanatāya brahmuno ca abhinimantanatāya, tasmā imassa veyyākaraṇassa brahmanimantanikantveva adhivacanan”ti.**And so, because of the silencing of Māra, and because of the invitation of Brahmā, the name of this discussion is “On the Invitation of Brahmā”.*";
P_HTM[8480]="*Brahmanimantanikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8481]="*50. Māratajjanīyasutta**The Rebuke of Māra*";
P_HTM[8482]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8483]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time Venerable Mahāmoggallāna was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[8484]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā mahāmoggallāno abbhokāse caṅkamati.**At that time Moggallāna was walking meditation in the open air.*";
P_HTM[8485]="*Tena kho pana samayena māro pāpimā āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa kucchigato hoti koṭṭhamanupaviṭṭho.**Now at that time Māra the Wicked had got inside Moggallāna’s belly.*";
P_HTM[8486]="*Atha kho āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa etadahosi:**Moggallāna thought,*";
P_HTM[8487]="*“kiṃ nu kho me kucchi garugaro viya?**“Why now is my belly so very heavy,*";
P_HTM[8488]="*Māsācitaṃ maññe”ti.**like I’ve just eaten a load of beans?”*";
P_HTM[8489]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno caṅkamā orohitvā vihāraṃ pavisitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then he stepped down from the walking path, entered his dwelling, sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[8490]="*Nisajja kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno paccattaṃ yoniso manasākāsi.**and investigated inside himself.*";
P_HTM[8491]="*Addasā kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno māraṃ pāpimantaṃ kucchigataṃ koṭṭhamanupaviṭṭhaṃ.**He saw that Māra the Wicked had got inside his belly.*";
P_HTM[8492]="*Disvāna māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavoca:**So he said to Māra,*";
P_HTM[8493]="*“nikkhama, pāpima;**“Come out, Wicked One,*";
P_HTM[8494]="*nikkhama, pāpima.**come out!*";
P_HTM[8495]="*Mā tathāgataṃ vihesesi, mā tathāgatasāvakaṃ.**Do not harass the Realized One or his disciple.*";
P_HTM[8496]="*Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**Don’t create lasting harm and suffering for yourself!”*";
P_HTM[8497]="*Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi:**Then Māra thought,*";
P_HTM[8498]="*“ajānameva kho maṃ ayaṃ samaṇo apassaṃ evamāha:**“This ascetic doesn’t really know me or see me when he tells me to come out.*";
P_HTM[8499]="*‘nikkhama, pāpima;* **";
P_HTM[8500]="*nikkhama, pāpima.* **";
P_HTM[8501]="*Mā tathāgataṃ vihesesi, mā tathāgatasāvakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8502]="*Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8503]="*Yopissa so satthā sopi maṃ neva khippaṃ jāneyya, kuto pana maṃ ayaṃ sāvako jānissatī”ti?**Not even the Teacher could recognize me so quickly, so how could a disciple?”*";
P_HTM[8504]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Moggallāna said to Māra,*";
P_HTM[8505]="*“evampi kho tāhaṃ, pāpima, jānāmi, mā tvaṃ maññittho:**“I know you even when you’re like this, Wicked One. Do not think,*";
P_HTM[8506]="*‘na maṃ jānātī’ti.**‘He doesn’t know me.’*";
P_HTM[8507]="*Māro tvamasi, pāpima;**You are Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[8508]="*tuyhañhi, pāpima, evaṃ hoti:**And you think,*";
P_HTM[8509]="*‘ajānameva kho maṃ ayaṃ samaṇo apassaṃ evamāha—**‘This ascetic doesn’t really know me or see me when he tells me to come out.*";
P_HTM[8510]="*nikkhama, pāpima;* **";
P_HTM[8511]="*nikkhama, pāpima.* **";
P_HTM[8512]="*Mā tathāgataṃ vihesesi, mā tathāgatasāvakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8513]="*Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyāti.* **";
P_HTM[8514]="*Yopissa so satthā sopi maṃ neva khippaṃ jāneyya, kuto pana maṃ ayaṃ sāvako jānissatī’”ti?**Not even the Teacher could recognize me so quickly, so how could a disciple?’”*";
P_HTM[8515]="*Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi:**Then Māra thought,*";
P_HTM[8516]="*“jānameva kho maṃ ayaṃ samaṇo passaṃ evamāha:**“This ascetic really does know me and see me when he tells me to come out.”*";
P_HTM[8517]="*‘nikkhama, pāpima;* **";
P_HTM[8518]="*nikkhama, pāpima.* **";
P_HTM[8519]="*Mā tathāgataṃ vihesesi, mā tathāgatasāvakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8520]="*Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8521]="*Atha kho māro pāpimā āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa mukhato uggantvā paccaggaḷe aṭṭhāsi.**Then Māra came up out of Moggallāna’s mouth and stood against the door bar.*";
P_HTM[8522]="*Addasā kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno māraṃ pāpimantaṃ paccaggaḷe ṭhitaṃ;**Moggallāna saw him there*";
P_HTM[8523]="*disvāna māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[8524]="*“etthāpi kho tāhaṃ, pāpima, passāmi; mā tvaṃ maññittho**“I see you even there, Wicked One. Do not think,*";
P_HTM[8525]="*‘na maṃ passatī’ti.**‘He doesn’t see me.’*";
P_HTM[8526]="*Eso tvaṃ, pāpima, paccaggaḷe ṭhito.**That’s you, Wicked One, standing against the door bar.*";
P_HTM[8527]="*Bhūtapubbāhaṃ, pāpima, dūsī nāma māro ahosiṃ, tassa me kāḷī nāma bhaginī.**Once upon a time, Wicked One, I was a Māra named Dūsī, and I had a sister named Kāḷī.*";
P_HTM[8528]="*Tassā tvaṃ putto.**You were her son,*";
P_HTM[8529]="*So me tvaṃ bhāgineyyo ahosi.**which made you my nephew.*";
P_HTM[8530]="*Tena kho pana, pāpima, samayena kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti.**At that time Kakusandha, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world.*";
P_HTM[8531]="*Kakusandhassa kho pana, pāpima, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa vidhurasañjīvaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ.**Kakusandha had a fine pair of chief disciples named Vidhura and Sañjīva.*";
P_HTM[8532]="*Yāvatā kho pana, pāpima, kakusandhassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sāvakā.**Of all the disciples of the Buddha Kakusandha,*";
P_HTM[8533]="*Tesu na ca koci āyasmatā vidhurena samasamo hoti yadidaṃ dhammadesanāya.**none were the equal of Venerable Vidhura in teaching Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[8534]="*Iminā kho evaṃ, pāpima, pariyāyena āyasmato vidhurassa vidhuroteva samaññā udapādi.**And that’s how he came to be known as Vidhura.*";
P_HTM[8535]="*Āyasmā pana, pāpima, sañjīvo araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi appakasireneva saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjati.**But when Venerable Sañjīva had gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, he easily attained the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[8536]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, pāpima, āyasmā sañjīvo aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno nisinno hoti.**Once upon a time, Sañjīva was sitting at the root of a certain tree having attained the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[8537]="*Addasaṃsu kho, pāpima, gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino āyasmantaṃ sañjīvaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannaṃ nisinnaṃ;**Some cowherds, shepherds, farmers, and passers-by saw him sitting there*";
P_HTM[8538]="*disvāna tesaṃ etadahosi:**and said,*";
P_HTM[8539]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata, bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[8540]="*Ayaṃ samaṇo nisinnakova kālaṅkato.**This ascetic passed away while sitting.*";
P_HTM[8541]="*Handa naṃ dahāmā’ti.**We should cremate him.’*";
P_HTM[8542]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca gomayañca saṅkaḍḍhitvā āyasmato sañjīvassa kāye upacinitvā aggiṃ datvā pakkamiṃsu.**They collected grass, wood, and cow-dung, heaped it all on Sañjīva’s body, set it on fire, and left.*";
P_HTM[8543]="*Atha kho, pāpima, āyasmā sañjīvo tassā rattiyā accayena tāya samāpattiyā vuṭṭhahitvā cīvarāni papphoṭetvā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then, when the night had passed, Sañjīva emerged from that attainment, shook out his robes, and, since it was morning, he robed up and entered the village for alms.*";
P_HTM[8544]="*Addasaṃsu kho te, pāpima, gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino āyasmantaṃ sañjīvaṃ piṇḍāya carantaṃ;**Those cowherds, shepherds, farmers, and passers-by saw him wandering for alms*";
P_HTM[8545]="*disvāna nesaṃ etadahosi:**and said,*";
P_HTM[8546]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata, bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[8547]="*Ayaṃ samaṇo nisinnakova kālaṅkato, svāyaṃ paṭisañjīvito’ti.**This ascetic passed away while sitting, and now he has come back to life!’*";
P_HTM[8548]="*Iminā kho evaṃ, pāpima, pariyāyena āyasmato sañjīvassa sañjīvoteva samaññā udapādi.**And that’s how he came to be known as Sañjīva.*";
P_HTM[8549]="*Atha kho, pāpima, dūsissa mārassa etadahosi:**Then it occurred to Māra Dūsī,*";
P_HTM[8550]="*‘imesaṃ kho ahaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sīlavantānaṃ kalyāṇadhammānaṃ neva jānāmi āgatiṃ vā gatiṃ vā.**‘I don’t know the course of rebirth of these ethical mendicants of good character.*";
P_HTM[8551]="*Yannūnāhaṃ brāhmaṇagahapatike anvāviseyyaṃ—**Why don’t I take possession of these brahmins and householders and say,*";
P_HTM[8552]="*etha, tumhe bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme akkosatha paribhāsatha rosetha vihesetha.**“Come, all of you, abuse, attack, harass, and trouble the ethical mendicants of good character.*";
P_HTM[8553]="*Appeva nāma tumhehi akkosiyamānānaṃ paribhāsiyamānānaṃ rosiyamānānaṃ vihesiyamānānaṃ siyā cittassa aññathattaṃ, yathā taṃ dūsī māro labhetha otāran’ti.**Hopefully by doing this we can upset their minds so that Māra Dūsī can find a vulnerability.”’*";
P_HTM[8554]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, dūsī māro brāhmaṇagahapatike anvāvisi:**And that’s exactly what he did.*";
P_HTM[8555]="*‘etha, tumhe bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme akkosatha paribhāsatha rosetha vihesetha.* **";
P_HTM[8556]="*Appeva nāma tumhehi akkosiyamānānaṃ paribhāsiyamānānaṃ rosiyamānānaṃ vihesiyamānānaṃ siyā cittassa aññathattaṃ, yathā taṃ dūsī māro labhetha otāran’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8557]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, brāhmaṇagahapatikā anvāvisiṭṭhā dūsinā mārena bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme akkosanti paribhāsanti rosenti vihesenti:**Then those brahmins and householders abused, attacked, harassed, and troubled the ethical mendicants of good character:*";
P_HTM[8558]="*‘ime pana muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kiṇhā bandhupādāpaccā “jhāyinosmā jhāyinosmā”ti pattakkhandhā adhomukhā madhurakajātā jhāyanti pajjhāyanti nijjhāyanti apajjhāyanti.**‘These shavelings, fake ascetics, riffraff, black spawn from the feet of our Kinsman, say, ‘We practice absorption meditation! We practice absorption meditation!’ And they meditate and concentrate and contemplate and ruminate.*";
P_HTM[8559]="*Seyyathāpi nāma ulūko rukkhasākhāyaṃ mūsikaṃ maggayamāno jhāyati pajjhāyati nijjhāyati apajjhāyati;**They’re just like an owl on a branch, which meditates and concentrates and contemplates and ruminates as it hunts a mouse.*";
P_HTM[8560]="*evamevime muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kiṇhā bandhupādāpaccā “jhāyinosmā jhāyinosmā”ti pattakkhandhā adhomukhā madhurakajātā jhāyanti pajjhāyanti nijjhāyanti apajjhāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[8561]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kotthu nadītīre macche maggayamāno jhāyati pajjhāyati nijjhāyati apajjhāyati;**They’re just like a jackal on a river-bank, which meditates and concentrates and contemplates and ruminates as it hunts a fish.*";
P_HTM[8562]="*evamevime muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kiṇhā bandhupādāpaccā “jhāyinosmā jhāyinosmā”ti pattakkhandhā adhomukhā madhurakajātā jhāyanti pajjhāyanti nijjhāyanti apajjhāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[8563]="*Seyyathāpi nāma biḷāro sandhisamalasaṅkaṭīre mūsikaṃ maggayamāno jhāyati pajjhāyati nijjhāyati apajjhāyati;**They’re just like a cat by an alley or a drain or a dustbin, which meditates and concentrates and contemplates and ruminates as it hunts a mouse.*";
P_HTM[8564]="*evamevime muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kiṇhā bandhupādāpaccā “jhāyinosmā jhāyinosmā”ti pattakkhandhā adhomukhā madhurakajātā jhāyanti pajjhāyanti nijjhāyanti apajjhāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[8565]="*Seyyathāpi nāma gadrabho vahacchinno sandhisamalasaṅkaṭīre jhāyati pajjhāyati nijjhāyati apajjhāyati;**They’re just like an unladen donkey by an alley or a drain or a dustbin, which meditates and concentrates and contemplates and ruminates.*";
P_HTM[8566]="*evamevime muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kiṇhā bandhupādāpaccā “jhāyinosmā jhāyinosmā”ti pattakkhandhā adhomukhā madhurakajātā jhāyanti pajjhāyanti nijjhāyanti apajjhāyantī’ti.**In the same way, these shavelings, fake ascetics, riffraff, black spawn from the feet of our Kinsman, say, ‘We practice absorption meditation! We practice absorption meditation!’ And they meditate and concentrate and contemplate and ruminate.’*";
P_HTM[8567]="*Ye kho pana, pāpima, tena samayena manussā kālaṃ karonti yebhuyyena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**Most of the people who died at that time—when their body broke up, after death—were reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[8568]="*Atha kho, pāpima, kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then Kakusandha the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[8569]="*‘anvāviṭṭhā kho, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇagahapatikā dūsinā mārena—**‘Mendicants, the brahmins and householders have been possessed by Māra Dūsī.*";
P_HTM[8570]="*etha, tumhe bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme akkosatha paribhāsatha rosetha vihesetha, appeva nāma tumhehi akkosiyamānānaṃ paribhāsiyamānānaṃ rosiyamānānaṃ vihesiyamānānaṃ siyā cittassa aññathattaṃ, yathā taṃ dūsī māro labhetha otāran’ti.**He told them to abuse you in the hope of upsetting your minds so that he can find a vulnerability.*";
P_HTM[8571]="*Etha, tumhe, bhikkhave, mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharatha, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharatha.**Come, all of you mendicants, meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[8572]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**Meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[8573]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**Meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[8574]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharatha, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharathā’ti.**Meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.’*";
P_HTM[8575]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, bhikkhū kakusandhena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena evaṃ ovadiyamānā evaṃ anusāsiyamānā araññagatāpi rukkhamūlagatāpi suññāgāragatāpi mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihariṃsu, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihariṃsu.**When those mendicants were instructed and advised by the Buddha Kakusandha in this way, they went to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, where they meditated spreading a heart full of love …*";
P_HTM[8576]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**compassion …*";
P_HTM[8577]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[8578]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihariṃsu, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihariṃsu.**equanimity.*";
P_HTM[8579]="*Atha kho, pāpima, dūsissa mārassa etadahosi:**Then it occurred to Māra Dūsī,*";
P_HTM[8580]="*‘evampi kho ahaṃ karonto imesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sīlavantānaṃ kalyāṇadhammānaṃ neva jānāmi āgatiṃ vā gatiṃ vā, yannūnāhaṃ brāhmaṇagahapatike anvāviseyyaṃ:**‘Even when I do this I don’t know the course of rebirth of these ethical mendicants of good character. Why don’t I take possession of these brahmins and householders and say,*";
P_HTM[8581]="*“etha, tumhe bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme sakkarotha garuṃ karotha mānetha pūjetha,**“Come, all of you, honor, respect, esteem, and venerate the ethical mendicants of good character.*";
P_HTM[8582]="*appeva nāma tumhehi sakkariyamānānaṃ garukariyamānānaṃ māniyamānānaṃ pūjiyamānānaṃ siyā cittassa aññathattaṃ, yathā taṃ dūsī māro labhetha otāran”’ti.**Hopefully by doing this we can upset their minds so that Māra Dūsī can find a vulnerability.”’*";
P_HTM[8583]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, dūsī māro brāhmaṇagahapatike anvāvisi:**And that’s exactly what he did.*";
P_HTM[8584]="*‘etha, tumhe bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme sakkarotha garuṃ karotha mānetha pūjetha,* **";
P_HTM[8585]="*appeva nāma tumhehi sakkariyamānānaṃ garukariyamānānaṃ māniyamānānaṃ pūjiyamānānaṃ siyā cittassa aññathattaṃ, yathā taṃ dūsī māro labhetha otāran’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8586]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, brāhmaṇagahapatikā anvāviṭṭhā dūsinā mārena bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti.**Then those brahmins and householders honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated the ethical mendicants of good character.*";
P_HTM[8587]="*Ye kho pana, pāpima, tena samayena manussā kālaṃ karonti yebhuyyena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**Most of the people who died at that time—when their body broke up, after death—were reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[8588]="*Atha kho, pāpima, kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then Kakusandha the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[8589]="*‘anvāviṭṭhā kho, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇagahapatikā dūsinā mārena:**‘Mendicants, the brahmins and householders have been possessed by Māra Dūsī.*";
P_HTM[8590]="*“etha, tumhe bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme sakkarotha garuṃ karotha mānetha pūjetha,**He told them to venerate you*";
P_HTM[8591]="*appeva nāma tumhehi sakkariyamānānaṃ garukariyamānānaṃ māniyamānānaṃ pūjiyamānānaṃ siyā cittassa aññathattaṃ, yathā taṃ dūsī māro labhetha otāran”ti.**in the hope of upsetting your minds so that he can find a vulnerability.*";
P_HTM[8592]="*Etha, tumhe, bhikkhave, asubhānupassino kāye viharatha, āhāre paṭikūlasaññino, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññino, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassino’ti.**Come, all you mendicants, meditate observing the ugliness of the body, perceiving the repulsiveness of food, perceiving dissatisfaction with the whole world, and observing the impermanence of all conditions.’*";
P_HTM[8593]="*Atha kho te, pāpima, bhikkhū kakusandhena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena evaṃ ovadiyamānā evaṃ anusāsiyamānā araññagatāpi rukkhamūlagatāpi suññāgāragatāpi asubhānupassino kāye vihariṃsu, āhāre paṭikūlasaññino, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññino, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassino.**When those mendicants were instructed and advised by the Buddha Kakusandha in this way, they went to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, where they meditated observing the ugliness of the body, perceiving the repulsiveness of food, perceiving dissatisfaction with the whole world, and observing the impermanence of all conditions.*";
P_HTM[8594]="*Atha kho, pāpima, kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āyasmatā vidhurena pacchāsamaṇena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha Kakusandha robed up in the morning and, taking this bowl and robe, entered the village for alms with Venerable Vidhura as his second monk.*";
P_HTM[8595]="*Atha kho, pāpima, dūsī māro aññataraṃ kumārakaṃ anvāvisitvā sakkharaṃ gahetvā āyasmato vidhurassa sīse pahāramadāsi; sīsaṃ vobhindi.**Then Māra Dūsī took possession of a certain boy, picked up a rock, and hit Vidhura on the head, cracking it open.*";
P_HTM[8596]="*Atha kho, pāpima, āyasmā vidhuro bhinnena sīsena lohitena gaḷantena kakusandhaṃyeva bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi.**Then Vidhura, with blood pouring from his cracked skull, still followed behind the Buddha Kakusandha.*";
P_HTM[8597]="*Atha kho, pāpima, kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nāgāpalokitaṃ apalokesi:**Then the Buddha Kakusandha turned his whole body, the way that elephants do, to look back, saying,*";
P_HTM[8598]="*‘na vāyaṃ dūsī māro mattamaññāsī’ti.**‘This Māra Dūsī knows no bounds.’*";
P_HTM[8599]="*Sahāpalokanāya ca pana, pāpima, dūsī māro tamhā ca ṭhānā cavi mahānirayañca upapajji.**And with that look Māra Dūsī fell from that place and was reborn in the Great Hell.*";
P_HTM[8600]="*Tassa kho pana, pāpima, mahānirayassa tayo nāmadheyyā honti—**Now that Great Hell is known by three names:*";
P_HTM[8601]="*chaphassāyataniko itipi, saṅkusamāhato itipi, paccattavedaniyo itipi.**‘The Six Fields of Contact’ and also ‘The Impaling With Spikes’ and also ‘Individually Painful’.*";
P_HTM[8602]="*Atha kho maṃ, pāpima, nirayapālā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**Then the wardens of hell came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[8603]="*‘yadā kho te, mārisa, saṅkunā saṅku hadaye samāgaccheyya.**‘When stake meets stake in your heart,*";
P_HTM[8604]="*Atha naṃ tvaṃ jāneyyāsi:**you will know that*";
P_HTM[8605]="*“vassasahassaṃ me niraye paccamānassā”’ti.**you’ve been roasting in hell for a thousand years.’*";
P_HTM[8606]="*So kho ahaṃ, pāpima, bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni tasmiṃ mahāniraye apacciṃ.**I roasted for many years, many centuries, many millennia in that Great Hell.*";
P_HTM[8607]="*Dasavassasahassāni tasseva mahānirayassa ussade apacciṃ vuṭṭhānimaṃ nāma vedanaṃ vediyamāno.**For ten thousand years I roasted in the annex of that Great Hell, experiencing the pain called ‘coming out’.*";
P_HTM[8608]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, pāpima, evarūpo kāyo hoti, seyyathāpi manussassa.**My body was in human form,*";
P_HTM[8609]="*Evarūpaṃ sīsaṃ hoti, seyyathāpi macchassa.**but I had the head of a fish.*";
P_HTM[8610]="*Kīdiso nirayo āsi,**What kind of hell was that,*";
P_HTM[8611]="*yattha dūsī apaccatha;**where Dūsī was roasted*";
P_HTM[8612]="*Vidhuraṃ sāvakamāsajja,**after attacking the disciple Vidhura*";
P_HTM[8613]="*kakusandhañca brāhmaṇaṃ.**along with the brahmin Kakusandha?*";
P_HTM[8614]="*Sataṃ āsi ayosaṅkū,**There were 100 iron spikes,*";
P_HTM[8615]="*sabbe paccattavedanā;**each one individually painful.*";
P_HTM[8616]="*Īdiso nirayo āsi,**That’s the kind of hell*";
P_HTM[8617]="*yattha dūsī apaccatha;**where Dūsī was roasted*";
P_HTM[8618]="*Vidhuraṃ sāvakamāsajja,**after attacking the disciple Vidhura*";
P_HTM[8619]="*kakusandhañca brāhmaṇaṃ.**along with the brahmin Kakusandha.*";
P_HTM[8620]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8621]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8622]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8623]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8624]="*Majjhe sarassa tiṭṭhanti,**There are mansions that last for an eon*";
P_HTM[8625]="*vimānā kappaṭṭhāyino;**standing in the middle of a lake.*";
P_HTM[8626]="*Veḷuriyavaṇṇā rucirā,**Sapphire-colored, brilliant,*";
P_HTM[8627]="*accimanto pabhassarā;**they sparkle and shine.*";
P_HTM[8628]="*Accharā tattha naccanti,**Dancing there are nymphs*";
P_HTM[8629]="*puthu nānattavaṇṇiyo.**shining in all different colors.*";
P_HTM[8630]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8631]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8632]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8633]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8634]="*Yo ve buddhena codito,**I’m the one who, encouraged by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8635]="*bhikkhu saṅghassa pekkhato;**shook the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother*";
P_HTM[8636]="*Migāramātupāsādaṃ,**with his big toe*";
P_HTM[8637]="*pādaṅguṭṭhena kampayi.**as the Saṅgha of mendicants watched.*";
P_HTM[8638]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8639]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8640]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8641]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8642]="*Yo vejayantaṃ pāsādaṃ,**I’m the one who shook the Palace of Victory*";
P_HTM[8643]="*pādaṅguṭṭhena kampayi;**with his big toe*";
P_HTM[8644]="*Iddhibalenupatthaddho,**owing to psychic power,*";
P_HTM[8645]="*saṃvejesi ca devatā.**inspiring deities to awe.*";
P_HTM[8646]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8647]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8648]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8649]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8650]="*Yo vejayantapāsāde,**I’m the one who asked Sakka*";
P_HTM[8651]="*sakkaṃ so paripucchati;**in the Palace of Victory:*";
P_HTM[8652]="*Api vāsava jānāsi,**‘Vāsava, do you know the freedom*";
P_HTM[8653]="*taṇhākkhayavimuttiyo;**that comes with the ending of craving?’*";
P_HTM[8654]="*Tassa sakko viyākāsi,**And I’m the one to whom Sakka*";
P_HTM[8655]="*pañhaṃ puṭṭho yathātathaṃ.**admitted the truth when asked.*";
P_HTM[8656]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8657]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8658]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8659]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8660]="*Yo brahmaṃ paripucchati,**I’m the one who asked Brahmā*";
P_HTM[8661]="*sudhammāyābhito sabhaṃ;**in the Hall of Justice before the assembly:*";
P_HTM[8662]="*Ajjāpi tyāvuso diṭṭhi,**‘Friend, do you still have the same view*";
P_HTM[8663]="*yā te diṭṭhi pure ahu;**that you had in the past?*";
P_HTM[8664]="*Passasi vītivattantaṃ,**Or do you see the radiance*";
P_HTM[8665]="*brahmaloke pabhassaraṃ.**transcending the Brahmā realm?’*";
P_HTM[8666]="*Tassa brahmā viyākāsi,**And I’m the one to whom Brahmā*";
P_HTM[8667]="*anupubbaṃ yathātathaṃ;**truthfully admitted his progress:*";
P_HTM[8668]="*Na me mārisa sā diṭṭhi,**‘Good sir, I don’t have that view*";
P_HTM[8669]="*yā me diṭṭhi pure ahu.**that I had in the past.*";
P_HTM[8670]="*Passāmi vītivattantaṃ,**I see the radiance*";
P_HTM[8671]="*brahmaloke pabhassaraṃ;**transcending the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[8672]="*Sohaṃ ajja kathaṃ vajjaṃ,**So how could I say today*";
P_HTM[8673]="*ahaṃ niccomhi sassato.**that I am permanent and eternal?’*";
P_HTM[8674]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8675]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8676]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8677]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8678]="*Yo mahāmeruno kūṭaṃ,**I’m the one who has touched the peak of Mount Meru*";
P_HTM[8679]="*vimokkhena aphassayi;**using the power of meditative liberation.*";
P_HTM[8680]="*Vanaṃ pubbavidehānaṃ,**I’ve visited the forests of the people*";
P_HTM[8681]="*ye ca bhūmisayā narā.**who dwell in the Eastern Continent.*";
P_HTM[8682]="*Yo etamabhijānāti,**Dark One, if you attack*";
P_HTM[8683]="*bhikkhu buddhassa sāvako;**a mendicant who directly knows this,*";
P_HTM[8684]="*Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,**a disciple of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8685]="*kaṇha dukkhaṃ nigacchasi.**you’ll fall into suffering.*";
P_HTM[8686]="*Na ve aggi cetayati,**Though a fire doesn’t think,*";
P_HTM[8687]="*‘ahaṃ bālaṃ ḍahāmī’ti;**‘I’ll burn the fool!’*";
P_HTM[8688]="*Bālo ca jalitaṃ aggiṃ,**Still the fool who attacks*";
P_HTM[8689]="*āsajja naṃ sa ḍayhati.**the fire gets burnt.*";
P_HTM[8690]="*Evameva tuvaṃ māra,**In the same way, Māra,*";
P_HTM[8691]="*āsajja naṃ tathāgataṃ;**in attacking the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[8692]="*Sayaṃ ḍahissasi attānaṃ,**you’ll only burn yourself,*";
P_HTM[8693]="*bālo aggiṃva samphusaṃ.**like a fool touching the flames.*";
P_HTM[8694]="*Apuññaṃ pasavī māro,**Māra’s done a bad thing*";
P_HTM[8695]="*āsajja naṃ tathāgataṃ;**in attacking the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[8696]="*Kiṃ nu maññasi pāpima,**Wicked One, do you imagine that*";
P_HTM[8697]="*na me pāpaṃ vipaccati.**your wickedness won’t bear fruit?*";
P_HTM[8698]="*Karoto cīyati pāpaṃ,**Your deeds heap up wickedness*";
P_HTM[8699]="*cirarattāya antaka;**that will last a long time, terminator!*";
P_HTM[8700]="*Māra nibbinda buddhamhā,**Forget about the Buddha, Māra!*";
P_HTM[8701]="*āsaṃ mākāsi bhikkhusu.**And give up your hopes for the mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[8702]="*Iti māraṃ atajjesi,**That is how, in the Bhesekaḷā grove,*";
P_HTM[8703]="*bhikkhu bhesakaḷāvane;**the mendicant rebuked Māra.*";
P_HTM[8704]="*Tato so dummano yakkho,**That spirit, downcast,*";
P_HTM[8705]="*tatthevantaradhāyathā”ti.**disappeared right there!*";
P_HTM[8706]="*Māratajjanīyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8707]="*Cūḷayamakavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[8708]="*Sāleyya verañjaduve ca tuṭṭhi,* **";
P_HTM[8709]="*Cūḷamahādhammasamādānañca;* **";
P_HTM[8710]="*Vīmaṃsakā kosambi ca brāhmaṇo,* **";
P_HTM[8711]="*Dūsī ca māro dasamo ca vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[8712]="*Mūlapariyāyo ceva,* **";
P_HTM[8713]="*sīhanādo ca uttamo;* **";
P_HTM[8714]="*Kakaco ceva gosiṅgo,* **";
P_HTM[8715]="*sāleyyo ca ime pañca.* **";
P_HTM[8716]="*Mūlapaṇṇāsakaṃ samattaṃ.* **";
